{
  "1": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "To Inhabit - To Settle",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "« » is used for inhabiting another place. (7 verses: 2:35, 2:128, 7:19, 7:161, 17:104, 23:18, 65:6)",
      "d": "« » means to take to a place and settle there.\nFor example, in the Quran regarding Prophet Ibrahim:\n«رَبَّنَآ اِنِّىْٓ اَسْكَنْتُ مِنْ ذُرِّيَّتِيْ بِوَادٍ غَيْرِ ذِيْ زَرْعٍ»\nTranslation: O our Lord! I have settled my progeny in a valley without cultivation."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "«ستارہ» refers to those bright celestial bodies that shine in the sky and it originates from the Arabic root ن-ج-م.",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "By « » is meant those bright celestial bodies that shine in the sky, and it comes from the Arabic root  - -  (n-j-m).",
      "d": "«چاند» «قَمَر» « یا » « ہے۔ اردو میں «چاند» «قَمَر» «چاند» «قَمَر» «قَمَر» «چاند»\n«وَالْقَمَرَ قَدَّرْنَاهُ مَنَازِلَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Inside - Dakhil",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "«ورق»",
      "d": "The Arabic root of « » is « - - » or « - - ». This word comes in both meanings of moon and month, because in ancient Arabic tradition, months were counted based on the moon. In contrast, in Arabic, « » is generally used for moon and « » for month. In Urdu, « » is actually derived from Sanskrit « », however, the word « » is also used in Urdu for the meaning of month.\n«إِنَّ عِدَّةَ الشُّهُورِ عِندَ اللَّهِ اثْنَا عَشَرَ شَهْرًا فِي كِتَابِ اللَّهِ يَوْمَ خَلَقَ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْأَرْضَ مِنْهَا أَرْبَعَةٌ حُرُمٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "To Be Inhabited (To Reside) - To Live",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "« » hands, feet, and the sides of the body (2 verses: 18:29-70:16)",
      "d": "«فہم» «سمجھنا» «جانچنا» «پہچاننا» «سُمْع» «فَهْم» «عِلْم» «فہم»\n«الَّذِينَ يُؤْمِنُونَ بِاللَّهِ وَالْيَوْمِ الْآخِرِ وَيَأْمُرُونَ بِالمَعْرُوفِ وَيَنْهَوْنَ عَنِ الْمُنكَرِ وَيُقِيمُونَ الصَّلَاةَ وَيُؤْتُونَ الزَّكَاةَ وَهُمْ يَرْجُونَ رَحْمَةَ رَبِّهِمْ ۚ أُولَٰئِكَ هُمُ الْمُهْتَدُونَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "To Be Inhabited (To Reside) - To Live",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "« » is generally used for bed or mattress (5 verses: 2:22-6:142-51:48-55:54-56:34)",
      "d": "«قُرُوْن» «قَرَن» «قُرُوْن» «قَرِیْن» «قَرَن» «قَرَنَ الثَّوْرَیْن» «قَرِیْن» « قُرَنَاء»\nFor example, in the Quran it is said:\n«وَ مَنۡ  یَّکُنِ  الشَّیۡطٰنُ  لَہٗ  قَرِیۡنًا فَسَآءَ  قَرِیۡنًا»\nTranslation: And whoever has Satan as a companion, then evil is the companion."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "To Be Inhabited (To Reside) - To Live",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "« » the skin of a living being (7 verses: 4:56-16:80-22:20-39:23-41:20-41:21-41:22)",
      "d": "«خَتَمَ» «خَتَمَ الْاَنَاء» «خَتَام» «خَتَمَ الْقُرآن»\n«خَتَمَ اللّٰہُ عَلٰی قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ وَ عَلٰی سَمۡعِہِمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "To Inhabit (to settle) - to reside",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "« » to shake something with such force that it remains firmly rooted but bends to one side (1 verse: 7:171)",
      "d": "«جَوِفَ» «جَوَّف» «جَوْف» «جَوفَ الْبَیْت» «مُجَّوَف» «جَوِفَ» «مَا جَعَلَ اللّٰہُ لِرَجُلٍ مِّنۡ قَلۡبَیۡنِ فِیۡ جَوۡفِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "To Populate - To Settle",
      "hw": "آباد",
      "s": "« » baseless events (9 verses: 6:25-8:31-16:24-23:83-25:5-27:68-46:17-68:15-83:13)",
      "d": "« » means elevation and « » means to invite someone to a high place or high purpose (muf). It is used to invite someone with respect, and only the imperative forms are used:\n«قُلۡ یٰۤاَہۡلَ الۡکِتٰبِ تَعَالَوۡا اِلٰی کَلِمَۃٍ سَوَآءٍۢ  بَیۡنَنَا وَ بَیۡنَکُمۡ اَلَّا نَعۡبُدَ اِلَّا اللّٰہَ»\nTranslation: (O Prophet) say, 'O People of the Book! Come to a word that is equal between us and you that we worship none but Allah.'"
    },
