  "2": [
    {
      "id": 12,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Hereafter",
      "hw": "Hereafter",
      "s": "«یَوْمُ الْاٰخِرَ»",
      "d": "« » means to stay in a place for a long period where no change (i.e., alteration) and corruption occur (m.f.).\n«وَلَھُمْ فِيْهَآ اَزْوَاجٌ مُّطَهَّرَةٌ وَّھُمْ فِيْهَا خٰلِدُوْنَ»\nTranslation: And they will have pure spouses therein, and they will abide therein forever."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Akhirah",
      "hw": "Hereafter",
      "s": "« » events that are famous among common people and transmitted from person to person (10 verses: 3:62-4:164-7:176-12:3-12:5-12:111-16:118-18:64-28:25-40:78)",
      "d": "« » –   means residence, i.e., home, and   (plural  , and   is its opposite). Its meaning is very broad. For example,   means home, mansion, area, homeland, country; in fact, the entire world is also a residence for humans, hence  , and its opposite is  . However, in the afterlife, every person will be given a residence ( ) according to their deeds.\n«وَلَنِعۡمَ  دَارُ الۡمُتَّقِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: How excellent is the residence (Paradise) for the pious!\n«اَلَمۡ تَرَ اِلَى الَّذِيۡنَ بَدَّلُوۡا نِعۡمَتَ اللّٰہِ کُفۡرًا وَّاَحَلُّوۡا قَوۡمَہُمۡ دَارَ الۡبَوَارِۙ‏ - جَهَـنَّمَ​ۚ يَصۡلَوۡنَہَا​ؕ وَبِئۡسَ الۡقَرَارُ‏»\nTranslation: Have you not seen those who exchanged the favor of Allah for disbelief and led their people to the home of ruin? – Hell, wherein they will burn; and evil is that destination.\n(Bad home and bad place) both refer to Hell."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Akhirah",
      "hw": "Hereafter",
      "s": "«Al-Akhirah» is generally used for the Day of Judgment, on which all humans will be resurrected and judged according to their deeds, and then granted eternal life (105 Ayahs: 2:4-2:86-2:102-2:114-2:130-2:200-2:201-2:217-2:220-3:22-3:45-3:56-3:72-3:77-3:85-3:145-3:148-3:152-3:176-4:74-4:77-4:134-5:5-5:33-5:41-6:92-6:113-6:150-7:45-7:147-7:156-8:67-9:38-9:69-9:74-10:64-11:16-11:19-11:22-11:103-12:37-12:57-12:101-13:26-13:34-14:3-14:27-16:22-16:41-16:60-16:107-16:109-16:122-17:7-17:10-17:19-17:21-17:45-17:72-17:104-20:127-22:11-22:15-23:33-23:74-24:14-24:19-24:23-27:3-27:4-27:5-27:66-28:70-29:20-29:27-30:7-30:16-31:4-33:57-34:1-34:8-34:21-38:7-39:9-39:26-39:45-40:39-40:43-41:7-41:16-41:31-42:20-43:35-53:25-53:27-57:20-59:3-60:13-68:33-74:53-75:21-79:25-87:17-92:13-93:4).",
      "d": "« » means to descend something upon something (m l) and means to descend upon something and envelop it. (muf) so it is a siege that is upon the besieged itself. The descending of calamity, affliction, or punishment upon someone from which they are surrounded. And « » means the recompense of deeds. The bad result of a bad deed (minajid) so this word is used in a bad sense.\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ حَاقَ بِہِمۡ  مَّا کَانُوۡا بِہٖ یَسۡتَہۡزِءُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And that (punishment) which they used to mock will encompass them.\nAt another place, the divine decree says:\n«وَ لَا یَحِیۡقُ الۡمَکۡرُ السَّیِّیئُ  اِلَّا بِاَہۡلِہٖ»\nTranslation: And the evil plan will only recoil upon its planners."
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Akhirah",
      "hw": "Hereafter",
      "s": "«Dar al-Akhirah» refers to the home whose fate will be decided on the Day of Judgment based on a person's good or bad deeds, and in which they will reside forever (9 Ayahs: 2:94-6:32-7:169-12:109-16:30-28:77-28:83-29:64-33:29).",
      "d": "«جزي» «وَمَا تُجْزَوْنَ إِلَّا مَا كُنتُمْ تَعْمَلُونَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "The Hereafter",
      "hw": "Hereafter",
      "s": "‘Dar al-Qarar’ refers to the good abode that Allah will grant to the believers in return for their righteous deeds, i.e., Paradise (1 verse: 40:39).",
      "d": "«سَکَنَ» «مَنۡ اِلٰہٌ غَیۡرُاللّٰہِ یَاۡتِیۡکُمۡ بِلَیۡلٍ تَسۡکُنُوۡنَ فِیۡہِ» «وَ صَلِّ عَلَیۡہِمۡ ؕ اِنَّ صَلٰوتَکَ سَکَنٌ لَّہُمۡ»"
    },
