      "d": "« » refers to a good state of a person, and   is every thing that fulfills a human's need and can cause his prosperity. This word is used for the genus, whether the favor is little or much. And the words   and   are specific to humans.\n«اَنْعَمَ» «اَنْعَمَ عَلیٰ فَرَسِہ»\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«اِذۡ تَقُوۡلُ لِلَّذِیۡۤ  اَنۡعَمَ اللّٰہُ عَلَیۡہِ وَاَنۡعَمۡتَ عَلَیۡہِ اَمۡسِکۡ عَلَیۡکَ زَوۡجَکَ»\nTranslation: When you say to the one upon whom Allah has bestowed favor and you too have bestowed favor: \"Retain your wife\" (do not divorce her)."
