      "d": "«زَکٰی ، زُكُوًّا» «زَکّٰی» «زَکّٰی نَفْسَہٗ»\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«فَلَا تُزَکُّوۡۤا اَنۡفُسَکُمۡ ؕ ہُوَاَعۡلَمُ بِمَنِ اتَّقٰی»\nTranslation: \"So do not purify yourselves; He is most knowing of who is pious.\" (Jalandhari)\nTranslation: \"So do not boast of your virtues; He knows well him who is guarded.\" (Osmani)\nAnd « » is generally used for the self. And tazkiyah of the self means to purify the self from spiritual diseases, impurities, and bad morals, and to create good attributes. (from maf)\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«قَدۡ اَفۡلَحَ مَنۡ زَکّٰىہَا وَقَدۡ خَابَ مَنۡ دَسّٰىہَا»\nTranslation: \"Indeed, he who purifies it will succeed, and he who corrupts it will fail.\"\nAnd a pure self is the person who is innocent and pure from all kinds of accusations.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«قَالَ اَقَتَلۡتَ نَفۡسًا زَکِیَّۃًۢ بِغَیۡرِ نَفۡسٍ ؕ لَقَدۡ جِئۡتَ شَیۡئًا نُّکۡرًا»\nTranslation: [Moses] said, \"Have you killed a pure soul other than for another soul? You have certainly done a terrible thing.\""
    },
