      "d": "« » in which, besides greatness, strength and intensity are found. Just as hqir and asghar are lesser, similarly azim is above akbar. (110 verses: 2:7-2:49-2:105-2:114-2:255-3:74-3:105-3:172-3:174-3:176-3:179-4:13-4:27-4:40-4:48-4:54-4:67-4:73-4:74-4:93-4:95-4:113-4:114-4:146-4:156-4:162-5:9-5:33-5:41-5:119-6:15-7:59-7:116-7:141-8:28-8:29-8:68-9:20-9:22-9:63-9:72-9:89-9:100-9:101-9:111-9:129-10:15-10:64-12:28-14:6-15:87-16:94-16:106-17:40-19:37-21:76-22:1-23:86-24:11-24:14-24:15-24:16-24:23-26:63-26:135-26:156-26:189-27:23-27:26-28:79-31:13-33:29-33:35-33:53-33:71-37:60-37:76-37:107-37:115-38:67-39:13-40:9-41:35-42:4-43:31-44:57-45:10-46:21-48:5-48:10-48:29-49:3-56:46-56:74-56:76-56:96-57:10-57:12-57:21-57:29-61:12-62:4-64:9-64:15-68:4-69:33-69:52-73:20-78:2-83:5)"
