      "h": "Definition",
      "s": "",
      "d": "« » is expressing gratitude in response to some favor or blessing. (43 verses)\n« » is the word used for the conception and expression of someone's favors and bounties (muf), and its opposite is « ». Meaning to forget someone's favor or to hide a blessing and not let it be apparent. Ingratitude or disbelief in blessings. So, « » is specific compared to « ». If we say that Allah has created the universe's system with excellence, that is « », and if we say that Allah feeds and gives us drink, that is « ».\nVerses: 2:52, 2:56, 2:152, 2:172, 2:185, 2:243, 3:123, 4:147, 5:6, 5:89, 7:10, 7:58, 8:26, 10:60, 12:38, 14:7, 14:37, 16:14, 16:78, 16:114, 22:36, 23:78, 27:19, 27:40, 27:73, 28:73, 29:17, 30:46, 31:12, 31:14, 32:9, 34:13, 34:15, 35:12, 36:35, 36:73, 39:7, 40:61, 45:12, 46:15, 54:35, 56:70, 67:23 (total 43 verses)\n«لَئِنۡ شَکَرۡتُمۡ لَاَزِیۡدَنَّکُمۡ وَ لَئِنۡ کَفَرۡتُمۡ اِنَّ عَذَابِیۡ لَشَدِیۡدٌ»"
