      "hw": "",
      "h": "",
      "s": "",
      "d": "« » means « » (the abode of eternity). (m, m. manjd) That is, after death, the body and soul will be reunited, and the human will be resurrected and given an eternal life in which there will never be death, and the righteous and wicked will be admitted to Paradise or Hell according to their deeds.\n«وَ بِالۡاٰخِرَۃِ ھُمۡ یُوۡقِنُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And the believers are certain about the Hereafter.\nHere, by 'Hereafter' is meant this kind of life. In this regard, the opposite of Hereafter in the Quran is ( ,  ,  ,  ) all of which are used."
    }
