      "hw": "",
      "h": "",
      "s": "« » to loosen a knot or bond, etc. (1 verse: 79:2)",
      "d": "«نَشَطَ» «نَشَطَ الْحَبْلَ» «نَشَطَ الْعُقْدَۃ» «اَلْنَشْط» «نَشَطَ» «حَلَّ» «حَلَّ الْعُقٌدَۃ»\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ النّٰزِعٰتِ غَرۡقًا وَّ النّٰشِطٰتِ نَشۡطًا»\nTranslation: By those angels who enter the body and draw out the soul, and by those who loosen all bonds.\nNote: (Lughat Addad are words that have two separate meanings and those meanings are opposite and contradictory to each other)"
