  "19": [
    {
      "id": 101,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » refers to a sound like clapping (1 verse: 8:35)",
      "d": "«وَمَا کَانَ صَلَاتُہُمۡ عِنۡدَ الۡبَیۡتِ اِلَّا مُکَآءً وَّ تَصۡدِیَۃً»"
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and Its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » (Taghayyuth) is used for the sound of fury and anger, i.e., irritation and harshness. (9 verses: 3:119-3:134-9:15-9:120-22:15-25:12-33:25-48:29-67:8)",
      "d": "« » (Taghayyuth) means fury and rage, i.e., the sound of anger and harshness (Majma'). Figuratively, it refers to the sounds produced by the intensity and fury of the Hellfire.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِذَارَاَتۡہُمۡ مِّنۡ مَّکَانٍۭ بَعِیۡدٍ سَمِعُوۡا لَہَا تَغَیُّظًا وَّ زَفِیۡرًا»\nTranslation: When they see it from a distant place, they will hear its fury and roaring."
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for a very light sound like the sound of footsteps (1 verse: 21:102)",
      "d": "«حَسِیْس» «لَا یَسۡمَعُوۡنَ حَسِیۡسَہَا ۚ وَ ہُمۡ  فِیۡ مَا اشۡتَہَتۡ اَنۡفُسُہُمۡ  خٰلِدُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for the sound of a calf or bull (2 verses: 7:148, 20:88)",
      "d": "«خُوَار» «وَ اتَّخَذَ قَوۡمُ  مُوۡسٰی مِنۡۢ بَعۡدِہٖ مِنۡ حُلِیِّہِمۡ عِجۡلًا جَسَدًا لَّہٗ خُوَارٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for a very faint sound like the buzzing of a fly (1 verse: 19:98)",
      "d": "«رِکْز» «وَکَمۡ اَہۡلَکۡنَا قَبۡلَہُمۡ مِّنۡ قَرۡنٍ ؕ ہَلۡ تُحِسُّ مِنۡہُمۡ مِّنۡ  اَحَدٍ اَوۡ تَسۡمَعُ لَہُمۡ رِکۡزًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 107,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » refers to the high-pitched sound at the end of a donkey's bray (2 verses: 11:106, 67:7)",
      "d": "«شَھِیْق» «فَاَمَّا الَّذِیۡنَ شَقُوۡا فَفِی النَّارِ لَہُمۡ فِیۡہَا زَفِیۡرٌ  وَّ شَہِیۡقٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 109,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for screaming, shouting, or groaning (2 verses: 15:94, 43:57)",
      "d": "«یَصِدُّ صَدِیْدًا» «وَ لَمَّا ضُرِبَ ابۡنُ مَرۡیَمَ  مَثَلًا  اِذَا قَوۡمُکَ مِنۡہُ  یَصِدُّوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 110,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for the sound of shouting in the form of a cry for help (3 verses: 14:22, 28:18, 35:37)",
      "d": "«صَرَخَ» «وَہُمۡ یَصۡطَرِخُوۡنَ فِیۡہَا ۚ رَبَّنَاۤ اَخۡرِجۡنَا نَعۡمَلۡ صَالِحًا غَیۡرَ الَّذِیۡ کُنَّا نَعۡمَلُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for every kind of sound, whether faint or loud, from a living being or inanimate object, meaningless or meaningful (3 verses: 17:64, 31:19, 49:2)",
      "d": "«صَوْت» «یٰۤاَیُّہَا  الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا لَا تَرۡفَعُوۡۤا اَصۡوَاتَکُمۡ  فَوۡقَ صَوۡتِ النَّبِیِّ» «صَد، صَرَخ، ھَمَس، حَسِیْس، مُکَاء (مَکُو) تَصْدِیَۃ، ضَبَح، خُوَار، زَفِیْر، شَھِیْق، لَھَث»"
    },
    {
      "id": 113,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sounds and Their Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for a loud and meaningless sound (13 verses: 11:67, 11:94, 15:73, 15:83, 23:41, 29:40, 36:29, 36:49, 36:53, 38:15, 50:42, 54:31, 63:4)",
      "d": "«صَیْحَۃً» «صَیْحَۃً» «فَاَخَذَتۡہُمُ الصَّیۡحَۃُ  مُشۡرِقِیۡنَ . فَجَعَلۡنَا عَالِیَہَا سَافِلَہَا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 114,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for the sound of panting while running (1 verse: 100:1)",
      "d": "«ضَبَحَ» «وَالۡعٰدِیٰتِ ضَبۡحًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 115,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sounds and Their Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for the sound of a cauldron boiling (3 verses: 44:45, 44:46)",
      "d": "«غَلْی» «کَالۡمُہۡلِ یَغۡلِیۡ  فِی الۡبُطُوۡنِ . کَغَلۡیِ  الۡحَمِیۡمِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 117,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » refers to the sound of a dog panting or gasping due to intense heat or thirst. (1 Verse: 7:176)",
      "d": "« » is the sound of a dog panting, caused by intense heat or thirst, where it sticks out its tongue and pants or gasps. (Source: Mufradat, Manjad)\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَمَثَلُہٗ کَمَثَلِ الۡکَلۡبِ ۚ اِنۡ تَحۡمِلۡ عَلَیۡہِ یَلۡہَثۡ اَوۡ تَتۡرُکۡہُ یَلۡہَثۡ»\nTranslation: The example of such a person is that of a dog; if you attack it, it pants, and if you leave it, it still pants.\nIt is also used for the sounds of inanimate objects."
    },
    {
      "id": 118,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for producing a whistling sound from the mouth. (1 Verse: 8:35)",
      "d": "« » means to whistle (Manjad), and it encompasses all melodies and tunes within it."
    },
    {
      "id": 119,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » is used for the sound of a building, wall, pillar, etc., collapsing. (1 Verse: 19:90)",
      "d": "« » refers to the sound of something like a building, wall, or pillar collapsing, such as a thudding sound. (Source: F L 194)\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«تَکَادُ السَّمٰوٰتُ یَتَفَطَّرۡنَ مِنۡہُ وَ تَنۡشَقُّ الۡاَرۡضُ وَ تَخِرُّ الۡجِبَالُ ہَدًّا»\nTranslation: The heavens are almost torn apart from above it, and the earth splits open, and the mountains crash down utterly."
    },
    {
      "id": 120,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Sound and its Types",
      "hw": "Sound",
      "s": "« » refers to any slight sound produced by a person's movement. (1 Verse: 20:108)",
      "d": "«ھَمْس» «اَلصَّوْتُ الْخَفِیِّ وَاَحَسّ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ خَشَعَتِ الۡاَصۡوَاتُ لِلرَّحۡمٰنِ فَلَا تَسۡمَعُ اِلَّا ہَمۡسًا»\nTranslation: And all voices will be humbled before the Most Merciful, so you will hear nothing but a whisper."
    }
  ],
  "20": [
    {
      "id": 121,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Gradually",
      "hw": " آہستہ",
      "s": "« » means to approach something else degree by degree and gradually. (2 Verses: 7:182, 68:44)",
      "d": "« » refers to the steps of a ladder when climbing up, while « » means to bring one thing near another gradually and step by step (Mufradat), so that it goes unnoticed. Thus, « » necessitates gradualness and caution in such matters.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ الَّذِیۡنَ کَذَّبُوۡا بِاٰیٰتِنَا سَنَسۡتَدۡرِجُہُمۡ مِّنۡ حَیۡثُ لَا یَعۡلَمُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And those who deny Our signs, We will gradually seize them from where they perceive not. (Jalandhari) We will seize them gradually. (Osmani)"
    },
    {
      "id": 123,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Gradually",
      "hw": " آہستہ",
      "s": "« » refers to wind blowing so gently and softly that it does not stir anything. (1 Verse: 38:36)",
      "d": "« » means wind blowing so gently and gradually that it does not move anything (Manjad). It signifies wind moving softly and slowly (Source: F L 46).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَسَخَّرۡنَا لَہُ الرِّیۡحَ تَجۡرِیۡ بِاَمۡرِہٖ رُخَآءً حَیۡثُ اَصَابَ»\nTranslation: Then We subjected the wind to him, so it blew gently in his direction wherever he willed."
    },
    {
      "id": 125,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Gradually",
      "hw": " آہستہ",
      "s": "« » refers to wind blowing with gentleness, where it carries comfort and peace. (1 Verse: 77:1)",
      "d": "« » means wind blowing softly, bringing peace and comfort. « » means fragrance. It is often used for fragrance (Manjad). And such winds that generally blow at a gentle pace. The breeze of dawn.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ الۡمُرۡسَلٰتِ عُرۡفًا»\nTranslation: By the winds sent forth, gently (Osmani)."
    },
    {
      "id": 126,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Gradually",
      "hw": " آہستہ",
      "s": "« » means to accomplish a task effortlessly, with ease and facility, without any resistance. (19 Verses: 2:185, 2:280, 18:88, 19:97, 20:26, 44:58, 51:3, 54:17, 54:22, 54:32, 54:40, 65:4, 65:7, 80:20, 87:8, 92:7, 92:10, 94:5, 94:6)",
      "d": "« » means ease and facility, and its opposite is « », meaning hardship. The word « » also describes a state where a task is accomplished effortlessly and smoothly, without any jolt or obstacle.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَالۡجٰرِیٰتِ یُسۡرًا»\nTranslation: Then the ships sailing with ease. (Jalandhari) Then the ships moving along easily. (Osmani)\nHere, « » does not imply slowness but rather that despite moving swiftly, there is no jolt, sway, or sound produced, making it seem as if they are moving gently and smoothly."
    }
  ],
  "21": [
    {
      "id": 127,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Boiling / Seething",
      "hw": "اُبلنا",
      "s": "« » means to boil or surge due to heat, exceeding its original level because of an obstruction. (2 Verses: 44:45, 44:46)",
      "d": "«غَلَا» «غَلَا الْقِدْر» «غَلَا السَّعْر»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«کَالۡمُہۡلِ ۚ ۛ یَغۡلِیۡ فِی الۡبُطُوۡنِ کَغَلۡیِ الۡحَمِیۡمِ»\nTranslation: Like molten metal; it will boil within their bellies like the boiling of hot water."
    },
    {
      "id": 128,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Boiling / Seething",
      "hw": "اُبلنا",
      "s": "« » means the continuous boiling or seething of something due to intensity and haste. (2 Verses: 11:40, 23:27)",
      "d": "«فَار» «اَلْفَوْر» «رَجَعَ مِنْ فَوْرَہٗ» «فوارہ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«حَتّٰۤی اِذَا جَآءَ اَمۡرُنَا وَ فَارَ التَّنُّوۡرُ»\nTranslation: Until, when Our command came and the oven boiled over."
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "To boil; to surge",
      "hw": "اُبلنا",
      "s": "« » means water gushing forth forcefully due to abundance and pressure (1 Verse: 55:66)",
      "d": "«نَضَخَ» «نَضَخَ» «نَضَّاخ» «عَیْنٌ نَضَّاخَۃٌ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فِیۡہِمَا عَیۡنٰنِ نَضَّاخَتٰنِ»\nTranslation: In both (gardens) are two gushing springs."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "a": "نَکَسَ",
      "arabic_raw": "نکس",
      "ayaat": [
        [
          21,
          65
        ],
        [
          36,
          68
        ]
      ],
      "hw": "",
      "h": "",
      "s": "",
      "d": "«حَورَتِ الْعَیْن»\n«اَحْوَرْ» «حَوْرَاء» «حُوْر»\n«حُوۡرٌ مَّقۡصُوۡرٰتٌ فِی  الۡخِیَامِ»\n«وَ حُوۡرٌ عِیۡنٌ کَاَمۡثَالِ اللُّؤۡلُوءِ  الۡمَکۡنُوۡنِ»"
    }
