  "40": [
    {
      "id": 217,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "to obey (to follow, to be a follower, to carry out commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » means to follow behind someone or to walk in their footsteps, and it is used in both outward and inward senses (150 verses: 2:38-2:102-2:120-2:143-2:145-2:166-2:167-2:168-2:170-2:208-2:262-2:263-3:7-3:20-3:31-3:53-3:55-3:68-3:73-3:95-3:162-3:167-3:174-4:27-4:83-4:115-4:125-4:135-5:16-5:48-5:49-5:77-6:50-6:56-6:106-6:116-6:142-6:148-6:150-6:153-6:155-7:3-7:18-7:90-7:142-7:157-7:158-7:175-7:176-7:193-7:203-8:64-9:42-9:100-9:117-10:15-10:35-10:36-10:66-10:89-10:90-10:109-11:27-11:59-11:60-11:97-11:99-11:116-12:38-12:108-13:37-14:21-14:36-14:44-15:18-15:42-15:65-16:123-17:47-17:63-18:28-18:66-18:70-18:85-18:89-18:92-19:43-19:59-20:16-20:47-20:78-20:90-20:93-20:108-20:123-20:134-22:3-23:44-23:71-24:21-25:8-26:40-26:52-26:60-26:111-26:215-26:224-28:35-28:42-28:47-28:49-28:50-28:57-29:12-30:29-31:15-31:21-33:2-34:20-36:11-36:20-36:21-37:10-38:26-38:85-39:18-39:55-40:7-40:38-40:47-42:15-43:61-44:23-45:18-46:9-47:3-47:14-47:16-47:28-48:15-52:21-53:23-53:28-54:3-54:24-57:27-71:21-75:18-77:17-79:7)",
      "d": "« » means to follow behind someone or to walk in their footsteps (lit.) and it is used in both outward and inward senses. Inwardly, such as following the guidance of religion or following a person's habits and character.\n«فَمَنۡ تَبِعَ ہُدَایَ فَلَا خَوۡفٌ عَلَیۡہِمۡ وَلَا ہُمۡ یَحۡزَنُوۡنَ»\nAnd outwardly, for following someone behind, « » is used.\n«فَاَتۡبَعَہُمۡ فِرۡعَوۡنُ بِجُنُوۡدِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 218,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "to obey (to follow, to be a follower, to carry out commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » means to follow someone and to do as they do, and « » means to follow someone in goodness and the path of religion (Munjid) as is the case when a follower (muqtadi) follows the Imam in prayer (2 verses: 6:90-43:23)",
      "d": "« » means to follow someone and to do as they do, and « » means to follow someone in goodness and the path of religion (Munjid) as is the case when a follower (muqtadi) follows the Imam in prayer.\n«اُولٰٓئِکَ الَّذِیۡنَ ہَدَی اللّٰہُ  فَبِہُدٰىہُمُ اقۡتَدِہۡ»\nAnd the word iqtida can also be used in a bad sense. « » actually refers to the state of a person when they are a follower of another (lit.) and « » also means a leader, guide, or exemplar.\n«اِنَّا وَجَدۡنَاۤ اٰبَآءَنَاعَلٰۤی اُمَّۃٍ وَّ اِنَّاعَلٰۤی اٰثٰرِہِمۡ مُّقۡتَدُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 220,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "to obey (to follow, to be a follower, to carry out commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » to carry out someone's command with happiness of heart (13 verses: 2:184-3:83-3:168-4:64-4:80-4:81-13:15-24:53-40:18-41:11-43:54-47:21-81:21)",
      "d": "« » means to carry out someone's command with happiness of heart.\n« » means happiness and consent, and its opposite is « » meaning aversion, hatred, dislike. And « » refers to obedience that is performed with happiness of heart.\n«فَقَالَ لَہَا وَ لِلۡاَرۡضِ ائۡتِیَا طَوۡعًا اَوۡ کَرۡہًا ؕ قَالَتَاۤ اَتَیۡنَا طَآئِعِیۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 221,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "to obey (to follow, to be a follower, to carry out commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » to accept a command and act upon it, to agree, and this is possible even from a subordinate (20 verses: 2:186-3:172-3:195-6:36-7:194-8:9-8:24-11:14-12:34-13:14-13:18-17:52-28:50-28:64-35:14-42:16-42:26-42:38-42:47-46:5)",
      "d": "« » means to answer, to agree, to obey, and to accept a command. It is used in all these senses. The difference between obedience and response is that obedience is only done to a superior, while response can be done by a subordinate to a superior if it is in relation to Allah, it means accepting the servant's supplication, and if it is in relation to a servant, it means the servant accepting Allah's command (Faqih 184).\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوا اسۡتَجِیۡبُوۡا لِلّٰہِ وَ لِلرَّسُوۡلِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 222,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "To obey (to follow, to show allegiance, to comply with commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » to bow one's head in submission before someone's pleasure (17 verses: 2:112-2:131-3:20-3:83-4:65-4:125-5:44-6:14-6:71-22:34-27:44-37:103-39:54-40:66-49:14-49:17-72:14)",
      "d": "«As-Salam» «aslama» «اِذۡ قَالَ لَہٗ رَبُّہٗۤ  اَسۡلِمۡ ۙ قَالَ اَسۡلَمۡتُ لِرَبِّ الۡعٰلَمِیۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 223,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "To obey (to follow, to show allegiance, to comply with commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » such obedience in worship that also includes humility and meekness (2 verses: 3:43-33:31)",
      "d": "«Qunut» «وَ مَنۡ یَّقۡنُتۡ مِنۡکُنَّ لِلّٰہِ وَ رَسُوۡلِہٖ وَ تَعۡمَلۡ صَالِحًا نُّؤۡتِہَاۤ اَجۡرَہَا مَرَّتَیۡنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 224,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "To obey (to follow, to show allegiance, to comply with commands)",
      "hw": "اطاعت",
      "s": "« » to obey someone for one's own interests (1 verse: 24:49)",
      "d": "«Dha'ana» «mudh'aan» «naaqatun mudh'aanun» «ذَعَنَ» «وَ اِنۡ یَّکُنۡ  لَّہُمُ الۡحَقُّ یَاۡتُوۡۤا اِلَیۡہِ مُذۡعِنِیۡنَ» «مُذْعِنِیْن» «مُطِیْعِیْن و سَارِعِیْن»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3900,
      "hw": "Dabuna",
      "s": "« » to immerse (2 verses: 2:138-23:20)",
      "d": "",
      "h": "To immerse"
    },
