  "41": [
    {
      "id": 225,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "moderation",
      "hw": "اعتدال",
      "s": "« » to avoid excess and deficiency in an action and choose the path of moderation (3 verses: 9:42-16:9-31:19)",
      "d": "« » and « » both mean to choose the middle path while avoiding excess and deficiency. The only difference is that « » is generally used in the context of expenditures and spending, whereas « » is a general term.\n«وَ اقۡصِدۡ فِیۡ  مَشۡیِکَ»\n«قَصْدُ السَّبِیۡل»\n«وَعَلَی اللّٰہِ قَصۡدُ السَّبِیۡلِ وَ مِنۡہَا جَآئِرٌ»\nNote: (Excess and deficiency: less and more, unbalanced state, less and more, a little and a lot. Excess: means to exceed the limit, to exaggerate in describing someone's status. The Quran has described it as ' ' and in Arabic it is also called ' ' (Excessiveness). Deficiency: means to decrease in someone's status and lower them from their rank.)"
    },
    {
      "id": 226,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "moderation",
      "hw": "اعتدال",
      "s": "« » is used for the middle of a single thing or the middle thing among two or more things (2 verses: 2:143-2:238)",
      "d": "« » is the middle of a single thing or the middle among two or more things. It seems this word is stronger than « » and « » means in every matter to choose the middle and moderate path.\n«وَ کَذٰلِکَ جَعَلۡنٰکُمۡ اُمَّۃً وَّسَطًا لِّتَکُوۡنُوۡا شُہَدَآءَ عَلَی النَّاسِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 227,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Moderation",
      "hw": "اعتدال",
      "s": "« » to maintain moderation from every aspect in one thing (1 verse: 95:4)",
      "d": "«تَقْوِیْم» «قَوْمُ الشَّیءِ» «تَقْوِیْمُ الْبَدَان» «قَوَّمَ دَرْأَہٗ»\n«لَقَدۡ خَلَقۡنَا الۡاِنۡسَانَ فِیۡۤ  اَحۡسَنِ تَقۡوِیۡمٍ»"
    },
