      "id": 412,
      "a": "ل",
      "h": "Child (Boy)",
      "hw": "لڑکا",
      "s": "« » immature child (4  : 22:5-24:31-24:59-40:67)",
      "d": "« » means soft and delicate, and « » refers to a woman with a tender body. Therefore, as long as the child remains soft and delicate, he is « » (pl.  ). However, it refers to children who have not yet reached puberty. Its plural is  .\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَاِذَا بَلَغَ الۡاَطۡفَالُ مِنۡکُمُ الۡحُلُمَ فَلۡیَسۡتَاۡذِنُوۡا کَمَا اسۡتَاۡذَنَ الَّذِیۡنَ مِنۡ قَبۡلِہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And when your children reach puberty, they should seek permission as those before them used to do.\nThis verse clarifies that after puberty, the child exits the stage of childhood and enters the stage of adulthood."
    },
    {
      "id": 413,
      "a": "ل",
      "h": "Child (Boy)",
      "hw": "لڑکا",
      "s": "« » ignorant child engaged in childish habits and play (2  : 19:12-19:29)",
      "d": "«صَبِیٌّ» «صَبِیٌّ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«یٰیَحۡیٰی خُذِ الۡکِتٰبَ بِقُوَّۃٍ ؕ وَاٰتَیۡنٰہُ الۡحُکۡمَ صَبِیًّا»\nTranslation: O Yahya! Hold the Book with strength. And We gave him wisdom while he was still a child (i.e., at an age when other children are occupied with play)."
    },
    {
      "id": 414,
      "a": "ل",
      "h": "Child (Boy)",
      "hw": "لڑکا",
      "s": "« » a boy who has reached puberty (13  : 3:40-12:19-15:53-18:74-18:80-18:82-19:7-19:8-19:19-19:20-37:101-51:28-52:24)",
      "d": "«غُلَامٌ» «اِغْتَلَمَ الْفَحْلُ غُلْمَۃً» «غَلِیْم» «اِغلَام» «غُلَام» «غِلْمَۃٌ» «غِلْمَانٌ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَیَطُوۡفُ عَلَیۡہِمۡ غِلۡمَانٌ لَّہُمۡ کَاَنَّہُمۡ لُؤۡلُؤٌ مَّکۡنُوۡنٌ»\nTranslation: And young boys will circulate among them, as if they were hidden pearls."
    }
