      "id": 416,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "To spread",
      "hw": "بچھانا",
      "s": "« » to spread or lay out and then level it (1  : 88:20)",
      "d": "«سَطَحَ» «سَطَحَ الْبَیْتَ» «مَسْطَحْ» «سَطْح» «اَلسَّطْحُ اَعْلَی الْبَیْتِ جُعِلَ سَوِیًّا»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَاِلَی الۡاَرۡضِ کَیۡفَ سُطِحَتۡ»\nTranslation: And (do they not look) at the earth, how it is spread out (i.e., how its surface has been made level)?"
    },
    {
      "id": 417,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "To spread",
      "hw": "بچھانا",
      "s": "« » to spread something completely or lay it out and level it (5  : 2:22-6:142-51:48-55:54-56:34)",
      "d": "«فَرَشَ» «فرش» «فِراش» «فَرَشَ الدَّار»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«الَّذِیۡ جَعَلَ لَکُمُ الۡاَرۡضَ فِرَاشًا وَّالسَّمَآءَ بِنَآءً»\nTranslation: Who has made the earth a spread for you and the sky a canopy."
    },
    {
      "id": 418,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "To spread",
      "hw": "بچھانا",
      "s": "« » to spread while also providing means of upbringing (7  : 3:46-5:110-19:29-20:53-30:44-43:10-74:14)",
      "d": "«سَطَحَ» «مَھَدَ» «مَھْد» «مَھَدَ الْاَرْض»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَّمَہَّدۡتُّ لَہٗ  تَمۡہِیۡدًا ثُمَّ  یَطۡمَعُ اَنۡ اَزِیۡدَ»\nTranslation: And I have spread out for him every kind of ease. Yet he desires that I give more!\nAt another place, the Almighty says:\n«وَالۡاَرۡضَ فَرَشۡنٰہَا فَنِعۡمَ الۡمٰہِدُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And the earth We have spread out; how excellent are the Spreaders!\nThis verse also proves that « » has a broader meaning than « », i.e., preparing related provisions beyond necessity."
    }
  ],
  "88": [
    {
      "id": 419,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Spread",
      "hw": "بچھونا",
      "s": "« » metaphorically refers to the earth, which provides a place of upbringing and rest for all creatures (7 verses: 2:206-3:12-3:197-7:41-13:18-38:56-78:6)",
      "d": "« » means to spread and provide means of upbringing. As detailed above. Allah has described the earth as « » because both these aspects are found in it.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اَلَمۡ  نَجۡعَلِ الۡاَرۡضَ مِہٰدًا»\nTranslation: Have We not made the earth a spread?"
    },
    {
      "id": 420,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Spread (noun)",
      "hw": "بچھونا",
      "s": "« » generally used for bed or sheet (5  : 2:22-6:142-51:48-55:54-56:34)",
      "d": "«فَرَشَ» «اَلْفَرَش» «فَرَشَ الرَّجُلُ» «فِرَاش» «اَلْوَلَدُ لِلْفِرَاشِ» «لِلْعَاہِرِ الْحَجَر» «فُرُشٍ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«مُتَّکِئِیۡنَ عَلٰی فُرُشٍۭ بَطَآئِنُہَا مِنۡ اِسۡتَبۡرَقٍ»\nTranslation: Reclining on beds, whose linings are of rich brocade."
    }
