      "id": 494,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Great (Magnificent)",
      "hw": "بزرگ ",
      "s": "« » in which greatness is accompanied by strength and intensity. Just as insignificant is lower than minor, similarly   is above akbar. (110 verses: 2:7-2:49-2:105-2:114-2:255-3:74-3:105-3:172-3:174-3:176-3:179-4:13-4:27-4:40-4:48-4:54-4:67-4:73-4:74-4:93-4:95-4:113-4:114-4:146-4:156-4:162-5:9-5:33-5:41-5:119-6:15-7:59-7:116-7:141-8:28-8:29-8:68-9:20-9:22-9:63-9:72-9:89-9:100-9:101-9:111-9:129-10:15-10:64-12:28-14:6-15:87-16:94-16:106-17:40-19:37-21:76-22:1-23:86-24:11-24:14-24:15-24:16-24:23-26:63-26:135-26:156-26:189-27:23-27:26-28:79-31:13-33:29-33:35-33:53-33:71-37:60-37:76-37:107-37:115-38:67-39:13-40:9-41:35-42:4-43:31-44:57-45:10-46:21-48:5-48:10-48:29-49:3-56:46-56:74-56:76-56:96-57:10-57:12-57:21-57:29-61:12-62:4-64:9-64:15-68:4-69:33-69:52-73:20-78:2-83:5)",
      "d": "«عَظِیْم» «حَقِیْر» «اَعْظَمَ ، عَظْمٌ» «عَظْم» «عَظْم» «عَظِیْم» «عِظَام» «عَظِیْم» «اَعْظَمَ»\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَّ لَہُمۡ عَذَابٌ عَظِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: And for those disbelievers is a great punishment.\n«فَسَبِّحۡ  بِاسۡمِ  رَبِّکَ الۡعَظِیۡمِ»\nTranslation: So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great.\nIn a group, there can be many « » and « », but « » is only one (Fiqh 150)."
    },
    {
      "id": 495,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Great (Magnificent)",
      "hw": "بزرگ ",
      "s": "« » greatness in honor and status; specifically for the blessed essence of Allah alone. (2 verses: 55:27-55:78)",
      "d": "«جَلَال» «ذُوْالْجَلَال» «عَظِیمُ الْمَرْتَبَت» «جَلِیْل»\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«تَبٰرَکَ اسۡمُ رَبِّکَ ذِی الۡجَلٰلِ وَالۡاِکۡرَامِ»\nTranslation: Blessed is the name of your Lord, the Possessor of Majesty and Honor. (Uthmani)"
    },
    {
      "id": 496,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Great (Magnificent)",
      "hw": "بزرگ ",
      "s": "« » the entity that has reached the utmost limit in glory, honor, and nobility. (4 verses: 11:73-50:1-85:15-85:21)",
      "d": "The meanings of « » are to be vast in glory and honor (Muf). And according to Ibn al-Faris: one who has reached the utmost limit in grace, honor, and nobility (M. L). And « » means one who is great in people's sight (M. Q).\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَہُوَالۡغَفُوۡرُ الۡوَدُوۡدُ ذُوالۡعَرۡشِ الۡمَجِیۡدُ»\nTranslation: And He is the Forgiving, the Affectionate, the Owner of the Throne, the Magnificent."
    },
    {
      "id": 498,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Greatness (Magnificence)",
      "hw": "بزرگ ",
      "s": "« » the ultimate degree of greatness in honor and status. (2 verses: 55:27-55:78)",
      "d": "« » is greatness in honor and status, the ultimate degree after which there is no other rank. And the word « » is specific only to Allah the Almighty. Whereas « » can be for other things as well. And « » is everything that is great and strong in all matters. Magnificent (Muf).\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«تَبٰرَکَ اسۡمُ رَبِّکَ ذِی الۡجَلٰلِ وَالۡاِکۡرَامِ»\nTranslation: Blessed is the name of your Lord, the Possessor of Majesty and Honor."
    },
    {
      "id": 499,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Greatness (Magnificence)",
      "hw": "بزرگ ",
      "s": "« » divine grace, as He grants greatness to others as well. (1 verse: 72:3)",
      "d": "«جَدّ» «جُدِدْتُ» «جَدَّ» «جَدّ» «جَدّ» «اَجْدَاد» «فُلَانٌ ذُوْجَدٍّ»\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَّاَنَّہٗ تَعٰلٰی جَدُّ رَبِّنَا مَا اتَّخَذَ صَاحِبَۃً وَّلَا وَلَدًا»\nTranslation: And indeed, the greatness of our Lord is exalted; He has not taken a wife or a son."
    }
  ],
  "102": [
    {
      "id": 502,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Increase and Causing Increase",
      "hw": "بڑھنا",
      "s": "« » is used to mean double or even more (10 verses: 2:245-2:261-3:130-4:40-11:20-25:69-33:30-57:11-57:18-64:17)",
      "d": "«ضِعْفٌ» «نِصْف» «ضَعَفَ الشَّيء» «ضَعَّف» «ضَاعَفَ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَاللّٰہُ یُضٰعِفُ لِمَنۡ یَّشَآءُ ؕ وَاللّٰہُ وَاسِعٌ عَلِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: And Allah gives increase manifold to whom He wills. And Allah is All-Encompassing and Knowing."
    },
    {
      "id": 503,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "To Increase and to Cause to Increase",
      "hw": "بڑھنا",
      "s": "« » means to leave something in its state so that it may increase. (2 verses: 2:219-7:95)",
      "d": "«عَفَا» «عَفَا اَلْشَعْر» «قَصُّوا الشَّوَارِبَ وَاعْفُوا اللُّحْیٰ» «ثُمَّ بَدَّلۡنَا مَکَانَ السَّیِّئَۃَ الۡحَسَنَۃَ حَتّٰی عَفَوۡا» «عَفْو» «وَیَسۡئَلُوۡنَکَ مَا ذَا یُنۡفِقُوۡنَ ۬ ؕ قُلِ الۡعَفۡوَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 504,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Increase and Causing Increase",
      "hw": "بڑھنا",
      "s": "« » means to do a good deed or give charity, etc., of one's own free will (7 verses: 2:158-2:184-3:83-9:53-9:79-13:15-41:11)",
      "d": "The basic meaning of « » is to obey with happiness of the heart. The original meaning of « » is to perform a command with great effort. However, in common usage, it refers to good deeds and acts of worship performed voluntarily, beyond the obligatory duties, out of one's own desire—such as voluntary prayers and charities.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَعَلَی الَّذِیۡنَ یُطِیۡقُوۡنَہٗ فِدۡیَۃٌ طَعَامُ مِسۡکِیۡنٍ ؕ فَمَنۡ تَطَوَّعَ خَیۡرًا فَہُوَ خَیۡرٌ لَّہٗ»\nTranslation: And for those who cannot afford it, the expiation is the feeding of a poor person. Then whoever volunteers good (by doing more than the minimum), it is better for him."
    },
    {
      "id": 505,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Increase and Augmentation",
      "hw": "بڑھنا",
      "s": "« » refers to voluntary acts of worship such as charity, tahajjud prayer, voluntary fasts, etc. (3 verses: 8:1-17:79-21:72)",
      "d": "«نَفْل» «اَنْفَال» «نَفْل» «تَطَوُّع» «تَطَوُّع» «وَمِنَ الَّیۡلِ فَتَہَجَّدۡ بِہٖ نَافِلَۃً لَّکَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 506,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Increase and Augmentation",
      "hw": "بڑھنا",
      "s": "« » means to nurture or raise something. (6 verses: 2:275-2:276-2:278-3:130-4:161-30:39)",
      "d": "«رِبَا الْمَال» «رِبٰو» «رِبَا الْفَرْس» «رِبَا الْوَلْد» «اَرْبٰی» «یَمۡحَقُ اللّٰہُ الرِّبٰوا وَیُرۡبِی الصَّدَقٰتِ»"
    }
  ],
  "103": [
