      "hw": "پھونک",
      "s": "« » to blow out a lamp or extinguish a fire (3 verses: 5:64-9:32-61:8)",
      "d": "«طَفَئَتِ النَّار» «اَطْفَاَ» «یُرِیۡدُوۡنَ لِیُطۡفِئُوۡا نُوۡرَاللّٰہِ بِاَفۡوَاہِہِمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "172": [
    {
      "id": 837,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "To spread",
      "hw": "پھیلانا",
      "s": "« » to raise, to spread, and to publicize (11 verses: 17:13-18:16-21:21-42:28-43:11-44:35-74:52-77:3-80:22-81:10-94:1)",
      "d": "«نَشَرَ» «طَوَي» «نَشَرَتُ الْکِتَابَ ثُمَّ طَوَیْتُہٗ» «وَ ہُوَ الَّذِیۡ یُنَزِّلُ الۡغَیۡثَ مِنۡۢ بَعۡدِ مَا قَنَطُوۡا وَ یَنۡشُرُ رَحۡمَتَہٗ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 838,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "To spread",
      "hw": "پھیلانا",
      "s": "« » meaning to open, to spread, and to make vast (22 verses: 2:245-2:247-5:11-5:28-6:93-7:69-13:14-13:26-17:29-17:30-18:18-28:82-29:62-30:37-30:48-34:36-34:39-39:52-42:12-42:27-60:2-71:19)",
      "d": "«بَسَطَ» «بَسَاطُ» «قَبَضَ» «قَدَرَ» «اَللّٰہُ الَّذِیۡ یُرۡسِلُ الرِّیٰحَ فَتُثِیۡرُ سَحَابًا فَیَبۡسُطُہٗ فِی السَّمَآءِ کَیۡفَ یَشَآءُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 839,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "to spread",
      "hw": "پھیلانا",
      "s": "« » to spread in such a way that its parts are scattered and dispersed (8 verses: 2:164-4:1-31:10-42:29-45:4-56:6-88:16-101:4)",
      "d": "« » means scattered (i.e., scattered, dispersed, scattered, distributed). And « » is also used for a distressed state and intense grief (manjad). Thus, « » is used in the meanings of spreading such that the parts of that thing are scattered. Like dust or the wick of a lamp.\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا النَّاسُ اتَّقُوۡا رَبَّکُمُ الَّذِیۡ خَلَقَکُمۡ مِّنۡ نَّفۡسٍ وَّاحِدَۃٍ وَّ خَلَقَ مِنۡہَا زَوۡجَہَا وَ بَثَّ مِنۡہُمَا رِجَالًا کَثِیۡرًا وَّ نِسَآءً»\nTranslation: O people! Fear your Lord, who created you from a single soul, and created from it its mate, and then spread many men and women from them both across the earth."
    }
  ],
  "173": [
    {
      "id": 840,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "To throw",
      "hw": "پھینکنا",
      "s": "« » to throw something away without regard, i.e., to discard it (10 verses: 2:100-2:101-3:187-8:58-20:96-28:40-37:145-51:40-68:49-104:4)",
      "d": "« » means to throw something considering it useless and worthless, to discard it without regard (muf. Fal 190).\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«اَوَ کُلَّمَا عٰہَدُوۡا عَہۡدًا نَّبَذَہٗ فَرِیۡقٌ مِّنۡہُمۡ»\nTranslation: Whenever they made a covenant, a group among them would throw it away (disregard it)."
    },
    {
      "id": 841,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "To throw",
      "hw": "پھینکنا",
      "s": "« » to throw something considering it worthless and reject it. (1 verse: 12:9)",
      "d": "«طَرَحَ» «رَاَیْتُہٗ مِنْ طَرْح» «طَرُوْحُ» «طَرَحَ»\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«اقۡتُلُوۡا یُوۡسُفَ اَوِ اطۡرَحُوۡہُ  اَرۡضًا یَّخۡلُ لَکُمۡ وَجۡہُ  اَبِیۡکُمۡ»\nTranslation: (The brothers of Yusuf said) Either kill Yusuf or throw him into some land, so that your father's attention may be solely towards you."
    },
    {
      "id": 842,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "To throw",
      "hw": "پھینکنا",
      "s": "« » to throw stones from a distance to kill or to stone (6 verses: 11:91-18:20-18:22-19:46-36:18-44:20)",
      "d": "« » to throw stones and pebbles to kill someone, to stone (Fal 189).\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«اِنَّہُمۡ اِنۡ یَّظۡہَرُوۡا عَلَیۡکُمۡ یَرۡجُمُوۡکُمۡ اَوۡ یُعِیۡدُوۡکُمۡ فِیۡ مِلَّتِہِمۡ»\nTranslation: If they gain power over you, they will stone you or force you back into their religion."
    },
    {
      "id": 844,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "To throw",
      "hw": "پھینکنا",
      "s": "« » for a river to throw its foam or a pot's scum to the banks (1 verse: 13:17)",
      "d": "«اَلْجَفَاء» «اَجْفَاْتِ الْقِدْرِزَ بَدَہَا»\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«فَاَمَّا الزَّبَدُ فَیَذۡہَبُ جُفَآءً»\nTranslation: And the foam goes away as scum (i.e., the river throws it onto the banks where it dries up)."
    }
  ],
  "174": [
    {
      "id": 845,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Thirsty. To be thirsty.",
      "hw": "پیاسا",
      "s": "« » to be restless from thirst (3 verses: 9:120-20:119-24:39)",
      "d": "« » means to be thirsty. And « » means thirst. And « » is a degree higher than « » (thirst) (Fal 162). And « » is the intensive form of the noun, meaning a person who is very restless from thirst, extremely thirsty.\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«وَالَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡۤا اَعۡمَالُہُمۡ کَسَرَابٍۭ بِقِیۡعَۃٍ یَّحۡسَبُہُ الظَّمۡاٰنُ مَآءً»\nTranslation: And the deeds of those who disbelieved are like a mirage in a lowland which the thirsty one thinks is water."
    },
    {
      "id": 846,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Thirsty. To be thirsty.",
      "hw": "پیاسا",
      "s": "« » A thirsty person who sets out in search of water (2 verses: 11:98-19:86)",
      "d": "« » refers to a thirsty man or caravan that sets out in search of water (m.f.) and « » means to reach a water source to drink (12/90). Also, « » means water source (11/98), and « » also means water source. The opposite of « » is « », meaning to return after drinking water.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَّ نَسُوۡقُ الۡمُجۡرِمِیۡنَ اِلٰی جَہَنَّمَ وِرۡدًا»\nTranslation: And We will drive the criminals to Hell, thirstily."
    },
    {
      "id": 847,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Thirsty. To be thirsty.",
      "hw": "پیاسا",
      "s": "« » Extremely thirsty, such that the thirst is never quenched (1 verse: 56:55)",
      "d": "« » means extreme thirst (m.l. f.l. 162). « » means to be intensely thirsty (manjada). And « » is a disease in camels where the camel remains extremely thirsty. And « » is a camel suffering from a disease where its thirst is never quenched.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَشٰرِبُوۡنَ عَلَیۡہِ مِنَ الۡحَمِیۡمِ فَشٰرِبُوۡنَ شُرۡبَ الۡہِیۡمِ»\nTranslation: And they will drink boiling water on top of it, and they will drink as the intensely thirsty camel drinks."
    },
    {
      "id": 848,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Thirsty. To be thirsty.",
      "hw": "پیاسا",
      "s": "« » The tongue protruding due to severe thirst (1 verse: 7:176)",
      "d": "« » means to protrude the tongue and pant due to severe thirst. According to some, this word is used for both desperation (compulsion and helplessness) and thirst (m.f.). « » means severe thirst, and « » is the thirst caused by internal heat or stomach heat (Q.m.).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَمَثَلُہٗ  کَمَثَلِ الۡکَلۡبِ ۚ اِنۡ تَحۡمِلۡ عَلَیۡہِ یَلۡہَثۡ اَوۡ تَتۡرُکۡہُ یَلۡہَثۡ»\nTranslation: So his example is like that of a dog: if you chase it, it pants with its tongue out, and if you leave it, it still pants with its tongue out."
    }
  ],
  "175": [
    {
      "id": 850,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "cup",
      "hw": "پیالہ",
      "s": "« » a cup filled with drink. (6 verses: 37:45-52:23-56:18-76:5-76:17-78:34)",
      "d": "« » a cup filled with drink. Goblet. A clinking goblet. And if it is not filled with drink, it is called « » (f. l 30). « » generally refers to a cup filled with wine. And « » also means wine (manjad).\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«یَطُوۡفُ عَلَیۡہِمۡ  وِلۡدَانٌ مُّخَلَّدُوۡنَ ۔ بِاَکۡوَابٍ وَّ اَبَارِیۡقَ ۬ ۙ وَ کَاۡسٍ مِّنۡ مَّعِیۡنٍ ۔ لَّا یُصَدَّعُوْنَ عَنْہَا وَ لَا یُنْزِفُوۡنَۙ»\nTranslation: Eternal young boys will circulate among them with cups and pitchers and a cup from a flowing spring. They will not suffer headache from it, nor will they be intoxicated."
    },
    {
      "id": 851,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Cup",
      "hw": "پیالہ",
      "s": "« » A cup or vessel for drinking water (3 verses: 9:19, 12:70, 76:21)",
      "d": "«سَقٰی» «سِقَایۃ» «فَلَمَّا جَہَّزَہُمۡ بِجَہَازِہِمۡ جَعَلَ السِّقَایَۃَ فِیۡ رَحۡلِ اَخِیۡہِ»"
    }
  ],
