      "h": "harm, damage",
      "hw": "تکلیف",
      "s": "« » is used for light affliction. (12 verses: 2:196, 2:222, 2:262, 2:263, 2:264, 3:111, 3:186, 4:102, 9:61, 33:57, 33:58, 61:5)",
      "d": "«اَذًی» «اَلضُّرُّ الْیَسِیْر» «لَنۡ یَّضُرُّوۡکُمۡ  اِلَّاۤ اَذًی» «وَ مِنۡہُمُ الَّذِیۡنَ یُؤۡذُوۡنَ النَّبِیَّ وَ یَقُوۡلُوۡنَ ہُوَ اُذُنٌ» «اَذًی»"
    },
    {
      "id": 957,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To Bear Hardship, To Give Hardship",
      "hw": "تکلیف",
      "s": "« » is used for ordinary hardship, whether mental or physical (4 verses: 2:64-4:16-14:12-33:69)",
      "d": "« » is used for ordinary hardship, whether mental or physical.\nFor example, in the Quran it is said:\n«لَا تَکُوۡنُوۡا کَالَّذِیۡنَ اٰذَوۡا مُوۡسٰی»\nTranslation: And do not be like those who harmed Moses."
    },
    {
      "id": 958,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To Bear Hardship, To Give Hardship",
      "hw": "تکلیف",
      "s": "« » is used for great hardship and loss (13 verses: 2:231-4:95-5:76-7:188-9:107-10:49-13:16-20:89-25:3-34:42-41:50-48:11-72:21)",
      "d": "« » is used for great hardship and loss.\nFor example, in the Quran it is said:\n«وَاِنۡ تَصۡبِرُوۡا وَ تَتَّقُوۡا لَا یَضُرُّکُمۡ کَیۡدُہُمۡ شَیۡئًا»\nTranslation: And if you are patient and fear Allah, their plot will not harm you at all.\n«ضَارَّ، یُضَارُّ»\nFor example, in the Quran it is said:\n«لَا تُضَآرَّ وَالِدَۃٌۢ بِوَلَدِہَا وَ لَا مَوۡلُوۡدٌ لَّہٗ بِوَلَدِہٖ»\nTranslation: A mother should not be harmed by her child, nor a father by his child."
    },
    {
      "id": 960,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to impose a burden; to give",
      "hw": "تکلیف",
      "s": "« » means to take from something more than its capacity and strength. (7 verses: 2:233, 2:286, 4:84, 6:152, 7:42, 23:62, 65:7)",
      "d": "«کَلَّفَ» «لَا یُکَلِّفُ اللّٰہُ نَفۡسًا اِلَّا وُسۡعَہَا» «تَکَلُّف»"
    },
