  "203": [
    {
      "id": 964,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To become healthy. To heal.",
      "hw": "تندرست",
      "s": "« » means to recover from illness (6 verses: 9:14-10:57-16:69-17:82-26:80-41:44)",
      "d": "«شِفَاء» «شَفٰی یَشْفِیْ»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اِذَا مَرِضۡتُ فَہُوَ یَشۡفِیۡنِ»\nTranslation: And when I fall ill, it is He who cures me.\nAnd « » is used for physical illnesses, similarly it also comes for salvation from spiritual illnesses.\nFor example, the Divine Command states:\n«وَ یَشۡفِ صُدُوۡرَ قَوۡمٍ  مُّؤۡمِنِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And He will heal the hearts of a group of believers."
    },
    {
      "id": 965,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To become healthy. To heal.",
      "hw": "تندرست",
      "s": "« » means to save from a severe illness (2 verses: 3:49-5:110)",
      "d": "«بَرَءَ» «بُرْءُ» «رَجُلٌ بَزِیْءٌ» «بَرَءَ مِنَ الْمَرْض» «اَبْرَءَ الْمَرِیْض»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَاُبۡرِئُ الۡاَکۡمَہَ وَ الۡاَبۡرَصَ وَ اُحۡیِ الۡمَوۡتٰی بِاِذۡنِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And I heal the blind and the leper, and I bring the dead to life by the permission of Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 966,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To become healthy. To heal.",
      "hw": "تندرست",
      "s": "« » means to regain consciousness after unconsciousness (1 verse: 7:143)",
      "d": "«اَفَاقَ» «صَاحِبِ فِقْہُ الْلُغَۃ» «اَفَاقَ»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«فَلَمَّا تَجَلّٰی رَبُّہٗ  لِلۡجَبَلِ جَعَلَہٗ  دَکًّا وَّ خَرَّ مُوۡسٰی صَعِقًا ۚ فَلَمَّاۤ  اَفَاقَ قَالَ سُبۡحٰنَکَ»\nTranslation: So when his Lord manifested Himself to the mountain, He made it [into] dust, and Moses fell unconscious. Then when he recovered, he said, \"Exalted are You!\""
    }
  ],
  "204": [
    {
      "id": 967,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Poverty, destitution",
      "hw": "تنگدستی",
      "s": "« » means destitution, poverty, extreme poverty (8 verses: 2:268-2:271-2:273-9:60-24:32-35:15-47:38-59:8)",
      "d": "«فَقْرُ» «فَقِرَ» «فِقْرَۃٌ» «فِقْرَۃٌ» «فِقَار» «فِقْرَۃٌ» «فَقْرٌ» «فَقْرَتْہُ الدَّاھِیَۃُ» «فَقْر»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«اِنۡ یَّکُوۡنُوۡا فُقَرَآءَ یُغۡنِہِمُ اللّٰہُ مِنۡ فَضۡلِہٖ»\nTranslation: If they are poor, Allah will enrich them from His bounty."
    },
    {
      "id": 969,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Poverty, destitution",
      "hw": "تنگدستی",
      "s": "« » means being crushed under the expenses of one's family and dependents (1 verse: 9:28)",
      "d": "« » is everything that burdens a person and crushes them under its weight. And « » refers to those individuals for whom a person is responsible for their livelihood expenses, thus becoming a burden (Majid). Thus, « » is that destitution and need which occurs because of dependents.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اِنۡ خِفۡتُمۡ عَیۡلَۃً فَسَوۡفَ یُغۡنِیۡکُمُ اللّٰہُ مِنۡ فَضۡلِہٖۤ»\nTranslation: And if you fear poverty, Allah will enrich you from His bounty, if He wills."
    },
    {
      "id": 970,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Poverty, destitution",
      "hw": "تنگدستی",
      "s": "« » means the fear of becoming destitute (2 verses: 6:151-17:31)",
      "d": "«اِمْلَاق» «اَمْلَقَ الدَّھْرُ مَللَہٗ» «اَمْلَقَ»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تَقۡتُلُوۡۤا اَوۡلَادَکُمۡ خَشۡیَۃَ  اِمۡلَاقٍ»\nTranslation: And do not kill your children for fear of poverty.\n«خَشْیْۃَ اِنْفَاق»"
    },
    {
      "id": 971,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Poverty, destitution",
      "hw": "تنگدستی",
      "s": "« » means being stingy in spending on one's dependents (2 verses: 2:236-25:67)",
      "d": "« » means need, destitution, and poverty.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَّ مَتِّعُوۡہُنَّ ۚ عَلَی الۡمُوۡسِعِ قَدَرُہٗ  وَعَلَی الۡمُقۡتِرِ قَدَرُہٗ»\nTranslation: And give them [something] [upon] the capacity of the wealthy and according to the capacity of the poor.\nHowever, linguists define its meaning as \"to make nafaqah (maintenance) tight for one's dependents\" (Maqayis, Mu'jam Maqayis). That is, « » is a person who is not actually poor but is stingy in spending on his dependents according to his capacity.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ الَّذِیۡنَ اِذَاۤ اَنۡفَقُوۡا لَمۡ یُسۡرِفُوۡا وَلَمۡ یَقۡتُرُوۡا وَکَانَ بَیۡنَ ذٰلِکَ قَوَامًا»\nTranslation: And those who, when they spend, are neither extravagant nor stingy, but are moderate between that."
    },
    {
      "id": 972,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Poverty, destitution",
      "hw": "تنگدستی",
      "s": "« » means a time of poverty and destitution (5 verses: 2:177-2:214-6:42-7:94-22:28)",
      "d": "«بَئِسَ یَبْئَسُ» «بَاسْ» «بَاْسَآءِ» «سَرَّاء» «مُسَرَّۃٌ فِی الْیُسْر» «بَاسَاء»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«فَکُلُوۡا مِنۡہَا وَ اَطۡعِمُوا الۡبَآئِسَ الۡفَقِیۡرَ»\nTranslation: So eat from it and feed the desperate poor.\nAt another place, the Divine Command states:\n«مَسَّتۡہُمُ الۡبَاۡسَآءُ وَ الضَّرَّآءُ وَ زُلۡزِلُوۡا»\nTranslation: They were touched by poverty and hardship and were shaken [to their core].\nIn this verse, « » refers to economic hardship and « » refers to other afflictions and calamities."
    },
    {
      "id": 973,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Poverty, destitution",
      "hw": "تنگدستی",
      "s": "« » means to become mixed with dust due to poverty (1 verse: 90:16)",
      "d": "«تُرَاب» «تَرِبَ الرَّجُل»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«اَوۡ اِطۡعٰمٌ فِیۡ یَوۡمٍ ذِیۡ مَسۡغَبَۃٍ یَّتِیۡمًا ذَا مَقۡرَبَۃٍ اَوۡ مِسۡکِیۡنًا ذَا مَتۡرَبَۃٍ»\nTranslation: Or [giving] food on a day of severe hunger to an orphan near of kin, or a needy person in misery [who is mixed with dust]."
    }
  ],
  "205": [
    {
      "id": 974,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Constriction",
      "hw": "تنگی",
      "s": "« » is used for times of constriction (9 verses: 2:185-2:280-9:117-18:73-54:8-65:7-92:10-94:5-94:6)",
      "d": "« » meaning constriction or a time of constriction. Calamity and distress (m l) whether this constriction is economic or of another kind. This word is general and its opposite is « » meaning ease and prosperity.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«اِنَّ مَعَ الۡعُسۡرِ  یُسۡرًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, with constriction comes ease."
    },
    {
      "id": 975,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Constriction",
      "hw": "تنگی",
      "s": "« » is used for constriction and narrowing of the heart (11 verses: 4:65-5:6-6:125-7:2-9:91-22:78-24:61-33:37-33:38-33:50-48:17)",
      "d": "« » meaning narrowing of the heart. The heart feeling constricted due to unlawful restrictions (f l 54).\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَ مَا جَعَلَ عَلَیۡکُمۡ فِی الدِّیۡنِ مِنۡ حَرَجٍ»\nTranslation: And He has not placed upon you in the religion any constriction."
    },
    {
      "id": 976,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Constriction",
      "hw": "تنگی",
      "s": "« » is used for constriction of life and distresses or for being debilitated by thoughts (1 verse: 20:124)",
      "d": "« » meaning constriction in lifestyle and living. (f l 54) restlessness and anxiety of the heart, remaining engrossed in thoughts. « » meaning a constricted life (minjd).\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَ مَنۡ اَعۡرَضَ عَنۡ ذِکۡرِیۡ فَاِنَّ لَہٗ مَعِیۡشَۃً ضَنۡکًا»\nTranslation: And whoever turns away from My reminder - indeed, his life will be constricted."
    },
    {
      "id": 977,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Constriction",
      "hw": "تنگی",
      "s": "« » is used for constriction of space (11 verses: 6:125-9:25-9:118-11:77-15:97-16:127-25:13-26:13-27:70-29:33-65:6)",
      "d": "« » is used for constriction of space. (f l 54) and its opposite is « » meaning spaciousness. (m l)\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَاِذَاۤ اُلۡقُوۡا مِنۡہَا مَکَانًا ضَیِّقًا»\nTranslation: And when they are thrown into a constricted place from it.\nSometimes its opposite « » also occurs.\nFor example, the divine declaration is:\n«حَتّٰۤی اِذَا ضَاقَتۡ عَلَیۡہِمُ الۡاَرۡضُ بِمَا رَحُبَتۡ»\nTranslation: Until the earth, despite its spaciousness, became constricted for them.\nThen sometimes « » is used in the meaning of « » i.e., constriction of the heart. So this is the metaphorical use of « ».\nFor example, the divine declaration is:\n«وَ لَا تَکُ فِیۡ  ضَیۡقٍ مِّمَّا یَمۡکُرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And do not be constricted in heart by what they plot."
    },
    {
      "id": 978,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Constriction",
      "hw": "تنگی",
      "s": "« » is that constriction and narrowness that arises from the non-fulfillment of a desire or need (3 verses: 12:68-40:80-59:9)",
      "d": "« » meaning need, necessity, and poverty. And « » meaning to be in need. And « » meaning necessity. That constriction which is felt in the heart due to the non-fulfillment of a desire or need.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَ لَا یَجِدُوۡنَ  فِیۡ صُدُوۡرِہِمۡ حَاجَۃً  مِّمَّاۤ اُوۡتُوۡا»\nTranslation: And they do not find in their hearts any constriction from what they are given."
    }
  ],
  "206": [
    {
      "id": 979,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To constrict / To become constricted",
      "hw": "تنگ ",
      "s": "« » is used for constriction of space (4 verses: 9:25-9:118-11:77-29:33)",
      "d": "« » indicates constriction of space.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَاِذَاۤ اُلۡقُوۡا مِنۡہَا مَکَانًا ضَیِّقًا»\nTranslation: And when they are thrown into a constricted place from it."
    },
    {
      "id": 980,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To constrict / To become constricted",
      "hw": "تنگ ",
      "s": "« » if associated with provision, then it is used for constriction of provision (11 verses: 13:26-17:30-28:82-29:62-30:37-34:36-34:39-39:52-42:12-65:7-89:16)",
      "d": "The basic meaning of « » is to estimate something, to manage and devise for it (minjd), but when this word is associated with provision, then it means constriction of provision, and its opposite is « ».\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«اَللّٰہُ یَبۡسُطُ الرِّزۡقَ لِمَنۡ یَّشَآءُ مِنۡ عِبَادِہٖ وَیَقۡدِرُ لَہٗ»\nTranslation: Allah extends provision for whom He wills of His servants and constricts it for whom He wills."
    },
    {
      "id": 981,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To constrict / To become constricted",
      "hw": "تنگ ",
      "s": "« » meaning to seize something with the full fist (2 verses: 2:245-9:67)",
      "d": "The meaning of « » is to seize something with the full fist, to enclose in the fist and to contract (muf). And « » meaning a fist and what is enclosed in it. Its opposite is « ». And « » is used when constriction or reduction is made in something that was previously abundant. Whether it be provision or something else.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«مَنۡ ذَا الَّذِیۡ یُقۡرِضُ اللّٰہَ  قَرۡضًا حَسَنًا فَیُضٰعِفَہٗ لَہٗۤ اَضۡعَافًا کَثِیۡرَۃً ؕ وَ اللّٰہُ یَقۡبِضُ وَ یَبۡصُۜطُ»\nTranslation: Who is it that would loan Allah a goodly loan so He will multiply it for him many times over? And Allah withholds and expands [provision]."
    },
    {
      "id": 982,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To constrict / To become constricted",
      "hw": "تنگ ",
      "s": "« » (it is a masdar) is used for constriction and distress of the heart (4 verses: 2:196-2:273-4:90-9:5)",
      "d": "«حَصِرَ» «حَصِرَ الرَّجُل»\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«اِلَّا الَّذِیۡنَ یَصِلُوۡنَ اِلٰی قَوۡمٍۭ بَیۡنَکُمۡ وَ بَیۡنَہُمۡ مِّیۡثَاقٌ اَوۡ جَآءُوۡکُمۡ حَصِرَتۡ صُدُوۡرُہُمۡ اَنۡ یُّقَاتِلُوۡکُمۡ اَوۡ یُقَاتِلُوۡا قَوۡمَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: Except for those who join a people between whom and you there is a treaty, or those who come to you with their hearts constricted from fighting you or fighting their own people."
    },
    {
      "id": 983,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To constrict / To become constricted",
      "hw": "تنگ ",
      "s": "« » comes in the meaning of constricting someone through exaggeration and insistence in asking (3 verses: 7:187-19:47-47:37)",
      "d": "The lexical meaning of « » is to exaggerate and insist in seeking something. (muf. m. q) And « » means one who has complete knowledge about something. One who exaggerates in honor, respect, and showing happiness. One who inquires too much about someone's condition and insists on asking (minjd). So from this exaggeration and insistence, sometimes the meaning of constricting arises.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«اِنۡ یَّسۡئَلۡکُمُوۡہَا  فَیُحۡفِکُمۡ  تَبۡخَلُوۡا»\nTranslation: And if he asks you for it and constricts you [by making excessive demands], you become stingy."
    }
  ],
  "207": [
    {
      "id": 984,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to break",
      "hw": "توڑنا",
      "s": "« » is used for breaking a sale, an oath, and a covenant, or for tearing down something built (6 verses: 7:135, 9:12, 9:13, 16:92, 43:50, 48:10)",
      "d": "«نَکَثَ» «نِكْث» «نَكَّاث» «أَلَا تُقَاتِلُوۡنَ قَوۡمًا نَّكَثُوۡۤا أَيۡمَانَہُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 985,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to break",
      "hw": "توڑنا",
      "s": "« » comes for unraveling anything, scattering a weave, and breaking a firm covenant or oath, or ruining it through trickery (9 verses: 2:27, 4:155, 5:13, 8:56, 13:20, 13:25, 16:91, 16:92, 18:77)",
      "d": "«نَقَضَ» «اَبْرَم» «نَكَثَ» «نَقَضتُ الْبِنَاء» «اَلْعَظْمُ» «اَلْعَقْدُ» «نَقَضْتُ الْحَبْلَ» «نَقَضَ» «نَكَثَ» «وَأَوۡفُوۡا بِعَہۡدِ اللّٰہِ إِذَا عَٰهَدۡتُمۡ وَلَا تَنۡقُضُوا الۡأَيۡمَانَ بَعۡدَ تَوۡكِیۡدِہَا» «الَّذِیۡنَ یَنۡقُضُوۡنَ عَہۡدَ اللّٰہِ مِنۡۢ بَعۡدِ مِیۡثَاقِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 986,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to break",
      "hw": "توڑنا",
      "s": "« » means to break something in such a way that a cracking sound is produced (1 verse: 94:3)",
      "d": "«اَنْقَضَ» «اَنْقَضَتِ الدُّجَاجَة» «الادِیم» «اَنْقَضَ أَصَابِعَہٗ» «اَنْقَضَ الْحَمَلُ الظَّھْرَ» «وَضَعۡنَا عَنۡکَ وِزۡرَکَ الَّذِیۡۤ أَنۡقَضَ ظَہۡرَکَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 987,
