  "209": [
    {
      "id": 992,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "layered/stacked",
      "hw": "تہ",
      "s": "« » means to pile something up without any order or arrangement, above or below, or forward or backward (3 verses: 8:37, 24:43, 52:44)",
      "d": "«رَکَمَ» «رُکَام» «مَرْکُوْم» «أَلَمۡ تَرَ أَنَّ اللّٰہَ یُزۡجِی سَحَابًا ثُمَّ یُؤَلِّفُ بَیۡنَہٗ ثُمَّ یَجۡعَلُہٗ رُکَامًا» «لِیَمِیۡزَ اللّٰہُ الۡخَبِیۡثَ مِنَ الطَّیِّبِ وَ یَجۡعَلَ الۡخَبِیۡثَ بَعۡضَہٗ عَلٰی بَعۡضٍ فَیَرۡکُمَہٗ جَمِیۡعًا فَیَجۡعَلَہٗ فِیۡ جَہَنَّمَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 993,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "layered/stacked",
      "hw": "تہ",
      "s": "« » means to place something in an ordered and systematic way, above or below, or forward or backward, so that they are connected to each other (2 verses: 6:99, 84:19)",
      "d": "«رَکِبَ» «رَکِیْب» «تَرَاكِب» «مُتَرَاكِب» «فَأَخۡرَجۡنَا مِنۡہُ خَضِرًا نُّخۡرِجُ مِنۡہُ حَبًّا مُّتَرَاكِبًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 995,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "layered/stacked",
      "hw": "تہ",
      "s": "« » means to place something porous, like wool or clouds, above or below. (Porous: meaning hollow inside, fluffy, full of holes) (5 verses: 17:92, 26:187, 30:48, 34:9, 52:44)",
      "d": "«کِسْفَۃٌ» «کِسْفٌ» «کِسَفًا» «اللّٰہُ الَّذِیۡ یُرۡسِلُ الرِّیٰحَ فَتُثِیۡرُ سَحَابًا فَیَبۡسُطُہٗ فِی السَّمَآءِ کَیۡفَ یَشَآءُ وَ یَجۡعَلُہٗ کِسَفًا»"
    }
  ],
  "210": [
    {
      "id": 996,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to get tired",
      "hw": "تھکنا",
      "s": "« » to become weary or disgusted with something due to prolonged engagement (3 verses: 2:282-41:38-41:49)",
      "d": "« » means to become weary or disgusted in heart due to staying with something for a long time. To become bored with something from the heart. To become satiated while doing a task. This is the initial state of getting tired.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«لَا یَسۡئَمُ الۡاِنۡسَانُ مِنۡ دُعَآءِ الۡخَیۡرِ»\nTranslation: Man does not get tired of praying for good."
    },
    {
      "id": 997,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to get tired",
      "hw": "تھکنا",
      "s": "« » to get very tired, to become emaciated due to exhaustion (6 verses: 9:120-15:48-18:62-35:35-88:3-94:7)",
      "d": "«نَصِبَ» «عَلِمَ یَعْلَمُ» «نَصِبَ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَلَمَّا جَاوَزَا قَالَ لِفَتٰىہُ اٰتِنَا غَدَآءَنَا ۫ لَقَدۡ لَقِیۡنَا مِنۡ سَفَرِنَا ہٰذَا نَصَبًا»\nTranslation: When they had passed beyond that, he (Moses) said to his young companion: 'Bring us our morning meal; indeed, we have encountered much fatigue from this journey of ours.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 998,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to get tired",
      "hw": "تھکنا",
      "s": "« » to become weak due to exhaustion (2 verses: 35:35-50:38)",
      "d": "« » means to get tired and become weak due to excessive work or toil. To become incapable (of doing more).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَقَدۡ خَلَقۡنَا السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضَ وَ مَا بَیۡنَہُمَا فِیۡ سِتَّۃِ اَیَّامٍ ٭ۖ وَّ مَا مَسَّنَا مِنۡ لُّغُوۡبٍ»\nTranslation: And We created the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them in six days, and We were not touched by any fatigue."
    },
    {
      "id": 999,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to get tired",
      "hw": "تھکنا",
      "s": "« » to be unable to do more work due to exhaustion (2 verses: 46:33-50:15)",
      "d": "«عَیَّ» «اَلْعَیُّ» «اَلْعَیَّانُ» «دَاءٌ عَیَاءٌ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اَوَ لَمۡ یَرَوۡا اَنَّ اللّٰہَ الَّذِیۡ خَلَقَ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضَ وَ لَمۡ یَعۡیَ بِخَلۡقِہِنَّ»\nTranslation: Do they not see that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth, was not wearied by their creation?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1001,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to get tired",
      "hw": "تھکنا",
      "s": "« » to get tired due to burden and heavy weight (1 verse: 2:255)",
      "d": "«اٰدَ، یَؤُدُّ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَسِعَ کُرۡسِیُّہُ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضَ ۚ وَلَا یَئُوۡدُہٗ حِفۡظُہُمَا ۚ وَ ہُوَ الۡعَلِیُّ الۡعَظِیۡمُ»\nTranslation: His Kursi (throne) extends over the heavens and the earth, and their preservation does not tire Him. And He is the Most High, the Most Great."
    }
  ],
  "211": [
    {
      "id": 1002,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/rest",
      "hw": "رکنا",
      "s": "« » is general; used for the cessation of movement of any thing (20 verses: 2:231-2:256-4:15-5:4-6:13-6:96-7:170-7:189-9:103-10:67-16:79-16:80-23:18-25:45-27:86-28:72-28:73-30:21-40:61-42:33-)",
      "d": "« » refers to the pause after the movement of any thing. It is used in both external and spiritual senses. Its opposite is movement and agitation.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنۡ یَّشَاۡ یُسۡکِنِ الرِّیۡحَ»\nTranslation: If He wills, He can calm the wind."
    },
    {
      "id": 1003,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/rest",
      "hw": "رکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop while speaking, to become silent (2 verses: 7:154-17:100)",
      "d": "«سَکَتَ» «سَکِیْت» «سَاکُوْت» «سَکَتَ الْغَضَب»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَمَّا سَکَتَ عَنۡ مُّوۡسَی الۡغَضَبُ»\nTranslation: And when the anger subsided from Moses..."
    },
    {
      "id": 1004,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/rest",
      "hw": "رکنا",
      "s": "« » used for the calming of waves and surges on water (1 verse: 44:24)",
      "d": "«رَھَا، یَرْھُوْا» «رَھَا الْبَحْرَ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ اتۡرُکِ الۡبَحۡرَ رَہۡوًا»\nTranslation: And leave the sea as calm (or parted)."
    }
  ],
  "212": [
    {
      "id": 1005,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "a little",
      "hw": "تھوڑا",
      "s": "« » used for anything that is little in comparison to something more. Its usage is general (70 verses: 2:41-2:79-2:83-2:88-2:126-2:174-2:246-2:249-3:77-3:187-3:197-3:199-4:46-4:66-4:77-4:83-4:142-4:155-5:13-5:44-7:3-7:10-7:86-8:26-8:43-8:44-9:9-9:38-9:82-11:40-11:116-12:47-12:48-16:95-16:117-17:52-17:62-17:74-17:76-17:85-18:22-23:40-23:78-23:114-26:54-27:62-28:58-31:24-32:9-33:16-33:18-33:20-33:60-34:13-34:16-38:24-39:8-40:58-44:15-48:15-51:17-53:34-56:14-67:23-69:41-69:42-73:2-73:3-73:11-77:46)",
      "d": "« » is the opposite of « ». That is, little in comparison to more. Its usage is general. It is used for quantity, weight, distance, duration, etc., everywhere.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تَشۡتَرُوۡا بِاٰیٰتِیۡ ثَمَنًا قَلِیۡلًا»\nTranslation: And do not exchange My verses for a small price."
    },
    {
      "id": 1006,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "a little",
      "hw": "تھوڑا",
      "s": "« » used for a very small quantity (3 verses: 4:49-4:77-17:71)",
      "d": "« » means to twist a rope, etc. And « » refers to a twisted rope. Its feminine form is « », which means a wick (for a lamp). Also, « » refers to that thin thread which is in the crack of a date stone. And from this word, a very small quantity is understood.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَا یُظۡلَمُوۡنَ فَتِیۡلًا»\nTranslation: And they will not be wronged by a thread (i.e., an iota)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1008,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "A little",
      "hw": "تھوڑا",
      "s": "« » (Qitmir) refers to an extremely small quantity, so minute it is as if it does not exist (1 verse: 35:13).",
      "d": "«قِطْمِیْر» «مَآ أَصَبْتُ عَنْهُ قِطْمِیْرًا»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ الَّذِیۡنَ تَدۡعُوۡنَ مِنۡ دُوۡنِہٖ مَا یَمۡلِکُوۡنَ مِنۡ قِطۡمِیۡرٍ»\nTranslation: 'And those you call upon besides Him do not possess even the skin of a date pit.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1009,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "A little",
      "hw": "تھوڑا",
      "s": "« » (Fawaq) denotes a very short period of time or a brief pause.\nNote: Similarly, in the Quran, « » (a grain of mustard) and « » (a speck) also represent an extremely small quantity (1 verse: 38:15).",
      "d": "« » (Fawaq) is the interval between two milkings, the moment between pressing and releasing the udder. It signifies a very short time or duration.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ مَا یَنۡظُرُ ہٰۤؤُلَآءِ إِلَّا صَیۡحَۃً وَاحِدَۃً مَّا لَہَا مِنۡ فَوَاقٍ»\nTranslation: 'And these [disbelievers] await only one blast [of the Horn] which will have no delay.'"
    }
  ],
  "213": [
    {
      "id": 1012,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "to prepare",
      "hw": "تیار",
      "s": "« » means to complete everything and bring it forth, ready. (20 verses: 2:24, 3:131, 3:133, 4:93, 4:102, 8:60, 9:46, 9:89, 9:100, 33:8, 33:29, 33:35, 33:44, 33:57, 33:64, 48:6, 57:21, 58:15, 65:10, 76:31)",
      "d": "«اَعَدَّ» «عَدَّ» «اَعَدَّ» «فَاتَّقُوا النَّارَ الَّتِیۡ وَقُوۡدُہَا النَّاسُ وَ الۡحِجَارَۃُ  ۚ ۖ اُعِدَّتۡ لِلۡکٰفِرِیۡنَ» «اَعْتَدَ» «عَدَدَ» «اَعْتَدْنَا» «اَعْدَدْنَا» «اَعْتَدْنَا» «اَعَدَّ» «اَعْتَدَ»"
    }
  ],
  "214": [
    {
      "id": 1014,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Arrow",
      "hw": "تیر",
      "s": "« » (Sahm) refers to an arrow used in gambling, for drawing lots, and also a general arrow (1 verse: 37:141).",
      "d": "« » (Sahm) is an arrow for gambling, for drawing lots, and also a general arrow. Its plural is « » (Saham) and « » (Sahama) means to draw lots. « » (Tasahama) means to divide something among themselves by lot. « » means a divided share, a lot, or destiny.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَسَاہَمَ فَکَانَ مِنَ الۡمُدۡحَضِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: 'Then they drew lots, and he was among the losers.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1015,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Arrow",
      "hw": "تیر",
      "s": "« » (Zalam) is a featherless arrow, a divining arrow, used for drawing lots (2 verses: 5:3, 5:90).",
      "d": "« » (Zalam) is a featherless arrow, an arrow used for divination (azlam). In pre-Islamic Arabia, people used arrows to determine fate. They would write 'permission' or 'prohibition' on arrows, place them in a container, and draw one to decide on an action. If the drawn arrow had 'permission,' they proceeded; if 'prohibition,' they refrained. Its plural is « » (Azlam). It is a small arrow without feathers or a nock, a gambling arrow.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡۤا اِنَّمَا الۡخَمۡرُ وَ الۡمَیۡسِرُ وَ الۡاَنۡصَابُ وَ الۡاَزۡلَامُ رِجۡسٌ مِّنۡ عَمَلِ الشَّیۡطٰنِ فَاجۡتَنِبُوۡہُ لَعَلَّکُمۡ تُفۡلِحُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: 'O you who have believed, indeed, intoxicants, gambling, [sacrificing on] stone altars, and divining arrows are but defilement from the work of Satan, so avoid it that you may be successful.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1017,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Sharp",
      "hw": "تیر",
      "s": "« » (Salaqa) means to speak or act with harshness (anger) and force (power) (1 verse: 33:19).",
      "d": "«سَلَقَ» «سَلَقَ الْلِسَان»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَاِذَا ذَہَبَ الۡخَوۡفُ سَلَقُوۡکُمۡ بِاَلۡسِنَۃٍ حِدَادٍ أَشِحَّۃً عَلَی الۡخَیۡرِ»\nTranslation: 'Then when fear departs, they will assail you with sharp tongues, stingy toward good.'"
    }
  ],
  "215": [
    {
      "id": 1018,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Oil",
      "hw": "تیل",
      "s": "« » (Zayt) specifically refers to olive oil.\nAnd « » (Duhn) refers to all kinds of oil, including olive oil.\nAnd « » (Dihan) refers to the dregs or residue of oil (6 verses: 6:99, 6:141, 16:11, 24:35, 80:29, 95:1).",
      "d": "«زَیْت» «زَیْتُونَۃٌ» «زَاتَ الطَّعَام»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«یَّکَادُ زَیۡتُہَا یُضِیۡٓءُ وَ لَوۡ لَمۡ تَمۡسَسۡہُ نَارٌ»\nTranslation: 'Its oil would glow [with light], almost, without even touching it, fire.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1019,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Oil",
      "hw": "تیل",
      "s": "« » (Duhn) is a general term for grease and fat (1 verse: 23:20).",
      "d": "« » (Duhn) means oil, grease, fat. It is a general term for any kind of oil, whether plant-based or animal-based. « » (Dahana) and « » (Adhana) mean to deceive, to practice hypocrisy. « » (Tadahhanna) means to anoint with oil.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ شَجَرَۃً تَخۡرُجُ مِنۡ طُوۡرِ سَیۡنَآءَ تَنۡۢبُتُ بِالدُّہۡنِ»\nTranslation: 'And [He brought forth] a tree, growing from the mount of Sinai, which produces oil and [its] seasoning.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1020,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "Oil",
      "hw": "تیل",
      "s": "« » (Dihan) is the dregs or residue of oil (the sediment that settles at the bottom) (1 verse: 55:37).",
      "d": "« » (Dihan) means the dregs or lees of oil (the muddy or greasy sediment that settles at the bottom). It also means a slippery place, a stain, or paint.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَاِذَا انۡشَقَّتِ السَّمَآءُ فَکَانَتۡ وَرۡدَۃً کَالدِّہَانِ»\nTranslation: 'And when the heaven is split open and becomes rose-colored like oil [or: like a dye].'"
    }
  ],
  "216": [
    {
      "id": 1021,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To frown",
      "hw": "تیوری",
      "s": "« » (Abasa) means for a frown to appear between the two eyes on the forehead (2 verses: 74:22, 80:1).",
      "d": "« » (Abasa) means to frown, to knit the brows. It signifies a wrinkle forming on the forehead between the eyes. It conveys meanings like sternness, lack of mercy, crookedness in conduct, sullenness, and a scowling expression. This is the primary meaning.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«عَبَسَ وَ تَوَلّٰۤی أَنۡ جَآءَہُ الۡاَعۡمٰی»\nTranslation: '[The Prophet] frowned and turned away because there came to him the blind man.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1022,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To Contort the Face",
      "hw": "تیوری",
      "s": "« » refers to wrinkles appearing on the face in such a way that the shape distorts. (1 verse: 23:104)",
      "d": "« » is the next degree after « ». Meaning: wrinkles appear on the face causing distortion of features. (F. L 139) Some scholars say it means raising the lips such that teeth become visible and the face looks ugly. (M. Q)\n«تَلۡفَحُ وُجُوۡہَہُمُ النَّارُ وَ ہُمۡ فِیۡہَا کٰلِحُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: The Fire will scorch their faces, and they will be disfigured therein."
    },
    {
      "id": 1023,
      "a": "ت",
      "h": "To Contort the Face",
      "hw": "تیوری",
      "s": "« » when the act of raising the nose/mouth (facial contortion) reaches its extreme, it is called « ». (1 verse: 74:22)",
      "d": "« » is the final degree of « ». When the act of raising the nose/mouth (facial contortion) reaches its extreme, it is called « ». Meaning: to frown severely. (F. L 139)\n«ثُمَّ نَظَرَ ثُمَّ عَبَسَ وَ بَسَرَ»\nTranslation: Then he looked, then he contorted his face and scowled."
    }
  ],
  "217": [
    {
      "id": 1024,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » means a part of something that completes it. (3 verses: 2:260, 15:44, 43:15)",
      "d": "«جُزء» «کُلّ» «اَجْزَاء» «جَزَءَ الشَّیْء»\n«ثُمَّ اجۡعَلۡ عَلٰی کُلِّ جَبَلٍ مِّنۡہُنَّ جُزۡءًا»\nTranslation: Then place a portion of them on every mountain."
    },
    {
      "id": 1026,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » is that piece of land which is distinct from others. (1 verse: 28:30)",
      "d": "According to the author of Muqayyas al-Lughah, « » is a piece of land that is prominent from surrounding pieces. (M. L)\n«فَلَمَّاۤ اَتٰىہَا نُوۡدِیَ مِنۡ شَاطِیَٔ الۡوَادِ الۡاَیۡمَنِ فِی الۡبُقۡعَۃِ الۡمُبٰرَکَۃِ مِنَ الشَّجَرَۃِ»\nTranslation: When he came to it, he was called from the right side of the valley in the blessed spot from the tree."
    },
    {
      "id": 1027,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » means pieces of porous bodies such as clouds, wool, or sky. (5 verses: 17:92, 26:187, 30:48, 34:9, 52:44)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « ». Meaning: pieces of porous bodies like clouds or wool (Muf) that can be easily separated and joined.\n«فَاَسۡقِطۡ عَلَیۡنَا کِسَفًا مِّنَ السَّمَآءِ اِنۡ کُنۡتَ مِنَ الصّٰدِقِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: If you are truthful, then drop a piece from the sky upon us."
    },
    {
      "id": 1028,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » means iron sheets, leaves (of books). (8 verses: 3:184, 16:44, 18:96, 23:53, 26:196, 35:25, 54:43, 54:52)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « ». Meaning: large pieces of iron, iron sheets, planks (Munjid). Then it applies to any spread-out thing that has less thickness but more width. For example, sheets of paper, book leaves, scrolls, etc.\n«اٰتُوۡنِیۡ زُبَرَ الۡحَدِیۡدِ»\nTranslation: So bring me iron sheets (large pieces).\n«وَ اِنَّہٗ لَفِیۡ زُبُرِ الۡاَوَّلِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And indeed, it is in the scriptures of the earlier peoples.\n« » has also been used in a spiritual sense.\n«فَتَقَطَّعُوۡۤا اَمۡرَہُمۡ بَیۡنَہُمۡ زُبُرًا»\nTranslation:\n1 - Then they cut off their matter between themselves into fragments (Jalandhari )\n2 - Then they broke and made their work into pieces. (Osmani )"
    },
    {
      "id": 1029,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » means pieces of woven wool or felt. (6 verses: 7:135, 9:12, 9:13, 16:92, 43:50, 48:10)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « ». Meaning: a blanket or tent that is turned upside down for re-weaving. And « » refers to one who turns upside down a woven or wrapped thing (Munjid). Then, since in turning upside down, such things become damaged and torn into pieces, therefore « » means such pieces.\n«وَ لَا تَکُوۡنُوۡا کَالَّتِیۡ نَقَضَتۡ غَزۡلَہَا مِنۡۢ بَعۡدِ قُوَّۃٍ اَنۡکَاثًا»\nTranslation: And do not be like the woman who, after having spun her yarn with strength, tore it into pieces."
    },
    {
      "id": 1030,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » means pieces of meat, limbs. (2 verses: 3:119, 15:91)",
      "d": "«اَلْعُضْو» «اَلْعِضْو» «اَعْضاء» «عَضَا یَعْضُوا» «اَلْعِضَۃُ» «عِضِیِن» «عَضُوْن» «عَضَنَ» «عُضْو» «عِضْو»\n«الَّذِیۡنَ جَعَلُوا الۡقُرۡاٰنَ عِضِیۡنَ»\nTranslation:\n1 - That is, they tore the Quran into pieces (by accepting some and rejecting others) (Jalandhari )\n2 - Those who have made the Quran into fragments (Osmani )"
    },
    {
      "id": 1031,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » means filings and small pieces of precious metals. (1 verse: 21:58)",
      "d": "«جَذَّ» «جِذَّ» «جُذَاذُ» «جُذَّاذَات» «جُذَاذَةُ مِنَ الْفِضَّۃ» «جُذَاذ» «جُذَاذُ»\n«فَجَعَلَہُمۡ جُذٰذًا اِلَّا کَبِیۡرًا لَّہُمۡ لَعَلَّہُمۡ اِلَیۡہِ یَرۡجِعُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: Then he broke them into pieces, except the largest one, so that they might return to it."
    },
    {
      "id": 1032,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Piece",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » generally means one part of two parts of something. (32 verses: 2:50-2:53-2:102-2:136-2:185-2:285-3:4-3:84-3:103-3:105-4:130-4:150-4:152-5:25-6:153-6:159-8:29-8:41-9:122-12:39-12:67-17:106-20:94-21:48-25:1-26:63-30:14-30:32-42:13-42:14-77:4-98:4)",
      "d": "« » means a broken or cut piece (Munjid). It generally involves the concept of two pieces. One piece that is cut and separated. The other that remains after cutting. And « » also refers to the middle parting of hair on the head (Munjid), and « » refers to the gap between the two front teeth (Munjid).\n«فَانۡفَلَقَ فَکَانَ کُلُّ فِرۡقٍ کَالطَّوۡدِ الۡعَظِیۡمِ»\nTranslation: Then it split, and each part became like a huge mountain.\n(For the difference between « » and « », see \"Phaarna\" (To Split).)"
    },
    {
      "id": 1033,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "portion",
      "hw": "ٹکڑا",
      "s": "« » is used for a 'part' in contrast to the 'whole' and for an individual or some individuals in contrast to a group (86 verses: 2:36-2:73-2:76-2:85-2:145-2:251-2:253-2:259-2:283-3:34-3:50-3:64-3:155-3:195-4:19-4:21-4:25-4:32-4:34-4:150-5:49-5:51-6:53-6:65-6:112-6:128-6:129-6:158-6:165-7:24-8:37-8:72-8:73-8:75-9:67-9:71-9:127-10:46-11:12-11:54-12:10-13:4-13:36-13:40-16:71-17:21-17:55-17:88-18:19-18:99-20:123-22:40-23:44-23:91-23:113-24:40-24:58-24:62-24:63-25:20-26:198-27:72-29:25-30:41-33:6-34:31-34:42-35:40-37:27-37:50-38:22-38:24-40:28-40:77-43:32-43:63-43:67-45:19-47:4-47:26-49:2-49:12-52:25-66:3-68:30-69:44)",
      "d": "«بَعْض» «فَقُلۡنَا اضۡرِبُوۡہُ بِبَعۡضِہَا» «بَعْضُ الْلَیَالِی» «بَعْضُ النَّاس» «فَاَقۡبَلَ بَعۡضُہُمۡ عَلٰی بَعۡعٍ یَّتَلَاوَمُوۡنَ» «وَ لِاُبَیِّنَ  لَکُمۡ بَعۡضَ الَّذِیۡ تَخۡتَلِفُوۡنَ فِیۡہِ»"
    }
  ],
