      "d": "«بَرَدَ» «بَرْد ۔ بُرُوْدَت» «بَرَد» «بُرِدَتِ الْاَرَض» «بَارِدْ» «اُرۡکُضۡ بِرِجۡلِکَ ۚ ہٰذَا مُغۡتَسَلٌۢ  بَارِدٌ وَّ  شَرَابٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1039,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to become cool (pleasant)",
      "hw": "ٹھنڈا",
      "s": "« » refers to coolness that is pleasant and brings comfort (7 verses: 19:26-20:40-25:74-28:9-28:13-32:17-33:51)",
      "d": "«قَرَّ الْیَوْم» «یَوْمٌ قَرٌّ» «لَیْلَۃٌ قَرَّۃٌ» «قَرَّتْ ( قُرَۃٌ وقُرَّۃٌ ) عَیْنُہٗ» «قَرَّ» «فَکُلِیۡ وَ اشۡرَبِیۡ وَ قَرِّیۡ عَیۡنًا»"
    }
  ],
  "220": [
    {
      "id": 1040,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to stop (meaning to halt)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » means for something to stop after movement (20 verses: 2:231-2:256-4:15-5:4-6:13-6:96-7:170-7:189-9:103-10:67-16:79-16:80-23:18-25:45-27:86-28:72-28:73-30:21-40:61-42:33-)",
      "d": "« » is used for stopping after movement (lexically)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1041,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to stop (meaning to halt)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » means for a moving thing to stop firmly and steadily with its support (2 verses: 42:33-53:34)",
      "d": "«رَکَدَ» «رَکَدَ الْمِیْزَان» «رَکَدَ الَشَّمْس» «اِنۡ یَّشَاۡ یُسۡکِنِ الرِّیۡحَ فَیَظۡلَلۡنَ رَوَاکِدَ عَلٰی ظَہۡرِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1042,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to stop (meaning to halt)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » means to become completely still; for inanimate objects to have a permanent stop (1 verse: 27:88)",
      "d": "«جَمَدَ» «جَمَدَ الْمَاء» «جَمَدَ الدَّمْ» «جَمْد» «وَ تَرَی الۡجِبَالَ تَحۡسَبُہَا جَامِدَۃً  وَّ  ہِیَ تَمُرُّ مَرَّ السَّحَابِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1043,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to stop (meaning to halt)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » means the surface of water becoming calm, or an open space between two stable things (1 verse: 44:24)",
      "d": "«رَھْوًا» «وَ اتۡرُکِ  الۡبَحۡرَ رَہۡوًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1044,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to stop (meaning to halt)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » means for something to settle in a place; to remain stopped for some time (1 verse: 22:5)",
      "d": "«قَرَّ» «وَ نُقِرُّ  فِی الۡاَرۡحَامِ مَا نَشَآءُ  اِلٰۤی اَجَلٍ مُّسَمًّی»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1045,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to stop (meaning to halt)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » To stop in the middle of an action, to take a brief pause (7 verses: 2:87-5:46-6:27-6:30-34:31-37:24-57:27)",
      "d": "« » To stand still, without movement or sensation (intransitive). To stop in the middle of an action for a short while (e.g., like a bus stopping), or a pause after which the initial movement or action is expected. This word is used both as intransitive and transitive.\nIntransitive example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَوۡ تَرٰۤی اِذۡ  وُقِفُوۡا عَلٰی رَبِّہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And if you could see when they are made to stand before their Lord.\nTransitive (meaning to make someone stop):\nFor example: The Divine command states:\n«وَ قِفُوۡہُمۡ   اِنَّہُمۡ  مَّسۡئُوۡلُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And make them wait; indeed, they will be questioned."
    },
    {
      "id": 1046,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to reside (meaning to inhabit)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » Used to mean residing for a very long period (26 verses: 2:259-10:16-10:45-11:69-12:42-17:52-17:76-18:12-18:19-18:25-18:26-20:40-20:103-20:104-23:112-23:113-23:114-26:18-29:14-30:55-30:56-33:14-34:14-37:144-46:35-79:46)",
      "d": "« » Meaning to settle and remain permanently in a place (intransitive).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَبِثُوۡا فِیۡ  کَہۡفِہِمۡ ثَلٰثَ مِائَۃٍ سِنِیۡنَ وَ ازۡدَادُوۡا  تِسۡعًا»\nTranslation: And they remained in their cave for three hundred years and added nine."
    },
    {
      "id": 1047,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to reside (meaning to inhabit)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » Used to mean waiting in a place (7 verses: 13:17-17:106-18:3-20:10-27:22-28:29-43:77)",
      "d": "« » To wait in a place (intransitive).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَقَالَ  لِاَہۡلِہِ  امۡکُثُوۡۤا  اِنِّیۡۤ اٰنَسۡتُ نَارًا»\nTranslation: Moses said to his family, 'Wait here; indeed, I have perceived a fire.'\nAt another instance, the Divine command states:\n«فَمَکَثَ غَیۡرَ بَعِیۡدٍ»\nTranslation: Then he (the hoopoe) stayed not but a little while.\nAt a third instance:\n«وَ قُرۡاٰنًا فَرَقۡنٰہُ لِتَقۡرَاَہٗ  عَلَی النَّاسِ عَلٰی  مُکۡثٍ»\nTranslation: And a Quran which We have divided, that you may recite it to mankind at intervals.\nHowever, later this word deviated from its original meaning and became synonymous with « ».\nFor example:\n«مَّاکِثِیۡنَ فِیۡہِ اَبَدًا»\nTranslation: They will abide therein forever."
    },
    {
      "id": 1048,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "to reside (meaning to inhabit)",
      "hw": "ٹھہرنا",
      "s": "« » To reside in a sacred place for worship.\n«سَکَنَ، خَلَدَ»",
      "d": "« » Meaning to turn towards something with reverence and remain attached to it (intransitive), and also meaning to seclude oneself, to improve oneself, and to keep oneself (from sins) (transitive). That is, to reside and remain in a sacred place for worship.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تُبَاشِرُوۡہُنَّ وَ اَنۡتُمۡ عٰکِفُوۡنَ  ۙ فِی الۡمَسٰجِدِ»\nTranslation: And do not approach them (your wives) while you are in a state of i'tikaf (seclusion) in the mosques."
    }
  ],
  "221": [
    {
      "id": 1049,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "elevated land and its types",
      "hw": "ٹیلہ",
      "s": "« » means elevated, soft, sandy land. (2 verses: 2:265, 23:50)",
      "d": "«رَبْوَۃ» «رَبَا ، یَرْبُوا» «رَبْوَۃً» « کَمَثَلِ جَنَّۃٍۭ بِرَبۡوَۃٍ اَصَابَہَا وَابِلٌ فَاٰتَتۡ اُکُلَہَا ضِعۡفَیۡنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1051,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "hill and its types",
      "hw": "ٹیلہ",
      "s": "« » A hill that is wider in extent but lower in height (1 verse: 21:96)",
      "d": "« » Its literal meaning is prominence and crookedness. And metaphorically, it is also used for high and hard land of this shape (intransitive). That is, a hill that is wider in extent but lower in height. « » is the opposite of « ». Concave lenses used for correcting near and farsightedness are called « » because they are bulging out on both sides like the shape of a lentil seed.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«حَتّٰۤی  اِذَا  فُتِحَتۡ یَاۡجُوۡجُ وَ مَاۡجُوۡجُ وَ ہُمۡ  مِّنۡ  کُلِّ  حَدَبٍ  یَّنۡسِلُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: Until when Gog and Magog are released, and they swoop down from every elevated place."
    },
    {
      "id": 1052,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Hill and its Types",
      "hw": "ٹیلہ",
      "s": "« » refers to valleys between mountains that are suitable for habitation (1 verse: 26/128)",
      "d": "«رِیَعَ» «رِیْعَۃ» «رِیْعَۃ» «اَتَبۡنُوۡنَ بِکُلِّ رِیۡعٍ  اٰیَۃً  تَعۡبَثُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1053,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "hill and its types",
      "hw": "ٹیلہ",
      "s": "« » Sand dunes; long and winding hills of sand (1 verse: 46:21)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « ». Meaning a sandy, uneven (high and low) hill (intransitive). A long and winding hill of sand, i.e., a sand dune. And « » also means sand hills. A desert. The name of a desert.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ اذۡکُرۡ  اَخَا عَادٍ ؕ اِذۡ  اَنۡذَرَ قَوۡمَہٗ بِالۡاَحۡقَافِ»\nTranslation: And remember the brother of 'Ad, when he warned his people in the Ahqaf (the sand dunes)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1054,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "hill and its types",
      "hw": "ٹیلہ",
      "s": "« » A mountain pass and the path to ascend and descend it (1 verse: 90:10)",
      "d": "« » High and hard land. It is used for a hill and also for a ridge (according to Manjad). Meaning a small mountain.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ ہَدَیۡنٰہُ  النَّجۡدَیۡنِ فَلَا  اقۡتَحَمَ الۡعَقَبَۃَ»\nTranslation: And We have shown him the two highways (of good and evil), but he has not ascended the steep path."
    }
  ],
  "222": [
    {
      "id": 1055,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Crookedness (Bent) to be Crooked",
      "hw": "ٹیڑھا",
      "s": "« » means the upper part of a vertical object, such as a wall or tree, being crooked. In a metaphorical sense, it means complexity, entanglement, or ambiguity (9 verses: 3:99-7:45-7:86-11:19-14:3-18:1-20:107-20:108-39:28)",
      "d": "«عِوَجَ» «اَعْوَج» «اَلْعَرْج» «اَلْعِوَج» «لَّا  تَرٰی  فِیۡہَا عِوَجًا  وَّ  لَاۤ   اَمۡتًا» «عِوَجَ» «أَمْتُ» «عِوَجَ» «اَلۡحَمۡدُ لِلّٰہِ الَّذِیۡۤ  اَنۡزَلَ عَلٰی عَبۡدِہِ الۡکِتٰبَ  وَ لَمۡ  یَجۡعَلۡ  لَّہٗ عِوَجًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1056,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Crookedness (Deviation) To Become Crooked",
      "hw": "ٹیڑھا",
      "s": "« » is used for crookedness in angle of vision and viewpoints (6 verses: 3:7, 9:117, 33:10, 38:63, 53:17, 61:5)",
      "d": "«زَاغَ» «زَاغَ الْبَصَر»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فَاَمَّا الَّذِیۡنَ فِیۡ قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ زَیۡغٌ فَیَتَّبِعُوۡنَ مَا تَشَابَہَ مِنۡہُ»\nTranslation: Then as for those in whose hearts is deviation, they follow the ambiguous parts of it.\nAt another place, the Lord Almighty declares:\n«فَلَمَّا زَاغُوۡۤا اَزَاغَ اللّٰہُ قُلُوۡبَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: So when they deviated, Allah made their hearts deviate."
    },
    {
      "id": 1058,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "Crookedness (Deviation) To Become Crooked",
      "hw": "ٹیڑھا",
      "s": "« » is used for straying (going astray) in the implementation of Shariah commands (1 verse: 16:9)",
      "d": "«جَارَ» «مَیْل عَنِ الطَّرِیْق» «جَائِر»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ عَلَی اللّٰہِ قَصۡدُ السَّبِیۡلِ وَ مِنۡہَا جَآئِرٌ»\nTranslation: And upon Allah lies the direction of the path, and some of them are crooked (i.e., they do not reach it) (Jalandhari )."
    }
  ],
  "223": [
    {
      "id": 1060,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "To Lean (To Rely On)",
      "hw": "ٹیک ",
      "s": "« » comes for leaning on any thing (9 verses: 18:31, 36:56, 38:51, 43:34, 52:20, 55:54, 55:76, 56:16, 76:13)",
      "d": "«اَتْکَاَ» «اَتْکَاَ عَلَی الشَّیْ» «تَوَکَّاَ عَلَی الْعَصَا» «تَکَاَۃٌ» «اِتَّکَاَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«مُّتَّکِئِیۡنَ فِیۡہَا عَلَی الۡاَرَآئِکِ»\nTranslation: They will be reclining in it (Paradise) on thrones."
    },
    {
      "id": 1061,
      "a": "ٹ",
      "h": "To Lean (To Rely On)",
      "hw": "ٹیک ",
      "s": "« » comes specifically for leaning on comfortable things (3 verses: 18:16, 18:29, 18:31)",
      "d": "« » means elbow and every thing from which support is taken. And « » means a small support or cushion. And « » means to lean on the elbow or support. And « » is a place where supports are placed and all kinds of comfort are available (manjad).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«نِعۡمَ الثَّوَابُ ؕ وَ حَسُنَتۡ مُرۡتَفَقًا»\nTranslation: What an excellent reward! And what a beautiful place of rest!"
    }
  ],
  "224": [
    {
      "id": 1062,
      "a": "ث",
      "h": "To Be Established / True",
      "hw": "ثابت",
      "s": "« » is used for truth, veracity (252 verses: 2:26, 2:42, 2:61, 2:71, 2:91, 2:109, 2:119, 2:121, 2:144, 2:146, 2:147, 2:149, 2:176, 2:180, 2:213, 2:236, 2:241, 2:252, 2:282, 3:3, 3:21, 3:60, 3:62, 3:71, 3:86, 3:102, 3:108, 3:112, 3:154, 3:181, 4:105, 4:122, 4:151, 4:155, 4:170, 4:171, 5:27, 5:48, 5:77, 5:83, 5:84, 5:107, 5:116, 6:5, 6:30, 6:57, 6:62, 6:66, 6:73, 6:91, 6:93, 6:114, 6:141, 6:151, 7:8, 7:30, 7:33, 7:43, 7:44, 7:53, 7:89, 7:105, 7:118, 7:146, 7:159, 7:169, 7:181, 8:4, 8:5, 8:6, 8:7, 8:8, 8:32, 8:74, 9:29, 9:33, 9:48, 9:111, 10:4, 10:5, 10:23, 10:30, 10:32, 10:33, 10:35, 10:36, 10:53, 10:55, 10:76, 10:77, 10:82, 10:94, 10:96, 10:103, 10:108, 11:17, 11:45, 11:79, 11:120, 12:51, 12:100, 13:1, 13:14, 13:17, 13:19, 14:19, 14:22, 15:8, 15:55, 15:64, 15:85, 16:3, 16:36, 16:38, 16:102, 17:16, 17:26, 17:33, 17:81, 17:105, 18:13, 18:21, 18:29, 18:44, 18:56, 18:98, 19:34, 20:114, 21:18, 21:24, 21:55, 21:97, 21:112, 22:6, 22:18, 22:40, 22:54, 22:62, 22:74, 22:78, 23:41, 23:62, 23:70, 23:71, 23:90, 23:116, 24:25, 24:49, 25:26, 25:33, 25:68, 27:79, 28:3, 28:13, 28:39, 28:48, 28:53, 28:63, 28:75, 29:44, 29:68, 30:8, 30:38, 30:47, 30:60, 31:9, 31:30, 31:33, 32:3, 32:13, 33:4, 33:53, 34:6, 34:23, 34:26, 34:43, 34:48, 34:49, 35:5, 35:24, 35:31, 36:7, 36:70, 37:31, 37:37, 38:14, 38:22, 38:26, 38:64, 38:84, 39:2, 39:5, 39:19, 39:41, 39:67, 39:69, 39:71, 39:75, 40:5, 40:6, 40:20, 40:25, 40:55, 40:75, 40:77, 40:78, 41:15, 41:25, 41:53, 42:17, 42:18, 42:24, 42:42, 43:29, 43:30, 43:78, 43:86, 44:39, 45:6, 45:22, 45:29, 45:32, 46:3, 46:7, 46:17, 46:18, 46:20, 46:30, 46:34, 47:2, 47:3, 48:27, 48:28, 50:5, 50:14, 50:19, 50:42, 51:19, 51:23, 53:28, 56:95, 57:16, 57:27, 60:1, 61:9, 64:3, 69:51, 70:24, 78:39, 84:2, 84:5, 103:3)",
      "d": "« » means to be established, to be binding (manjad). Its opposite is « » (m. l). And « » means an established statement, truth, fidelity. Its opposite is « ».\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فَفَسَقُوۡا فِیۡہَا فَحَقَّ عَلَیۡہَا الۡقَوۡلُ فَدَمَّرۡنٰہَا تَدۡمِیۡرًا»\nTranslation: So they committed evil deeds therein. Then the word [of punishment] was established against it, and We destroyed it completely."
    },
    {
      "id": 1063,
      "a": "ث",
      "h": "To Be Established / True",
      "hw": "ثابت",
      "s": "« » is for a truth that remained hidden due to some pressure (1 verse: 12:51)",
      "d": "« » means a truth that remained hidden due to some pressure, and then after the pressure is lifted or ends, it becomes clearly apparent (muf). The manifestation of truth after it remained hidden (manjad).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«قَالَتِ امۡرَاَتُ الۡعَزِیۡزِ الۡئٰنَ حَصۡحَصَ الۡحَقُّ ۫ اَنَا رَاوَدۡتُّہٗ عَنۡ نَّفۡسِہٖ»\nTranslation: The wife of Al-Aziz said, \"Now the truth has become manifest. Indeed, it was I who sought to seduce him.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 1064,
      "a": "ث",
      "h": "To Remain Steadfast / To Hold Firm",
      "hw": "ثابت",
      "s": "« » means to remain firm on something (13 verses: 2:250, 3:147, 8:11, 8:12, 8:45, 11:120, 13:39, 14:24, 14:27, 16:102, 17:74, 25:32, 47:7)",
      "d": "« » means to become firm on something, to remain in one's place, to be steadfast. Its opposite is « ».\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡۤا اِذَا لَقِیۡتُمۡ فِئَۃً فَاثۡبُتُوۡا»\nTranslation: O you who have believed, when you meet a force, stand firm."
    },
    {
      "id": 1065,
      "a": "ث",
      "h": "To Remain Steadfast / To Hold Firm",
      "hw": "ثابت",
      "s": "« » means to proceed on a correct path and remain steadfast, to adopt constancy (perpetuity) on it (4 verses: 9:7, 41:30, 46:13, 72:16)",
      "d": "«قَامَ عَلَی الْاَمْر» «اَقَاَمَ الشَّئْ» «اِسْتَقَام» «اِسْتَقَام»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«اِنَّ الَّذِیۡنَ قَالُوۡا رَبُّنَا اللّٰہُ ثُمَّ اسۡتَقَامُوۡا فَلَا خَوۡفٌ عَلَیۡہِمۡ وَ لَا ہُمۡ یَحۡزَنُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: Indeed, those who have said, \"Our Lord is Allah,\" and then remained steadfast—no fear will there be concerning them, nor will they grieve."
    },
    {
      "id": 1066,
      "a": "ث",
      "h": "To Remain Steadfast / To Hold Firm",
      "hw": "ثابت",
      "s": "« » means to present a chest like a shield before calamities and hardships and to make it a habit (3 verses: 19:65, 20:132, 54:27)",
      "d": "«صَابَرَ» «صَبَرَ» «جَزَعَ» «صَبَرَ الدَّایَۃ» «صَابَرَ» «اِصْطَبِر»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اۡمُرۡ اَہۡلَکَ بِالصَّلٰوۃِ وَ اصۡطَبِرۡ عَلَیۡہَا»\nTranslation: And enjoin upon your people prayer, and be constant in it."
    },
    {
      "id": 1067,
      "a": "ث",
      "h": "To Remain Steadfast / To Hold Firm",
      "hw": "ثابت",
      "s": "« » means to remain steadfast on a task whose stability and protection is necessary (5 verses: 3:200, 8:11, 8:60, 18:14, 28:10)",
      "d": "«رَبَطَ الْفَرَس» «رَبَاط» «رَبَاطَ الجَّیْش» «رَابَطَ الْجَّیْش» «رَابَطَ اْلاَمْرَ» «رَابَطَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوا اصۡبِرُوۡا وَ صَابِرُوۡا وَ رَابِطُوۡا»\nTranslation: O you who have believed, persevere and endure and remain stationed [in readiness] (Jalandhari ).\nAnd for holding firm, « » is used.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ کُلًّا نَّقُصُّ عَلَیۡکَ مِنۡ اَنۡۢبَآءِ الرُّسُلِ مَا نُثَبِّتُ بِہٖ فُؤَادَکَ»\nTranslation: And each [story] We relate to you from the news of the messengers is that by which We strengthen your heart."
    }
  ],
  "225": [
    {
      "id": 1068,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To Spy",
      "hw": "جاسوسی",
      "s": "« » generally carries a negative meaning. It means to search for someone's faults and to investigate them, by any means (1 verse: 49/12)",
      "d": "«جَسّ» «جَسَّ بِعَیْنِہٖ» «جَسَّسَ» «تَجَسَّس» «جَسِیْس» «وَّ لَا تَجَسَّسُوۡا وَ لَا یَغۡتَبۡ بَّعۡضُکُمۡ بَعۡضًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1069,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To Spy",
      "hw": "جاسوسی",
      "s": "« » is a person who eavesdrops to spy and then informs others (3 verses: 5:41-5:42-9:47)",
      "d": "«سَمِعَ» «سَامِع» «سَمَّاع» «سَمّٰعُوۡنَ لِلۡکَذِبِ سَمّٰعُوۡنَ لِقَوۡمٍ اٰخَرِیۡنَ ۙ  لَمۡ  یَاۡتُوۡکَ»"
    }
  ],
  "226": [
    {
      "id": 1070,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To Know",
      "hw": "جاننا",
      "s": "« » means to know something correctly and accurately (448 verses: 2:13-2:22-2:26-2:30-2:32-2:33-2:42-2:75-2:77-2:78-2:80-2:101-2:102-2:103-2:106-2:107-2:113-2:118-2:120-2:140-2:143-2:144-2:145-2:146-2:151-2:169-2:184-2:188-2:194-2:196-2:197-2:203-2:209-2:216-2:220-2:223-2:230-2:231-2:232-2:233-2:235-2:239-2:244-2:247-2:255-2:259-2:260-2:267-2:270-2:280-3:7-3:18-3:19-3:29-3:36-3:61-3:66-3:71-3:75-3:78-3:135-3:140-3:142-3:166-3:167-4:25-4:43-4:45-4:63-4:83-4:113-4:157-4:162-4:166-5:34-5:40-5:49-5:61-5:92-5:94-5:97-5:98-5:99-5:104-5:109-5:113-5:116-6:3-6:33-6:37-6:50-6:53-6:58-6:59-6:60-6:67-6:80-6:81-6:91-6:97-6:100-6:105-6:108-6:114-6:117-6:119-6:124-6:135-6:140-6:143-6:144-6:148-7:7-7:28-7:32-7:33-7:38-7:52-7:62-7:75-7:89-7:123-7:131-7:182-7:187-7:188-8:24-8:25-8:27-8:28-8:34-8:40-8:41-8:60-8:70-9:2-9:3-9:6-9:11-9:16-9:36-9:41-9:42-9:43-9:63-9:78-9:93-9:97-9:101-9:104-9:123-10:5-10:18-10:39-10:40-10:55-10:68-10:89-10:93-11:5-11:6-11:14-11:31-11:39-11:46-11:47-11:49-11:79-11:93-12:21-12:22-12:40-12:46-12:51-12:52-12:68-12:73-12:76-12:77-12:80-12:81-12:86-12:89-12:96-13:8-13:19-13:33-13:37-13:42-13:43-14:9-14:38-14:52-15:3-15:24-15:96-15:97-16:8-16:19-16:23-16:25-16:27-16:38-16:39-16:41-16:43-16:55-16:56-16:70-16:74-16:75-16:78-16:91-16:95-16:101-16:103-16:125-17:12-17:25-17:36-17:47-17:54-17:55-17:84-17:85-17:102-17:107-18:5-18:12-18:19-18:21-18:22-18:26-18:65-19:43-19:65-19:70-19:75-20:7-20:52-20:71-20:98-20:104-20:110-20:114-20:135-21:4-21:7-21:24-21:28-21:39-21:65-21:74-21:79-21:110-22:3-22:5-22:8-22:54-22:68-22:70-22:71-22:76-23:84-23:88-23:96-23:114-24:15-24:19-24:25-24:29-24:31-24:33-24:63-24:64-25:6-25:42-26:49-26:112-26:132-26:188-26:197-26:227-27:15-27:25-27:40-27:42-27:52-27:61-27:65-27:66-27:74-27:84-28:13-28:14-28:37-28:38-28:50-28:56-28:57-28:69-28:75-28:78-28:80-28:85-29:3-29:8-29:10-29:11-29:16-29:32-29:41-29:42-29:45-29:49-29:52-29:64-29:66-30:6-30:7-30:29-30:30-30:34-30:56-30:59-31:6-31:15-31:20-31:25-31:34-32:17-33:5-33:18-33:50-33:51-33:63-34:2-34:6-34:14-34:21-34:28-34:36-35:11-36:16-36:26-36:36-36:76-37:158-37:170-38:69-38:88-39:9-39:26-39:29-39:39-39:49-39:52-39:70-40:7-40:19-40:42-40:57-40:70-40:83-41:3-41:22-41:47-42:14-42:18-42:25-42:35-43:20-43:61-43:85-43:86-43:89-44:32-44:39-45:17-45:18-45:23-45:24-45:26-46:4-46:8-46:23-47:16-47:19-47:26-47:30-47:31-48:25-48:27-49:7-49:16-49:18-50:16-50:45-52:47-53:28-53:30-53:32-53:35-54:26-56:61-56:76-57:4-57:17-57:20-57:25-57:29-58:7-58:11-58:14-60:1-60:10-61:5-61:11-62:9-63:1-63:8-64:4-65:12-67:14-67:17-67:26-67:29-68:7-68:33-68:44-69:49-70:39-71:4-72:24-72:28-73:20-74:31-78:4-78:5-82:12-84:23-87:7-96:5-96:14-100:9-102:3-102:4-102:5)",
      "d": "«عَلِمَ» «قَدۡ عَلِمَ کُلُّ اُنَاسٍ مَّشۡرَبَہُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1071,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To Know",
      "hw": "جاننا",
      "s": "« » means to have knowledge of something indirectly, i.e., through a means (28 verses: 4:11-10:16-21:109-21:111-31:34-33:63-42:17-42:52-45:32-46:9-65:1-69:3-69:26-72:10-72:25-74:27-77:14-80:3-82:17-82:18-83:8-83:19-86:2-90:12-97:2-101:3-101:10-104:5)",
      "d": "«اَدْرٰی» «لَا» «مَا» «اِنْ» «قُلۡ  اِنۡ  اَدۡرِیۡۤ  اَقَرِیۡبٌ مَّا تُوۡعَدُوۡنَ اَمۡ  یَجۡعَلُ  لَہٗ  رَبِّیۡۤ   اَمَدًا» «وَ مَاۤ  اَدۡرٰىکَ مَا ہِیَہۡ نَارٌ حَامِیَۃٌ» «لَا تَدۡرِیۡ  لَعَلَّ اللّٰہَ  یُحۡدِثُ بَعۡدَ ذٰلِکَ  اَمۡرًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1072,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To Know",
      "hw": "جاننا",
      "s": "« » means to know something through outward senses (2 verses: 3:52-21:12)",
      "d": "«اَحَسَّ» «فَلَمَّاۤ  اَحَسَّ عِیۡسٰی مِنۡہُمُ الۡکُفۡرَ»"
    }
  ],
  "227": [
    {
      "id": 1074,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Side (Direction)",
      "hw": "جانب",
      "s": "« » means the farthest limit or edge of something (6 verses: 3:127-11:114-13:41-20:130-21:44-42:45)",
      "d": "«طَرْف» «اَطْرَاف» «طَرْف» «وَ اَقِمِ الصَّلٰوۃَ طَرَفَیِ النَّہَارِ وَ زُلَفًا مِّنَ الَّیۡلِ» «یَنۡظُرُوۡنَ مِنۡ طَرۡفٍ خَفِیٍّ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1076,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Side (Direction)",
      "hw": "جانب",
      "s": "« » means to face something from a distant and remote place (3 verses: 2:144-2:149-2:150)",
      "d": "«شَطْر» «نِصْفُ الشَّئْ» «اَلْبُعْد وَالْمَوَاجِھَۃ» «شَطْر» «وِجْھَۃ» «وَ مِنۡ حَیۡثُ خَرَجۡتَ فَوَلِّ وَجۡہَکَ شَطۡرَ الۡمَسۡجِدِ الۡحَرَامِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1077,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Side (Direction)",
      "hw": "جانب",
      "s": "« » means towards the front, to be opposite something (3 verses: 7:47-10:15-28:22)",
      "d": "«لَقِیَ» «تِلْقَاءِ ، لِقَاء» «جَلَسَ تِلْقَاءَہٗ» «فَعَلَ الْاَمْرُ مِنْ تِلْقَاءِ نَفْسِہٖ» «قُلۡ مَا یَکُوۡنُ لِیۡۤ اَنۡ اُبَدِّلَہٗ  مِنۡ تِلۡقَآیِٔ  نَفۡسِیۡ» «وَ لَمَّا تَوَجَّہَ  تِلۡقَآءَ مَدۡیَنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1078,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "side (direction)",
      "hw": "جانب",
      "s": "« » means towards the front, the direction in which something is visible. (21 Verses: 2:142-2:143-2:144-2:145-2:177-6:111-10:87-12:26-12:71-18:55-27:37-28:31-37:27-37:50-37:94-46:24-51:29-52:25-57:13-68:30-70:36)",
      "d": "« » also means confrontation, and for one thing to be in front of another. It is as if « » is that side which is visible in front.\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«لَیۡسَ الۡبِرَّ اَنۡ تُوَلُّوۡا وُجُوۡہَکُمۡ  قِبَلَ الۡمَشۡرِقِ وَ الۡمَغۡرِبِ وَ لٰکِنَّ الۡبِرَّ مَنۡ اٰمَنَ بِاللّٰہِ وَ الۡیَوۡمِ الۡاٰخِرِ»\nTranslation: Righteousness is not that you turn your faces toward the east or the west, but righteousness is in one who believes in Allah and the Last Day..."
    }
  ],
  "228": [
    {
      "id": 1079,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "when",
      "hw": "جب",
      "s": "« » comes for the remembrance of a past event. (218 Verses: 2:30-2:34-2:49-2:50-2:51-2:53-2:54-2:55-2:58-2:60-2:61-2:63-2:67-2:72-2:83-2:84-2:93-2:124-2:125-2:126-2:127-2:131-2:133-2:165-2:166-2:246-2:258-2:260-3:8-3:35-3:42-3:44-3:45-3:55-3:80-3:81-3:103-3:121-3:122-3:124-3:152-3:153-3:164-3:187-4:64-4:72-4:108-5:7-5:11-5:20-5:27-5:110-5:111-5:112-5:116-6:27-6:30-6:43-6:71-6:74-6:91-6:93-6:144-7:5-7:12-7:69-7:74-7:80-7:86-7:89-7:141-7:160-7:161-7:163-7:164-7:167-7:171-7:172-8:7-8:9-8:11-8:12-8:17-8:26-8:30-8:32-8:42-8:43-8:44-8:48-8:49-8:50-9:25-9:40-9:115-10:61-10:71-12:4-12:8-12:51-12:89-12:100-12:102-14:6-14:7-14:35-15:28-15:52-17:47-17:60-17:61-17:94-17:101-18:10-18:14-18:16-18:21-18:39-18:50-18:55-18:60-18:63-19:3-19:16-19:39-19:42-20:10-20:38-20:40-20:92-20:104-20:116-21:52-21:76-21:78-21:83-21:87-21:89-22:26-24:12-24:15-24:16-25:29-26:10-26:70-26:72-26:98-26:106-26:124-26:142-26:161-26:177-27:7-27:54-28:44-28:46-28:76-28:87-29:16-29:28-31:13-32:12-33:7-33:9-33:10-33:12-33:13-33:37-34:31-34:32-34:33-34:51-36:13-36:14-37:84-37:85-37:124-37:134-37:140-38:21-38:22-38:31-38:41-38:69-38:71-39:32-40:10-40:18-40:47-40:71-41:14-43:26-43:39-46:11-46:21-46:26-46:29-48:18-48:26-50:17-51:25-51:38-51:41-51:43-53:16-53:32-59:16-60:4-61:5-61:6-66:3-66:11-68:17-68:48-74:33-79:16-85:6-91:12)",
      "d": "« » is used for the past tense, and a sentence follows it, or the sentence is omitted (implied).\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَ اِذۡ قَالَ رَبُّکَ لِلۡمَلٰٓئِکَۃِ اِنِّیۡ جَاعِلٌ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ خَلِیۡفَۃً»\nTranslation: And when your Lord said to the angels, 'I am going to place a vicegerent on earth.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1080,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "When",
      "hw": "جب",
      "s": "« » is an adverb of time in Arabic grammar that carries a conditional meaning. It often enters into past tense verbs, transforming their meaning into the future. (326 verses: 2:11-2:13-2:14-2:20-2:76-2:91-2:117-2:145-2:156-2:170-2:177-2:180-2:186-2:196-2:205-2:206-2:231-2:232-2:233-2:282-3:25-3:47-3:119-3:135-3:152-3:156-4:6-4:8-4:18-4:41-4:58-4:61-4:62-4:67-4:77-4:83-4:86-4:94-4:101-4:102-4:140-4:142-5:2-5:5-5:6-5:58-5:61-5:83-5:89-5:93-5:104-5:105-5:106-5:107-6:25-6:31-6:44-6:54-6:56-6:61-6:68-6:99-6:109-6:124-6:141-6:152-7:28-7:37-7:38-7:47-7:57-7:90-7:135-7:201-7:203-7:204-8:2-8:15-8:24-8:31-8:45-9:38-9:58-9:86-9:91-9:92-9:94-9:95-9:118-9:122-9:124-9:127-10:12-10:15-10:21-10:22-10:23-10:24-10:49-10:51-10:90-10:106-11:31-11:40-11:102-12:14-12:62-12:79-12:110-13:11-15:8-16:24-16:40-16:53-16:54-16:58-16:85-16:86-16:91-16:101-17:16-17:35-17:42-17:45-17:46-17:67-17:73-17:75-17:76-17:83-17:100-17:107-18:14-18:17-18:20-18:24-18:57-18:71-18:74-18:77-18:86-18:90-18:93-18:96-19:35-19:58-19:73-19:75-21:12-21:36-22:72-21:45-21:96-22:35-22:52-23:34-23:35-23:64-23:77-23:91-23:99-24:39-24:40-24:48-24:51-24:59-24:62-25:12-25:13-25:41-25:60-25:63-25:67-25:72-25:73-26:20-26:42-26:80-26:130-27:18-27:34-27:62-27:80-27:82-27:84-28:53-28:55-29:48-29:65-30:20-30:25-30:33-30:36-30:48-30:52-31:7-31:21-31:32-32:15-33:16-33:36-33:37-33:49-33:53-34:7-34:23-34:43-36:24-36:45-36:47-36:82-37:13-37:14-37:35-39:8-39:45-39:49-39:71-39:73-40:12-40:34-41:20-41:51-42:29-42:37-42:39-42:48-43:13-43:17-43:38-43:47-43:50-43:57-45:9-45:25-45:32-46:6-46:7-46:15-47:4-47:16-47:18-47:27-48:15-53:1-53:22-53:46-54:24-56:1-56:4-56:83-58:8-58:9-58:11-58:12-60:10-60:12-62:9-62:11-63:1-63:4-63:5-63:11-65:1-67:7-68:15-70:20-70:21-71:4-72:24-74:34-75:26-76:19-76:20-76:28-77:9-77:10-77:11-77:48-79:12-80:22-81:1-81:2-81:3-81:4-81:5-81:6-81:7-81:8-81:10-81:11-81:12-81:13-81:17-81:18-82:1-82:2-82:3-82:4-83:2-83:3-83:13-83:30-83:31-83:32-84:1-84:3-84:18-84:21-89:4-89:15-89:16-89:21-91:2-91:3-91:4-92:1-92:2-92:11-93:2-96:10-99:1-100:9-110:1-113:3-113:5)",
      "d": "« » is an adverb of time in Arabic grammar that carries a conditional meaning. It often enters into past tense verbs, transforming their meaning into the future.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اِذَا لَقُوا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا قَالُوۡۤا اٰمَنَّا»\nTranslation: And when they meet those who believe, they say, \"We believe.\"\nSimilarly, in another instance, the Divine declaration states:\nTranslation: When Ramadan comes, the gates of Paradise are opened.\nIn another instance, the Divine declaration states:\n«اِذَا الشَّمۡسُ کُوِّرَتۡ»\nTranslation: When the sun is wrapped up.\nSometimes, with a tanwīn (nunation), it specifies a future time, meaning \"at that time\", \"in that situation\", or \"in that state\".\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اِذًا لَّارۡتَابَ الۡمُبۡطِلُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: At that time, those who reject the truth will be in doubt.\nAdding it after « » forms « », meaning \"at that time\". Adding it after « » forms « », specifying \"on that day\". All these are used as adverbs of time referring to the future.\nOccasionally, this particle also enters into the imperfect (present/future) verb.\nNote: (Adverb of time: a noun in which the meaning of time or period is present, e.g., morning, evening, today, tomorrow, month, week, century, etc.)"
    },
    {
      "id": 1081,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "When",
      "hw": "جب",
      "s": "« » is called a negative particle in Arabic grammar and comes for condition in the past tense. (150 verses: 2:17-2:33-2:89-2:101-2:214-2:246-2:249-2:250-2:259-3:36-3:52-3:142-3:165-4:77-5:117-6:5-6:44-6:76-6:77-6:78-7:22-7:116-7:126-7:134-7:135-7:143-7:149-7:150-7:154-7:155-7:165-7:166-7:189-7:190-8:48-9:16-9:76-9:114-10:12-10:13-10:23-10:39-10:54-10:76-10:77-10:80-10:81-10:98-11:58-11:66-11:70-11:74-11:77-11:82-11:94-11:101-11:111-12:15-12:22-12:28-12:31-12:50-12:54-12:59-12:63-12:65-12:66-12:68-12:69-12:70-12:80-12:88-12:94-12:96-12:99-14:22-15:61-17:67-18:59-18:61-18:62-19:49-20:11-21:12-25:37-26:21-26:41-26:61-27:8-27:10-27:13-27:36-27:40-27:42-27:44-28:14-28:19-28:22-28:23-28:25-28:29-28:30-28:31-28:36-28:48-29:31-29:33-29:65-29:68-31:32-32:24-33:22-33:37-34:14-34:33-34:43-35:42-37:102-37:103-40:25-40:66-40:83-40:84-40:85-41:41-42:44-43:30-43:35-43:47-43:50-43:55-43:57-43:63-46:7-46:24-46:29-49:14-50:5-59:16-61:5-61:6-62:3-66:3-67:27-68:26-68:51-69:11-72:13-72:19-80:23)",
      "d": "« » is called a negative particle in Arabic grammar and comes for condition in the past tense.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَلَمَّا أَن جَاءَ الْبَشِيرُ»\nTranslation: So when the bearer of good news arrived."
    },
    {
      "id": 1082,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "When",
      "hw": "جب",
      "s": "« » is used to encompass certain matters (actions). (15 verses: 2:20-2:25-2:87-2:100-3:37-4:56-5:64-5:70-7:38-11:38-17:97-22:22-32:20-67:8-71:7)",
      "d": "« » is used to encompass certain matters (actions). It means 'whenever', 'every time'. It comes as a temporal adverb (past) to encompass many matters (actions).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«أَفَكُلَّمَا جَاءَكُمْ رَسُولٌ بِمَا لَا تَهْوَى أَنْفُسُكُمْ اسْتَكْبَرْتُمْ»\nTranslation: So whenever a messenger came to you with what your souls did not desire, you grew arrogant."
    }
  ],
  "229": [
    {
      "id": 1083,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Root",
      "hw": "جڑ",
      "s": "« » is used for the root of trees and plants. (3 verses: 14:24-37:64-59:5)",
      "d": "« » means the foundation or basis of something, and the root of trees and plants. Its opposite is « » meaning 'branch'. Its plural is « ». (See Mufradat, Majma') And 'usul' also refers to the rules upon which a science is based (Majma').\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«مَثَلًا كَلِمَةً طَيِّبَةً كَشَجَرَةٍ طَيِّبَةٍ أَصْلُهَا ثَابِتٌ وَفَرْعُهَا فِي السَّمَاءِ»\nTranslation: A goodly word is like a goodly tree, whose root is firm [i.e., firmly fixed in the earth] and whose branches are in the sky."
    },
    {
      "id": 1084,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Root",
      "hw": "جڑ",
      "s": "« » are those parts of a tree's root that become embedded in the ground. (2 verses: 54:20-69:7)",
      "d": "«أَعْجَازُ النَّخْلِ» «أَعْجَاز»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَتَرَى الْقَوْمَ فِيهَا صَرْعَى كَأَنَّهُمْ أَعْجَازُ نَخْلٍ خَاوِيَةٍ»\nTranslation: Then you will see the people fallen prone, as if they were hollow palm trunks."
    },
    {
      "id": 1085,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Root (from rope, etc.)",
      "hw": "جڑ",
      "s": "« » is used for uprooting. It also refers to the root or foundation of any thing's corruption. (4 verses: 6:45-7:72-8:7-15:66)",
      "d": "«دُبُر» «دَابِر» «قَطَعَ اللَّهُ دَابِرَهُمْ» «إِدْبَار» «إِقْبَال» «دَابِر»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«يُرِيدُ اللَّهُ أَنْ يُحِقَّ الْحَقَّ بِكَلِمَاتِهِ وَيَقْطَعَ دَابِرَ الْكَافِرِينَ»\nTranslation: Allah intends to establish the truth by His words and to cut off the root of the disbelievers.\nNote: (To destroy. To uproot the root. To dig up the root. To cut off the lineage. To ruin completely.)"
    }
  ],
  "230": [
    {
      "id": 1086,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Body",
      "hw": "جسم",
      "s": "« » is every material thing that has a body. (2 verses: 2:247-63:4)",
      "d": "« » is every material thing that has length, width, and depth, and possesses a body (Majma'). Whether it is animate or inanimate. Its plural is « » (Mufrad). Jism means 'bulk', 'stature', 'tall and big'.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ إِذَا رَأَيْتَهُمْ تُعْجِبُكَ أَجْسَامُهُمْ»\nTranslation: And when you see them, their bodies [i.e., their physical appearance] impress you."
    },
    {
      "id": 1087,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Body",
      "hw": "جسم",
      "s": "« » is specific to the body, meaning the body of a living being in which blood has dried up. (4 verses: 7:148-20:88-21:8-38:34)",
      "d": "« » is specific to the body, meaning the body of a living being in which blood has dried up.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَأَخْرَجَ لَهُمْ عِجْلًا جَسَدًا لَهُ خُوَارٌ»\nTranslation: So he brought out for them a calf, a [mere] body [i.e., without life], which had a lowing sound.\nIn another place, the divine revelation states:\n«وَمَا جَعَلْنَاهُمْ جَسَدًا لَا يَأْكُلُونَ الطَّعَامَ وَمَا كَانُوا خَالِدِينَ»\nTranslation: And We have not made them [i.e., the prophets] bodies that do not eat food, nor were they immortal.\nTherefore, a dead human is called 'jasad khaaki' (dust body) or 'jasad unsuri' (elemental body)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1088,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Body",
      "hw": "جسم",
      "s": "« » meaning a living being's body in which blood is flowing or has not yet dried. (1 verse: 10:92)",
      "d": "« » meaning a living being's body in which blood is flowing or has not yet dried.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَالْيَوْمَ نُنَجِّيكَ بِبَدَنِكَ لِتَكُونَ لِمَنْ خَلْفَكَ آيَةً»\nTranslation: So today We will save you in your body [i.e., your corpse] that you may be a sign for those after you."
    }
  ],
  "231": [
    {
      "id": 1089,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To bind (with rope, etc.)",
      "hw": "جکڑنا",
      "s": "« » is used only for binding with rope, etc. (4 verses: 2:256-31:22-47:4-89:26)",
      "d": "« » means to tie with a rope and to give a knot. And « » and « » refer to the thing with which one is bound, i.e., a rope, etc. (Majma'). Also, « » refers to the rope with which animals are tied.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«حَتَّى إِذَا أَثْخَنْتُمُوهُمْ فَشُدُّوا الْوَثَاقَ»\nTranslation: When you have overcome them, then bind [i.e., capture] them firmly.\nIn this verse, the inclusion of « » (to make firm) gives « » the meaning of 'to bind firmly' or 'to tie tightly'."
    },
    {
      "id": 1090,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To tie (with rope, etc.)",
      "hw": "جکڑنا",
      "s": "« » refers to a rope whose connection is also with another thing for additional strength. (4 verses: 14:49, 25:13, 38:38, 43:13)",
      "d": "«قَرَن» «قَرَن» «قَرَّنَ» «وَّ اٰخَرِیۡنَ مُقَرَّنِیۡنَ فِی الۡاَصۡفَادِ»"
    }
  ],
  "232": [
    {
      "id": 1091,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Place",
      "hw": "جگہ",
      "s": "« » means the place of standing or remaining. (18 verses: 2:125-3:97-5:107-10:71-14:14-17:79-19:73-25:66-25:76-26:58-27:39-33:13-35:35-37:164-44:26-44:51-55:46-79:40)",
      "d": "« » means to stand. And « » is used for the place where one stands.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اتَّخِذُوۡا مِنۡ مَّقَامِ اِبۡرٰہٖمَ مُصَلًّی»\nTranslation: And take the place where Abraham stood as a place of prayer.\n«مُقَام» «قَامَ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ  لِمَنۡ خَافَ مَقَامَ  رَبِّہٖ  جَنَّتٰنِ»\nTranslation: And for whoever fears the standing before his Lord, there will be two gardens.\nNote: (\"Mimetic source\" is a type of verbal noun where an extra mīm is added at the beginning.)"
    },
    {
      "id": 1092,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Place",
      "hw": "جگہ",
      "s": "« » means place, location, spot. (47 verses: 4:20, 5:60, 6:6, 6:135, 7:10, 7:95, 7:143, 10:22, 10:28, 11:93, 11:121, 12:21, 12:54, 23:13, 12:56, 12:77, 12:78, 14:17, 16:101, 16:112, 18:84, 18:95, 22:41, 19:16, 19:22, 19:57, 19:75, 20:58, 22:26, 22:31, 24:55, 25:12, 25:13, 25:34, 28:6, 28:57, 28:82, 34:51, 34:52, 34:53, 36:67, 39:39, 41:44, 46:26, 50:41, 77:21, 81:20)",
      "d": "«مَکَان» «مَکِیْن» «فَاجۡعَلۡ بَیۡنَنَا وَ بَیۡنَکَ مَوۡعِدًا لَّنُخۡلِفُہٗ نَحۡنُ وَ لَاۤ اَنۡتَ مَکَانًا سُوًی»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1093,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Place",
      "hw": "جگہ",
      "s": "« » means a place gained through struggle and effort. (1 verse: 4/100)",
      "d": "«رَغِمَ» «رَغِمَ اَنْفُ فُلَانٍ» «رَاغَمَ» «مَرَاغَم» «وَ مَنۡ یُّہَاجِرۡ فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ یَجِدۡ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ مُرٰغَمًا کَثِیۡرًا وَّ سَعَۃً»"
    }
  ],
  "233": [
    {
      "id": 1094,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Exile",
      "hw": "جلا وطنی",
      "s": "« » means to exile someone. (1 verse: 59/3)",
      "d": "«جَلَا» «جَلَا اَلْرَجُلُ عَنْ بَلَدِہٖ» «جَلَا النَّحْل» «اَلْجَالِی» «وَ لَوۡ لَاۤ اَنۡ کَتَبَ اللّٰہُ عَلَیۡہِمُ الۡجَلَآءَ لَعَذَّبَہُمۡ فِی الدُّنۡیَا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1095,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Exile",
      "hw": "جلا وطنی",
      "s": "« » means to remove someone with humiliation and disgrace. (1 verse: 5/33)",
      "d": "«نَفٰی» «ثَبَتَ» «مَنْفٰی» «نَفٰی الْرَجُلُ مِنْ بَلَدِہٖ» «نَفٰی ، یَنْفُوا» «اَلنِّفَایَۃ» «نَفٰی ، یَنْفُوا» «اِنَّمَا جَزٰٓؤُا الَّذِیۡنَ یُحَارِبُوۡنَ اللّٰہَ وَ رَسُوۡلَہٗ وَ یَسۡعَوۡنَ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ فَسَادًا اَنۡ یُّقَتَّلُوۡۤا اَوۡ یُصَلَّبُوۡۤا اَوۡ تُقَطَّعَ اَیۡدِیۡہِمۡ وَ اَرۡجُلُہُمۡ مِّنۡ خِلَافٍ اَوۡ یُنۡفَوۡا مِنَ الۡاَرۡضِ»"
    }
  ],
  "234": [
    {
      "id": 1096,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To hurry",
      "hw": "جلدی",
      "s": "« » means to complete a task quickly, to hurry. (12 verses: 2:202, 3:19, 3:199, 5:4, 6:62, 6:165, 7:167, 10:21, 13:41, 14:51, 24:39, 40:17)",
      "d": "«سَرِعَ» «بَطَأَ» «اُولٰٓئِکَ لَہُمۡ نَصِیۡبٌ مِّمَّا کَسَبُوۡا ؕ وَ اللّٰہُ سَرِیۡعُ الۡحِسَابِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1097,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To hurry",
      "hw": "جلدی",
      "s": "« » means hastiness, trying to obtain something before its appropriate time so that it is not properly fulfilled. (32 verses: 2:203, 6:57, 6:58, 7:150, 10:11, 10:50, 10:51, 13:6, 16:1, 17:11, 17:18, 18:58, 19:84, 20:83, 20:84, 20:114, 21:37, 22:47, 26:204, 27:46, 27:72, 29:53, 29:54, 37:176, 38:16, 42:18, 46:24, 46:35, 48:20, 51:14, 51:59, 75:16)",
      "d": "«عَجِلَ» «وَ یَدۡعُ الۡاِنۡسَانُ بِالشَّرِّ دُعَآءَہٗ بِالۡخَیۡرِ ؕ وَ کَانَ الۡاِنۡسَانُ عَجُوۡلًا» «اِسْتَعْجَل» «وَ یَسۡتَعۡجِلُوۡنَکَ بِالسَّیِّئَۃِ قَبۡلَ الۡحَسَنَۃِ وَ قَدۡ خَلَتۡ مِنۡ قَبۡلِہِمُ الۡمَثُلٰتُ ؕ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1098,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To hurry",
      "hw": "جلدی",
      "s": "« » means to hurry by reducing the required time for a task. (1 verse: 4/6)",
      "d": "«بَدَرَ» «لَا تُبَادِ رُوْنِیْ بِالرُّکُوْعِ وَ السُّجُوۡدِ» «وَ لَا تَاۡکُلُوۡہَاۤ اِسۡرَافًا وَّ بِدَارًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1099,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To hurry",
      "hw": "جلدی",
      "s": "« » means to do something with zeal and enthusiasm. (4 verses: 3:125, 11:40, 23:27, 67:7)",
      "d": "«فَارَ» «فَوْر» «رَجَعَ مِنْ فَوْرِہٖ» «بَلٰۤی ۙ اِنۡ تَصۡبِرُوۡا وَ تَتَّقُوۡا وَ یَاۡتُوۡکُمۡ مِّنۡ فَوۡرِہِمۡ ہٰذَا یُمۡدِدۡکُمۡ رَبُّکُمۡ بِخَمۡسَۃِ اٰلٰفٍ مِّنَ الۡمَلٰٓئِکَۃِ مُسَوِّمِیۡنَ»"
    }
  ],
  "235": [
    {
      "id": 1101,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to a gathering of people, people assembling at a place.",
      "d": "« » means a gathering of people, or people assembling at a place. This word is general for any group, whether it's a small gathering or a large one, of any kind.\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«سَیُہۡزَمُ الۡجَمۡعُ وَ  یُوَلُّوۡنَ الدُّبُرَ»\nTranslation: Soon this group will be defeated, and they will turn their backs and flee.\nAt another place, the divine command states:\n«وَ اِنَّا  لَجَمِیۡعٌ  حٰذِرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And indeed, we are a large group, watchful against them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1102,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » is a group of young men from the same family, numbering up to ten, and having a leader. (3 verses: 11:91-11:92-27:48)",
      "d": "«رَھْط» «عِشْرُوْنَ رَھْطًا»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ کَانَ فِی الۡمَدِیۡنَۃِ  تِسۡعَۃُ  رَہۡطٍ یُّفۡسِدُوۡنَ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ وَ لَا یُصۡلِحُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And in the city were nine men who caused corruption in the land and did not amend [it].\nIn another instance, the Divine declaration states:\n«قَالَ یٰقَوۡمِ اَرَہۡطِیۡۤ اَعَزُّ  عَلَیۡکُمۡ  مِّنَ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: [Shu'ayb] said, \"O my people, is my family more esteemed to you than Allah?\""
    },
    {
      "id": 1104,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » is a small, strong, and powerful group that supports and aids one another. (4 verses: 12:8-12:14-24:11-28:76)",
      "d": "« » is a small, strong, and powerful group that supports and aids one another. (Muf) In terms of size, it is larger than « » (F. L. 205), but this does not seem correct to the author of Fiqh al-Lughah. Because the Quran has used this term for the ten brothers of Prophet Yusuf as well.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«قَالُوۡا  لَئِنۡ  اَکَلَہُ  الذِّئۡبُ وَ نَحۡنُ عُصۡبَۃٌ  اِنَّاۤ   اِذًا  لَّخٰاسِرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: They said, \"If a wolf has eaten him while we were a strong group, indeed we, then, are losers.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 1108,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » is used specifically for a large number. (3 verses: 56:13-56:39-56:40)",
      "d": "«ثُلَّۃٌ» «فُلَانٌ لَا یُفَرَّقُ بَیْنَ الثَّلَّۃَ وَالثُّلَّۃَ» «ثُلَّۃٌ» «طَآئِفَۃ» «فِرَقَۃَ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«ثُلَّۃٌ  مِّنَ الۡاَوَّلِیۡنَ وَ قَلِیۡلٌ  مِّنَ الۡاٰخِرِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: A large number from the former [people] and a few from the latter."
    },
    {
      "id": 1109,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to small, separate groups that move in scattered formation from a larger group. (2 verses: 39:71-39:73)",
      "d": "According to the author of Fiqh al-Lughah, « » refers to a group larger than « » and its plural is « ». (F. L. 205)\n«زُمْرَۃٌ» «شَاۃٌ زَمِرَۃٌ» «زَمِرٌ» «زُمُر»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ سِیۡقَ الَّذِیۡنَ اتَّقَوۡا رَبَّہُمۡ  اِلَی الۡجَنَّۃِ زُمَرًا»\nTranslation: And those who feared their Lord will be driven to Paradise in groups."
    },
    {
      "id": 1110,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to people of the same lineage. (1 verse: 70:37)",
      "d": "«اَلْعِزَۃ» «عِزِیْن» «عِزُوْن» «اَلْعِزَۃُ» «اَلْاِعْتِزَآءُ فِی الْحَرْبِ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَمَالِ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا قِبَلَکَ مُہۡطِعِیۡنَ عَنِ الۡیَمِیۡنِ وَ عَنِ الشِّمَالِ عِزِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: So what is [the matter] with those who disbelieve, hastening toward you from the right and from the left in groups?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1111,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » means a party, a faction, or a group that attempts to interfere in the affairs of a state. (17 verses: 5:56-11:17-13:36-18:12-19:37-23:53-30:32-33:20-33:22-35:6-38:11-38:13-40:5-40:30-43:65-58:19-58:22)",
      "d": "« » refers to a group in which intensity and severity are found (Muf). And « » means party, faction, group, weapon, an army of men, and like-minded companions who provide support and strength (Munjid). People gathered under one banner (M. Q). Thus, the word « » also comes in the meanings of a political party or an army, with the aim of interfering in state affairs.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ لَمَّا رَاَ  الۡمُؤۡمِنُوۡنَ الۡاَحۡزَابَ ۙ قَالُوۡا ہٰذَا مَا وَعَدَنَا اللّٰہُ  وَ رَسُوۡلُہٗ»\nTranslation: And when the believers saw the [allied] forces, they said, \"This is what Allah and His Messenger had promised us.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 1112,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to all members of a group with a specific purpose, wherein there is mutual harmony and agreement. (3 verses: 6:128-6:130-55:33)",
      "d": "« » means ten, and « » refers to all members of a family who are related through the father. In this sense, « » refers to all members of a group whose purpose and objective are one, and among whom there is harmony and agreement (M. L).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«یٰمَعۡشَرَ الۡجِنِّ وَ الۡاِنۡسِ  اِنِ اسۡتَطَعۡتُمۡ اَنۡ  تَنۡفُذُوۡا مِنۡ  اَقۡطَارِ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضِ فَانۡفُذُوۡا»\nTranslation: O company of jinn and mankind, if you are able to pass beyond the regions of the heavens and the earth, then pass. You will not pass except by authority [from Allah]."
    },
    {
      "id": 1113,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to the two great creations: jinn and humans. (1 verse: 55:31)",
      "d": "« » means burden, weight, heaviness. And « » and « » mean a heavy or weighty thing. And « » means two heavy groups, two great kinds, i.e., jinn and humans. (Munjid. F. L. 134)\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«سَنَفۡرُغُ   لَکُمۡ  اَیُّہَ  الثَّقَلٰنِ»\nTranslation: \"We will attend to you, O two heavy groups.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 1114,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Community / Group",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to a group of similar beings (humans, animals, birds) or people of the same creed who follow a single Imam. (54 verses: 2:143-2:213-3:104-3:110-3:113-4:41-5:48-5:66-6:38-6:42-6:108-7:34-7:38-7:159-7:160-7:164-7:168-7:181-10:19-10:47-10:49-11:8-11:48-11:118-12:45-13:30-15:5-16:36-16:63-16:84-16:89-16:92-16:93-16:120-21:92-22:34-22:67-23:43-23:44-23:52-27:83-28:23-28:75-29:18-35:24-35:42-40:5-41:25-42:8-43:22-43:23-43:33-45:28-46:18)",
      "d": "« » means a group of similar beings (humans, animals, birds) or people of the same creed who follow a single Imam.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ مَا مِنۡ  دَآبَّۃٍ  فِی الۡاَرۡضِ وَ لَا طٰٓئِرٍ یَّطِیۡرُ  بِجَنَاحَیۡہِ  اِلَّاۤ  اُمَمٌ  اَمۡثَالُکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And there is no creature on earth or bird that flies with its wings except [that they are] communities like you.\nAnd when this term is applied to humans, it refers to people of the same creed. For example: The Divine Command states:\n«کَانَ النَّاسُ اُمَّۃً  وَّاحِدَۃً»\nTranslation: [Initially] all people were one community.\nAnd in common usage, « » refers to the community of like-minded people formed by a prophet or messenger.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«کُنۡتُمۡ خَیۡرَ اُمَّۃٍ اُخۡرِجَتۡ لِلنَّاسِ»\nTranslation: [O believers] you are the best community ever raised for mankind.\nAnd the word « » has also been used in the Noble Quran for Prophet Ibrahim (peace be upon him) as an individual. The reason is that Prophet Ibrahim (peace be upon him) single-handedly accomplished the work of an entire community in proclaiming the truth. And according to some, « » also means Imam, i.e., a leader or guide. (Jalandhari, Osmani).\nFor example: The Divine Command states:\n«اِنَّ  اِبۡرٰہِیۡمَ کَانَ اُمَّۃً  قَانِتًا لِّلّٰہِ حَنِیۡفًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, Ibrahim was a community, obedient to Allah and inclined to truth [alone]."
    },
    {
      "id": 1115,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group (of animals)",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to that caravan of camels in which there are ten or more riders (1 verse: 8:42)",
      "d": "The word « » is also used to mean a herd of camels, a caravan, and a camel rider (mufradat).\n«اِذۡ اَنۡتُمۡ بِالۡعُدۡوَۃِ الدُّنۡیَا وَ ہُمۡ  بِالۡعُدۡوَۃِ الۡقُصۡوٰی وَ الرَّکۡبُ اَسۡفَلَ  مِنۡکُمۡ»\nTranslation: When you were on the near bank and they were on the far bank, and the caravan was below you."
    },
    {
      "id": 1116,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group (of animals)",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » refers to a caravan of horses, and the term is also used for the collective of horses and riders (4 verses: 3:14-8:60-16:8-59:6)",
      "d": "« » means a herd of horses; then, like « », the word « » is also applied to a horse rider (meaning faras) (manjad, mufradat), and it is also used for the collective of horses and riders (mufradat).\n«وَ اَعِدُّوۡا لَہُمۡ مَّا اسۡتَطَعۡتُمۡ مِّنۡ قُوَّۃٍ وَّ مِنۡ رِّبَاطِ الۡخَیۡلِ تُرۡہِبُوۡنَ بِہٖ عَدُوَّ اللّٰہِ وَ عَدُوَّکُمۡ »\nTranslation: And (O believers) prepare against them whatever force and cavalry you can, by which you may terrify the enemy of Allah and your enemy."
    },
    {
      "id": 1117,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Group (of animals)",
      "hw": "جماعت",
      "s": "« » is used for a flock of goats/sheep (3 verses: 6:146-20:18-21:78)",
      "d": "« » is used for a flock of goats/sheep. (mufradat)\n«وَ دَاوٗدَ  وَ سُلَیۡمٰنَ  اِذۡ یَحۡکُمٰنِ فِی الۡحَرۡثِ  اِذۡ  نَفَشَتۡ فِیۡہِ غَنَمُ  الۡقَوۡمِ»\nTranslation: And (mention) David and Solomon when they judged concerning the field - when the people's sheep grazed therein."
    }
  ],
  "236": [
    {
      "id": 1119,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Jinn",
      "hw": "جن",
      "s": "« » refers to another hidden and fiery creation besides humans, which is accountable under Sharia (31 verses: 6:100-6:112-6:128-6:130-7:38-7:179-7:184-11:119-17:88-18:50-23:25-23:70-27:17-27:39-32:13-34:8-34:12-34:14-34:41-34:46-37:158-41:25-41:29-46:18-46:29-51:56-55:33-72:1-72:5-72:6-114:6)",
      "d": "«اَلْجِنّ وَالْجِنَّۃ» «جَآنٌّ» «جِن»\n«وَ مَا خَلَقۡتُ الۡجِنَّ وَ الۡاِنۡسَ  اِلَّا لِیَعۡبُدُوۡنِ»\nTranslation: And I did not create the jinn and mankind except to worship Me."
    },
    {
      "id": 1121,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Jinn",
      "hw": "جن",
      "s": "« » refers to that devil who reaches the extreme in causing harm and mischief and rebellion (1 verse: 37:7)",
      "d": "If a devil reaches the limit in his rebellion and causing harm, he is called « » (F L 135).\n«وَ  حِفۡظًا مِّنۡ کُلِّ شَیۡطٰنٍ مَّارِدٍ»\nTranslation: And (a means of) protection from every devil, rebellious (or) rebellious devil."
    },
    {
      "id": 1122,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Jinn",
      "hw": "جن",
      "s": "« » refers to the devil who casts evil suggestions into hearts and minds (1 verse: 114:4)",
      "d": "«خَنَسَ» «خَانِس، خُنَّس» «خَنَّاس»\n«مِنۡ  شَرِّ الۡوَسۡوَاسِ  ۬ ۙ الۡخَنَّاسِ . الَّذِیۡ یُوَسۡوِسُ فِیۡ صُدُوۡرِ النَّاسِ . مِنَ الۡجِنَّۃِ وَ النَّاسِ»\nTranslation: From the evil of the retreating whisperer, who whispers [evil] into the breasts of mankind, from among the jinn and mankind."
    },
    {
      "id": 1123,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Jinn",
      "hw": "جن",
      "s": "« » refers to a very strong, powerful, and tall jinn (1 verse: 27:39)",
      "d": "« » means a very strong, powerful, and tall jinn. (F L 135)\n«قَالَ عِفۡرِیۡتٌ مِّنَ الۡجِنِّ اَنَا اٰتِیۡکَ بِہٖ قَبۡلَ  اَنۡ  تَقُوۡمَ مِنۡ مَّقَامِکَ»\nTranslation: A powerful one from among the jinn said, \"I will bring it to you before you rise from your place.\""
    }
  ],
  "237": [
    {
      "id": 1124,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Paradise and its various names",
      "hw": "جنت",
      "s": "« » means garden; in common usage, it is used for Paradise (143 verses: 2:25-2:35-2:82-2:111-2:214-2:221-2:265-2:266-3:15-3:133-3:136-3:142-3:185-3:195-3:198-4:13-4:57-4:122-4:124-5:12-5:65-5:72-5:85-5:119-6:99-6:141-7:19-7:22-7:27-7:40-7:42-7:43-7:44-7:46-7:49-7:50-9:21-9:72-9:89-9:100-9:111-10:9-10:26-11:23-11:108-13:4-13:23-13:35-14:23-15:45-16:31-16:32-17:91-18:31-18:32-18:33-18:35-18:39-18:40-18:107-19:60-19:61-19:63-20:76-20:117-20:121-22:14-22:23-22:56-23:19-25:8-25:10-25:15-25:24-26:57-26:85-26:90-26:134-26:147-29:58-31:8-32:19-34:15-34:16-35:33-36:26-36:34-36:55-37:43-38:50-39:73-39:74-40:8-40:40-41:30-42:7-42:22-43:70-43:72-44:25-44:52-46:14-46:16-47:6-47:12-47:15-48:5-48:17-50:9-50:31-51:15-52:17-53:15-54:54-55:46-55:54-55:62-56:12-56:89-57:12-57:21-58:22-59:20-61:12-64:9-65:11-66:8-66:11-68:17-68:34-69:22-70:35-70:38-71:12-74:40-76:12-78:16-79:41-81:13-85:11-88:10-89:30-98:8)",
      "d": "«جَنَّۃٌ» «جَنَّاتٌ، جَنَّ» «جَنَّۃٌ»\n«اَیَوَدُّ اَحَدُکُمۡ اَنۡ تَکُوۡنَ لَہٗ جَنَّۃٌ مِّنۡ نَّخِیۡلٍ وَّ اَعۡنَابٍ»\nTranslation: Would any of you wish to have a garden of palm trees and grapevines?\n«اَلْجَنَّۃ» «جَنَّۃ» «وَ بَشِّرِ الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا وَ عَمِلُوا الصّٰلِحٰتِ اَنَّ لَہُمۡ جَنّٰتٍ تَجۡرِیۡ مِنۡ تَحۡتِہَا الۡاَنۡہٰرُ»\nTranslation: And give good tidings to those who believe and do righteous deeds that they will have gardens beneath which rivers flow."
    },
    {
      "id": 1125,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Paradise and its various names",
      "hw": "جنت",
      "s": "«جَنّٰتُ عَدْنٍ»",
      "d": "«عَدَنَ» «جَنّٰتُ عَدْنٍ»\n«جَزَآؤُہُمۡ عِنۡدَ  رَبِّہِمۡ جَنّٰتُ عَدۡنٍ تَجۡرِیۡ مِنۡ تَحۡتِہَا الۡاَنۡہٰرُ»\nTranslation: Their reward with their Lord is gardens of perpetual residence beneath which rivers flow."
    },
    {
      "id": 1126,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Paradise and its various names",
      "hw": "جنت",
      "s": "«جَنّٰتُ الْفِرْدَوْس»",
      "d": "«فِرْدَوْس» «فردوس» «جَنّٰتُ الْفِرْدَوْس» «اَللّٰھُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ الْجَنَّۃَ الْفِرْدَوْس»\n«اِنَّ الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا وَ عَمِلُوا الصّٰلِحٰتِ کَانَتۡ لَہُمۡ  جَنّٰتُ الۡفِرۡدَوۡسِ نُزُلًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, those who have believed and done righteous deeds - for them are the gardens of Paradise as a lodging."
    },
    {
      "id": 1127,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Paradise and its various names",
      "hw": "جنت",
      "s": "«جَنّٰتُ النَّعِیْمِ»",
      "d": "«نَعْم» «جَنَّاتُ النَّعِیْم»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«اِنَّ  لِلۡمُتَّقِیۡنَ عِنۡدَ رَبِّہِمۡ جَنّٰتِ النَّعِیۡمِ»\nTranslation: For the pious, there are gardens of bliss with their Lord."
    }
  ],
  "238": [
    {
      "id": 1128,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "War",
      "hw": "جنگ",
      "s": "« » means to intend to kill another person. It signifies war and the battlefield (10 verses: 2:216-2:217-2:246-3:121-3:167-4:77-8:16-8:65-33:25-47:20)",
      "d": "« » means to kill someone. And « » means a fight in which there is an intention to kill another.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«کُتِبَ عَلَیۡکُمُ الۡقِتَالُ وَ ہُوَ کُرۡہٌ لَّکُمۡ»\nTranslation: Fighting has been prescribed for you (in the way of Allah), and you dislike it.\nSometimes « » also means « » or the battlefield. The Divine Command states:\n«وَ اِذۡ غَدَوۡتَ مِنۡ اَہۡلِکَ تُبَوِّئُ الۡمُؤۡمِنِیۡنَ مَقَاعِدَ لِلۡقِتَالِ»\nTranslation: And (remember) when you left your home in the morning to post the believers at their stations for the battle."
    },
    {
      "id": 1129,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "War",
      "hw": "جنگ",
      "s": "« » means to fight and to seize property from an enemy (4 verses: 2:279-5:64-8:57-47:4)",
      "d": "«حَرَبَ» «حَرْبَۃٌ» «اَحْرَبَ الْحَرْب» «حَرْب» «قِتَال»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«کُلَّمَاۤ  اَوۡقَدُوۡا  نَارًا لِّلۡحَرۡبِ اَطۡفَاَہَا اللّٰہُ»\nTranslation: Whenever they kindle a fire for war, Allah extinguishes it. (Uthmani)"
    },
    {
      "id": 1130,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "War",
      "hw": "جنگ",
      "s": "« » means the slow, steady advance of a large army towards the battlefield (1 verse: 8:15)",
      "d": "«زَحَفَ» «زَحَفَ الْعَسْکَرُ اِلَی الْعَدُوِّ» «اَلزَّحْفُ» «زَحْفًا» «زَحُوْف» «زَھَافَات»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡۤا  اِذَا لَقِیۡتُمُ  الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا  زَحۡفًا  فَلَا  تُوَلُّوۡہُمُ  الۡاَدۡبَارَ»\nTranslation: O you who have believed, when you meet those who disbelieve in battle, do not turn your backs to them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1131,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "War",
      "hw": "جنگ",
      "s": "« » refers to the hardships and physical damage encountered during war (26 verses: 2:177-2:214-4:84-6:42-6:43-6:147-6:148-7:4-7:5-7:94-7:97-7:98-12:110-16:81-17:5-18:2-21:12-21:80-27:33-33:18-40:29-40:84-40:85-48:16-57:25-59:14)",
      "d": "The fundamental meaning of « » is hardship, severity, strength, and aversion. (m l. maf) Whether it is in livelihood, such as poverty and destitution, or in the form of punishment. Generally, the word « » is used for it, whether in the context of punishment or fighting. The author of Manjad has written the meanings of « » as courage, bravery, strength, fear, and punishment. And when the word « » comes in the context of war or the battlefield, it refers to the hardships, trials, and physical damage of the fight.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ الصّٰبِرِیۡنَ فِی الۡبَاۡسَآءِ وَ الضَّرَّآءِ  وَ حِیۡنَ الۡبَاۡسِ»\nTranslation: And those who are patient in [the face of] hardship and illness and in the heat of battle."
    },
    {
      "id": 1132,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "War",
      "hw": "جنگ",
      "s": "« » means to fight solely for the exaltation of religion, leaving behind personal motives and interests (30 verses: 2:218-3:142-4:95-5:35-5:54-8:72-8:74-8:75-9:16-9:19-9:20-9:24-9:41-9:44-9:73-9:81-9:86-9:88-16:110-22:78-25:52-29:6-29:8-29:69-31:15-47:31-49:15-60:1-61:11-66:9)",
      "d": "«جِھَاد» «جِھَاد» «جِھَاد بِالسَّیْف»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اِذَاۤ اُنۡزِلَتۡ سُوۡرَۃٌ اَنۡ اٰمِنُوۡا بِاللّٰہِ وَ جَاہِدُوۡا مَعَ رَسُوۡلِہِ اسۡتَاۡذَنَکَ اُولُوا الطَّوۡلِ مِنۡہُمۡ وَ قَالُوۡا ذَرۡنَا نَکُنۡ مَّعَ الۡقٰعِدِیۡنَ »\nTranslation: When a Surah is revealed [that says], 'Believe in Allah and strive along with His Messenger,' the affluent among them ask your permission [to stay back] and say, 'Leave us to be with those who sit [at home].'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1133,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "War",
      "hw": "جنگ",
      "s": "« » means to set out with the intention of fighting an enemy for the sake of Jihad (1 verse: 3:156)",
      "d": "« » means to set out with the intention of fighting an enemy. And a Ghazi is one who sets out with that intention. Its plurals are « » and « » (maf).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا لَا تَکُوۡنُوۡا کَالَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا وَ قَالُوۡا لِاِخۡوَانِہِمۡ اِذَا ضَرَبُوۡا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ اَوۡ کَانُوۡا غُزًّی لَّوۡ کَانُوۡا عِنۡدَنَا مَا مَاتُوۡا وَ مَا قُتِلُوۡا»\nTranslation: O you who have believed, do not be like those who disbelieved and said about their brothers when they traveled throughout the land or were fighting, 'If they had been with us, they would not have died or been killed.'"
    }
  ],
  "239": [
    {
      "id": 1134,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To give birth",
      "hw": "جننا",
      "s": "« » is used in the meaning of laying down a burden (19 verses: 3:36-3:96-4:102-7:157-18:49-21:47-22:2-24:58-24:60-35:11-39:69-41:47-46:15-47:4-55:7-55:10-65:4-65:6-94:2)",
      "d": "«وَضَعَ» «وَضَعْتُ الْحَمْل» «حَمَلَ» «وَضَعَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فَلَمَّا وَضَعَتۡہَا قَالَتۡ رَبِّ اِنِّیۡ وَضَعۡتُہَاۤ  اُنۡثٰی»\nTranslation: When she delivered her, she said, 'My Lord, I have delivered a female.'\nAt another place, the Divine Command states:\n«وَ تَضَعُ کُلُّ ذَاتِ حَمۡلٍ حَمۡلَہَا»\nTranslation: And every pregnant one will deliver her burden."
    },
    {
      "id": 1135,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To give birth",
      "hw": "جننا",
      "s": "« » is generally used for the purpose of having offspring (35 verses: 2:116-2:233-3:47-4:11-4:12-4:171-4:176-6:101-10:68-12:21-17:111-18:4-18:39-19:15-19:33-19:35-19:77-19:88-19:91-19:92-21:26-23:91-25:2-26:18-28:9-31:33-37:152-39:4-43:81-58:2-71:21-71:26-72:3-90:3-112:3)",
      "d": "«وَلَدَ» «وَلَدَ» «وَلَدَ الولد»\nFor example: In the Quran, Pharaoh, addressing Prophet Musa (AS), said:\n«قَالَ اَلَمۡ نُرَبِّکَ فِیۡنَا وَلِیۡدًا وَّ لَبِثۡتَ فِیۡنَا مِنۡ عُمُرِکَ سِنِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: Pharaoh said, 'Did we not raise you among us as a child? And you remained among us for years of your life.'"
    }
  ],
  "240": [
    {
      "id": 1136,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "To answer",
      "hw": "جواب",
      "s": "« » means to answer a question (2 verses: 5:109-28:65)",
      "d": "« » is the opposite of « ». « » means to ask a question or to request something. Similarly, « » also means to answer a question. And if something is requested, it also means to accept or give it. Here, the answer to a question is under discussion.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«یَوۡمَ یَجۡمَعُ اللّٰہُ الرُّسُلَ فَیَقُوۡلُ مَا ذَاۤ اُجِبۡتُمۡ»\nTranslation: The Day Allah will gather the messengers and say, 'What was the response [you received]?'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1137,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "to answer",
      "hw": "جواب",
      "s": "Responding to a letter with « » (98 verses: 2:18-2:28-2:196-2:210-2:245-2:281-3:55-3:72-3:83-3:109-5:48-5:105-6:36-6:60-6:108-6:164-7:150-7:168-7:174-8:44-9:83-9:94-9:122-10:4-10:23-10:46-10:56-10:70-11:4-11:34-11:123-12:46-12:50-12:62-12:63-12:81-19:40-20:40-20:86-20:89-20:91-21:13-21:35-21:58-21:64-21:95-22:76-23:99-23:115-24:28-24:64-27:28-27:35-27:37-28:39-28:70-28:88-29:8-29:17-29:57-30:11-30:41-31:15-31:23-32:11-32:12-32:21-33:13-34:31-35:4-36:22-36:31-36:50-36:67-36:83-37:68-39:7-39:44-40:77-41:21-41:50-43:28-43:48-43:85-45:15-46:27-50:3-56:87-57:5-57:13-60:10-63:8-67:3-67:4-86:8-86:11-89:28-96:8)",
      "d": "«رَجَعَ» «اَلْرَجْعُ» «اِذۡہَبۡ بِّکِتٰبِیۡ ہٰذَا فَاَلۡقِہۡ  اِلَیۡہِمۡ ثُمَّ تَوَلَّ عَنۡہِمۡ فَانۡظُرۡ  مَا ذَا یَرۡجِعُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1138,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "to answer",
      "hw": "جواب",
      "s": "Issuing a fatwa with « » for a difficult and complex issue. Giving a fatwa. (5 verses: 4:127-4:176-12:43-12:46-27:32)",
      "d": "«اَفْتٰی» «فتوٰی» «اِسْتِفْتَاء» «یَسۡتَفۡتُوۡنَکَ ؕ قُلِ اللّٰہُ یُفۡتِیۡکُمۡ فِی الۡکَلٰلَۃِ»"
    }
  ],
