      "hw": "دھواں",
      "s": "« » means smoke (2 verses: 41:11, 44:10)",
      "d": "«دُخَان» «دُخَان» «ثُمَّ  اسۡتَوٰۤی  اِلَی السَّمَآءِ وَ ہِیَ دُخَانٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1546,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Smoke",
      "hw": "دھواں",
      "s": "« » refers to smoke with a copper-like color (1 verse: 55:35)",
      "d": "«نُحَاس» «یُرۡسَلُ عَلَیۡکُمَا شُوَاظٌ مِّنۡ نَّارٍ ۙ وَّ نُحَاسٌ فَلَا  تَنۡتَصِرٰنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1547,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Smoke",
      "hw": "دھواں",
      "s": "« » refers to thick, black smoke (1 verse: 56:43)",
      "d": "«حَمَّ» «حُمَّۃ» «یَحْمُوْم» «فِیۡ  سَمُوۡمٍ  وَّ  حَمِیۡمٍ وَّ ظِلٍّ  مِّنۡ  یَّحۡمُوۡمٍ»"
    }
  ],
  "336": [
    {
      "id": 1548,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Sunlight",
      "hw": "دھوپ",
      "s": "« » means sun and is also used for sunlight (32 verses: 2:258, 6:78, 6:96, 7:54, 10:5, 12:4, 13:2, 14:33, 16:12, 17:78, 18:17, 18:86, 18:90, 20:130, 21:33, 22:18, 25:45, 27:24, 29:61, 31:29, 35:13, 36:38, 36:40, 39:5, 41:37, 50:39, 55:5, 71:16, 75:9, 76:13, 81:1, 91:1)",
      "d": "«شَمْس» «شَمَسَ یَوْمُنَا» «شَمَّسَ» «شَمْس» «لَا یَرَوۡنَ فِیۡہَا شَمۡسًا وَّ  لَا  زَمۡہَرِیۡرًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1549,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Sunlight",
      "hw": "دھوپ",
      "s": "« » means the sunlight of the forenoon (7 verses: 7:98, 20:59, 20:119, 79:29, 79:46, 91:1, 93:1)",
      "d": "«ضُحٰی» «وَ اَغۡطَشَ لَیۡلَہَا وَ اَخۡرَجَ ضُحٰہَا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1550,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Sunlight",
      "hw": "دھوپ",
      "s": "« » means the intense midday sunlight (2 verses: 9:81, 16:81)",
      "d": "«حَرَّ» «حَرَارَت» «حَرّ» «وَ قَالُوۡا لَا تَنۡفِرُوۡا فِی الۡحَرِّ ؕ قُلۡ نَارُ جَہَنَّمَ اَشَدُّ حَرًّا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1551,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Sunlight",
      "hw": "دھوپ",
      "s": "« » refers to heat waves arising from intense sunlight (1 verse: 35:21)",
      "d": "«حَرُوْر» «ظَلّ» «حَرُوْر» «وَ لَا الظُّلُمٰتُ وَ لَا  النُّوۡرُ وَ لَا الظِّلُّ  وَ لَا  الۡحَرُوۡرُ»"
    }
  ],
  "337": [
    {
      "id": 1552,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To Deceive",
      "hw": "دھوکا",
      "s": "« » means to deceive by taking advantage of someone's negligence (21 verses: 3:24-3:185-3:196-4:120-6:70-6:112-6:130-7:22-7:51-8:49-17:64-31:33-33:12-35:5-35:40-40:4-45:35-57:14-57:20-67:20-82:6)",
      "d": "«غَرَّ» «غُرُوْر» «مَتَاعُ الْغُرُوْر» «اَبَاطِیْلُ الدُّنْیَا» «غُرُوْر» «غَرُوْر» «غُرُوْر» «وَ غَرَّتۡکُمُ الۡاَمَانِیُّ حَتّٰی جَآءَ  اَمۡرُ اللّٰہِ  وَ غَرَّکُمۡ بِاللّٰہِ الۡغَرُوۡرُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1553,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Deception",
      "hw": "دھوکا",
      "s": "« » means to hide the truth to achieve one's objective and deceive the opponent (3 verses: 2:9-4:142-8:62)",
      "d": "«خَدَعَ» «طَرِیْقَ الْخُدُوٌع» «خُدْعَۃٌ»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«یُخٰدِعُوۡنَ اللّٰہَ وَ الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا ۚ وَ مَا یَخۡدَعُوۡنَ  اِلَّاۤ  اَنۡفُسَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: The hypocrites seek to deceive Allah and the believers, but in reality, they deceive only themselves."
    },
    {
      "id": 1554,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Deception",
      "hw": "دھوکا",
      "s": "« » means to secretly breach a covenant, trust, or commit treachery in religion (8 verses: 4:105-5:13-8:27-8:58-8:71-12:52-40:19-66:10)",
      "d": "« » means to secretly break a covenant. And this word is specific for covenant, trust, and hypocrisy (treachery in religion) (Muf). And « » is the intensive form meaning a great deceiver, a major traitor.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ  اِمَّا  تَخَافَنَّ مِنۡ قَوۡمٍ خِیَانَۃً  فَانۡۢبِذۡ اِلَیۡہِمۡ عَلٰی سَوَآءٍ ؕ اِنَّ اللّٰہَ  لَا یُحِبُّ الۡخَآئِنِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And if you fear treachery from a people, then throw back their covenant to them on equal terms. Indeed, Allah does not like the treacherous."
    },
    {
      "id": 1555,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Deception",
      "hw": "دھوکا",
      "s": "« » means to deceive a friend when the time comes (3 verses: 3:160-17:22-25:29)",
      "d": "« » refers to one who verbally professes friendship but betrays when needed (see details under 'friend')."
    },
    {
      "id": 1557,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Deception",
      "hw": "دھوکا",
      "s": "« » means to act treacherously in a bad way and continuously (1 verse: 31:32)",
      "d": "« » means to act treacherously in a vile manner. And « » means to be weak, to be sluggish (Munjid). According to Imam Raghib, « » is such treachery done with so much effort that a person becomes weak and their limbs become limp (Muf), i.e., to continue deceiving and acting treacherously.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ مَا یَجۡحَدُ بِاٰیٰتِنَاۤ  اِلَّا  کُلُّ  خَتَّارٍ  کَفُوۡرٍ»\nTranslation: And none deny Our signs except every treacherous ingrate."
    }
  ],
  "338": [
    {
      "id": 1558,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Seeing",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "« » is used for contemplating something (56 verses: 3:143-4:61-6:40-6:46-6:47-6:68-10:50-10:59-11:28-11:63-11:88-12:4-17:62-18:63-19:77-20:92-21:36-25:43-26:75-26:205-27:10-27:40-28:31-28:71-28:72-33:19-35:8-35:40-39:37:55-38-41:52-45:23-46:4-46:10-47:20-53:13-53:19-53:33-56:58-56:63-56:68-56:71-59:21-63:4-63:5-67:28-67:30-76:19-76:20-81:23-96:7-96:9-96:11-96:13-107:1-110:2)",
      "d": "« » means to perceive something, to see, whether through eyesight or through contemplation, intellect, insight, or imagination and thought. Its usage is general, whether in a state of wakefulness or in a dream, and it means the final look. To see with contemplation and reflection. To perceive something with the eyes.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«اِنِّیۡ  رَاَیۡتُ اَحَدَعَشَرَ کَوۡکَبًا»\nTranslation: I saw eleven stars.\nAnd to contemplate and reflect on something to perceive it.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«اَرَءَیۡتَ  الَّذِیۡ یُکَذِّبُ بِالدِّیۡنِ»\nTranslation: Have you seen the one who denies the Recompense?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1559,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Seeing",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "« » is generally used for looking (102 verses: 2:50-2:55-2:104-2:162-2:210-2:259-2:280-3:77-3:88-3:137-3:143-4:46-4:50-5:75-6:8-6:11-6:24-6:46-6:65-6:99-6:158-7:14-7:15-7:53-7:84-7:86-7:103-7:129-7:143-7:185-7:195-7:198-8:6-9:127-10:14-10:39-10:43-10:71-10:73-10:101-11:55-12:109-15:8-15:36-15:37-16:33-16:36-16:85-17:21-17:48-18:19-20:97-21:40-22:15-25:9-26:203-27:14-27:27-27:28-27:33-27:41-27:51-27:69-28:40-29:20-30:9-30:42-30:50-32:29-33:19-35:43-35:44-36:49-37:19-37:73-37:88-37:102-38:15-38:79-38:80-39:68-40:21-40:82-42:45-43:25-43:66-44:29-47:10-47:18-47:20-50:6-51:44-56:84-57:13-59:18-74:21-78:40-80:24-83:23-83:35-86:5-88:17)",
      "d": "« » means to look, to see, so that something becomes visible, whether that thing is seen or not. Its usage is also in both ways.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ  اِذَا مَاۤ  اُنۡزِلَتۡ سُوۡرَۃٌ  نَّظَرَ  بَعۡضُہُمۡ اِلٰی بَعۡضٍ»\nTranslation: And whenever a surah is revealed, some of them look at others.\nAt another place, the Divine command says:\n«فَانۡظُرِیۡ مَاذَا تَاۡمُرِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: Then see what you will command.\nHowever, the usage of 'nazar' generally pertains to seeing with the eyes."
    },
    {
      "id": 1562,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Seeing",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "« » is used for going to see something or to visit (1 verse: 102:2)",
      "d": "«زَارَہٗ» «زَوْر» «زُرۡتُ فَلَانًا»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«اَلۡہٰکُمُ  التَّکَاثُرُ حَتّٰی زُرۡتُمُ  الۡمَقَابِرَ»\nTranslation: You are preoccupied with rivalry in worldly increase until you visit the graves."
    },
    {
      "id": 1563,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Seeing (Quality of Sight)",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "« » means the eyes becoming fixed (2 verses: 14:42-21:97)",
      "d": "« » means for the eyes to become fixed, to lose light, and not to blink (F. L. 103).\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ اقۡتَرَبَ الۡوَعۡدُ الۡحَقُّ فَاِذَا ہِیَ شَاخِصَۃٌ  اَبۡصَارُ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا»\nTranslation: And the true promise will approach, then behold, the sights of the disbelievers will be fixed."
    },
    {
      "id": 1564,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Seeing (Quality of Sight)",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "« » means the blinking of the eye (2 verses: 16:77-54:50)",
      "d": "« » means the swiftness of a glance. To look quickly at something. The blinking of the eye (F. L. 102).\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ مَاۤ اَمۡرُ السَّاعَۃِ  اِلَّا کَلَمۡحِ الۡبَصَرِ اَوۡ ہُوَ اَقۡرَبُ»\nTranslation: And the coming of the Hour is no more than the blink of an eye or even quicker."
    },
    {
      "id": 1565,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Seeing (Quality of Sight)",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "« » means to look with fixed gaze while running (3 verses: 14:43-54:8-70:36)",
      "d": "« » means to look with fixed gaze while running.\n«مُہۡطِعِیۡنَ مُقۡنِعِیۡ رُءُوۡسِہِمۡ لَا یَرۡتَدُّ اِلَیۡہِمۡ  طَرۡفُہُمۡ»\nTranslation: People will be running with their heads raised, their glances not returning to them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1568,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To see (quality of sight)",
      "hw": "دیکھنا",
      "s": "«زَاغَ البَصَر»",
      "d": "«زَاغَ البَصَر» «زَاغَ الْبَصَرُ» «مَا زَاغَ الۡبَصَرُ وَ مَا طَغٰی»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1571,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To show",
      "hw": "دکھلانا",
      "s": "« »: to show in such a way that another recognizes (1 verse: 70:11)",
      "d": "«بَصَّرَ» «وَ لَا یَسۡئَلُ حَمِیۡمٌ حَمِیۡمًا یُّبَصَّرُوۡنَہُمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "340": [
    {
      "id": 1574,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Religion (Sharia)",
      "hw": "دین",
      "s": "« »: those divine commands that change according to the needs of the time (4 verses: 5:48-42:13-42:21-45:48)",
      "d": "«شَرَعَ» «شَرِیْعَۃ» «اَلْاَنْبِیَاءُ اِخْوَۃُ الْعَلَّاتِ أُمَّھَاتُھُمْ شَتّٰی وَ دِیْنُھُمْ وَاحِدٌ» «شَرَعَ لَکُمۡ مِّنَ الدِّیۡنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1575,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Religion (Millat)",
      "hw": "دین",
      "s": "« »: that system which a prophet establishes among his followers (adherents) by enforcing divine commands (15 verses: 2:120-2:130-2:135-3:95-4:125-6:161-7:88-7:89-12:37-12:38-14:13-16:123-18:20-22:78-38:7)",
      "d": "«فَاتَّبِعُوۡا مِلَّۃَ اِبۡرٰہِیۡمَ حَنِیۡفًا»"
    }
  ],
  "341": [
    {
      "id": 1576,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To give",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« »: to give something to someone (150 verses: 2:43-2:53-2:63-2:83-2:87-2:93-2:110-2:121-2:146-2:177-2:200-2:201-2:211-2:229-2:233-2:251-2:253-2:258-2:265-2:277-3:81-3:148-3:170-3:180-3:194-4:2-4:4-4:19-4:20-4:24-4:25-4:33-4:37-4:54-4:67-4:77-4:153-4:163-5:5-5:12-5:20-5:46-5:48-6:20-6:83-6:89-6:114-6:141-6:154-6:165-7:38-7:144-7:171-7:175-7:189-7:190-9:5-9:11-9:18-9:59-9:75-9:76-10:88-11:28-11:63-11:110-12:22-12:31-12:66-12:101-13:36-14:34-15:81-15:87-16:55-16:122-17:2-17:26-17:55-17:59-17:101-18:10-18:33-18:62-18:65-18:84-18:96-19:12-19:30-20:99-21:48-21:51-21:74-21:79-21:84-22:41-22:78-23:49-23:60-24:33-24:56-25:35-27:7-27:15-27:36-27:39-27:40-28:14-28:29-28:43-28:52-28:76-28:77-29:27-29:47-29:66-30:34-30:38-30:39-31:12-32:13-32:23-33:33-33:50-33:51-33:68-34:10-34:44-34:45-35:40-37:117-38:20-40:53-41:45-43:21-44:33-45:16-45:17-47:17-51:16-52:18-57:23-57:27-58:13-59:7-60:10-60:11-65:6-65:7-73:20)",
      "d": "«اٰتٰی» «وَ اٰتَی الۡمَالَ عَلٰی حُبِّہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1577,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To give",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« »: to give as a reward, favor, or in return for service and obedience (11 verses: 9:29-9:58-11:108-17:20-20:50-38:39-53:34-78:36-92:5-93:5-108:1)",
      "d": "«اَعْطٰی» «قَالَ رَبُّنَا الَّذِیۡۤ اَعۡطٰی کُلَّ شَیۡءٍ خَلۡقَہٗ ثُمَّ ہَدٰی» «اَعْطٰی» «اَعْطٰی» «وَ اَمَّا الَّذِیۡنَ سُعِدُوۡا فَفِی الۡجَنَّۃِ خٰلِدِیۡنَ فِیۡہَا مَا دَامَتِ السَّمٰوٰتُ وَ الۡاَرۡضُ اِلَّا مَا شَآءَ رَبُّکَ ؕ عَطَآءً غَیۡرَ مَجۡذُوۡذٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1578,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To give",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« »: to pay rights and settle financial transactions (2 verses: 2:178-2:283)",
      "d": "«اَدَاءٌ» «فَاِنۡ اَمِنَ بَعۡضُکُمۡ بَعۡضًا فَلۡیُؤَدِّ الَّذِی اؤۡتُمِنَ اَمَانَتَہٗ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1580,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To give",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« »: more general than « »; to give a reward greater than the actual compensation for any deed (3 verses: 3:153-5:85-48:18)",
      "d": "«اَثَابَ» «اَعْطٰی» «اَعْطٰی» «فَاَثَابَہُمُ اللّٰہُ بِمَا قَالُوۡا جَنّٰتٍ تَجۡرِیۡ مِنۡ تَحۡتِہَا الۡاَنۡہٰرُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1581,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To give",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« »: to give without compensation and not expecting any return or benefit later (21 verses: 3:8-3:38-6:84-14:39-19:5-19:19-19:49-19:50-19:53-21:72-21:90-25:74-26:21-26:83-29:27-33:50-37:100-38:30-38:35-38:43-42:49)",
      "d": "«وَھْبَ» «یَہَبُ لِمَنۡ یَّشَآءُ اِنَاثًا وَّ یَہَبُ لِمَنۡ یَّشَآءُ الذُّکُوۡرَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1582,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "To give",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« »: to give aid, stipend, or support to a poor and needy person (1 verse: 11:99)",
      "d": "«رَفَدَ» «رَفَادَہ» «اَرْفَدَ» «رَفَدَ» «وَ اُتۡبِعُوۡا فِیۡ ہٰذِہٖ لَعۡنَۃً وَّ یَوۡمَ الۡقِیٰمَۃِ ؕ بِئۡسَ الرِّفۡدُ الۡمَرۡفُوۡدُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1584,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Gift",
      "hw": "دینا",
      "s": "« » Giving gifts and presents to strengthen relationships (1 verse: 27:35)",
      "d": "« » refers to those gifts which we present to each other to strengthen relationships. And « » refers to the thing in which the gift is placed.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَمَاۤ  اٰتٰىنِۦَ اللّٰہُ خَیۡرٌ  مِّمَّاۤ   اٰتٰىکُمۡ  ۚ بَلۡ  اَنۡتُمۡ  بِہَدِیَّتِکُمۡ  تَفۡرَحُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: (Prophet Solomon PBUH said) What Allah has given me is better than what you have given, so remain happy with your gift."
    }
  ],
  "342": [
    {
      "id": 1586,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Wall",
      "hw": "دیوار",
      "s": "« » A wall of a building or enclosure (3 verses: 18:77-18:82-59:14)",
      "d": "«جِدَار» «جُدُر» «جُدْرَان» «جِدَار» «جَدَرَ» «ھُوَ الْحَائِطُ»\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَ اَمَّا الۡجِدَارُ فَکَانَ لِغُلٰمَیۡنِ یَتِیۡمَیۡنِ فِی الۡمَدِیۡنَۃِ»\nTranslation: And as for the wall, it belonged to two orphaned boys in the city."
    },
    {
      "id": 1587,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Wall",
      "hw": "دیوار",
      "s": "« » A barrier or wall built between two things that serves as an obstruction (3 verses: 18:93-18:94-36:9)",
      "d": "« » means obstruction. A barrier. A large wall built between two things that serves as an obstruction and is constructed. And if this wall or barrier is natural, it is called « » (muf) and « » means to seal a crack with stones. And « » refers to the method with which crevices, holes, or cracks are filled, and « » in the terminology of physicians refers to the lodging of corrupt matter in the intestines.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَہَلۡ نَجۡعَلُ لَکَ خَرۡجًا عَلٰۤی اَنۡ  تَجۡعَلَ بَیۡنَنَا وَ  بَیۡنَہُمۡ  سَدًّا»\nTranslation: (O Dhul-Qarnayn!) Should we collect some money for you so that you build a barrier between us and them?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1588,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Wall",
      "hw": "دیوار",
      "s": "« » A wall or barrier whose all holes and cracks are sealed (1 verse: 18:95)",
      "d": "«رَدْم» «سَدّ» «رَدَمَ» «رَدْمَ الثَّوْب»\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَاَعِیۡنُوۡنِیۡ بِقُوَّۃٍ  اَجۡعَلۡ بَیۡنَکُمۡ وَ بَیۡنَہُمۡ  رَدۡمًا»\nTranslation: (Dhul-Qarnayn replied) Give me strength from your manpower so that I may build a strong barrier between you and them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1589,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Wall",
      "hw": "دیوار",
      "s": "« » A high wall of a fortress or enclosure that cannot be scaled (2 verses: 38:21-57:13)",
      "d": "«سُوْر» «یَدُلُّ عَلٰی عُلُوِّ وَ اِرْتِفَاعِ (م ۔ ل)» «سُوْرَۃ اَلْمَدِیْنَۃ»\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَضُرِبَ بَیۡنَہُمۡ بِسُوۡرٍ لَّہٗ  بَابٌ»\nTranslation: So a wall will be placed between them, having a gate."
    },
    {
      "id": 1590,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Wall",
      "hw": "دیوار",
      "s": "« » A wall or structure whose parts are firmly interlocked and rooted (6 verses: 9:109-9:110-16:26-18:21-37:97-61:4)",
      "d": "« » means to build. To construct a building, such that all its parts are interlocked. And « » refers to any construction that fulfills this condition, whether it is just a foundation, a wall, or a complete building.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«اِنَّ اللّٰہَ یُحِبُّ الَّذِیۡنَ یُقَاتِلُوۡنَ فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِہٖ  صَفًّا کَاَنَّہُمۡ  بُنۡیَانٌ  مَّرۡصُوۡصٌ»\nTranslation: Allah loves those who fight in His cause in ranks, as if they were a wall cemented firmly."
    }
  ],
  "343": [
    {
      "id": 1592,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Madness. Insanity",
      "hw": "دیوانہ",
      "s": "« » Impairment and deficiency in intellect, which is temporary (1 verse: 2:275)",
      "d": "« » means to beat someone until they lose consciousness (muf). And « » means mentally impaired (i.e., a person whose intellect has been impaired). That is, whose intellect does not function properly. According to Arabs, this was also due to jinn and devils.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«اَلَّذِیۡنَ یَاۡکُلُوۡنَ الرِّبٰوا لَا یَقُوۡمُوۡنَ اِلَّا کَمَا یَقُوۡمُ الَّذِیۡ یَتَخَبَّطُہُ الشَّیۡطٰنُ مِنَ الۡمَسِّ»\nTranslation: Those who consume usury will not stand except as one stands who is driven to madness by the touch of the devil.\nThe difference between « » and « » is that « » is a temporary illness, while « » is long-term."
    },
    {
      "id": 1593,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Madness. Insanity",
      "hw": "دیوانہ",
      "s": "« » Madness caused by events of the time (1 verse: 68:6)",
      "d": "« » means to entice into temptation. To allure, incline, and cause amazement. And « » means mad and insane (manjad). And « » refers to such a mad person whom events of time have made mentally impaired and unconscious.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَسَتُبۡصِرُ وَ یُبۡصِرُوۡنَ بِاَىیِّکُمُ  الۡمَفۡتُوۡنُ»\nTranslation: So you will see and they will see which of you is insane."
    },
    {
      "id": 1594,
      "a": "د",
      "h": "Madness. Insanity",
      "hw": "دیوانہ",
      "s": "« » Impairment resulting from immediate agitation of nature (2 verses: 54:24-54:47)",
      "d": "«سَعَرَ» «اِسْتَعَرَّ الِلصَّوْص» «اِسْتَعَرَّ الْحَرَب» «مِسْعَرْ» «سُعُر»\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَقَالُوۡۤا اَبَشَرًا مِّنَّا وَاحِدًا نَّتَّبِعُہٗۤ ۙ اِنَّاۤ  اِذًا  لَّفِیۡ ضَلٰلٍ  وَّ  سُعُرٍ»\nTranslation: They said, 'Shall we follow a human being from among ourselves? Then indeed we would be in error and madness.'"
    }
  ],
  "344": [
    {
      "id": 1595,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To throw",
      "hw": "ڈالنا",
      "s": "« » To throw, cast, or place something in such a way that others can see it (66 verses: 2:37-3:44-4:90-4:91-4:94-4:171-5:64-7:115-7:107-7:116-7:117-7:120-7:150-8:12-10:80-10:81-12:10-12:93-12:96-15:19-16:15-16:28-16:86-16:87-17:39-20:20-20:39-20:65-20:66-20:69-20:70-20:87-22:52-22:53-25:8-25:13-26:32-26:43-26:44-26:45-26:46-26:223-27:6-27:10-27:28-27:29-28:7-28:31-28:86-31:10-37:97-38:34-40:15-41:35-41:40-43:53-50:7-50:24-50:26-50:37-54:25-60:1-67:7-67:8-75:15-84:4)",
      "d": "« » means for two opposing things to meet face to face. To meet. But in the chapter of verbs, the basic meanings change. « » means to throw, cast, or place something in such a way that others can see it (muf).\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«فَاَلۡقٰی عَصَاہُ  فَاِذَا ہِیَ ثُعۡبَانٌ  مُّبِیۡنٌ»\nTranslation: So he threw his staff, and at once it was a clear serpent.\nAnd « » is also used metaphorically.\nFor example, the divine command says:\n«وَ اَلۡقَیۡتُ عَلَیۡکَ مَحَبَّۃً مِّنِّیۡ»\nTranslation: And I have cast upon you love from Me.\nThen this word is also used for 'implanting a thought in the heart', and it is called « ». This discussion is in 'implanting a thought in the heart'."
    },
    {
      "id": 1596,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Throw",
      "hw": "ڈالنا",
      "s": "« » to throw one thing into another, to insert (12 verses: 15:12-16:69-20:53-23:27-26:200-28:32-39:21-69:32-71:20-72:17-72:27-74:42)",
      "d": "The discussion of « » has passed under 'to insert'. Its basic meaning is to draw one thing into another or to place one thing into another. In this sense, this word sometimes means 'to throw'.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«اُسۡلُکۡ یَدَکَ فِیۡ جَیۡبِکَ»\nTranslation: Put your hand into your bosom."
    },
    {
      "id": 1597,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Throw",
      "hw": "ڈالنا",
      "s": "« » to throw something behind without considering it worthy of attention (10 verses: 2:100-2:101-3:187-8:58-20:96-28:40-37:145-51:40-68:49-104:4)",
      "d": "The basic meanings of « » are to throw something without considering it worthy of attention or to throw it behind (see this discussion in 'to throw'). Like « », its translation is sometimes also 'to throw'.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«فَنَبَذۡنٰہُ  بِالۡعَرَآءِ  وَ  ہُوَ  سَقِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: So We threw him onto the barren ground while he was sick."
    },
    {
      "id": 1598,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Throw",
      "hw": "ڈالنا",
      "s": "« » to throw or to throw with force and intensity (8 verses: 20:39-20:87-21:18-33:26-34:48-34:53-37:8-59:2)",
      "d": "« » means to throw from a distance (see this discussion in 'to throw'), but in some places its translation is also done as 'to throw'.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ قَذَفَ فِیۡ  قُلُوۡبِہِمُ  الرُّعۡبَ»\nTranslation: And Allah has cast terror into their hearts."
    },
    {
      "id": 1599,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Throw",
      "hw": "ڈالنا",
      "s": "« » to throw or pour in such a manner as water is poured slowly from a jug (3 verses: 2:250-7:126-18:96)",
      "d": "«فَرَغَ» «شَغَل» «اَفْرَغَ الدَّلْو»\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«رَبَّنَاۤ  اَفۡرِغۡ عَلَیۡنَا صَبۡرًا وَّ ثَبِّتۡ اَقۡدَامَنَا»\nTranslation: Our Lord! Pour upon us patience and plant our feet firmly.\nAt another place, the divine command is:\n«قَالَ اٰتُوۡنِیۡۤ  اُفۡرِغۡ عَلَیۡہِ قِطۡرًا»\nTranslation: He (Dhul-Qarnayn) said, 'Bring me blocks of iron.' Then when he filled the valley between the two mountain walls, he said, 'Blow (upon it),' until when he made it fire, he said, 'Bring me molten copper to pour over it.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1600,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Throw",
      "hw": "ڈالنا",
      "s": "« » to throw something and then make it settle (19 verses: 4:100-5:91-7:71-7:118-7:134-7:171-10:51-18:53-27:82-27:85-42:22-51:6-52:7-56:1-56:2-56:75-69:15-70:1-77:7)",
      "d": "The basic meanings of « » are two: (1) to be established, (2) to fall down (masc.). And « » means to cause to happen, i.e., to throw something and then make it settle (majd).\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«اِنَّمَا یُرِیۡدُ الشَّیۡطٰنُ اَنۡ  یُّوۡقِعَ  بَیۡنَکُمُ الۡعَدَاوَۃَ  وَ الۡبَغۡضَآءَ»\nTranslation: Satan only wants to cause between you animosity and hatred."
    }
  ],
  "346": [
    {
      "id": 1603,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to fear an upcoming danger (105 verses: 2:38-2:62-2:112-2:155-2:182-2:229-2:239-2:262-2:274-2:277-3:170-3:175-4:3-4:9-4:34-4:35-4:83-4:101-4:128-5:23-5:28-5:54-5:69-5:94-5:108-6:15-6:48-6:51-6:80-6:81-7:35-7:49-7:56-7:59-8:26-8:48-8:58-9:28-10:15-10:62-10:83-11:3-11:26-11:70-11:84-11:103-12:13-13:12-13:21-14:14-16:47-16:50-16:112-17:57-17:60-19:5-19:45-20:21-20:45-20:46-20:68-20:77-20:112-24:37-24:50-24:55-26:12-26:14-26:21-26:135-27:10-28:7-28:25-28:31-28:33-28:34-29:33-30:24-30:28-32:16-33:19-38:22-39:13-39:16-39:36-40:26-40:30-40:32-41:30-43:68-46:13-46:21-48:27-50:45-51:28-51:37-55:46-59:16-72:13-74:53-76:7-76:10-79:40-91:15-106:4)",
      "d": "« » means to apprehend an upcoming danger based on evidence and signs (masc.). Its opposite is security. That is, « » generally relates to the future.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«قَالُوۡا لَا تَخَفۡ  اِنَّاۤ  اُرۡسِلۡنَاۤ  اِلٰی  قَوۡمِ  لُوۡطٍ»\nTranslation: They said, 'Fear not. Indeed, we have been sent to the people of Lot.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1604,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to fear due to the greatness of something (13 verses: 2:74-4:25-4:77-17:31-17:100-18:80-20:94-21:28-23:57-36:11-50:33-59:21-98:8)",
      "d": "« » is such a fear that befalls the heart due to someone's greatness (masc.).\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ لَا تَقۡتُلُوۡۤا  اَوۡلَادَکُمۡ  خَشۡیَۃَ  اِمۡلَاقٍ»\nTranslation: And do not kill your children for fear of poverty."
    },
    {
      "id": 1605,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » such a fear whose effect also falls on limbs and organs (15 verses: 2:45-3:199-20:108-21:90-23:2-33:35-41:39-42:45-54:7-57:16-59:21-68:43-70:44-79:9-88:2)",
      "d": "« » refers to such fear whose effects become apparent on limbs and organs besides the heart. The heart becoming soft (masc.). Therefore, this word is also used for 'limbs'.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«خَاشِعَۃً  اَبۡصَارُہُمۡ»\nTranslation: Their eyes will be humbled.\nAt another place, the divine command is:\n«وُجُوۡہٌ  یَّوۡمَئِذٍ خَاشِعَۃٌ»\nTranslation: Faces on that Day will be humbled.\nAt another place, the divine command is:\n«وَ خَشَعَتِ الۡاَصۡوَاتُ»\nTranslation: And voices will be lowered.\nAt another place, the divine command is:\n«اَلَمۡ یَاۡنِ  لِلَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡۤا  اَنۡ  تَخۡشَعَ قُلُوۡبُہُمۡ  لِذِکۡرِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: Has the time not come for those who have believed that their hearts should become humble for the remembrance of Allah?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1606,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to avoid sins due to fear of consequences (223 verses: 2:2-2:21-2:24-2:41-2:48-2:63-2:66-2:103-2:123-2:177-2:179-2:180-2:183-2:187-2:189-2:194-2:196-2:197-2:203-2:206-2:212-2:223-2:224-2:231-2:233-2:237-2:241-2:278-2:281-2:282-2:283-3:15-3:28-3:50-3:76-3:102-3:115-3:120-3:123-3:125-3:130-3:131-3:133-3:138-3:172-3:179-3:186-3:198-3:200-4:1-4:9-4:77-4:128-4:129-4:131-5:2-5:4-5:7-5:8-5:11-5:27-5:35-5:46-5:57-5:65-5:88-5:93-5:96-5:100-5:108-5:112-6:32-6:51-6:69-6:72-6:153-6:155-7:26-7:35-7:63-7:65-7:96-7:128-7:156-7:164-7:169-7:171-7:201-8:1-8:25-8:29-8:34-8:56-8:69-9:4-9:7-9:36-9:44-9:108-9:109-9:115-9:119-9:123-10:6-10:31-10:63-11:49-11:78-12:57-12:90-12:109-13:35-15:45-15:69-16:2-16:30-16:31-16:52-16:81-16:128-19:13-19:18-19:63-19:72-19:85-19:97-20:113-20:132-21:48-22:1-22:32-22:37-23:23-23:32-23:52-23:87-24:34-24:52-25:15-25:74-26:11-26:90-26:106-26:108-26:110-26:124-26:126-26:131-26:132-26:142-26:144-26:150-26:161-26:163-26:177-26:179-26:184-27:53-28:83-29:16-30:31-31:33-33:1-33:32-33:37-33:55-33:70-36:45-37:124-38:28-38:49-39:10-39:16-39:20-39:24-39:28-39:33-39:57-39:61-39:73-40:9-41:18-43:35-43:63-43:67-44:51-45:19-47:15-47:17-47:36-48:26-49:1-49:3-49:10-49:12-49:13-50:31-51:15-52:17-53:32-54:54-57:28-58:9-59:7-59:18-60:11-64:16-65:1-65:2-65:4-65:5-65:10-68:34-69:48-71:3-73:17-74:56-77:41-78:31-91:8-92:5-92:17-96:12)",
      "d": "« » means to fear the outcomes of one's actions. Inclining the nature towards avoiding sins and doing good deeds (masc.). To keep in mind Allah's commands and prohibitions (i.e., what He has commanded and what He has forbidden) out of His fear (majd). Its opposite is « ». And « » means to try to avoid sins by fearing their consequences. To adopt piety.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n« کَذٰلِکَ یُبَیِّنُ اللّٰہُ  اٰیٰتِہٖ لِلنَّاسِ لَعَلَّہُمۡ  یَتَّقُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: Thus does Allah make clear His verses to the people so that they may become pious (fear and avoid)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1608,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To Fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to be astonished, to fear from a fictitious and imaginary danger (1 verse: 11:74)",
      "d": "«رَاعَ» «رَوْعَ» «رَعْتُہٗ» «نَاقَۃٌ رَوْعَاء» «اَلرَّوْع»\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«فَلَمَّا ذَہَبَ عَنۡ اِبۡرٰہِیۡمَ الرَّوۡعُ»\nTranslation: Then when the fear left Abraham."
    },
    {
      "id": 1609,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to fear in the heart and attempt to conceal it (3 verses: 11:70-20:67-51:28)",
      "d": "« » means to be concealed (of the ear) to perceive a sound. To feel fear from something heard (Manjad). And « » means to try to hide one's fear. And not allowing signs of fear to appear on the face.\n«فَلَمَّا رَاٰۤ  اَیۡدِیَہُمۡ لَا تَصِلُ  اِلَیۡہِ  نَکِرَہُمۡ وَ اَوۡجَسَ مِنۡہُمۡ خِیۡفَۃً»\nTranslation: When (Prophet Ibrahim ﷺ saw that their hands did not reach towards it, he disliked them and concealed his fear from them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1610,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » the heart beating due to fear, anxiety and restlessness (1 verse: 79:8)",
      "d": "« » means to be restless, anxious, and agitated. The heart beating. And it means to fall due to fear (Manjad). In « », two things are found: restlessness and fear. And from these, the heart starts beating.\n«قُلُوۡبٌ یَّوۡمَئِذٍ وَّاجِفَۃٌ»\nTranslation: On that day, (people's) hearts will be fearful (Jalandhari). Beating hearts. (Osmani)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1611,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to feel fear in the heart due to one's shortcomings and to be restless (5 verses: 8:2-15:52-15:53-22:35-23:60)",
      "d": "« » means to feel fear in the heart (Muf) and means to have one's hair stand on end (M. Q.). To increase in fear. To become old (Manjad). And it means to fear someone due to one's shortcomings and to be restless (Faq. L 202).\n«اِنَّمَا الۡمُؤۡمِنُوۡنَ الَّذِیۡنَ اِذَا ذُکِرَ اللّٰہُ وَجِلَتۡ قُلُوۡبُہُمۡ»\nTranslation: The believers are only those who, when Allah is mentioned, their hearts fear (become fearful)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1612,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » a fear that includes caution and anxiety and is prolonged (8 verses: 2:40-7:116-7:154-8:60-16:51-21:90-28:32-59:13)",
      "d": "«رَھَبَ» «رَغِبَ» «رَاہِبْ» «رَھْبَاِنیَۃ» «طول الخوف و استمرارہ»\n«اِنَّہُمۡ کَانُوۡا یُسٰرِعُوۡنَ فِی الۡخَیۡرٰتِ وَ یَدۡعُوۡنَنَا رَغَبًا وَّ رَہَبًا»\nTranslation: They used to hasten towards good deeds and call upon Us with hope and fear."
    },
    {
      "id": 1613,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » intensity of fear and terror (5 verses: 3:151-8:12-18:18-33:26-59:2)",
      "d": "« » means the intensity of fear, terror. And « » means to be filled with fear (Muf), to shrink due to someone's fear.\n«لَوِ اطَّلَعۡتَ عَلَیۡہِمۡ لَوَلَّیۡتَ مِنۡہِمۡ فِرَارًا  وَّ  لَمُلِئۡتَ مِنۡہِمۡ  رُعۡبًا»\nTranslation: If you could see them, you would turn away from them in flight and be filled with terror from them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1614,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to fear",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to fear for someone's well-being along with hoping for their good, mixed feelings of fear and mercy (10 verses: 18:49-21:28-21:49-23:57-33:72-42:18-42:22-52:26-58:13-70:27)",
      "d": "«شَفِقَ عَلٰی» «اَشْفَقَ» «شَفَقَۃ» «اَشْفَقَ مِنْہُ»\n«وَ وُضِعَ الۡکِتٰبُ فَتَرَی الۡمُجۡرِمِیۡنَ مُشۡفِقِیۡنَ  مِمَّا فِیۡہِ»\nTranslation: And the record (of deeds) will be placed, and you will see the criminals fearful of what is in it."
    },
    {
      "id": 1617,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "to frighten",
      "hw": "ڈرنا",
      "s": "« » to frighten, to threaten, to give a warning (41 verses: 6:134-7:86-11:17-11:81-14:14-15:43-18:48-18:58-18:59-19:75-20:58-20:59-20:86-20:87-20:97-20:113-21:103-21:109-23:36-23:93-26:206-36:63-38:53-41:30-43:83-46:16-46:35-50:14-50:20-50:28-50:32-50:45-51:5-51:22-51:60-54:46-70:42-70:44-72:24-72:25-77:7-)",
      "d": "« » the word 'wa'd' is general. Meaning to give someone hope. But 'wa'id' refers to the consequence of a bad deed and its punishment, a threat. And « » means to threaten, to frighten (Manjad), whether verbally or by practically providing such means.\n«وَ لَا تَقۡعُدُوۡا بِکُلِّ صِرَاطٍ تُوۡعِدُوۡنَ وَ تَصُدُّوۡنَ عَنۡ  سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And do not sit on every path, threatening and turning people away from the way of Allah."
    }
  ],
  "347": [
    {
      "id": 1618,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "bucket",
      "hw": "ڈول",
      "s": "« » a bucket that is completely empty.\nAnd « » a bucket that is filled with water.\nAnd « » a bucket that has some water in it (1 verse: 12:19)",
      "d": "« » a vessel for drawing water from a well. Bucket, pail, etc. (provided that it is empty of water (F L. 32))\n«وَ جَآءَتۡ سَیَّارَۃٌ  فَاَرۡسَلُوۡا وَارِدَہُمۡ فَاَدۡلٰی دَلۡوَہٗ»\nTranslation: And a caravan came, and they sent their water-drawer, and he let down his bucket (into the well)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1619,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "bucket",
      "hw": "ڈول",
      "s": "« » a vessel for drawing water. (1 verse: 51:59)",
      "d": "« » a vessel for drawing water. Bucket or pail, etc., when it is filled with water (FL 31)\n«فَاِنَّ لِلَّذِیۡنَ ظَلَمُوۡا ذَنُوۡبًا مِّثۡلَ ذَنُوۡبِ اَصۡحٰبِہِمۡ»\nTranslation: So indeed, for those who wronged, a bucket (of sins) like the bucket of their companions (has been filled)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1620,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "shield",
      "hw": "ڈول",
      "s": "« » meaning shield, the weapon used for protection from attacks (2 verses: 58:16-63:2)",
      "d": "« » means shield. The shield is the well-known weapon used to protect oneself from the enemy's attack by holding it in front to block the strike and safeguard oneself. Its use is in both material and spiritual contexts.\n«اِتَّخَذُوۡۤا  اَیۡمَانَہُمۡ جُنَّۃً  فَصَدُّوۡا عَنۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: They have taken their oaths as a shield, and they turn people away from the way of Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 1621,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "Shield",
      "hw": "ڈول",
      "s": "« » any thing that serves as a shield for protection (1 verse: 2:224)",
      "d": "«عَرَضَ» «عُرْضَۃ» «عُرْضَۃ» «ھُوَ عُرْضَۃٌ لِلنَّاسِ» «ھُوَ عُرْضَۃٌ لِلْکَلَامِ» «عُرْضَۃً» «جُنَّۃ» «وَ لَا تَجۡعَلُوا اللّٰہَ عُرۡضَۃً  لِّاَیۡمَانِکُمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "348": [
    {
      "id": 1622,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To cover, to conceal",
      "hw": " ڈھانپنا",
      "s": "« » to cover and hide from sight (1 verse: 6:76)",
      "d": "«جَنَّ» «جَنِّيْن» «جَنِیْن» «فَلَمَّا جَنَّ عَلَیۡہِ الَّیۡلُ  رَاٰ کَوۡکَبًا»"
    }
  ],
  "349": [
    {
      "id": 1626,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To incline, to slope",
      "hw": "ڈھلنا",
      "s": "« » meaning to incline for the setting of the sun (1 verse: 17:78)",
      "d": "«دَلَکَتِ الشَّمْسُ دُلُوْکًا» «اَلْدَلْک» «اَقِمِ الصَّلٰوۃَ  لِدُلُوۡکِ الشَّمۡسِ اِلٰی غَسَقِ  الَّیۡلِ وَ  قُرۡاٰنَ  الۡفَجۡرِ»"
    }
  ],
  "350": [
    {
      "id": 1631,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To search",
      "hw": "ڈھونڈنا",
      "s": "« » to repeatedly attempt to find something (2 verses: 57:13-72:8)",
      "d": "«لَمَسَ» «اَلْتَمَسَ» «قِیۡلَ ارۡجِعُوۡا وَرَآءَکُمۡ فَالۡتِمِسُوۡا نُوۡرًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1632,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To search",
      "hw": "ڈھونڈنا",
      "s": "« » to reach the extreme in seeking something, to search intensely (1 verse: 17:5)",
      "d": "«جَاسَ» «بَعَثۡنَا عَلَیۡکُمۡ  عِبَادًا  لَّنَاۤ   اُولِیۡ  بَاۡسٍ  شَدِیۡدٍ فَجَاسُوۡا خِلٰلَ الدِّیَارِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1633,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To search",
      "hw": "ڈھونڈنا",
      "s": "« » to rummage and extract something (2 verses: 82:4-100:9)",
      "d": "«بَعْثَرَ» «بَعْثَرَ الْمَتَاعَ» «بُعْثِرَ» «بُعِثَ» «عُثِرَ» «وَ  اِذَا الۡقُبُوۡرُ بُعۡثِرَتۡ» «اَفَلَا یَعۡلَمُ  اِذَا بُعۡثِرَ مَا فِی الۡقُبُوۡرِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1634,
      "a": "ڈ",
      "h": "To search",
      "hw": "ڈھونڈنا",
      "s": "« » to seek what is better and more suitable (1 verse: 72:14)",
      "d": "«حَرُّو» «حَرّٰی» «اَلْاَحْرٰی» «تَحَرّٰی» «وَّ اَنَّا مِنَّا  الۡمُسۡلِمُوۡنَ وَ مِنَّا الۡقٰسِطُوۡنَ ؕ فَمَنۡ  اَسۡلَمَ فَاُولٰٓئِکَ تَحَرَّوۡا  رَشَدًا»"
    }
  ],
  "351": [
    {
      "id": 1635,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To slaughter",
      "hw": "ذبح کرنا",
      "s": "« » to slaughter an animal according to the prescribed Islamic method (9 verses: 2:49-2:67-2:71-5:3-14:6-27:21-28:4-37:102-37:107)",
      "d": "«ذَبَحَ» «فَذَبَحُوۡہَا وَ مَا کَادُوۡا یَفۡعَلُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1636,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To slaughter",
      "hw": "ذبح کرنا",
      "s": "« » to slaughter an animal with consideration for its ease (1 verse: 5:3)",
      "d": "«ذَکّٰی» «وَ مَاۤ اَکَلَ السَّبُعُ اِلَّا مَا ذَکَّیۡتُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1637,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To slaughter",
      "hw": "ذبح کرنا",
      "s": "« » any form of cutting the throat, whether it is slaughter or sacrifice or any other form (1 verse: 108:2)",
      "d": "«نَحَرَ» «نَحْر» «نَحُوْر» «اِنْتَحَرَ» «یَوْمُ النَّحْر» «نَحَرَ» «نَحْر» «فَصَلِّ  لِرَبِّکَ وَ انۡحَرۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "352": [
    {
      "id": 1638,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Means",
      "hw": "ذریعہ",
      "s": "« » That which serves as a means to reach something else (9 verses: 2:166-18:84-18:85-18:89-18:92-22:15-38:10-40:36-40:37)",
      "d": "« » refers to the rope with which one climbs and descends a date palm. Then, by extension, every thing that serves as a means to reach something else is called 'cause'. Furthermore, this term is also applied to a path and its related equipment.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ اٰتَیۡنٰہُ مِنۡ کُلِّ شَیۡءٍ سَبَبًا فَاَتۡبَعَ سَبَبًا»\nTranslation: We had granted Dhul-Qarnayn every kind of means, so he pursued a course."
    },
    {
      "id": 1639,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Means",
      "hw": "ذریعہ",
      "s": "« » The means chosen to attain proximity (2 verses: 5:35-17:57)",
      "d": "«وَسَلَ» «وَسَلَ اِلَی اللہ» «اَلْوَاسَطَہ» «اَلْوَسِیْلَۃ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ ابۡتَغُوۡۤا اِلَیۡہِ الۡوَسِیۡلَۃَ وَ جَاہِدُوۡا فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِہٖ»\nTranslation: And seek the means of nearness to Him and strive hard in His way."
    }
  ],
  "353": [
    {
      "id": 1640,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Humiliation",
      "hw": "ذلت",
      "s": "« » To bow before the powerful and authoritative, becoming subservient (7 verses: 2:61-3:112-7:152-10:26-10:27-68:43-70:44)",
      "d": "« » means subjugation (i.e., being overpowered), weakness, and being crushed before strength and power. Its opposite is « », meaning supremacy and authority.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«ضُرِبَتۡ عَلَیۡہِمُ الذِّلَّۃُ اَیۡنَ مَا ثُقِفُوۡۤا»\nTranslation: Wherever they are found, humiliation has been decreed for them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1641,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Humiliation",
      "hw": "ذلت",
      "s": "« » Humiliation of becoming small after greatness and acknowledging it (1 verse: 6:124)",
      "d": "« » means the humiliation of being diminished after greatness and its acknowledgment. It also means enduring the humiliation of becoming a subject after having been a ruler or free.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«سَیُصِیۡبُ الَّذِیۡنَ اَجۡرَمُوۡا صَغَارٌ عِنۡدَ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And those who commit sins will be afflicted with humiliation from Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 1642,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Humiliation",
      "hw": "ذلت",
      "s": "« » To fall in people's eyes, disgrace (11 verses: 2:85-2:114-5:33-5:41-9:63-10:98-11:66-16:27-22:9-39:26-41:16)",
      "d": "« » means disgrace, shame, and falling in the eyes of others due to one's evil deeds. If this feeling is limited to oneself, it is called 'nadāmah' (remorse).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«لَقَالُوۡا رَبَّنَا لَوۡ لَاۤ اَرۡسَلۡتَ اِلَیۡنَا رَسُوۡلًا فَنَتَّبِعَ اٰیٰتِکَ مِنۡ قَبۡلِ اَنۡ نَّذِلَّ وَ نَخۡزٰی»\nTranslation: They will say, 'Our Lord, why did You not send a messenger to us so we could follow Your signs before we are humiliated and disgraced?'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1643,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Humiliation",
      "hw": "ذلت",
      "s": "« » means to face humiliation due to being despised (5 verses: 6:93-16:59-25:63-41:17-46:20)",
      "d": "«ھُوْن» «یَتَوَارٰی مِنَ الۡقَوۡمِ مِنۡ سُوۡٓءِ مَا بُشِّرَ بِہٖ ؕ اَیُمۡسِکُہٗ عَلٰی ہُوۡنٍ اَمۡ  یَدُسُّہٗ  فِی التُّرَابِ» «ھَوْن» «وَ عِبَادُ  الرَّحۡمٰنِ الَّذِیۡنَ  یَمۡشُوۡنَ عَلَی الۡاَرۡضِ ہَوۡنًا»"
    }
  ],
  "354": [
    {
      "id": 1645,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Despicable",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » Despicable, fallen in others' eyes due to evil deeds (18 verses: 2:90-3:178-4:14-4:37-4:102-4:151-22:57-31:6-32:8-33:57-34:14-43:52-44:30-45:9-58:5-58:16-68:10-77:20)",
      "d": "« » means to become insignificant, weak. « » means insignificant, worthless, despicable, and humiliated. According to Imam Raghb, « » is a person over whom another human has dominion, making him undignified and humiliated.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اَمۡ اَنَا خَیۡرٌ مِّنۡ ہٰذَا الَّذِیۡ ہُوَ مَہِیۡنٌ»\nTranslation: (Pharaoh said) Am I not better than this contemptible man?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1646,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Despicable",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » One who descends below the ruler, becoming a subject and acknowledging it (5 verses: 7:13-7:119-9:29-12:32-27:37)",
      "d": "« » is the opposite of « ». « » means humiliation. « » means one who holds a secondary position, humiliated with the pride of greatness, forced into subjugation, and acknowledging it.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«حَتّٰی یُعۡطُوا الۡجِزۡیَۃَ عَنۡ ‌یَّدٍ وَّ ہُمۡ صٰغِرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: (Fight them) until they give the jizyah willingly while they are humiliated."
    },
    {
      "id": 1647,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Despicable",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » To become obedient and submissive with humiliation due to lack of intellect (4 verses: 16:48-27:87-37:18-40:60)",
      "d": "« » implies three things: helplessness, humiliation, and contempt. « » means one who, due to lack of intellect and awareness, accepts humiliation and obedience.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنَّ الَّذِیۡنَ یَسۡتَکۡبِرُوۡنَ عَنۡ عِبَادَتِیۡ سَیَدۡخُلُوۡنَ جَہَنَّمَ دٰخِرِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: Indeed, those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell humiliated.\nAt another place, Allah says:\n«وَ یَوۡمَ یُنۡفَخُ فِی الصُّوۡرِ فَفَزِعَ مَنۡ فِی السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ مَنۡ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ اِلَّا مَنۡ شَآءَ اللّٰہُ ؕ وَ کُلٌّ اَتَوۡہُ دٰخِرِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And the Day the Horn is blown, whoever is in the heavens and whoever is on the earth will be terrified except whom Allah wills. And all will come to Him humbled."
    },
    {
      "id": 1649,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Despicable",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » Low and despicable compared to the exalted (7 verses: 4:145-8:42-9:40-33:10-37:98-41:29-95:5)",
      "d": "« » means lowly people, like « » and « », meaning low and despicable. Its opposite is « » (exalted).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«نَجۡعَلۡہُمَا تَحۡتَ اَقۡدَامِنَا لِیَکُوۡنَا مِنَ الۡاَسۡفَلِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: We will make them the lowest of the low."
    },
    {
      "id": 1650,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Humiliated",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » means abused. Most humiliated. (4 verses: 2:65-7:166-23:108-67:4)",
      "d": "«خَسَاَ» «خَاسِئُ مِنَ الْخَنَازِیْرِ وَ الْکِلَاب» «وَ لَقَدۡ عَلِمۡتُمُ  الَّذِیۡنَ اعۡتَدَوۡا مِنۡکُمۡ فِی السَّبۡتِ فَقُلۡنَا لَہُمۡ کُوۡنُوۡا قِرَدَۃً خٰسِئِیۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1651,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To humiliate",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » means to make the superior subdue the inferior or to humiliate. (3 verses: 3:26-58:20-63:8)",
      "d": "«اَذَلَّ» «اَعَزَّ» «وَ تُعِزُّ مَنۡ تَشَآءُ وَ تُذِلُّ مَنۡ تَشَآءُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1652,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To humiliate",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » means to insult and humiliate someone due to enmity, and even an equal can do this. (3 verses: 22:18-25:69-89:16)",
      "d": "«اَھَانَ» «اَکْرَمَ» «وَ مَنۡ  یُّہِنِ اللّٰہُ  فَمَا لَہٗ  مِنۡ مُّکۡرِمٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1653,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To humiliate",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » to humiliate someone due to their apparent fault. (15 verses: 3:192-3:194-9:2-9:14-11:39-11:78-11:93-15:69-16:27-20:134-26:87-39:40-41:16-59:5-66:8)",
      "d": "«اَخْزٰی» «وَ لَا تُخۡزِنَا یَوۡمَ الۡقِیٰمَۃِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1654,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To humiliate",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » to degrade someone by mentioning their faults, making them fall in others' eyes. (1 verse: 15:68)",
      "d": "«فَضَحَ» «قَالَ  اِنَّ ہٰۤؤُلَآءِ ضَیۡفِیۡ فَلَا تَفۡضَحُوۡنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1656,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "To humiliate",
      "hw": "ذلیل",
      "s": "« » to humiliate and disgrace someone in a state of anger. (2 verses: 3:127-58:5)",
      "d": "«کَبَتَ» «اِنَّ  الَّذِیۡنَ یُحَآدُّوۡنَ اللّٰہَ  وَ رَسُوۡلَہٗ کُبِتُوۡا کَمَا کُبِتَ الَّذِیۡنَ مِنۡ  قَبۡلِہِمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "355": [
    {
      "id": 1657,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Responsibility",
      "hw": "ذمہ داری",
      "s": "« » refers to the responsibility of fulfilling a covenant with others. (2 verses: 9:8-9:10)",
      "d": "«ذِمَّۃ» «اَنْتَ فِیْ ذِمَّۃِ اللہِ» «ذِمِّی» «اَھْلِ الذّمّۃ» «لَا یَرۡقُبُوۡنَ فِیۡ مُؤۡمِنٍ اِلًّا وَّ لَا ذِمَّۃً»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1658,
      "a": "ذ",
      "h": "Responsibility",
      "hw": "ذمہ داری",
      "s": "« » refers to the responsibility of fulfilling a self-imposed obligation. (1 verse: 33:23)",
      "d": "«نَحْب» «نَحَبَ الرَّجُل» «نَحْب» «فَمِنۡہُمۡ مَّنۡ قَضٰی نَحۡبَہٗ  وَ مِنۡہُمۡ مَّنۡ یَّنۡتَظِرُ»"
    }
  ],
  "356": [
    {
      "id": 1659,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » means night. (77 verses: 2:51-2:164-2:187-2:274-3:27-3:113-3:190-6:13-6:60-6:76-6:96-7:54-7:142-10:6-10:24-10:27-10:67-11:81-11:114-13:3-13:10-14:33-15:65-16:12-17:1-17:12-17:78-17:79-20:130-21:20-21:33-21:42-22:61-23:80-24:44-25:47-25:62-27:86-28:71-28:72-28:73-30:23-31:29-34:33-35:13-36:37-36:40-37:138-39:5-39:9-40:61-41:37-41:38-44:3-44:23-45:5-50:40-51:17-52:49-57:6-71:5-73:2-73:6-73:20-74:33-76:26-78:10-79:29-81:17-84:17-89:4-91:4-92:1-93:2-97:1-97:2-97:3)",
      "d": "«لَیْل» «نَھَار» «لَیْل» «شَفَقَ ، غَسَقَ ، عَتَمَہ ، دَقَّۃَ ، فَحَّمَہ ، زُلْفَۃ ، زَلْقَۃ ، بَھْرَۃ ، سَحَر ، فَجَر ، صَبَحَ ، صَبَاح»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1660,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » means to spend the night. (3 verses: 7:4-7:97-10:50)",
      "d": "«بَاتَ» «وَ الَّذِیۡنَ یَبِیۡتُوۡنَ لِرَبِّہِمۡ سُجَّدًا وَّ قِیَامًا» «بَیَاتًا» «قُلۡ اَرَءَیۡتُمۡ اِنۡ اَتٰىکُمۡ عَذَابُہٗ بَیَاتًا اَوۡ نَہَارًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1661,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night-related matters",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » meaning to spend the night, to pass the night, and the place where one spends the night (1 verse: 25:64)",
      "d": "« » meaning to spend the night. To pass the night. And the place where one spends the night. That is the house (i.e., home). (M L)\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ الَّذِیۡنَ یَبِیۡتُوۡنَ لِرَبِّہِمۡ سُجَّدًا وَّ قِیَامًا»\nTranslation: And those who spend the night in prostration and standing before their Lord."
    },
    {
      "id": 1662,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night-related matters",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » to gather at home after part of the night has passed to consult on a matter (3 verses: 4:81-4:108-27:49)",
      "d": "« » meaning to gather at home after part of the night has passed to consult on a matter (M. L)\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«اِذۡ یُبَیِّتُوۡنَ مَا لَا یَرۡضٰی مِنَ الۡقَوۡلِ»\nTranslation: When they consult at night about matters which He (Allah) does not approve of.\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«قَالُوۡا تَقَاسَمُوۡا بِاللّٰہِ لَنُبَیِّتَنَّہٗ وَ اَہۡلَہٗ ثُمَّ لَنَقُوۡلَنَّ لِوَلِیِّہٖ مَا شَہِدۡنَا مَہۡلِکَ اَہۡلِہٖ»\nTranslation: They said, 'Swear by Allah that we will certainly attack him and his family by night, then we will say to his heir, \"We were not present at the death of his family.\"'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1663,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night-related matters",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » meaning to travel at night (6 verses: 11:81-15:65-17:1-20:77-26:52-44:23)",
      "d": "« » meaning to travel at night. To take away. To lead out.\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«سُبۡحٰنَ الَّذِیۡۤ اَسۡرٰی بِعَبۡدِہٖ لَیۡلًا مِّنَ الۡمَسۡجِدِ الۡحَرَامِ اِلَی الۡمَسۡجِدِ الۡاَقۡصَا»\nTranslation: Glorified is He who took His servant by night from the Sacred Mosque to the Farthest Mosque."
    },
    {
      "id": 1664,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night-related matters",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » meaning path (2 verses: 86:1-86:2)",
      "d": "« » means path and « » means the one who travels the path. But in common usage, it particularly refers to the traveler who comes at night. And stars are called « » because they generally appear at night. (M F)\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ السَّمَآءِ وَ الطَّارِقِ»\nTranslation: By the sky and the night-comer.\nIn this verse, « » could refer to stars or the night-visiting guest."
    },
    {
      "id": 1665,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night-related matters",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » refers to those sheep/goats that have spread out at night to graze without a shepherd (1 verse: 21:78)",
      "d": "«نَفْشُ الْغَنَم» «اَلنَّفْش»\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ دَاوٗدَ وَ سُلَیۡمٰنَ اِذۡ یَحۡکُمٰنِ فِی الۡحَرۡثِ اِذۡ نَفَشَتۡ فِیۡہِ غَنَمُ الۡقَوۡمِ»\nTranslation: And remember David and Solomon when they were judging in the matter of the field when the sheep of the people had scattered therein at night and grazed."
    },
    {
      "id": 1666,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Night-related matters",
      "hw": "رات",
      "s": "« » to wake up at night to perform voluntary prayers (1 verse: 17:79)",
      "d": "« » means both to sleep at night and to wake up (this is from the category of opposite words in lexicon, where words have two distinct and opposite meanings).\n«ھَجَّدَ تَھَجَّدَ»\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ مِنَ الَّیۡلِ فَتَہَجَّدۡ بِہٖ نَافِلَۃً لَّکَ»\nTranslation: And during some parts of the night, wake up and perform voluntary prayers for yourself."
    }
  ],
  "357": [
    {
      "id": 1667,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Path. Way",
      "hw": "راستہ",
      "s": "« » is a general term for path (7 verses: 4:168-4:169-20:63-20:77-20:104-46:30-72:16)",
      "d": "The plural of « » is « ». This word is used for every type of path (F L 269). This word is also used in both material and spiritual contexts. An example of its material usage is:\nThe divine command is:\n«فَاضۡرِبۡ لَہُمۡ طَرِیۡقًا فِی الۡبَحۡرِ یَبَسًا»\nTranslation: (O Moses!) Strike for them a dry path in the sea.\nAnd an example of its spiritual usage is:\nThe divine command is:\n«وَ لَا لِیَہۡدِیَہُمۡ طَرِیۡقًا اِلَّا طَرِیۡقَ جَہَنَّمَ»\nTranslation: And He will not guide them except the path of Hell."
    },
    {
      "id": 1668,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Path. Way",
      "hw": "راستہ",
      "s": "« » a path upon which one must tread with caution (45 verses: 1:5-1:6-2:142-2:213-3:51-3:101-4:68-4:175-5:16-6:39-6:87-6:126-6:153-6:161-7:16-7:86-10:25-11:56-14:1-15:41-16:76-16:121-19:36-19:43-20:135-22:24-22:54-23:73-23:74-24:46-34:6-36:4-36:61-36:66-37:23-37:118-38:22-42:52-42:53-43:43-43:61-43:64-48:2-48:20-67:22)",
      "d": "« » refers to a long and sharp-edged sword (Minaj). And it is the path that will be built to cross over Hell, commonly called the Bridge of Sirat. It has been described as being sharper than a sword and thinner than a hair. Thus, « » is the path that must be traversed with utmost vigilance and caution. And there are many dangers surrounding it. The name for traversing this path with such vigilance and caution is Taqwa (piety). The word « » is used in both material and spiritual contexts. In the spiritual sense, its meaning is generally the path of guidance. And according to Abu Halaal, « » means the easy path (F Q L 246). And Allah knows best.\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«اِہۡدِ نَا الصِّرَاطَ الۡمُسۡتَقِیۡمَ»\nTranslation: Our Lord, guide us to the straight path.\nAnd an example of its material usage is:\nThe divine command is:\n«وَ لَا تَقۡعُدُوۡا بِکُلِّ صِرَاطٍ تُوۡعِدُوۡنَ وَ تَصُدُّوۡنَ عَنۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And do not sit on every path, threatening and turning people away from the way of Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 1669,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Path. Way",
      "hw": "راستہ",
      "s": "« » a path upon which one can walk with ease and upon which there is frequent traffic (157 verses: 2:108-2:154-2:190-2:195-2:217-2:218-2:244-2:246-2:261-2:262-2:273-3:13-3:75-3:97-3:99-3:146-3:157-3:167-3:169-3:195-4:15-4:22-4:34-4:44-4:51-4:74-4:75-4:76-4:84-4:88-4:89-4:90-4:94-4:95-4:98-4:100-4:115-4:137-4:141-4:143-4:150-4:160-4:167-5:12-5:16-5:35-5:54-5:60-5:77-6:55-6:116-6:117-6:153-6:153-7:45-7:86-7:142-7:146-7:148-8:36-8:47-8:60-8:72-8:74-9:5-9:9-9:19-9:20-9:24-9:34-9:38-9:41-9:60-9:81-9:91-9:93-9:111-9:120-10:88-10:89-11:19-12:108-13:33-14:3-14:12-14:30-15:76-16:9-16:15-16:69-16:88-16:94-16:125-17:32-17:42-17:48-17:72-17:84-17:110-18:61-18:63-20:53-21:31-22:9-22:25-22:58-24:22-25:9-25:17-25:27-25:34-25:42-25:44-25:57-27:24-28:22-29:12-29:29-29:38-29:69-31:6-31:15-33:4-33:67-38:26-39:8-40:7-40:11-40:29-40:37-40:38-42:41-42:42-42:44-42:46-43:10-43:37-47:1-47:4-47:32-47:34-47:38-49:15-53:30-57:10-58:16-60:1-61:4-61:11-63:2-68:7-71:20-73:19-73:20-76:3-76:29-80:20)",
      "d": "«سَبِیْل» «اِبْنُ السَّبِیْل» «عَابِرِی سَّبِیْل» «سُبُل» «سبیل» «اَسْبَلُ الطَّرِیْق» «اَسْبَلُ الدَّمْعِ وَالْمَطَر» «سَبِیْل»\nFor example, in the Quran, Allah Almighty says through the honeybee:\n«فَاسۡلُکِیۡ سُبُلَ رَبِّکِ ذُلُلًا»\nTranslation: And follow the ways of your Lord in humility.\nHere, « » refers to the natural guidance that Allah has inherently placed in everything, upon which one can proceed with ease. And all are equally traversed. This word is also used in both spiritual and material contexts. The above example is of the spiritual context, and an example of the material context is this:\nThe divine command is:\n«وَ اِنَّہَا لَبِسَبِیۡلٍ مُّقِیۡمٍ»\nTranslation: And indeed, it (the city of Lot) is still on a straight path.\nNow observe that for this 'path of guidance', Allah has used all three words « », « », and « » in the Quran. « » is general, used for any path. « » is one that is surrounded by the limits and confines of commands and prohibitions. And « » is such that when a person embarks upon it with determination, the Sharia has taken into account all kinds of facilities for him, and the number of people traversing it is also large."
    },
    {
      "id": 1670,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Path. Way",
      "hw": "راستہ",
      "s": "« » an open path between two mountains (3 verses: 21:31-22:27-71:20)",
      "d": "« » refers to the opening between two mountains, and « » refers to the valley between two mountains, and « » refers to that open path which passes through that valley and connects the two mountains. The plural of « » is « ».\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ اَذِّنۡ فِی النَّاسِ بِالۡحَجِّ یَاۡتُوۡکَ رِجَالًا وَّ عَلٰی کُلِّ ضَامِرٍ یَّاۡتِیۡنَ مِنۡ کُلِّ فَجٍّ عَمِیۡقٍ»\nTranslation: And proclaim to the people the Hajj; they will come to you on foot and on every lean camel, coming from every distant path."
    },
    {
      "id": 1671,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Path. Way.",
      "hw": "راستہ",
      "s": "« » main road, open street (6 verses: 2:124, 11:17, 15:79, 17:71, 25:74, 46:12)",
      "d": "«إمام» «فَانْتَقَمْنَا مِنْهُمْ ۘ وَ إِنَّهُمَا لَبِإِمَامٍ مُّبِينٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1672,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Path. Way.",
      "hw": "راستہ",
      "s": "« » a path that ascends and descends a valley (1 verse: 90:10)",
      "d": "«نجد» «وَ هَدَيْنَاهُ النَّجْدَيْنِ فَلَا اقْتَحَمَ الْعَقَبَةَ»"
    }
  ],
  "358": [
    {
      "id": 1675,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To lay a path. To establish.",
      "hw": "رائج",
      "s": "« » comes to establish every good and bad way. However, in Shariah terminology, « » refers specifically to the actions and sayings of the Messenger of Allah ﷺ (9 verses: 8:38, 15:13, 17:77, 18:55, 33:38, 33:62, 35:43, 40:85, 48:23)",
      "d": "«سنّ» «مَنْ سَنَّ سُنَّةً» «فَهَلْ يَنْظُرُونَ إِلَّا سُنَّةَ الْأَوَّلِينَ ۚ فَلَنْ تَجِدَ لِسُنَّةِ اللّٰهِ تَبْدِيلًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1676,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To Lay a Path. To Establish.",
      "hw": "رائج",
      "s": "« » means for Allah to set a clear and defined path for His servants through the Prophet. From Adam to Muhammad, changes occurred in this, but now this part of the religion is also unchangeable (in which it cannot be). Because the Prophet was the last prophet and the religion was completed upon him. (4 verses: 5:48-42:13-42:21-45:48)",
      "d": "«شَرَعَ» «شَرَعَ لِلْقَوْمِ» «شَرَعَ» «شَرَعَ  لَکُمۡ مِّنَ الدِّیۡنِ مَا وَصّٰی بِہٖ نُوۡحًا» «اَمۡ لَہُمۡ شُرَکٰٓؤُا شَرَعُوۡا  لَہُمۡ مِّنَ الدِّیۡنِ مَا لَمۡ یَاۡذَنۡۢ بِہِ اللّٰہُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1677,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To lay a path. To establish.",
      "hw": "رائج",
      "s": "« » to introduce a custom or way into religion, considering it part of it, for which there is no proof in Shariah (1 verse: 57:27)",
      "d": "«الابتداع» «بدعة» «ابتدا» «وَرَهْبَانِيَّةَ ابْتَدَعُوهَا مَا كَتَبْنَاهَا عَلَيْهِمْ»"
    }
  ],
  "359": [
    {
      "id": 1678,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To please. To be pleased.",
      "hw": "راضی",
      "s": "« » to be pleased, to be happy, is a general word (26 verses: 2:144, 4:24, 5:3, 5:119, 9:38, 9:58, 9:59, 9:83, 9:87, 9:93, 9:96, 9:100, 10:7, 19:6, 19:55, 20:109, 27:19, 33:51, 46:15, 48:18, 58:22, 69:21, 88:9, 89:28, 98:8, 101:7)",
      "d": "«رضی» «رَضِيَ اللّٰهُ عَنْهُمْ وَ رَضُوا عَنْهُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1679,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To please. To be pleased.",
      "hw": "راضی",
      "s": "« » to make one's heart willingly pleased with a bad deed (8 verses: 2:158, 2:184, 3:83, 5:30, 9:53, 9:79, 13:15, 41:11)",
      "d": "«أطاع» «طوّع» «فَطَوَّعَتْ لَهُ نَفْسُهُ قَتْلَ أَخِيهِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1680,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To please. To be pleased.",
      "hw": "راضی",
      "s": "« » to complain with the intention of pleasing one who is offended (4 verses: 16:84, 30:57, 41:24, 45:35)",
      "d": "«عتَب» «اعتب» «عتاب» «وَ إِنْ يَسْتَعْتِبُوا فَمَا هُمْ مِنَ الْمُعْتَبِينَ»"
    }
  ],
  "360": [
    {
      "id": 1681,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Rank. To attain rank.",
      "hw": "رتبہ",
      "s": "« » a station of excellence and superiority (18 verses: 2:228, 2:253, 3:163, 4:95, 4:96, 6:83, 6:132, 6:165, 8:4, 9:20, 12:76, 17:21, 20:75, 40:15, 43:32, 46:19, 57:10, 58:11)",
      "d": "«درجَة» «درج» «درک» «درجات» «دركات» «درجات الجنة» «دركات النار» «وَلَهُنَّ مِثْلُ الَّذِي عَلَيْهِنَّ بِالْمَعْرُوفِ ۪ وَلِلرِّجَالِ عَلَيْهِنَّ دَرَجَةٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1682,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Rank. To attain rank.",
      "hw": "رتبہ",
      "s": "« » nearness in honor and status (9 verses: 26:64, 26:90, 34:37, 38:25, 38:40, 39:3, 50:31, 67:27, 81:13)",
      "d": "«زلفی» «وَ إِنَّ لَهُ عِنْدَنَا لَزُلْفَىٰ وَ حُسْنَ مَآبٍ» «وَ أَزْلَفْنَا ثَمَّ الْآخَرِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1683,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Rank; Attaining Rank",
      "hw": "رتبہ",
      "s": "« » To grant rank and make oneself close (36 verses: 2:35-2:187-2:222-2:237-3:167-4:11-4:43-4:172-5:8-5:82-6:151-6:152-7:19-7:114-9:28-9:99-12:60-16:77-17:32-17:34-17:57-18:24-18:81-19:52-22:13-26:42-34:37-39:3-46:28-50:16-51:27-56:11-56:85-56:88-83:21-83:28)",
      "d": "« » means to be near. And to perform an act that becomes a means of nearness in rank. And « » is that offering (sacrifice) through which the attainment of rank and status is sought.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اتۡلُ عَلَیۡہِمۡ  نَبَاَ ابۡنَیۡ اٰدَمَ  بِالۡحَقِّ ۘ اِذۡ قَرَّبَا قُرۡبَانًا»\nTranslation: And recite to them, [O Muhammad], the true story of the two sons of Adam when they both offered an offering.\nAt another place, the Divine declaration states:\n«وَ السّٰبِقُوۡنَ  السّٰبِقُوۡنَ اُولٰٓئِکَ  الۡمُقَرَّبُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And the forerunners, the forerunners – those are the ones brought near."
    },
    {
      "id": 1684,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Rank; Attaining Rank",
      "hw": "رتبہ",
      "s": "« » When rank is attained along with authority (13 verses: 6:6-7:10-8:71-12:21-12:54-12:56-18:84-18:95-22:41-24:55-28:6-28:57-46:26)",
      "d": "« » means to be of high rank. And « » means place, abode. A place that holds a body. And « » means to grant someone authority, to bestow sovereignty. And « » also means one who resides in a place, and also a person of high rank.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«اِنَّہٗ  لَقَوۡلُ رَسُوۡلٍ  کَرِیۡمٍ ذِیۡ  قُوَّۃٍ  عِنۡدَ ذِی الۡعَرۡشِ مَکِیۡنٍ»\nTranslation: Indeed, it is the word of a noble messenger, possessor of power, with the Lord of the Throne, established in rank."
    }
  ],
  "361": [
    {
      "id": 1686,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To Turn (One's Face)",
      "hw": "رخ",
      "s": "« » To be attentive, to turn towards (1 verse: 28:22)",
      "d": "«وَجْہ» «وَجَّہَ» «تَوَجَّہَ اِلَیْہِ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَمَّا تَوَجَّہَ  تِلۡقَآءَ مَدۡیَنَ»\nTranslation: Then when he turned his face towards Madyan..."
    }
  ],
  "362": [
    {
      "id": 1687,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Worthless; Invalid",
      "hw": "ناکارہ",
      "s": "« » Something that is difficult to obtain, low in quantity, and deficient in goodness (1 verse: 7:58)",
      "d": "«نَکِدَ» «قَلِیْلُ الْخَیر» «نَاقَۃَ نَکِدَاء» «نَکَدَ» «نَکِدَ الرَّجُل» «نَکِدَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ الَّذِیۡ خَبُثَ لَا یَخۡرُجُ  اِلَّا نَکِدًا»\nTranslation: And whatever land is bad – nothing comes out of it except scanty [production]."
    },
    {
      "id": 1688,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Worthless; Invalid",
      "hw": "ناکارہ",
      "s": "« » Bitter, sour, and bad-tasting thing (1 verse: 34:16)",
      "d": "« » means every sour or bitter thing. The few fruits of every tree. Every long-thorned tree (Majid).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«اُکُلٍ خَمۡطٍ وَّ اَثۡلٍ وَّ شَیۡءٍ مِّنۡ سِدۡرٍ قَلِیۡلٍ»\nTranslation: And for both of them [i.e., the two gardens] were fruits and date-palms and pomegranates. And [He] made them [into] gardens of bitter fruit and tamarisk and a few lote trees."
    },
    {
      "id": 1690,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Worthless; Invalid",
      "hw": "ناکارہ",
      "s": "« » A defective thing; incomplete (9 verses: 2:155-7:130-9:4-11:84-13:41-21:44-35:11-50:4-73:3)",
      "d": "«نَاقِصْ» «دِرْھمٌ ناقصٌ» «نَقْص»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَقَدۡ اَخَذۡنَاۤ  اٰلَ فِرۡعَوۡنَ بِالسِّنِیۡنَ وَ نَقۡصٍ مِّنَ الثَّمَرٰتِ»\nTranslation: And We certainly seized the people of Pharaoh with years [of famine] and scarcity of fruits that they might be reminded."
    },
    {
      "id": 1691,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Worthless; Invalid",
      "hw": "ناکارہ",
      "s": "« » Cheap and worthless thing (7 verses: 2:282-7:85-11:15-11:85-12:20-26:183-72:13)",
      "d": "« » means deficient, cheap, contemptible (Majid). And it also means a vile and deficient thing (Muf).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ شَرَوۡہُ بِثَمَنٍۭ بَخۡسٍ دَرَاہِمَ مَعۡدُوۡدَۃٍ»\nTranslation: And they sold him for a cheap price, a few dirhams, counted out."
    },
    {
      "id": 1692,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Worthless; Invalid",
      "hw": "ناکارہ",
      "s": "« » Dirty and impure or unlawful thing (10 verses: 2:267-3:179-4:2-5:100-7:58-7:157-8:37-14:26-21:74-24:26)",
      "d": "« » means to be filthy and impure, to be worthless, to be useless. And « » means impure, worthless, detestable. Every corrupt and dirty thing. Its opposite is « » (Majid).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تَتَبَدَّلُوا الۡخَبِیۡثَ بِالطَّیِّبِ»\nTranslation: And do not exchange the bad for the good."
    },
    {
      "id": 1693,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Worthless; Invalid",
      "hw": "ناکارہ",
      "s": "« » That which is inferior compared to a good thing (12 verses: 2:61-2:282-4:3-5:108-7:169-30:3-32:21-33:51-33:59-53:9-58:7-73:20)",
      "d": "« » Its opposite is « ». That thing which is deficient or worthless in comparison to a good thing.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«قَالَ اَتَسۡتَبۡدِلُوۡنَ الَّذِیۡ ہُوَ اَدۡنٰی بِالَّذِیۡ ہُوَ خَیۡرٌ»\nTranslation: [Moses] said, \"Would you exchange what is inferior for what is good?\""
    }
  ],
  "363": [
    {
      "id": 1695,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Rope",
      "hw": "رسی",
      "s": "« » Used for all types of rope (6 verses: 3:103-3:112-20:66-26:44-50:16-111:5)",
      "d": "«حَبْل» «حَبَال» «حَبْلُ الْوَرِیْد» «حَبَالَۃُ الْصَیَّاد»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فِیۡ  جِیۡدِہَا حَبۡلٌ مِّنۡ مَّسَدٍ»\nTranslation: Around her neck will be a rope of twisted palm fiber."
    },
    {
      "id": 1696,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Rope",
      "hw": "رسی",
      "s": "The term « » is used specifically for a rope that can be employed as a means for travel or climbing (9 verses: 2:166, 18:84, 18:85, 18:89, 18:92, 22:15, 38:10, 40:36, 40:37).",
      "d": "«سَبَب» «مَنۡ کَانَ یَظُنُّ اَنۡ لَّنۡ یَّنۡصُرَہُ اللّٰہُ فِی الدُّنۡیَا وَ الۡاٰخِرَۃِ فَلۡیَمۡدُدۡ بِسَبَبٍ اِلَی السَّمَآءِ ثُمَّ لۡیَقۡطَعۡ فَلۡیَنۡظُرۡ ہَلۡ یُذۡہِبَنَّ کَیۡدُہٗ مَا یَغِیۡظُ»"
    }
  ],
  "364": [
    {
      "id": 1697,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Relative (Close Kin)",
      "hw": "رشتہ دار",
      "s": "« » refers to close relatives who have a prescribed share in inheritance (23 verses: 2:83, 2:177, 2:180, 2:215, 3:45, 4:7, 4:8, 4:33, 4:36, 4:135, 5:106, 6:152, 8:41, 9:113, 16:90, 17:26, 24:22, 26:214, 30:38, 35:18, 42:23, 59:7, 90:15).",
      "d": "«قَرُبَ» «اَقْرَبَ» «اَقْرَبُوْنَ» «اَقْرَبِیْن» «ذَا قُرْبٰی» «ذَوِی الْقُرْبٰی» «لِلرِّجَالِ نَصِیۡبٌ مِّمَّا تَرَکَ الۡوَالِدٰنِ وَ الۡاَقۡرَبُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1698,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Relative (Paternal Lineage)",
      "hw": "رشتہ دار",
      "s": "« » refers to relatives on the father's side (3 verses: 23:101, 25:54, 37:158).",
      "d": "«نَسَبَ یَنْسُبُ» «اِسْتَنْسَبَ» «نَسَب» «اَنْسَاب» «اَقْرَبُوْن» «فَاِذَا نُفِخَ فِی الصُّوۡرِ فَلَاۤ اَنۡسَابَ بَیۡنَہُمۡ یَوۡمَئِذٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1699,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Relative (In-Laws)",
      "hw": "رشتہ دار",
      "s": "« » means in-laws (1 verse: 25:54).",
      "d": "«صِھْر» «وَ ہُوَ الَّذِیۡ خَلَقَ مِنَ الۡمَآءِ بَشَرًا فَجَعَلَہٗ نَسَبًا وَّ صِہۡرًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1700,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Relative (Blood Relations)",
      "hw": "رشتہ دار",
      "s": "«اُولُو الْاَرْحَام»",
      "d": "«اُولُو الْاَرْحَام» «وَ اُولُوا الۡاَرۡحَامِ بَعۡضُہُمۡ اَوۡلٰی بِبَعۡضٍ فِیۡ کِتٰبِ اللّٰہِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1701,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "Relative",
      "hw": "رشتہ دار",
      "s": "« » means the covenant made with relatives (27 verses: 2:144-4:24-5:3-5:119-9:10-9:38-9:58-9:59-9:83-9:87-9:93-9:96-9:100-10:7-19:6-19:55-20:109-27:19-33:51-46:15-48:18-58:22-69:21-88:9-89:28-98:8-101:7)",
      "d": "«اِلَّ» «اِلَّ» «اِلَّ الرَّجُل» «جَارَ بِہٖ» «لَا یَرۡقُبُوۡنَ فِیۡ مُؤۡمِنٍ اِلًّا وَّ لَا ذِمَّۃً» «ذِمَّۃ» «اِلَّ»"
    }
  ],
  "365": [
    {
      "id": 1702,
      "a": "خ",
      "h": "Pleasure / Approval",
      "hw": "خوشنودی",
      "s": "« » and « » are used in the meaning of mere pleasure, while « » includes the aspect of attention along with pleasure (18 verses: 2:207, 2:265, 3:15, 3:162, 3:174, 4:114, 5:2, 5:16, 9:21, 9:72, 9:109, 47:28, 48:29, 57:20, 57:27, 59:8, 60:1, 66:1).",
      "d": "«رَضِیَ» «رِضْوَان» «رَضْوَان» «مَرْضَاۃ» «یَبۡتَغُوۡنَ فَضۡلًا مِّنۡ رَّبِّہِمۡ وَ رِضۡوَانًا» «یٰۤاَیُّہَا النَّبِیُّ لِمَ تُحَرِّمُ مَاۤ اَحَلَّ اللّٰہُ لَکَ ۚ تَبۡتَغِیۡ مَرۡضَاتِ اَزۡوَاجِکَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1703,
      "a": "خ",
      "h": "Pleasure / Countenance",
      "hw": "خوشنودی",
      "s": "« » means 'face' (66 verses: 2:112, 2:115, 2:144, 2:148, 2:149, 2:150, 2:177, 2:272, 3:20, 3:106, 3:107, 4:43, 4:47, 4:125, 5:6, 5:108, 6:52, 6:79, 7:29, 8:50, 10:26, 10:27, 10:105, 12:9, 12:93, 12:96, 13:22, 14:50, 16:58, 17:7, 17:97, 18:28, 18:29, 20:111, 21:39, 22:11, 22:72, 23:104, 25:34, 27:90, 28:88, 30:30, 30:38, 30:39, 30:43, 31:22, 33:66, 39:24, 39:60, 43:17, 47:27, 48:29, 51:29, 54:48, 55:27, 67:22, 67:27, 75:22, 75:24, 76:9, 80:38, 80:40, 83:24, 88:2, 88:8, 92:20).",
      "d": "«وَجْہ» «وَجْہُ النَّھَار» «وَجْھ» «وَ مَا تُنۡفِقُوۡنَ اِلَّا ابۡتِغَآءَ وَجۡہِ اللّٰہِ»"
    }
  ],
  "366": [
    {
      "id": 1704,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To Desire / To Incline",
      "hw": "رغبت",
      "s": "« » means to desire or to have a heartfelt longing for something and to strive for its attainment (6 verses: 4:127, 9:59, 9:120, 21:90, 68:32, 94:8).",
      "d": "«رَغِبَ» «فَاِذَا فَرَغۡتَ فَانۡصَبۡ وَ اِلٰی رَبِّکَ فَارۡغَبۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1705,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To Compete / To Strive in Rivalry",
      "hw": "رغبت",
      "s": "« » refers to competition in the desire for good deeds (1 verse: 83:26).",
      "d": "«نَفِسَ» «نَفَّسَ فِی الْاَمْر» «تَنَافُس» «یُسۡقَوۡنَ مِنۡ رَّحِیۡقٍ مَّخۡتُوۡمٍ خِتٰمُہٗ مِسۡکٌ ؕ وَ فِیۡ ذٰلِکَ فَلۡیَتَنَافَسِ الۡمُتَنَافِسُوۡنَ»"
    }
  ],
  "367": [
    {
      "id": 1706,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to place",
      "hw": "رکھنا",
      "s": "« » is general: placing something whether it is seen or not (7 verses: 3:36, 18:49, 39:69, 46:15, 55:7, 55:10, 94:2)",
      "d": "«وَضَعَ» «رَفَعَ» «وَضَعَ» «رَفِیْع» «وَضِیْع» «وَضَع حَمَل»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ وَضَعۡنَا عَنۡکَ وِزۡرَکَ الَّذِیۡۤ اَنۡقَضَ ظَہۡرَکَ»\nTranslation: And We have removed from you your burden which had broken your back."
    },
    {
      "id": 1707,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "To Keep",
      "hw": "رکھنا",
      "s": "« » means to place something down such that others cannot see it (66 verses: 2:37-3:44-4:90-4:91-4:94-4:171-5:64-7:115-7:107-7:116-7:117-7:120-7:150-8:12-10:80-10:81-12:10-12:93-12:96-15:19-16:15-16:28-16:86-16:87-17:39-20:20-20:39-20:65-20:66-20:69-20:70-20:87-22:52-22:53-25:8-25:13-26:32-26:43-26:44-26:45-26:46-26:223-27:6-27:10-27:28-27:29-28:7-28:31-28:86-31:10-37:97-38:34-40:15-41:35-41:40-43:53-50:7-50:24-50:26-50:37-54:25-60:1-67:7-67:8-75:15-84:4)",
      "d": "«اَلْقٰی» «اَلْقٰی» «اَلْقٰی» «وَضَعَ» «وَ اَلۡقٰی فِی الۡاَرۡضِ رَوَاسِیَ»"
    }
  ],
  "368": [
    {
      "id": 1708,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "color",
      "hw": "رنگ",
      "s": "« » refers to natural color (6 verses: 16:13, 16:69, 30:22, 35:27, 35:28, 39:21)",
      "d": "« » means natural color, such as black, white, green, red, yellow, blue, etc. Its plural is « ».\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ مِنَ الۡجِبَالِ جُدَدٌۢ بِیۡضٌ وَّ حُمۡرٌ مُّخۡتَلِفٌ اَلۡوَانُہَا»\nTranslation: And among the mountains are streaks white and red, of varying colors."
    },
    {
      "id": 1709,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "color",
      "hw": "رنگ",
      "s": "« » is the color that is applied or dyed, whether material or spiritual (2 verses: 2:138, 23:20)",
      "d": "«صَبَغَ» «صَبَّاغ» «صَبَغَہ» «صَبَّغَ بِالْمَاءِ» «تَصَبَّغْ فِیْ دِیْنِہٖ»\nThe Quran states:\n«صِبۡغَۃَ اللّٰہِ ۚ وَ مَنۡ اَحۡسَنُ مِنَ اللّٰہِ صِبۡغَۃً»\nTranslation: [Our religion is] the color of Allah. And who is better than Allah in coloring? [i.e., whose religion is better or who gives a better color?]\nNote: (Baptism: A Christian religious ritual where a non-Christian is made a Christian by immersion in or sprinkling with dyed water)."
    }
  ],
  "370": [
    {
      "id": 1717,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "fasting person",
      "hw": "روزہ دار",
      "s": "« » refers to a fasting person (1 verse: 33:35)",
      "d": "« » (its plural is « ») means fasting. « » means to observe fast. That is, from the pre-dawn meal (suhoor) to the sunset meal (iftar), abstaining from eating, drinking, and certain other acts according to Islamic law. And « » means a fasting person.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ الصَّآئِمِیۡنَ وَ الصّٰٓئِمٰتِ»\nTranslation: And the men who fast and the women who fast."
    },
    {
      "id": 1718,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "fasting person",
      "hw": "روزہ دار",
      "s": "« » refers to a fasting person who, besides abstaining from food and drink, also observes other prohibitions (2 verses: 9:112, 66:5)",
      "d": "«سَیْح، اَلسَّاحَۃ» «سَاحَ»\nAnd « » also means to fast and to observe all its rulings, meaning to abstain not only from food and drink but also from the sins of the faculties like eyes, ears, tongue, etc. According to the author of 'Munjid', « » refers to a fasting person who resides in the mosque (Munjid).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اَلتَّآئِبُوۡنَ الۡعٰبِدُوۡنَ الۡحٰمِدُوۡنَ السَّآئِحُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: The repentant, the worshippers, the praisers, the fasting ones."
    }
  ],
  "371": [
    {
      "id": 1719,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/prevent",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » means to stop or prevent with the hand or tongue (13 verses: 2:114, 4:141, 7:12, 9:54, 12:63, 17:59, 17:94, 18:55, 20:92, 21:43, 38:75, 59:2, 107:7)",
      "d": "« » is primarily used in two meanings:\n(1) To not give (opposite of giving), to be stingy. And « » means a stingy person.\n(2) To stop someone with the hand or tongue; to not let someone do something; to deprive; to prevent.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ مَنۡ اَظۡلَمُ مِمَّنۡ مَّنَعَ مَسٰجِدَ اللّٰہِ اَنۡ یُّذۡکَرَ فِیۡہَا اسۡمُہٗ»\nTranslation: And who is more unjust than he who prevents the name of Allah from being mentioned in His mosques?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1720,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/prevent",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » means to stop from evil deeds (18 verses: 3:104, 3:110, 3:114, 4:31, 4:161, 6:26, 6:28, 7:165, 7:166, 9:67, 9:71, 11:116, 16:90, 22:41, 29:45, 58:8, 79:40, 96:9)",
      "d": "« » is generally used for stopping and refraining from evil deeds (munkarat).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اَمَّا مَنۡ خَافَ مَقَامَ رَبِّہٖ وَ نَہَی النَّفۡسَ عَنِ الۡہَوٰی»\nTranslation: But as for he who feared the position of his Lord and prevented the soul from [following] desire,"
    },
    {
      "id": 1721,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/prevent",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » means to prevent someone from good deeds (1 verse: 33:18)",
      "d": "«اَلْعَوْق وَالْعُوْق» «عَوَّقَ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«قَدۡ یَعۡلَمُ اللّٰہُ الۡمُعَوِّقِیۡنَ مِنۡکُمۡ وَ الۡقَآئِلِیۡنَ لِاِخۡوَانِہِمۡ ہُلُمَّ اِلَیۡنَا»\nTranslation: Allah knows those who hinder among you and those who say to their brothers, 'Come to us.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1722,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop/prevent",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » means to keep someone from something in order to gain some benefit (2 verses: 2:232, 4:19)",
      "d": "« » means to constrict, to prevent (Munjid), to hinder strictly (Mufradat). « » means a muscle. « » means to cause constriction, to be an obstacle in achieving a goal (Munjid). This word is generally used in the context of a man preventing his wife from marriage, constricting and troubling her, to gain some benefit from that action.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تَعۡضُلُوۡہُنَّ لِتَذۡہَبُوۡا بِبَعۡضِ مَاۤ اٰتَیۡتُمُوۡہُنَّ»\nTranslation: And do not constrain them [i.e., the women] in order to take back some of what you gave them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1723,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to not let something present slip from the hand (22 verses: 2:231-2:256-4:15-5:4-7:170-16:59-16:79-17:100-22:65-31:22-33:37-35:2-35:41-38:39-39:38-39:42-43:21-43:43-60:10-65:2-67:19-67:21)",
      "d": "« » means to cling to something and protect it (muf). This word is generally used when something is already in one's possession and is not let slip from the hand. And « » also comes in the meaning of miser.\n«فَاَمۡسِکُوۡہُنَّ بِمَعۡرُوۡفٍ اَوۡ سَرِّحُوۡہُنَّ بِمَعۡرُوۡفٍ»\nTranslation: So either keep them (the divorced women) with goodness or release them with goodness."
    },
    {
      "id": 1724,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to gradually stop someone from their intention with gentle conduct (37 verses: 2:217-3:99-4:55-4:61-4:160-4:167-5:2-5:91-7:45-7:86-8:34-8:36-8:47-9:34-11:19-13:33-14:3-14:10-16:94-20:16-22:25-27:24-27:43-28:87-29:38-34:32-34:43-40:37-43:37-43:62-47:1-47:32-47:34-48:25-58:16-63:2-63:5)",
      "d": "«صَدَّ» «صَدَّ عَنْ» «المیل اِلٰی اَحَدِ الْجَانِبَیْن وَ عَدَلَ عَنْہُ (م ل) وَ صَدّٓ» «مَنَعَ عَنْ قَصْدِ الشَّیْءُ خَاصَۃٌ» «صَدّ»\n«وَ تَذُوۡقُوا السُّوۡٓءَ بِمَا صَدَدۡتُّمۡ  عَنۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And now taste the evil consequence of what you used to prevent from the way of Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 1725,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to encircle and stop, and to constrict (4 verses: 2:196-2:273-4:90-9:5)",
      "d": "« » means to encircle, to besiege, to make someone's place narrow. And « » means fortress. And « » means to besiege and prevent reinforcements. (manjad)\n«لِلۡفُقَرَآءِ الَّذِیۡنَ اُحۡصِرُوۡا فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ لَا یَسۡتَطِیۡعُوۡنَ ضَرۡبًا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ»\nTranslation: (This spending) is for the poor who are restrained in the way of Allah and cannot travel in the land."
    },
    {
      "id": 1726,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop by fencing (1 verse: 17:20)",
      "d": "« » means to fence around something for its protection or to gather something and fence around it.\n«وَ مَا  کَانَ  عَطَـآءُ  رَبِّکَ  مَحۡظُوۡرًا»\nTranslation: And the reward of your Lord is not restricted."
    },
    {
      "id": 1727,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop out of reverence from one's intention (8 verses: 2:125-2:187-7:138-20:91-20:97-21:52-22:25-26:71)",
      "d": "« » means to focus on something with reverence and remain attached to it (muf). To remain confined. To stay stopped. To be imprisoned (manjad).\n«عَنِ الۡمَسۡجِدِ الۡحَرَامِ  وَ الۡہَدۡیَ مَعۡکُوۡفًا اَنۡ یَّبۡلُغَ مَحِلَّہٗ»\nTranslation: They are the ones who disbelieved and prevented you from the Sacred Mosque and prevented the offerings from reaching their place."
    },
    {
      "id": 1728,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop an attack or defend (5 verses: 4:77-4:91-5:11-21:39-48:24)",
      "d": "« » means palm of the hand. And « » means to stop a strike with the palm, to defend, to save, to stop (muf). Then this word started to be used for stopping a strike or for defense.\n«اِذۡ ہَمَّ قَوۡمٌ اَنۡ یَّبۡسُطُوۡۤا اِلَیۡکُمۡ  اَیۡدِیَہُمۡ فَکَفَّ اَیۡدِیَہُمۡ عَنۡکُمۡ»\nTranslation: When a people intended to stretch their hands towards you, so He stopped their hands from you."
    },
    {
      "id": 1729,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop and delay due to sluggishness (1 verse: 9:46)",
      "d": "«ثَبَّطَ» «اَثْبَطَہُ الْمَرْض» «ثَبَّطَہُ الْمَرْض»\n«وَ لَوۡ  اَرَادُوا الۡخُرُوۡجَ لَاَعَدُّوۡا  لَہٗ  عُدَّۃً وَّ لٰکِنۡ  کَرِہَ  اللّٰہُ  انۡۢبِعَاثَہُمۡ  فَثَبَّطَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: And if they had intended to go forth, they would have prepared for it some preparation. But Allah disliked their being sent, so He stopped them."
    },
    {
      "id": 1730,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to push away and keep stopped, not let come near (1 verse: 28:23)",
      "d": "«ذَادَ» «ذَوَّدَ عَنْ حَسْبِہٖ»\n«وَ  وَجَدَ مِنۡ دُوۡنِہِمُ  امۡرَاَتَیۡنِ تَذُوۡدٰنِ»\nTranslation: And he found besides them two women who were keeping (their flocks) stopped."
    },
    {
      "id": 1731,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop for the sake of arrangement and order (3 verses: 27:17-27:83-41:19)",
      "d": "«وَزَعَ» «وَزَعَ الْجَیْش» «اَلْاَوْزَع» «اَلْوَزْعَۃُ» «وَازِعُ» «وَزَعَ»\n«وَ حُشِرَ لِسُلَیۡمٰنَ جُنُوۡدُہٗ  مِنَ الۡجِنِّ وَ الۡاِنۡسِ  وَ الطَّیۡرِ  فَہُمۡ  یُوۡزَعُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And gathered for Solomon were his hosts of the jinn, humans, and birds, and they were arranged in groups."
    },
    {
      "id": 1732,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop from standing, to stop from going (2 verses: 5:106-11:8)",
      "d": "« » means to imprison, to protect completely, to prevent (manjad). And to mean to stop someone from rising. (muf)\n«تَحۡبِسُوۡنَہُمَا مِنۡۢ بَعۡدِ الصَّلٰوۃِ»\nTranslation: So detain the two of them after the prayer."
    },
    {
      "id": 1733,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "«حِجْرًا مَّھْجُوْرًا»",
      "d": "«حَجَرَ» «حِجْرًا مَّھْجُوْرًا» «حِجْرًا مَّھْجُوْرًا»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«یَوۡمَ یَرَوۡنَ الۡمَلٰٓئِکَۃَ  لَا بُشۡرٰی یَوۡمَئِذٍ لِّلۡمُجۡرِمِیۡنَ وَ یَقُوۡلُوۡنَ حِجۡرًا مَّحۡجُوۡرًا»\nTranslation: On the day they see the angels, there will be no good news for the criminals that day, and they will say, '[May God] keep [you] away and sealed [from us]' (Jalandhari)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1734,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to stop from obscenities and nonsense. (19 verses: 2:192-2:193-2:275-4:171-5:73-5:91-8:19-8:38-8:39-9:12-19:46-26:116-26:167-33:60-36:18-53:14-53:42-59:7-96:15)",
      "d": "« » means to stop, to return. To adhere to the prohibition of obscenities and nonsense and to abandon them.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ یَصُدَّکُمۡ عَنۡ ذِکۡرِ اللّٰہِ وَ عَنِ الصَّلٰوۃِ ۚ فَہَلۡ اَنۡتُمۡ مُّنۡتَہُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And (so that Satan may) keep you away from the remembrance of Allah and from prayer. Then will you desist?"
    },
    {
      "id": 1735,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » heart becoming hard and stingy after spending a little. (2 verses: 7:58-53:34)",
      "d": "«اَلْکُدْیَۃ» «حَفَرَ فَاکْدٰی» «کَدّٰی» «سَاَلَہٗ فَاَکْدٰی»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ اَعۡطٰی قَلِیۡلًا  وَّ  اَکۡدٰی»\nTranslation: He gave a little, then stopped (withheld his hand)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1737,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to stop",
      "hw": "روکنا",
      "s": "« » to suddenly stop a started task. (1 verse: 11:44)",
      "d": "« » means to abandon a task, to leave it, and to stop (manjad). To suddenly abandon an ongoing task.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ قِیۡلَ یٰۤاَرۡضُ ابۡلَعِیۡ مَآءَکِ وَ یٰسَمَآءُ اَقۡلِعِیۡ وَ غِیۡضَ الۡمَآءُ»\nTranslation: And it was said, 'O earth, swallow your water, and O sky, cease,' and the water subsided."
    }
  ],
  "372": [
    {
      "id": 1738,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "to crush",
      "hw": "روندنا",
      "s": "« » to crush and pulverize or to break and smash. (1 verse: 27:18)",
      "d": "« » means to break, to twist. And « » is a fierce wind that breaks everything and leaves it destroyed. And « » is something broken, twisted, or pulverized (manjad). This word is used for crushing something to pieces.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«قَالَتۡ نَمۡلَۃٌ  یّٰۤاَیُّہَا النَّمۡلُ ادۡخُلُوۡا مَسٰکِنَکُمۡ ۚ لَا یَحۡطِمَنَّکُمۡ  سُلَیۡمٰنُ  وَ جُنُوۡدُہٗ  ۙ وَ ہُمۡ  لَا یَشۡعُرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: An ant said, 'O ants, enter your dwellings, lest Solomon and his armies crush you while they are unaware.'"
    }
  ],
  "373": [
    {
      "id": 1740,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "splendor",
      "hw": "رونق",
      "s": "« » is used for the external glow and splendor of worldly plants. (1 verse: 20:131)",
      "d": "«زَھْرَۃ» «زَھْرَۃُ الدُّنْیَا»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ لَا تَمُدَّنَّ عَیۡنَیۡکَ  اِلٰی مَا مَتَّعۡنَا بِہٖۤ اَزۡوَاجًا مِّنۡہُمۡ زَہۡرَۃَ الۡحَیٰوۃِ  الدُّنۡیَا»\nTranslation: And do not extend your eyes toward that which We have given some of them to enjoy, [as] the adornment of the worldly life."
    },
    {
      "id": 1742,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "splendor",
      "hw": "رونق",
      "s": "« » comes for the splendor of plants. (3 verses: 22:5-27:60-50:7)",
      "d": "« » means anything that pleases the heart, and its basic meaning is delight. According to Khalil, it is related to the good color and freshness of something. For humans, it also comes, but it is mostly used for the freshness, verdancy, and bloom of plants, for plants being in full blossom.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ اَنۡزَلَ لَکُمۡ مِّنَ السَّمَآءِ مَآءً ۚ فَاَنۡۢبَتۡنَا بِہٖ حَدَآئِقَ ذَاتَ بَہۡجَۃٍ»\nTranslation: And He sent down for you from the sky water, and We grew thereby gardens of beautiful bloom."
    }
  ],
  "374": [
    {
      "id": 1743,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "sand",
      "hw": "ریت",
      "s": "« » that sand which at noon in deserts appears as water due to intense sunlight. (2 verses: 24:39-78:20)",
      "d": "« » is that sand which at noon in forests or deserts appears as water due to the intensity of sunlight. Every drinkable thing is called « ». And that which appears to be wine but is not drinkable is called « » (mufrad). Then metaphorically, it is used for any unreal thing, and generally, this word is used for that vast field of sand which, when seen from a distance at an angle in the sunlight, seems to shimmer like water.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«کَسَرَابٍۭ بِقِیۡعَۃٍ یَّحۡسَبُہُ الظَّمۡاٰنُ مَآءً»\nTranslation: Like a mirage in a plain which the thirsty one thinks is water."
    },
    {
      "id": 1744,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "sand",
      "hw": "ریت",
      "s": "« » a mound of loose, slipping sand. (1 verse: 73:14)",
      "d": "« » a long, wide sandhill (fal 272).\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«یَوۡمَ تَرۡجُفُ الۡاَرۡضُ وَ الۡجِبَالُ وَ کَانَتِ الۡجِبَالُ  کَثِیۡبًا مَّہِیۡلًا»\nTranslation: The day the earth and the mountains will shake, and the mountains will be like loose sand dunes."
    },
    {
      "id": 1745,
      "a": "ر",
      "h": "sand",
      "hw": "ریت",
      "s": "« » a vast field comprising many sand dunes. (1 verse: 46:21)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « », meaning a field with many sand dunes. And « » means a vast field spread over hundreds of miles of sand (manjad). And also means the region of inhabited quarter western Yemen, which was the center of the people of Ad (maq).\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ اذۡکُرۡ  اَخَا عَادٍ ؕ اِذۡ  اَنۡذَرَ قَوۡمَہٗ بِالۡاَحۡقَافِ»\nTranslation: And remember the brother of Ad, when he warned his people in the sandy region of Al-Ahqaf."
    }
  ],
  "375": [
    {
      "id": 1748,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Excess",
      "hw": "زائد",
      "s": "« » means double or more than the original amount. Also see 'increase; to increase' (8 verses: 2:265-7:38-17:75-30:39-33:30-33:68-34:37-38:61)",
      "d": "«ضِعْف» «اِذًا لَّاَذَقۡنٰکَ ضِعۡفَ الۡحَیٰوۃِ وَ ضِعۡفَ الۡمَمَاتِ ثُمَّ لَا تَجِدُ لَکَ عَلَیۡنَا نَصِیۡرًا » «ضِعْف» «ضِعْفَیْن» «کَمَثَلِ جَنَّۃٍۭ بِرَبۡوَۃٍ اَصَابَہَا وَابِلٌ فَاٰتَتۡ اُکُلَہَا ضِعۡفَیۡنِ» «ضَاعَفَ» «وَ اللّٰہُ یُضٰاعِفُ لِمَنۡ یَّشَآءُ»"
    }
  ],
