      "a": "س",
      "h": "Severe",
      "hw": "سخت",
      "s": "« » Severe and devoid of good (1 verse: 11:77)",
      "d": "«عَصَبَ» «عَصَبَہ» «اَعْصَاب» «عُصْبَۃ» «وَنَحْنُ عُصْبَۃً» «تَعَصُّبْ» «عَصِیْب»\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«وَ لَمَّا جَآءَتۡ رُسُلُنَا لُوۡطًا سِیۡٓءَ بِہِمۡ وَ ضَاقَ بِہِمْ ذَرۡعًا وَّ قَالَ ہٰذَا یَوۡمٌ عَصِیۡبٌ»\nTranslation: When Our messengers came to Lut, he was distressed by their presence and felt helpless because of them, and he said, 'This is a day of severe distress.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 1842,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Severe",
      "hw": "سخت",
      "s": "« » Severe in terms of evil (1 verse: 76:10)",
      "d": "« » means causing hearts to be severely restless, impatient, and disturbed (fem.). « » is that wood which is used for stretching the feet of criminals and for administering punishment (M. Q.). And « » means severe evil or intense days (Majid).\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«اِنَّا نَخَافُ مِنۡ رَّبِّنَا یَوۡمًا عَبُوۡسًا قَمۡطَرِیۡرًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, we fear from our Lord a day that is frowning and severe."
    },
