      "hw": "سرکشی",
      "s": "« » to be rebellious, then to surpass in it, to fly (3 verses: 4:117-9:101-22:3)",
      "d": "«مَرَدَ» «مَرَدَ» «اِنۡ یَّدۡعُوۡنَ  اِلَّا شَیۡطٰنًا مَّرِیۡدًا»"
    }
  ],
  "398": [
    {
      "id": 1868,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Tunnel",
      "hw": "سرنگ",
      "s": "« » a tunnel with two openings (1 verse: 6:35)",
      "d": "«نَفَق» «نَیْفَقُ السَّرَاوِیْل» «نَافِقَاءَ الْیَرْبُوْع» «نَافَقَ الْیَرْبُوْعُ وَ نَفَقَ» «فَاِنِ اسۡتَطَعۡتَ اَنۡ تَبۡتَغِیَ نَفَقًا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ اَوۡ  سُلَّمًا فِی السَّمَآءِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 1869,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Tunnel",
      "hw": "سرنگ",
      "s": "« » is a tunnel that has only one opening (1 Verse: 18:61)",
      "d": "«سَرَب» «سَرَبَ» «اِنْسَرَبَتِ الْحَیَّۃُ اِلٰی جُحْرِھَا»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فَلَمَّا بَلَغَا مَجۡمَعَ بَیۡنِہِمَا نَسِیَا حُوۡتَہُمَا فَاتَّخَذَ سَبِیۡلَہٗ  فِی الۡبَحۡرِ  سَرَبًا»\nTranslation: Then when they reached the meeting point of the two rivers, they forgot their fish, and it made its way into the sea as if through a tunnel."
    }
  ],
  "399": [
    {
      "id": 1870,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Sluggishness / To be Sluggish",
      "hw": "سست",
      "s": "« » To be sluggish due to indifference or lack of interest (2 Verses: 4:142-9:54)",
      "d": "« » means to feel heavy or sluggish in one's nature due to lack of desire or indifference. To be lazy. To be loose, flabby, or to remain in such a state (intransitive).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اِذَا قَامُوۡۤا اِلَی الصَّلٰوۃِ قَامُوۡا کُسَالٰی»\nTranslation: And when these (hypocrites) stand up for prayer, they stand up lazily and sluggishly."
    },
    {
      "id": 1871,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Sluggishness / To be Sluggish",
      "hw": "سست",
      "s": "« » To be sluggish due to physical or moral weakness (8 Verses: 3:139-3:146-4:104-47:35-8:18-19:4-29:41-31:14)",
      "d": "« » means to become sluggish due to physical or moral weakness (intransitive).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تَہِنُوۡا فِی ابۡتِغَآءِ الۡقَوۡمِ»\nTranslation: And do not be sluggish in pursuing this (disbelieving) people."
    },
    {
      "id": 1872,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Sluggishness / To be Sluggish",
      "hw": "سست",
      "s": "« » To be sluggish due to carelessness (1 Verse: 20:42)",
      "d": "« » means to fall short, to be remiss, to be sluggish (Majid). It means not to make an effort despite having the power and capacity to do so.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«اِذۡہَبۡ اَنۡتَ وَ اَخُوۡکَ بِاٰیٰتِیۡ وَ لَا تَنِیَا فِیۡ  ذِکۡرِیۡ»\nTranslation: O Moses! Go you and your brother with My signs and do not be sluggish in remembering Me."
    },
    {
      "id": 1873,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Sluggishness / To be Sluggish",
      "hw": "سست",
      "s": "« » To be sluggish due to fatigue (1 Verse: 21:19)",
      "d": "«حَسَرَ» «حَسَرَ الْبَصَرَ» «حَسِیْر» «حَسَرَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ مَنۡ عِنۡدَہٗ  لَا یَسۡتَکۡبِرُوۡنَ عَنۡ عِبَادَتِہٖ وَ لَا یَسۡتَحۡسِرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And those who are with Him (the angels) do not disdain His worship, nor do they become weary/fed up."
    },
    {
      "id": 1874,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "Sluggishness / To be Sluggish",
      "hw": "سست",
      "s": "« » To be sluggish in movement or habitually sluggish, and then to cause delay (1 Verse: 4:72)",
      "d": "« » means to delay in moving and to be sluggish. And « » means sluggishness in movement, laziness, indolence. And « » means to be extremely sluggish and to delay (intransitive).\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اِنَّ مِنۡکُمۡ لَمَنۡ لَّیُبَطِّئَنَّ»\nTranslation: And indeed, there are some among you who would certainly delay (intentionally)."
    }
  ],
  "400": [
    {
      "id": 1875,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "To Travel",
      "hw": "سفر",
      "s": "« » The general word for traveling (7 Verses: 2:184-2:185-2:283-4:43-5:6-9:42-18:62)",
      "d": "« » means to depart from one's place of residence (M. L). And it means to cover a distance. This word is general. Whether the travel is for any purpose.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اِنۡ کُنۡتُمۡ مَّرۡضٰۤی اَوۡ عَلٰی سَفَرٍ»\nTranslation: If you are ill or on a journey."
    },
    {
      "id": 1876,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "To Travel",
      "hw": "سفر",
      "s": "« » To travel in different directions in a vast field, touring and sightseeing (1 Verse: 9:2)",
      "d": "«سَاحَ الْمَاءَ» «سَاحَۃ» «سَاحَۃُ الدَّار» «سَاحَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فَسِیۡحُوۡا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ اَرۡبَعَۃَ  اَشۡہُرٍ»\nTranslation: So travel freely in the land for four months (O disbelievers)."
    },
    {
      "id": 1877,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "To Travel",
      "hw": "سفر",
      "s": "« » To migrate or relocate (1 Verse: 16:80)",
      "d": "« » means to migrate. To depart from one place and go to another. To relocate (intransitive, M. L). « » means the rope for tying a camel's howdah (palanquin). « » means pack animals (camels that carry loads and move from one place to another). « » means a howdah (palanquin). And a woman who often resides in journeys and a howdah.\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«وَّ جَعَلَ لَکُمۡ مِّنۡ جُلُوۡدِ الۡاَنۡعَامِ بُیُوۡتًا تَسۡتَخِفُّوۡنَہَا یَوۡمَ ظَعۡنِکُمۡ وَ یَوۡمَ اِقَامَتِکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And He has made for you from the hides of cattle homes which you find light on the day of your migration and the day of your staying."
    },
    {
      "id": 1878,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "To Travel",
      "hw": "سفر",
      "s": "« » To set out on an expedition or to go out to face an enemy (10 Verses: 4:71-9:38-9:39-9:41-9:81-9:122-46:29-18:34-46:29-72:1)",
      "d": "«اَلنَّفِیْر» «اَلنَّفِیْرُ الْعَام» «نَفَرَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran states:\n«فَانۡفِرُوۡا ثُبَاتٍ اَوِ انۡفِرُوۡا جَمِیۡعًا»\nTranslation: Then set out (to battle), whether in small groups or all together."
    },
    {
      "id": 1880,
      "a": "س",
      "h": "To journey",
      "hw": "سفر",
      "s": "« » to migrate; to set out on a journey (3 verses: 12:70-12:75-106:2)",
      "d": "«اَلرَّحْل» «رَحَل» «اٖلٰفِہِمۡ  رِحۡلَۃَ  الشِّتَآءِ  وَ الصَّیۡفِ»"
    }
  ],
