  "479": [
    {
      "id": 2229,
      "a": "ک",
      "h": "Paper",
      "hw": "کاغذ",
      "s": "« » refers to any thin and soft thing that can be written on, whether blank or written. (1 verse: 52:3)",
      "d": "«رَقّ» «رِقَّت» «قساوت» «رَقّ» «رَقّ» «وَرْق» «اَوْرَاق» «وَ کِتٰبٍ مَّسۡطُوۡرٍ فِیۡ  رَقٍّ مَّنۡشُوۡرٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2230,
      "a": "ک",
      "h": "Paper",
      "hw": "کاغذ",
      "s": "« » means written paper or documents; the early rag-pulp form of modern paper (1 Verse: 6:7)",
      "d": "« » means a written letter or document (Majid), whether it consists of several pages or sheets (M. Q.). 'Qirtas al-abyad' is a famous phrase meaning a clear and complete report issued on an important issue. « » actually also refers to that early rag-pulp form of paper which the Egyptians invented. At the time of the Quran's revelation, such paper was available but very rare.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ لَوۡ نَزَّلۡنَا عَلَیۡکَ کِتٰبًا فِیۡ قِرۡطَاسٍ فَلَمَسُوۡہُ بِاَیۡدِیۡہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And even if We had sent down to you a written message on paper, and they had touched it with their hands..."
    }
  ],
  "480": [
    {
      "id": 2231,
      "a": "ک",
      "h": "To be sufficient",
      "hw": "کافی",
      "s": "« » means to be sufficient. To suffice for something and be independent of others. (30 verses: 2:137-3:124-4:6-4:45-4:50-4:55-4:70-4:79-4:81-4:132-4:166-4:171-10:29-13:43-15:95-17:14-17:17-17:65-17:96-21:47-25:31-25:58-29:51-29:52-33:3-33:25-33:39-33:48-46:8-48:28)",
      "d": "«کَفٰی» «کَفٰی» «کَفٰی بِاللہِ شَہِیْدَا» «کَفَایَۃ» «مَکَافَات» «کَفٰی» «وَ کَفَی اللّٰہُ  الۡمُؤۡمِنِیۡنَ الۡقِتَالَ ؕ وَ کَانَ  اللّٰہُ   قَوِیًّا عَزِیۡزًا» «کَفٰی» «حَسْب» «حَسۡبُہٗ جَہَنَّم» «وَ کَفٰی  بِجَہَنَّم» «کَفٰی» «حَسْب» «وَ کَفٰی بِاللّٰہِ حَسِیۡبًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2232,
      "a": "ک",
      "h": "To Be Sufficient",
      "hw": "کافی",
      "s": "« » means to reckon, to count, to enumerate, then to keep an account of it. (11 Verses: 2:206-3:173-5:104-8:62-8:64-9:59-9:68-9:129-39:38-58:8-65:3)",
      "d": "« » means to reckon, to count, to enumerate, then to keep an account of it. And « » is a verbal noun, meaning to keep an account of something in consideration of each individual thing. There is no specific word in Urdu for this meaning. Therefore, its translation is taken as 'sufficient' (kafi). However, in Punjabi, there is a word for it: 'eichi bechi', meaning to keep an account of each need. Which conveys this meaning. That is, this matter or this work is sufficient for each of our needs and requirements. In other words, the word « » is stronger than « ». For example, the Quran states:\n«حَسۡبُنَا اللّٰہُ وَ نِعۡمَ الۡوَکِیۡلُ»\nTranslation: Allah is sufficient for us, and He is the best Disposer of affairs."
    }
  ],
  "481": [
    {
      "id": 2234,
      "a": "ک",
      "h": "To be of use",
      "hw": "کام",
      "s": "« » means to be of use and to bring benefit. (10 verses: 7:48-11:101-12:67-15:84-26:207-39:50-40:82-46:26-69:28-111:2)",
      "d": "«اَغْنٰی» «مَاۤ  اَغۡنٰی عَنِّیۡ  مَالِیَہۡ ہَلَکَ عَنِّیۡ  سُلۡطٰنِیَہۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2235,
      "a": "ک",
      "h": "Work; to do work",
      "hw": "کام",
      "s": "« » is an action that may be done intentionally or unintentionally. (85 verses: 2:24-2:68-2:71-2:85-2:197-2:215-2:231-2:234-2:240-2:253-2:279-2:282-3:28-3:40-3:115-3:135-3:188-4:25-4:30-4:66-4:114-4:127-4:147-5:67-5:79-6:112-6:137-6:159-7:28-7:155-7:173-8:73-10:36-10:46-10:106-11:36-11:87-12:32-12:89-14:27-14:45-16:33-16:35-16:50-16:91-18:82-21:23-21:59-21:62-21:63-21:73-22:14-22:18-22:77-24:41-25:68-26:19-26:20-26:74-26:226-27:34-27:88-30:40-33:6-34:54-37:34-37:102-39:70-42:25-46:9-49:6-54:52-58:13-60:1-61:2-61:3-63:9-66:6-75:25-77:18-82:12-83:36-85:7-89:6-105:1)",
      "d": "«فِعْل» «افعال» «فَعْلَۃً» «وَ فَعَلۡتَ فَعۡلَتَکَ الَّتِیۡ فَعَلۡتَ وَ اَنۡتَ مِنَ الۡکٰفِرِیۡنَ» «فَافۡعَلُوۡا مَا تُؤۡمَرُوۡنَ»"
