      "d": "«مِلْک» «مَالِک» «مٰلِکِ یَوۡمِ الدِّیۡنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2584,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Owner",
      "hw": "مالک",
      "s": "« » household, family, owner of the house (69 verses: 2:196-2:126-2:217-3:121-4:25-4:35-4:58-4:75-4:92-5:89-6:131-7:83-7:94-7:100-7:123-10:24-11:40-11:45-11:46-11:81-11:117-12:26-12:62-12:65-12:88-12:93-15:65-18:71-18:77-19:16-19:55-20:10-20:29-20:132-21:76-21:84-23:27-24:27-26:169-26:170-27:7-27:34-27:49-27:57-28:4-28:15-28:29-28:59-29:31-29:32-29:33-29:34-35:43-36:50-37:76-37:134-38:43-39:15-42:45-48:11-48:12-48:26-51:26-52:26-66:6-75:33-83:31-84:9-84:13)",
      "d": "«اَھْل» «اَھْلَ الرَّجُل» «اَھَلَ الرَّجُل» «اَھْل» «اَھْل» «فَانۡکِحُوۡہُنَّ بِاِذۡنِ اَہۡلِہِنَّ»"
    }
  ],
  "565": [
    {
      "id": 2585,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Mother",
      "hw": "ماں",
      "s": "« » a woman who has given birth (3 verses: 2:233-5:110-19:32)",
      "d": "«وَالِدَۃ» «وَالِدَین» «وَالِدَات» «وَ الۡوَالِدٰتُ یُرۡضِعۡنَ اَوۡلَادَہُنَّ حَوۡلَیۡنِ کَامِلَیۡنِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2586,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Mother",
      "hw": "ماں",
      "s": "« » means biological mother. (29 verses: 3:7-4:11-4:23-5:17-5:75-5:116-6:92-7:150-13:39-16:78-19:28-20:38-20:40-23:50-24:61-28:7-28:10-28:13-31:14-33:4-33:6-39:6-42:7-43:4-46:15-53:32-58:2-80:35-101:9)",
      "d": "The word « » is used in a very broad meaning. « » means both the biological mother and every thing that becomes the cause of the existence, origination, or reform and training of another thing (muf). The word « » is used in the following ways:\n«وَ اَوۡحَیۡنَاۤ  اِلٰۤی اُمِّ مُوۡسٰۤی اَنۡ  اَرۡضِعِیۡہِ»\n(2) Just as the word « » is used for the biological father as well as the grandfather, great-grandfather, and upwards through generations, similarly the word « » is also used. Just as Prophet Adam (AS) is the father of mankind, similarly Hawwa (AS) is the mother of mankind.\n«اُمُّ الْقُرٰی»\n«اَلنَّبِیُّ  اَوۡلٰی بِالۡمُؤۡمِنِیۡنَ مِنۡ اَنۡفُسِہِمۡ وَ اَزۡوَاجُہٗۤ  اُمَّہٰتُہُمۡ»\n(5) As a nickname. Then in this nickname, sometimes there is a clear connection, like «Umm Arba' wa Arba'in», and sometimes there is not even a minor connection, like naming a newborn girl Umm Kulthum. However, such nicknames are not mentioned in the Quran."
    }
  ],
  "566": [
