      "h": "To have intercourse",
      "hw": "مجامعت",
      "s": "«Rafath» any speech whose expression is considered shameful (2 verses: 2:187-2:197)",
      "d": "«Rafath» «أُحِلَّ لَكُمْ لَيْلَةَ الصِّيَامِ الرَّفَثُ إِلَىٰ نِسَائِكُمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2609,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To have intercourse",
      "hw": "مجامعت",
      "s": "«Mass» to touch something or for something to come in contact with the body (56 verses: 2:80-2:214-2:236-2:237-2:275-3:24-3:47-3:120-3:140-3:174-5:73-6:7-6:17-6:49-7:73-7:95-7:188-7:201-8:68-10:12-10:21-10:107-11:10-11:48-11:64-11:113-12:88-15:48-15:54-16:53-17:67-17:83-19:20-19:45-20:97-21:46-21:83-24:14-24:35-26:156-30:33-33:49-35:35-36:18-38:41-39:8-39:49-39:61-41:49-41:50-41:51-50:38-54:48-56:79-70:20-70:21)",
      "d": "«Mass» «قَالَتْ رَبِّ أَنَّىٰ يَكُونُ لِي وَلَدٌ وَلَمْ يَمْسَسْنِي بَشَرٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2610,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To have intercourse",
      "hw": "مجامعت",
      "s": "«Lāmasa» to touch something with fingers or to search with fingers or another body part (2 verses: 4:43-5:6)",
      "d": "«Lamasa» «أَوْ لَامَسْتُمُ النِّسَاءَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2611,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To have intercourse",
      "hw": "مجامعت",
      "s": "«Ṭamath» menstrual blood (2 verses: 55:56-55:74)",
      "d": "«Ṭamath» «Ṭamitha yaṭmithu» «لَمْ يَطْمِثْهُنَّ إِنْسٌ قَبْلَهُمْ وَلَا جَانٌّ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2612,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To have intercourse",
      "hw": "مجامعت",
      "s": "«Qaruba» to be near (36 verses: 2:35-2:187-2:222-2:237-3:167-4:11-4:43-4:172-5:8-5:82-6:151-6:152-7:19-7:114-9:28-9:99-12:60-16:77-17:32-17:34-17:57-18:24-18:81-19:52-22:13-26:42-34:37-39:3-46:28-50:16-51:27-56:11-56:85-56:88-83:21-83:28)",
      "d": "«Qaruba» «وَلَا تَقْرَبُوهُنَّ حَتَّىٰ يَطْهُرْنَ»"
    }
  ],
  "570": [
    {
      "id": 2613,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Assembly",
      "hw": "مجلس",
      "s": "'Majlis' refers to members of the household or friends when they sit together (1 verse: 58:11)",
      "d": "«اِذَا قِیۡلَ لَکُمۡ تَفَسَّحُوۡا فِی الۡمَجٰلِسِ فَافۡسَحُوۡا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2614,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Assembly",
      "hw": "مجلس",
      "s": "'Nadi' refers to specific places such as clubs, gatherings, entertainment venues where assemblies typically engage in undesirable activities (2 verses: 29:29-96:17)",
      "d": "«وَ تَاۡتُوۡنَ فِیۡ نَادِیۡکُمُ الۡمُنۡکَرَ»"
    }
  ],
  "571": [
    {
      "id": 2616,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love. To love.",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "'Wadda' means to desire something, to befriend, to love (25 verses: 2:96-2:105-2:109-2:266-3:30-3:69-3:118-4:42-4:73-4:89-4:102-5:82-11:90-15:2-19:96-29:25-30:21-33:20-42:23-60:1-60:2-60:7-68:9-70:11-85:14)",
      "d": "«رُبَمَا یَوَدُّ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا لَوۡ کَانُوۡا مُسۡلِمِیۡنَ» «اِنَّ الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا وَ عَمِلُوا الصّٰلِحٰتِ سَیَجۡعَلُ لَہُمُ الرَّحۡمٰنُ وُدًّا» «اِنَّ رَبِّیۡ رَحِیۡمٌ وَّدُوۡدٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2617,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love. To love.",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "'Alafa' means a love that arises from harmony (2 verses: 3:103-8:63)",
      "d": "«لَوۡ اَنۡفَقۡتَ مَا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ جَمِیۡعًا مَّاۤ اَلَّفۡتَ بَیۡنَ قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2618,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love. To love.",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "'Shaghafa Hubbun' such a love that has penetrated to the innermost part of the heart (1 verse: 12:30)",
      "d": "«قَدۡ شَغَفَہَا حُبًّا»"
    }
  ],
  "573": [
    {
      "id": 2622,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Labor. Toil. To do. To bear.",
      "hw": "محنت",
      "s": "'Amila' means to labor, to work for wages. This word is also common and its usage is common (309 verses: 2:25-2:62-2:74-2:82-2:85-2:96-2:110-2:134-2:139-2:140-2:141-2:144-2:149-2:167-2:217-2:233-2:234-2:237-2:265-2:271-2:277-2:283-3:22-3:30-3:57-3:98-3:99-3:120-3:153-3:156-3:163-3:180-3:195-4:17-4:18-4:57-4:94-4:108-4:110-4:122-4:123-4:124-4:128-4:135-4:173-5:5-5:8-5:9-5:53-5:62-5:66-5:69-5:71-5:90-5:93-5:105-6:43-6:54-6:60-6:88-6:108-6:122-6:127-6:132-6:135-7:42-7:43-7:53-7:118-7:129-7:139-7:147-7:153-7:180-8:39-8:47-8:48-8:72-9:9-9:16-9:17-9:37-9:69-9:94-9:102-9:105-9:120-9:121-10:4-10:9-10:12-10:14-10:23-10:41-10:61-10:81-11:7-11:11-11:15-11:16-11:23-11:46-11:78-11:92-11:93-11:111-11:112-11:121-11:123-12:19-12:69-13:29-14:18-14:23-14:42-15:93-16:28-16:32-16:34-16:63-16:93-16:96-16:97-16:111-16:119-17:9-17:84-18:2-18:7-18:30-18:49-18:79-18:88-18:103-18:105-18:107-18:110-19:60-19:96-20:75-20:82-20:112-21:27-21:74-21:82-21:94-22:14-22:23-22:50-22:56-22:68-23:51-23:63-23:100-24:24-24:28-24:38-24:39-24:53-24:55-24:64-25:23-25:70-25:71-26:112-26:168-26:169-26:188-26:216-26:227-27:4-27:19-27:24-27:84-27:90-27:93-28:15-28:55-28:67-28:80-28:84-29:4-29:7-29:8-29:9-29:38-29:55-29:58-30:15-30:41-30:44-30:45-31:8-31:15-31:23-31:29-32:12-32:14-32:17-32:19-33:2-33:9-33:19-33:31-33:71-34:4-34:11-34:12-34:13-34:25-34:33-34:37-35:7-35:8-35:10-35:37-36:35-36:54-36:71-37:39-37:61-37:96-38:24-38:28-39:7-39:35-39:39-39:65-39:70-40:37-40:40-40:58-41:5-41:8-41:20-41:22-41:27-41:33-41:40-41:46-41:50-42:15-42:22-42:23-42:26-43:72-45:15-45:21-45:28-45:29-45:30-45:33-46:14-46:15-46:16-46:19-47:1-47:2-47:4-47:8-47:9-47:12-47:14-47:28-47:30-47:32-47:33-47:35-48:11-48:24-48:29-49:2-49:14-49:18-52:16-52:19-52:21-53:31-56:24-57:4-57:10-58:3-58:6-58:7-58:11-58:13-58:15-59:18-60:3-62:8-63:2-63:11-64:2-64:7-64:8-64:9-65:11-66:7-66:11-67:2-77:43-84:25-85:11-95:6-98:7-99:6-99:7-99:8-103:3)",
      "d": "«اَمَّا السَّفِیۡنَۃُ فَکَانَتۡ لِمَسٰکِیۡنَ یَعۡمَلُوۡنَ فِی الۡبَحۡرِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2623,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Labor. Toil. To do. To bear.",
      "hw": "محنت",
      "s": "'Jahada' means to use all means in doing something (27 verses: 2:218-3:142-5:35-5:54-8:72-8:74-8:75-9:16-9:19-9:20-9:41-9:44-9:73-9:79-9:81-9:86-9:88-16:110-22:78-25:52-29:6-29:8-29:69-31:15-49:15-61:11-66:9)",
      "d": "«وَ مَنۡ جَاہَدَ فَاِنَّمَا یُجَاہِدُ لِنَفۡسِہٖ» «وَ الَّذِیۡنَ لَا یَجِدُوۡنَ اِلَّا جُہۡدَہُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2624,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Labor. Toil. To do. To bear.",
      "hw": "محنت",
      "s": "'Nasaba' such toil that causes fatigue or is a cause of tiredness (6 verses: 9:120-15:48-18:62-35:35-88:3-94:7)",
      "d": "«لَقَدۡ لَقِیۡنَا مِنۡ سَفَرِنَا ہٰذَا نَصَبًا» «فَاِذَا فَرَغۡتَ فَانۡصَبۡ وَ اِلٰی رَبِّکَ فَارۡغَبۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2627,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Labor. Toil. To do. To bear.",
      "hw": "محنت",
      "s": "'Kurh' meaning forced toil, such toil in which a person's own will and choice have no part (26 verses: 2:216-3:83-4:19-8:8-9:32-9:33-9:46-9:53-9:81-10:82-10:99-13:15-16:62-16:106-20:73-24:33-40:14-41:11-46:15-47:9-47:26-47:28-49:7-49:12-61:8-61:9)",
      "d": "«حَمَلَتۡہُ اُمُّہٗ کُرۡہًا وَّ وَضَعَتۡہُ کُرۡہًا» «وَ لَا تُکۡرِہُوۡا فَتَیٰتِکُمۡ عَلَی الۡبِغَآءِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2628,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Labor. Toil. To do. To bear.",
      "hw": "محنت",
      "s": "'Shiqq' the hardship and toil of labor (6 verses: 13:34-16:7-20:2-20:117-20:123-28:27)",
      "d": "«وَ تَحۡمِلُ اَثۡقَالَکُمۡ اِلٰی بَلَدٍ لَّمۡ تَکُوۡنُوۡا بٰلِغِیۡہِ اِلَّا بِشِقِّ الۡاَنۡفُسِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2629,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Hardship. Labor. To do. To bear.",
      "hw": "محنت",
      "s": "« » is that station which one can reach with difficulty (1 verse: 9:42)",
      "d": "The difference between « » and « » is like that between « » and « » or « » and « » (for details, see 'burden'). That is, the station which one can reach with difficulty (lexical).\n«لَوۡ کَانَ عَرَضًا قَرِیۡبًا وَّ سَفَرًا قَاصِدًا لَّاتَّبَعُوۡکَ وَ لٰکِنۡۢ بَعُدَتۡ عَلَیۡہِمُ الشُّقَّۃُ»\nTranslation: If the gain (spoils) seemed near and the journey easy, they would have followed you, but the station seemed distant to them."
    }
  ],
  "574": [
    {
      "id": 2630,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Opposition. To oppose.",
      "hw": "مخالفت",
      "s": "« » means to oppose, to turn away (3 verses: 9:83-11:88-24:63)",
      "d": "« » means to oppose, to turn away (source) and means to go against something and to differ. To do something other than what has been instructed.\n«وَ مَاۤ  اُرِیۡدُ اَنۡ اُخَالِفَکُمۡ  اِلٰی مَاۤ اَنۡہٰکُمۡ عَنۡہُ»\nTranslation: I do not wish to oppose you in what I forbid you."
    },
    {
      "id": 2631,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Opposition. To oppose.",
      "hw": "مخالفت",
      "s": "« » two things that are opposite to each other, of the same kind, and can never coexist, like whiteness and blackness, their kind is color or hue (1 verse: 19:82)",
      "d": "« » means to oppose. And « » means opposite, adversary. Its plural is « ». Two opposing things are called « ». According to Imam Raghib, the definition of « » is: two things that are opposite to each other, of the same kind, and can never coexist, like whiteness and blackness, their kind is color or hue. And according to Ibn Faris, « » are two opposing things whose simultaneous existence is impossible, like day and night. So this word is specific to « ». That is, every opposite is a contrary, but not every contrary is an opposite.\n«کَلَّا ؕ سَیَکۡفُرُوۡنَ  بِعِبَادَتِہِمۡ وَ یَکُوۡنُوۡنَ  عَلَیۡہِمۡ  ضِدًّا»\nTranslation: No! They will disbelieve in their worship and will be adversaries to them.\nAnd the word « » itself is from the root 'addada' meaning opposite and adversary. And « » also means similar and counterpart (source).\nNote: (Lexical opposites are words that have two separate meanings that are opposite and contradictory to each other)"
    },
    {
      "id": 2632,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Opposition. To oppose.",
      "hw": "مخالفت",
      "s": "« » to be hostile and an enemy (5 verses: 4:115-8:13-16:27-47:32-59:4)",
      "d": "« » means to oppose, to harbor enmity (source). And « » means crack, fissure. And « » means separation, distance, split, discord, opposition. Such opposition where each party adopts the opposite stance (lexical), meaning whatever one dislikes, the other party adopts it.\n«ذٰلِکَ بِاَنَّہُمۡ  شَآقُّوا اللّٰہَ وَ رَسُوۡلَہٗ ۚ وَ مَنۡ یُّشَآقِّ  اللّٰہَ  فَاِنَّ اللّٰہَ شَدِیۡدُ الۡعِقَابِ»\nTranslation: That is because they opposed Allah and His Messenger. And whoever opposes Allah, then indeed Allah is severe in punishment."
    },
    {
      "id": 2634,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Opposition. To oppose.",
      "hw": "مخالفت",
      "s": "« » such discord where one party causes hardship for the other (1 verse: 65:6)",
      "d": "«عُسْر» «عَسَّرَ الْاَمْر» «تَعَاسَرَ» «تَعَاسَرَ»\n«وَ اۡتَمِرُوۡا  بَیۡنَکُمۡ بِمَعۡرُوۡفٍ ۚ وَ اِنۡ  تَعَاسَرۡتُمۡ فَسَتُرۡضِعُ  لَہٗۤ   اُخۡرٰی»\nTranslation: And consult each other in a fair manner. But if you oppose each other, then another woman will nurse (the child)."
    },
    {
      "id": 2635,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Opposition. To oppose.",
      "hw": "مخالفت",
      "s": "« » to knowingly oppose the truth and the path of truth (4 verses: 11:59-14:15-50:24-74:16)",
      "d": "« » means to knowingly oppose the truth and the path of truth (lexical, source). « » means a person who holds enmity and opposition against the path of truth. And « » means a person who deviates from the correct path (lexical).\n«اِنَّہٗ  کَانَ  لِاٰیٰتِنَا عَنِیۡدًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, he was an adversary to Our signs."
    }
  ],
  "575": [
    {
      "id": 2636,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Different",
      "hw": "مختلف",
      "s": "« » to be separate, of various kinds or types, different in species (9 verses: 6:141-11:118-16:13-16:69-35:27-35:28-39:21-51:8-78:3)",
      "d": "« » its opposite is « ». « » means things being separate, of various kinds or types, different in species. Having disagreement (opinion) in a matter.\n«یَخۡرُجُ مِنۡۢ بُطُوۡنِہَا شَرَابٌ مُّخۡتَلِفٌ اَلۡوَانُہٗ»\nTranslation: From their bellies comes a drink (honey) of varying colors.\n«وَّ النَّخۡلَ وَ الزَّرۡعَ مُخۡتَلِفًا اُکُلُہٗ»\nTranslation: And date-palms and crops, whose fruits are of various kinds."
    },
    {
      "id": 2637,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Different",
      "hw": "مختلف",
      "s": "« » when the intention is to express the scattered parts of one thing, i.e., separate components (5 verses: 20:53-24:61-59:14-92:4-99:6)",
      "d": "« » means the scattering of something, i.e., components becoming separate. Scattered, i.e., dispersed. Its opposite is « » (source) meaning to gather the separate parts of something and arrange them. And « » means dispersed. Its plural is « ». (source)\n«تَحۡسَبُہُمۡ جَمِیۡعًا وَّ قُلُوۡبُہُمۡ شَتّٰی»\nTranslation: You think they are all together, but their hearts are scattered.\nAnd the word « » itself is from the root 'addada' meaning opposite and adversary. And « » also means similar and counterpart (source).\nNote: (Lexical opposites are words that have two separate meanings that are opposite and contradictory to each other)"
    },
    {
      "id": 2638,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Different",
      "hw": "مختلف",
      "s": "« » means a pair and every individual of a pair. In common usage, it is used for husband and wife, and it is used for every same-gender pair. (47 verses: 2:25-2:232-2:234-2:240-3:15-4:12-4:57-6:139-6:143-9:24-13:23-13:38-15:88-16:72-20:53-20:131-23:6-24:6-25:74-26:166-30:21-33:4-33:6-33:28-33:37-33:50-33:52-33:53-33:59-35:11-36:36-36:56-37:22-38:58-39:6-40:8-42:11-43:12-43:70-56:7-60:11-64:14-66:1-66:3-66:5-70:30-78:8)",
      "d": "« » means a pair and every individual of a pair. For example, the husband is the zawj of the wife, and the wife is the zawj of the husband. And husband and wife together are also one zawj. In every creation where there is the existence of male and female, the concept of zawj is also present. The concept of male and female is known to humans in animals and plants, but this concept is also found in inanimate objects.\n«وَ مِنۡ کُلِّ  شَیۡءٍ خَلَقۡنَا زَوۡجَیۡنِ»\nSince the concept of companionship or partnership is also present in « », it is also used for several important groups of living things coming together. In this case, the meaning of zawj becomes kind, category, or sect.\n«وَّ کُنۡتُمۡ  اَزۡوَاجًا  ثَلٰثَۃً»\nAnd the word « » is also used for different kinds of same-gender groups. Each such group is considered as one, so the meaning of azwaj will be several kinds of such groups.\n«وَ لَا تَمُدَّنَّ عَیۡنَیۡکَ  اِلٰۤی مَا مَتَّعۡنَا بِہٖۤ اَزۡوَاجًا مِّنۡہُمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "576": [
    {
      "id": 2640,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Duration",
      "hw": "مدت",
      "s": "« » is used for a long period and its limit or distance (4 verses: 3:30-18:12-57:16-72:25)",
      "d": "The word « » comes for a long duration and is used for the limit and purpose of that duration (lexical). This word is used for both time and place. And in the case of place, it means distance (fiqh al-lughah 242).\n«اَیُّ الۡحِزۡبَیۡنِ اَحۡصٰی  لِمَا  لَبِثُوۡۤا  اَمَدًا»\nTranslation: Which of the two groups remembered more the extreme duration they had stayed.\n«تَوَدُّ لَوۡ اَنَّ بَیۡنَہَا وَ بَیۡنَہٗۤ اَمَدًۢا بَعِیۡدًا»\nTranslation: He will wish that between her and it there were a great distance."
    },
    {
      "id": 2641,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Period",
      "hw": "مدت",
      "s": "‘Iddat’ is a period that must be counted, which is necessary for a divorced woman. This is a technical term (4 verses: 18:22-65:1-65:4-74:31)",
      "d": "Derived from ‘ad’ meaning to count. It refers to the period that is counted and during which a divorced or widowed woman cannot remarry and spends this period in her former husband's house.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ الّٰٓـِٔىۡ یَئِسۡنَ مِنَ  الۡمَحِیۡضِ مِنۡ نِّسَآئِکُمۡ   اِنِ  ارۡتَبۡتُمۡ فَعِدَّتُہُنَّ  ثَلٰثَۃُ اَشۡہُرٍ»\nTranslation: And your divorced women who have despaired of menstruation, if you doubt, then their period is three months."
    },
    {
      "id": 2642,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Period",
      "hw": "مدت",
      "s": "‘Ummah’ is a period that has passed in the past (54 verses: 2:143-2:213-3:104-3:110-3:113-4:41-5:48-5:66-6:38-6:42-6:108-7:34-7:38-7:159-7:160-7:164-7:168-7:181-10:19-10:47-10:49-11:8-11:48-11:118-12:45-13:30-15:5-16:36-16:63-16:84-16:89-16:92-16:93-16:120-21:92-22:34-22:67-23:43-23:44-23:52-27:83-28:23-28:75-29:18-35:24-35:42-40:5-41:25-42:8-43:22-43:23-43:33-45:28-46:18)",
      "d": "‘Umm’ means mother and anything that contains all its related things. ‘Ummah’ is used for a period when it has passed.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ قَالَ الَّذِیۡ نَجَا مِنۡہُمَا وَ ادَّکَرَ  بَعۡدَ اُمَّۃٍ»\nTranslation: And the one who escaped from among them remembered after a period and said."
    },
    {
      "id": 2645,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Period",
      "hw": "مدت",
      "s": "‘Umur’ is the period from the birth of a living being to the present time (10 verses: 2:96-10:16-15:72-16:70-21:44-22:5-26:18-28:45-35:11-35:37)",
      "d": "‘Amara’ means to inhabit and to populate. ‘Umur’ means the period of inhabiting the body of the soul. The period from the birth of a living being to the present time.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ لٰکِنَّاۤ  اَنۡشَاۡنَا قُرُوۡنًا فَتَطَاوَلَ عَلَیۡہِمُ الۡعُمُرُ»\nTranslation: But We generated generations, then long periods passed over them."
    }
  ],
  "577": [
    {
      "id": 2646,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘A’ana’ to help someone. General; all forms of assistance (6 verses: 1:4-2:45-2:153-7:128-18:95-25:4)",
      "d": "‘Awn’ means helper. ‘A’ana’ means to lend a hand, to assist. ‘Ta’awwana’ means to help each other. This word is general.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَاَعِیۡنُوۡنِیۡ بِقُوَّۃٍ  اَجۡعَلۡ بَیۡنَکُمۡ وَ بَیۡنَہُمۡ  رَدۡمًا»\nTranslation: Help me with strength, so I may set up a barrier between you and them.\nAnd ‘ista’ana’ means to seek help and cooperation.\nFor example, the Divine command states:\n«اِیَّاکَ نَعۡبُدُ وَ اِیَّاکَ نَسۡتَعِیۡنُ»\nTranslation: You alone we worship, and You alone we seek help from."
    },
    {
      "id": 2647,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘Nasara’ to help someone to remove their hardship or oppression (70 verses: 2:48-2:86-2:123-2:214-2:250-2:286-3:13-3:81-3:111-3:123-3:126-3:147-3:160-6:34-7:157-7:192-7:197-8:10-8:26-8:62-8:72-8:74-9:14-9:25-9:40-11:30-11:63-11:113-12:110-18:43-21:39-21:43-21:68-21:77-22:15-22:39-22:40-22:60-23:26-23:39-23:65-25:19-26:93-28:18-28:41-28:81-29:10-29:30-30:5-30:47-36:74-36:75-37:116-39:54-40:29-40:51-41:16-42:46-44:41-46:28-47:7-48:3-52:46-57:25-59:8-59:11-59:12-61:13-67:20-110:1)",
      "d": "‘Nasara’ means to help someone to remove their hardship or oppression. This is more specific than general assistance.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ لَقَدۡ نَصَرَکُمُ اللّٰہُ بِبَدۡرٍ وَّ اَنۡتُمۡ اَذِلَّۃٌ»\nTranslation: And Allah has certainly aided you at Badr while you were weak.\nAnd ‘istanasara’ means to seek help from someone to remove oppression from oneself.\nFor example, the Divine command states:\n«وَ اِنِ اسۡتَنۡصَرُوۡکُمۡ فِی الدِّیۡنِ فَعَلَیۡکُمُ النَّصۡرُ»\nTranslation: And if they seek your help in religion, then you must aid them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2648,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘Ayyada’ to strengthen someone through assistance (9 verses: 2:87-2:253-5:110-8:26-8:62-9:40-38:17-58:22-61:14)",
      "d": "‘Al-ayyad’ means strong power. ‘Ayyada’ means to assist someone so that they gain strength and power; to support.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَاَنۡزَلَ اللّٰہُ سَکِیۡنَتَہٗ عَلَیۡہِ وَ اَیَّدَہٗ  بِجُنُوۡدٍ لَّمۡ تَرَوۡہَا»\nTranslation: Then Allah sent down His tranquility upon him and supported him with armies you did not see."
    },
    {
      "id": 2649,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘Azara’ to help someone with a sense of reverence (3 verses: 5:12-7:157-48:9)",
      "d": "‘Azara’ means to help someone with a feeling of reverence.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«لِّتُؤۡمِنُوۡا بِاللّٰہِ وَ رَسُوۡلِہٖ  وَ تُعَزِّرُوۡہُ وَ تُوَقِّرُوۡہُ»\nTranslation: So that you may believe in Allah and His Messenger and support him and revere him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2651,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘Zahara’ to back or provide protection (5 verses: 9:4-28:48-33:26-60:9-66:4)",
      "d": "In ‘zahr’, there are two basic meanings: (1) to be apparent, to come forward, to be evident. And ‘zahr’ means back. ‘Zahara’ means to provide strength upon which one can rely; to back or protect.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اَنۡزَلَ الَّذِیۡنَ ظَاہَرُوۡہُمۡ مِّنۡ اَہۡلِ الۡکِتٰبِ مِنۡ صَیَاصِیۡہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And those from the People of the Book who supported them, Allah brought them down from their fortresses."
    },
    {
      "id": 2652,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘Rafada’ to help the poor through gifts and charity (1 verse: 11:99)",
      "d": "‘Rafada’ means to aid the destitute and poor through gifts and charity.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اُتۡبِعُوۡا فِیۡ ہٰذِہٖ  لَعۡنَۃً وَّ یَوۡمَ الۡقِیٰمَۃِ ؕ بِئۡسَ الرِّفۡدُ  الۡمَرۡفُوۡدُ»\nTranslation: And they were followed in this [world] by a curse and on the Day of Resurrection. Evil is what they were given as a reward."
    },
    {
      "id": 2654,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helping: Doing and Willing",
      "hw": "مدد",
      "s": "‘Amadda’ to help by increasing the quantity or number of something; to strengthen, to fortify (7 verses: 3:124-3:125-17:6-26:132-26:133-52:22-71:12)",
      "d": "‘Madda’ means to pull, extend, or lengthen something, maintaining its connection. ‘Amadda’ means to help by increasing the quantity or number of something; to provide assistance.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«یُمۡدِدۡکُمۡ  بِاَمۡوَالٍ وَّ بَنِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And He will increase you in wealth and children.\nAt another place, the Divine command states:\n«یُمۡدِدۡکُمۡ رَبُّکُمۡ بِخَمۡسَۃِ اٰلٰفٍ مِّنَ الۡمَلٰٓئِکَۃِ مُسَوِّمِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: Then your Lord will reinforce you with five thousand angels, marked."
    }
  ],
  "578": [
    {
      "id": 2656,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helper",
      "hw": "مددگار",
      "s": "«Hawari» is a special group of helpers for the prophets (4 verses: 3:52-5:111-5:112-61:14)",
      "d": "«Hawari» means white cloth with which clothes etc. are cleaned (m. q.) and also means advisor, relative, helper. Hawari actually refers to those supporters of Prophet Jesus (peace be upon him) who stood by him in difficult times. And the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him) said that every prophet has a Hawari, and my Hawari is Zubair (may Allah be pleased with him).\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«قَالَ عِیۡسَی ابۡنُ  مَرۡیَمَ لِلۡحَوَارِیّٖنَ مَنۡ  اَنۡصَارِیۡۤ  اِلَی اللّٰہِ ؕ قَالَ الۡحَوَارِیُّوۡنَ نَحۡنُ  اَنۡصَارُ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: Prophet Jesus (peace be upon him) said to the Hawariyun, 'Who are my helpers in calling to Allah?' The Hawariyun said, 'We are helpers of Allah (in His religion).'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2658,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helper",
      "hw": "مددگار",
      "s": "«Shahid» is one who helps by being present at the occasion and giving testimony in favor of someone (32 verses: 2:143-2:282-3:98-4:33-4:41-4:72-4:79-4:159-4:166-5:117-6:19-10:29-10:46-13:43-16:84-16:89-17:96-22:17-22:78-28:75-29:52-33:55-34:47-41:47-41:53-46:8-48:28-50:21-50:37-58:6-85:9-100:7)",
      "d": "«Shahida» means to bear witness, whether that testimony is ocular or heartfelt—i.e., whether it pertains to sight or insight—and also means to be present (muf. manjad). And «Shahid» is also used for one who comes forward to give testimony in favor of someone before a judge (muf), and it proves to be a means of his help and support.\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«وَ ادۡعُوۡا شُہَدَآءَکُمۡ مِّنۡ دُوۡنِ اللّٰہِ  اِنۡ کُنۡتُمۡ صٰادِقِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And call upon those whom you consider helpers besides Allah, if you are truthful."
    },
    {
      "id": 2659,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helper",
      "hw": "مددگار",
      "s": "«Zahir» is a helper on whom one can rely. Patron. Supporter, helper, assistant (6 verses: 17:88-25:55-28:17-28:86-34:22-66:4)",
      "d": "«Zahr» means back. And it also means mount. Patron. Helper (muf). And «Zahir» means helper. A helper on whom a person relies.\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«فَلَا تَکُوۡنَنَّ  ظَہِیۡرًا  لِّلۡکٰفِرِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: Then never be a helper to the disbelievers."
    },
    {
      "id": 2660,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helper",
      "hw": "مددگار",
      "s": "«Wazir» is one who lends a hand in times of increased work (2 verses: 20:29-25:35)",
      "d": "«Wizr» means burden; its plural is «Awzar». And «Wazir» is a person who helps and accompanies, one who shares the burden in times of hardship and increased work.\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«وَ اجۡعَلۡ  لِّیۡ  وَزِیۡرًا مِّنۡ  اَہۡلِیۡ»\nTranslation: And appoint for me a minister (helper) from among my family."
    },
    {
      "id": 2661,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Helper",
      "hw": "مددگار",
      "s": "«A'ud» is a helper who is a firm hand and arm (2 verses: 18:51-28:35)",
      "d": "«A'ud» means arm. The part from the shoulder to the elbow. And «A'adtuhu» means to hold someone's arm and give him support. In this sense, «A'ud» is used metaphorically to mean helper (muf). Its plural is «A'dad» (manjad).\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«وَ مَا کُنۡتُ مُتَّخِذَ  الۡمُضِلِّیۡنَ  عَضُدًا»\nTranslation: And I was not one to take the misguiders as helpers."
    }
  ],
  "579": [
    {
      "id": 2662,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To mock",
      "hw": "مذاق",
      "s": "«Istihza» is to mock something by considering it unreasonable and strange (21 verses: 2:14-2:15-4:140-6:5-6:10-9:64-9:65-11:8-13:32-15:11-15:95-16:34-21:41-26:6-30:10-36:30-39:48-40:83-43:7-45:33-46:26)",
      "d": "«Al-haz» means to mock someone internally (muf). And «Istihza» means to mock a person's action that he has not even committed, considering it unreasonable (faq l 212).\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«وَ اِذَا خَلَوۡا اِلٰی شَیٰطِیۡنِہِمۡ  ۙ  قَالُوۡۤا اِنَّا مَعَکُمۡ  ۙ  اِنَّمَا نَحۡنُ مُسۡتَہۡزِءُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: When these hypocrites are alone with their evil companions, they say, 'We are with you; we are only mocking.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2663,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To mock",
      "hw": "مذاق",
      "s": "«Sakhkhara» is to mock by mentioning someone's faults with contempt (10 verses: 2:212-6:10-9:79-11:38-21:41-23:110-37:12-37:14-38:63-49:11)",
      "d": "«Maskhar» contains the aspect of humiliation and contempt (m. l). «Sakhkhara» means to take labor (i.e., work without wages) from someone, and also means to humiliate someone, to overpower (manjad), and also means to mock someone by mentioning his faults, intending his degradation and humiliation (faq l 211).\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا  الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا لَا یَسۡخَرۡ قَوۡمٌ مِّنۡ قَوۡمٍ عَسٰۤی اَنۡ یَّکُوۡنُوۡا خَیۡرًا مِّنۡہُمۡ»\nTranslation: O you who have believed, let not a people ridicule another people; perhaps they may be better than them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2664,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To mock",
      "hw": "مذاق",
      "s": "«Fanna» is to mock an old person's words by considering them nonsensical (1 verse: 12:94)",
      "d": "«Fand» means weakness of opinion. And «Fanna» means to declare someone as having weak opinion or deficient intellect (i.e., foolish, crazy, insane) (muf). And «Fanida» means to become senile. To become weak-minded due to old age and speak incoherently. And «Fanna» means to reproach someone for an old person's words, to declare them erroneous, to reproach.\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«قَالَ اَبُوۡہُمۡ اِنِّیۡ لَاَجِدُ رِیۡحَ یُوۡسُفَ لَوۡ لَاۤ اَنۡ تُفَنِّدُوۡنِ»\nTranslation: Their father said, 'I find the scent of Joseph, if you do not call me senile.'"
    }
  ],
  "580": [
    {
      "id": 2665,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Man",
      "hw": "مرد",
      "s": "«Rajul» is used when the expression of bravery and masculine strength is intended (49 verses: 2:228-2:282-4:1-4:7-4:12-4:32-4:34-4:75-4:98-4:176-5:23-6:9-7:46-7:48-7:63-7:69-7:81-7:155-9:108-10:2-11:78-12:109-16:43-16:76-17:47-18:32-18:37-21:7-23:25-23:38-24:31-24:37-25:8-27:55-28:15-28:20-29:29-33:4-33:23-33:40-34:7-34:43-36:20-38:62-39:29-40:28-43:31-48:25-72:6)",
      "d": "«Rajul» (meaning man) is used when the expression of strength, bravery, and masculinity is intended. «Rijaliyyah» is the verbal noun meaning masculine strength. Its plural is «Rijal». And its feminine is «Nisa'» and «Niswa».\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«اَلرِّجَالُ قَوّٰمُوۡنَ عَلَی النِّسَآءِ بِمَا فَضَّلَ اللّٰہُ بَعۡضَہُمۡ عَلٰی بَعۡضٍ»\nTranslation: Men are the protectors and maintainers of women, because Allah has given one of them more strength than the other."
    },
    {
      "id": 2666,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Man",
      "hw": "مرد",
      "s": "«Imra'» is used when one intends to express chivalry, humanity, and moral values (4 verses: 2:102-8:24-78:40-80:34)",
      "d": "«Mar'» (meaning man) person. This word is used when the intention is to refer to humanity-related ethics. «Maru'at» or «Murrat» is the verbal noun meaning humanity, human compassion. And its feminine is «Imra'at» or «Al-Mar'at». Its plural is also «Rijal» (manjad).\nFor example: In the Quran it says:\n«فَیَتَعَلَّمُوۡنَ مِنۡہُمَا مَا یُفَرِّقُوۡنَ بِہٖ بَیۡنَ الۡمَرۡءِ  وَ زَوۡجِہٖ»\nTranslation: People learn from them what causes separation between a man and his wife."
    },
    {
      "id": 2667,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "male",
      "hw": "مرد",
      "s": "« » is used when the expression of gender is intended (16 verses: 3:36-3:195-4:11-4:124-4:176-6:143-6:144-16:97-26:165-40:40-42:50-49:13-53:21-53:45-75:39-92:3)",
      "d": "«ذَکَرَ» «اُنْثٰی» «ذَكُوْر» «ذَکْرَان» «اَنَاث» «قُلۡ ءٰٓالذَّکَرَیۡنِ حَرَّمَ اَمِ الۡاُنۡثَیَیۡنِ» «لَیۡسَ الذَّکَرُ کَالۡاُنۡثٰی»"
    }
  ],
  "581": [
    {
      "id": 2668,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "taste",
      "hw": "مزا",
      "s": "« » is general meaning to taste. Taste, to taste (5 verses: 3:185-21:35-29:57-37:31-37:38)",
      "d": "«ذَاقَ» «ذَائِقَۃ» «ذَوَاق» «مَذَاق» «کُلُّ نَفۡسٍ ذَآئِقَۃُ الۡمَوۡتِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2671,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "pleasure",
      "hw": "مزا",
      "s": "« » means wealth that comes without effort, and being pleasant in appearance and delightful. Something being pleasant and delightful (4 verses: 4:4-52:19-69:24-77:43)",
      "d": "«اَلْھَنِیءُ» «ھَنَأ» «ھَنِیءَ الطَّعَام» «ھَنُؤَ» «ھَنَّاَ» «ھَنیئُ» «ھَنِئ» «فَاِنۡ طِبۡنَ لَکُمۡ عَنۡ شَیۡءٍ مِّنۡہُ نَفۡسًا فَکُلُوۡہُ ہَنِیۡٓئًا مَّرِیۡٓئًا»"
    }
  ],
  "583": [
    {
      "id": 2675,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "traveler",
      "hw": "مسافر",
      "s": "«اِبْنُ السَّبِیِل»",
      "d": "«اِبْنُ السَّبِیِل» «وَ اٰتَی الۡمَالَ عَلٰی حُبِّہٖ ذَوِی الۡقُرۡبٰی وَ الۡیَتٰمٰی وَ الۡمَسٰکِیۡنَ وَ ابۡنَ السَّبِیۡلِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2676,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "traveler",
      "hw": "مسافر",
      "s": "«عَابِرِی السَّبِیِل»",
      "d": "«عَابِرِ» «عَابِرِی السَّبِیِل» «وَ لَا جُنُبًا اِلَّا عَابِرِیۡ سَبِیۡلٍ حَتّٰی تَغۡتَسِلُوۡا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2677,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "traveler",
      "hw": "مسافر",
      "s": "« » those who move about in search of livelihood (1 verse: 56:73)",
      "d": "«اَلْقَوٰی» «بَاتَ الْقَوٰی» «اَلْقَاوِیَۃ» «تَقَاوِی» «تَقَاوِی» «تَقَاوٰی» «قُوَّتُ لَا یَمُوت» «مُقْوِیْن» «نَحۡنُ جَعَلۡنٰہَا تَذۡکِرَۃً وَّ مَتَاعًا لِّلۡمُقۡوِیۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2678,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "traveler",
      "hw": "مسافر",
      "s": "« » a caravan of people traveling together (3 verses: 5:96-12:10-12:19)",
      "d": "«سَارَ» «سیّار» «سَیَّارَہ» «وَ جَآءَتۡ سَیَّارَۃٌ فَاَرۡسَلُوۡا وَارِدَہُمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "584": [
    {
      "id": 2679,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to subjugate",
      "hw": "مسخر",
      "s": "« » the word emphasizes the aspect of (restlessness and discomfort) of a thing (24 verses: 2:164-7:54-13:2-14:32-14:33-16:12-16:14-16:79-21:79-22:36-22:37-22:65-29:61-31:20-31:29-35:13-38:18-38:36-39:5-43:13-43:32-45:12-45:13-69:7)",
      "d": "«سَخَّرَ» «وَ تَقُوۡلُوۡا سُبۡحٰنَ الَّذِیۡ سَخَّرَ لَنَا ہٰذَا وَ مَا کُنَّا لَہٗ مُقۡرِنِیۡنَ»"
    }
  ],
  "585": [
    {
      "id": 2681,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to subject",
      "hw": "مسلط",
      "s": "« » contains two aspects (1) power (2) might, i.e., dominance and with it pressure also. (2 verses: 4:90-59:6)",
      "d": "«سَلِطَ» «سَلَّطَ» «سُلْطان» «وَّ لٰکِنَّ اللّٰہَ یُسَلِّطُ رُسُلَہٗ عَلٰی مَنۡ یَّشَآءُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2682,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to subject",
      "hw": "مسلط",
      "s": "« » means to overpower and make someone helpless. (2 verses: 41:25-43:36)",
      "d": "«قَیْض» «قَیَّضَ» «وَ مَنۡ یَّعۡشُ عَنۡ ذِکۡرِ الرَّحۡمٰنِ نُقَیِّضۡ لَہٗ شَیۡطٰنًا»"
    }
  ],
  "586": [
    {
      "id": 2683,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To be occupied/engaged",
      "hw": "مشغول",
      "s": "« » is general. To be occupied with a task (2 verses: 36:55-48:11)",
      "d": "« » refers to a state of preoccupation where a person cannot attend to other tasks. Its opposite is « ».\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«سَیَقُوۡلُ لَکَ الۡمُخَلَّفُوۡنَ مِنَ الۡاَعۡرَابِ شَغَلَتۡنَاۤ اَمۡوَالُنَا وَ اَہۡلُوۡنَا»\nTranslation: Those of the bedouins who remained behind will say to you, 'We were occupied with our wealth and our families.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2684,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To be occupied/engaged",
      "hw": "مشغول",
      "s": "« » means to be engrossed in a negative sense (9 verses: 4:140-6:68-6:91-9:65-9:69-43:83-52:12-70:42-74:45)",
      "d": "«خَاضَ» «خَاضَ فِی الْمَاء» «خَاضَ فِی الْحَدِیْث»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ خُضۡتُمۡ کَالَّذِیۡ خَاضُوۡا ؕ اُولٰٓئِکَ حَبِطَتۡ اَعۡمَالُہُمۡ فِی الدُّنۡیَا وَ الۡاٰخِرَۃِ»\nTranslation: And you became like those who were engrossed in falsehood. Those are the ones whose deeds are wasted in this world and the Hereafter.\nAt another place, the Divine declaration is:\n«وَ اِذَا رَاَیۡتَ الَّذِیۡنَ یَخُوۡضُوۡنَ فِیۡۤ اٰیٰتِنَا فَاَعۡرِضۡ عَنۡہُمۡ»\nTranslation: When you see those who engage in vain discourse about Our verses, turn away from them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2685,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To be occupied/engaged",
      "hw": "مشغول",
      "s": "« » denotes an absorption so intense that one forgets oneself (6 verses: 2:199-5:83-7:50-9:92-10:61-46:8)",
      "d": "«فَاضَ، فَیْض» «فَاضَ السَّبیل» «فَاضَتْ عَیْنَہٗ» «اَفَاضَ اِنَاءَہٗ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«ثُمَّ اَفِیۡضُوۡا مِنۡ حَیۡثُ اَفَاضَ النَّاسُ»\nTranslation: Then depart from the place from which the people depart.\n«اَفَاضَ الْقَوْمُ مِنْ مَکَان» «اَفَاضَ فِی الْحَدِیْثِ»\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«وَّ لَا تَعۡمَلُوۡنَ مِنۡ عَمَلٍ اِلَّا کُنَّا عَلَیۡکُمۡ شُہُوۡدًا اِذۡ تُفِیۡضُوۡنَ فِیۡہِ»\nTranslation: And whatever you do, We are witnesses over you when you are engrossed in it.\n«تَفِیْضُوْنَ فِیْہِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2686,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To be occupied/engaged",
      "hw": "مشغول",
      "s": "« » denotes an absorption characterized by swiftness and intensity due to the multitude of tasks (4 verses: 21:33-36:40-73:7-79:3)",
      "d": "« » means to swim or float (i.e., to move on water, cross it, traverse it, or reach the other side). According to Imam Raghib, it means for something to pass through water or air swiftly or while swimming.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ کُلٌّ فِیۡ فَلَکٍ یَّسۡبَحُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And each [celestial body] floats in an orbit.\nLater, this word began to be used for performing a task with speed and vigor.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«اِنَّ لَکَ فِی النَّہَارِ سَبۡحًا طَوِیۡلًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, for you during the day is a prolonged occupation [with worldly affairs]."
    }
  ],
  "587": [
    {
      "id": 2687,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To plunge into hardship",
      "hw": "مشقت",
      "s": "« » means to cause someone else to fall into a dangerous and difficult task.\nAnd « » is used for plunging oneself into a dangerous and difficult task (3 verses: 2:220-3:118-9:128)",
      "d": "« » means for a person to become entangled in a matter where there is fear of ruin. « » means to cause someone else to fall into such affliction or calamity.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَوۡ شَآءَ اللّٰہُ لَاَعۡنَتَکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And if Allah had willed, He could have put you into hardship."
    },
    {
      "id": 2688,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To plunge into hardship",
      "hw": "مشقت",
      "s": "« » means to plunge oneself, along with hardship, into a matter (2 verses: 38:59-90:11)",
      "d": "«قَحَمَ فِی الْاَمْر» «اِقْتَحَمَ الْاَمْر» «اِقْتَحَمَ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«ہٰذَا فَوۡجٌ مُّقۡتَحِمٌ مَّعَکُمۡ»\nTranslation: This is a force that is plunging in with you [into Hell]."
    }
  ],
  "588": [
    {
      "id": 2689,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To consult",
      "hw": "مشورہ",
      "s": "« » means to consult. It is general (2 verses: 2:233-3:159)",
      "d": "« » means to consult. It involves several people gathering to consider the various aspects of a matter and taking each other's opinions. Its usage is general.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ شَاوِرۡہُمۡ فِی الۡاَمۡرِ ۚ فَاِذَا عَزَمۡتَ فَتَوَکَّلۡ عَلَی اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And consult them in the matter. Then when you have decided, put your trust in Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 2691,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To consult",
      "hw": "مشورہ",
      "s": "« » means secret whispering or counsel between two or a few people (14 verses: 4:114-9:78-12:80-17:47-19:52-20:62-21:3-43:80-58:7-58:8-58:9-58:10-58:12-58:13)",
      "d": "« » means a secret between two people. « » means a secret talk, a secret, a confidant, or one who shares a secret. « » means to whisper, to whisper specifically, or to make someone a confidant. « » means secret consultation.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ یَتَنٰجَوۡنَ بِالۡاِثۡمِ وَ الۡعُدۡوَانِ وَ مَعۡصِیَتِ الرَّسُوۡلِ»\nTranslation: They whisper to one another sinful [talk] and transgression and disobedience to the Messenger."
    },
    {
      "id": 2692,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To consult",
      "hw": "مشورہ",
      "s": "« » means to agree on a plan after consultation or to conspire to kill someone (2 verses: 28:20-65:6)",
      "d": "«اَمَرَ» «اِئْتَمَرَ» «اِئْتَمَرَ بِفُلَانٍ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«قَالَ یٰمُوۡسٰۤی اِنَّ الۡمَلَاَ یَاۡتَمِرُوۡنَ بِکَ لِیَقۡتُلُوۡکَ»\nTranslation: He said, 'O Moses, indeed the eminent ones are planning to kill you.'"
    }
  ],
  "589": [
    {
      "id": 2693,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To publicize/spread",
      "hw": "مشہور",
      "s": "« » means to publicize or spread news, whether good or bad (1 verse: 24:19)",
      "d": "«شَاعَ الْخَبْر» «شَاعَ الْقَوْم» «اَلْشِیَاعَ» «شَاعَ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنَّ الَّذِیۡنَ یُحِبُّوۡنَ اَنۡ تَشِیۡعَ الۡفَاحِشَۃُ فِی الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا لَہُمۡ عَذَابٌ اَلِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: Indeed, those who like that indecency should be spread [or publicized] among those who have believed will have a painful punishment in this world and the Hereafter."
    },
    {
      "id": 2694,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to publicize",
      "hw": "مشہور",
      "s": "« » means to spread news, to reveal and disseminate matters related to secrets and confidential affairs (1 verse: 4:83)",
      "d": "«ذَاعَ» «ذَاعَ الْخَبْر» «رَجُلٌ لِذَاعٌ» «اَزَاعَ» «اِذَاعَۃ»\n«وَ اِذَا جَآءَہُمۡ اَمۡرٌ مِّنَ الۡاَمۡنِ اَوِ الۡخَوۡفِ اَذَاعُوۡا بِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2695,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to publicize",
      "hw": "مشہور",
      "s": "« » means to spread something that causes anxiety and unrest (1 verse: 33:60)",
      "d": "«رَجْف» «رَجْفَۃ» «بَحْرٌ رِجَافٌ» «اَرْجَفَ» «اَرَاجِیْف»\n«لَئِنۡ لَّمۡ یَنۡتَہِ الۡمُنٰفِقُوۡنَ وَ الَّذِیۡنَ فِیۡ قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ مَّرَضٌ وَّ الۡمُرۡجِفُوۡنَ فِی الۡمَدِیۡنَۃِ لَنُغۡرِیَنَّکَ بِہِمۡ ثُمَّ لَا یُجَاوِرُوۡنَکَ فِیۡہَاۤ اِلَّا قَلِیۡلًا»\nTranslation: If the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is a disease and those who spread false rumors in the city do not desist, We will surely incite you against them, then they will not be your neighbors therein except for a little while."
    },
    {
      "id": 2696,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to publicize",
      "hw": "مشہور",
      "s": "« » means to raise one's voice mentioning something and to publicize it (4 verses: 2:173-5:3-6:145-16:105)",
      "d": "«اَھَلَّ» «ھِلَال» «تَھْلِیْل» «لَا اِلٰہَ اِلَّا اللہُ»\n«اِنَّمَا حَرَّمَ عَلَیۡکُمُ الۡمَیۡتَۃَ وَ الدَّمَ وَ لَحۡمَ الۡخِنۡزِیۡرِ وَ مَاۤ اُہِلَّ بِہٖ لِغَیۡرِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: He has only forbidden to you dead animals, blood, the flesh of swine, and that which has been dedicated to other than Allah."
    }
  ],
  "590": [
    {
      "id": 2697,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to remain established on one's foundation (2 verses: 14:24-14:27)",
      "d": "«ثَبَّتَ» «ثَبَّتَ عَلَی الْاَمْر» «زَلّ»\n«مَثَلًا کَلِمَۃً طَیِّبَۃً کَشَجَرَۃٍ طَیِّبَۃٍ اَصۡلُہَا ثَابِتٌ وَّ فَرۡعُہَا فِی السَّمَآءِ»\nTranslation: A goodly word is like a goodly tree, whose root is firm and whose branches are in the sky."
    },
    {
      "id": 2699,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means for something to be durable in itself (3 verses: 7:183-51:58-68:45)",
      "d": "«مَتِیْن» «حَبْلٌ مَّتِیْنٌ» «رَأیَ مَتِیْنٌ»\n«وَ اُمۡلِیۡ لَہُمۡ ؕ اِنَّ کَیۡدِیۡ مَتِیۡنٌ»\nTranslation: And I will give them respite. Indeed, my plan is firm."
    },
    {
      "id": 2700,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » proven by wisdom and experience. Firm. (2 verses: 3:7-47:20)",
      "d": "« » means to make something firm with wisdom and experience (minjadd). According to Imam Raghib, the decisive verses are those in which there is no doubt or ambiguity, either literal or contextual (muf).\n«ہُوَ الَّذِیۡۤ اَنۡزَلَ عَلَیۡکَ الۡکِتٰبَ مِنۡہُ اٰیٰتٌ مُّحۡکَمٰتٌ ہُنَّ اُمُّ الۡکِتٰبِ وَ اُخَرُ مُتَشٰبِہٰتٌ»\nTranslation: It is He who has sent down to you the Book. From it are verses [that are] precise - they are the foundation of the Book - and others unspecific."
    },
    {
      "id": 2701,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » such firmness that can be a support for others or serve as a standard for them (2 verses: 98:3-98:5)",
      "d": "«قَامَ» «قَامَ الْاَمْر» «اَقَامَ الْمَائِل» «قَیَام» «قَوَام»\n«وَ لَا تُؤۡتُوا السُّفَہَآءَ اَمۡوَالَکُمُ الَّتِیۡ جَعَلَ اللّٰہُ لَکُمۡ قِیٰمًا»\nTranslation: And do not give the foolish your wealth which Allah has made a means of support for you.\nAnd « » its feminine is « », meaning that which other things stand upon. That is, that which maintains and keeps things firm, and that which serves as a standard to distinguish between truth and falsehood.\n«رَسُوۡلٌ مِّنَ اللّٰہِ یَتۡلُوۡا صُحُفًا مُّطَہَّرَۃً فِیۡہَا کُتُبٌ قَیِّمَۃٌ»\nTranslation: A messenger from Allah, reciting purified scriptures. Within them are correct/established books."
    },
    {
      "id": 2702,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » such firmness that can be trusted (2 verses: 2:256-31:22)",
      "d": "«وَثِقَ یَثِقُ ثِقَۃً» «وَثُقَ یُوْثَقُ وَثَاقَۃً» «اَوْثَقَ» «ثِقَۃٌ» «اَوْثَقٌ» «وُثْقٰی»\n«قَدۡ تَّبَیَّنَ الرُّشۡدُ مِنَ الۡغَیِّ ۚ فَمَنۡ یَّکۡفُرۡ بِالطَّاغُوۡتِ وَ یُؤۡمِنۡۢ بِاللّٰہِ فَقَدِ اسۡتَمۡسَکَ بِالۡعُرۡوَۃِ الۡوُثۡقٰی ٭ لَا انۡفِصَامَ لَہَا»\nTranslation: Clear has become the path of truth from falsehood. So whoever disbelieves in false deities and believes in Allah has grasped the most trustworthy handhold, which will never break."
    },
    {
      "id": 2703,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to make firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to keep something firm and strong in its place (13 verses: 2:250-3:147-8:11-8:12-8:45-11:120-13:39-14:24-14:27-16:102-17:74-25:32-47:7)",
      "d": "« » means to make something firm in its place. To strengthen. To keep steadfast.\n«یُثَبِّتُ اللّٰہُ الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا بِالۡقَوۡلِ الثَّابِتِ فِی الۡحَیٰوۃِ الدُّنۡیَا وَ فِی الۡاٰخِرَۃِ»\nTranslation: Allah will keep firm those who believe with the firm word in the worldly life and in the Hereafter."
    },
    {
      "id": 2704,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to make firm",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » to purify something from doubt and suspicion through wisdom and experience (2 verses: 11:1-22:52)",
      "d": "«اَحْکَم» «حَکِیْم» «اَلْعَالَمُ بِاِحْکَامِ الْاُمُورِ»\n«ثُمَّ یُحۡکِمُ اللّٰہُ اٰیٰتِہٖ»\nTranslation: Then Allah will establish His verses.\nAnd the decisive verses are those in which there is no literal or contextual doubt or ambiguity."
    },
    {
      "id": 2705,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To make firm; to strengthen",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to make something firm and reliable through something else (3 verses: 12:66-12:80-89:26)",
      "d": "« » means to make a covenant or agreement firm and reliable, or to tie someone firmly with ropes, etc.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَّ لَا یُوۡثِقُ وَ ثَاقَہٗۤ  اَحَدٌ»\nTranslation: And no one will be bound like that.\nAt another place, Allah says:\n«وَ اذۡکُرُوۡا نِعۡمَۃَ اللّٰہِ عَلَیۡکُمۡ وَ مِیۡثَاقَہُ الَّذِیۡ وَاثَقَکُمۡ  بِہٖۤ»\nTranslation: And remember the favor of Allah upon you and His covenant with which He has bound you.\nBesides these, the following words also appear in the Quran with similar meanings: for example:\n«شَدَّ ، اَتْقَنَ ، رَبَطَ ، اٰزَرَ ، عَقَّدَ ، وَکَّدَ ، سَنَّدَ ، رَصَّ ، شَیَّد»\nThese words are also used in the same senses."
    },
    {
      "id": 2708,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To make firm; to strengthen",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to tie firmly (3 verses: 8:11-18:14-28:10)",
      "d": "«رَبَطَ» «رَبَطَ اللہُ عَلٰی قَلْبِہٖ» «رِبَاط» «رَابِطَہ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اَصۡبَحَ فُؤَادُ  اُمِّ مُوۡسٰی فٰرِغًا ؕ اِنۡ کَادَتۡ لَتُبۡدِیۡ بِہٖ  لَوۡ لَاۤ  اَنۡ رَّبَطۡنَا عَلٰی قَلۡبِہَا»\nTranslation: And the heart of Moses' mother became empty, almost revealing it, had We not strengthened her heart."
    },
    {
      "id": 2709,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To make firm; to strengthen",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to strengthen gradually by providing strength (1 verse: 48:29)",
      "d": "«اَلْاِزْر» «اَلْاَزَار» «اٰزَرَ الْنَبَات» «اَزَّرَہ» «اٰزَرَ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«کَزَرۡعٍ  اَخۡرَجَ  شَطۡئَہٗ  فَاٰزَرَہٗ»\nTranslation: Like a crop that produces its sprout and then strengthens it."
    },
    {
      "id": 2711,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To make firm; to strengthen",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » is used to make covenants, sales, marriages, and all kinds of agreements firm (7 verses: 2:235-2:237-4:33-5:1-5:89-20:27-113:4)",
      "d": "«عَقَدَ» «عَقَدَۃ» «عَقَّدُ الْبَیْع وَ الْیَمِیْن» «عَقْد» «عَقُوْد»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«لَا یُؤَاخِذُکُمُ اللّٰہُ بِاللَّغۡوِ فِیۡۤ  اَیۡمَانِکُمۡ وَ لٰکِنۡ یُّؤَاخِذُکُمۡ بِمَا عَقَّدۡتُّمُ الۡاَیۡمَانَ»\nTranslation: Allah will not hold you accountable for meaningless oaths, but He will hold you accountable for what you have firmly affirmed in oaths."
    },
    {
      "id": 2712,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To make firm; to strengthen",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to support and strengthen (1 verse: 63:4)",
      "d": "« » means to trust, rely on, take support. And « » means to give support and strengthen (see lexicon), as when the beams of a roof are weak, another wooden beam is placed under them to strengthen the roof.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«کَاَنَّہُمۡ خُشُبٌ مُّسَنَّدَۃٌ ؕ یَحۡسَبُوۡنَ  کُلَّ صَیۡحَۃٍ  عَلَیۡہِمۡ»\nTranslation: They are like wooden planks propped up (against a wall); they think every cry is against them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2713,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To make firm; to strengthen",
      "hw": "مضبوط",
      "s": "« » means to make something firm by soldering with lead (1 verse: 61:4)",
      "d": "« » means to join one thing with another, to connect and make continuous. And « » means lead. Thus, « » means to make something firm by soldering it with lead.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اِنَّ اللّٰہَ یُحِبُّ الَّذِیۡنَ یُقَاتِلُوۡنَ فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِہٖ  صَفًّا کَاَنَّہُمۡ  بُنۡیَانٌ  مَّرۡصُوۡصٌ»\nTranslation: Indeed, Allah loves those who fight in His cause in ranks, as if they are a solid structure."
    }
  ],
  "591": [
    {
      "id": 2715,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To forgive; to pardon; to show forbearance; to seek forgiveness",
      "hw": "معاف",
      "s": "« » means to let go of someone who deserves punishment (28 verses: 2:52-2:109-2:178-2:187-2:237-2:286-3:152-3:155-3:159-4:43-4:99-4:149-4:153-5:13-5:15-5:95-5:101-7:199-9:43-9:66-22:60-24:22-42:25-42:30-42:34-42:40-58:2-64:14)",
      "d": "« » means to renounce punishment or retaliation (lexicon). To let go of someone who deserves punishment, not to take retribution for their fault, whether minor or major. (See also the second meaning of « » as 'excess'.)\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«عَفَا اللّٰہُ عَنۡکَ ۚ لِمَ اَذِنۡتَ لَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: May Allah forgive you, [O Muhammad]. Why did you permit them?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2716,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To forgive; to pardon; to show forbearance; to seek forgiveness",
      "hw": "معاف",
      "s": "« » means to pardon graciously, not letting someone feel their fault (6 verses: 2:109-5:13-15:85-24:22-43:89-64:14)",
      "d": "« » means to pardon, to let go, to not make someone feel their fault, not to even reproach them. This is more difficult than forgiving. And « » is stronger than « ». « » is renouncing punishment, while « » is used for renouncing reproach (lexicon).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَاعۡفُوۡا وَ اصۡفَحُوۡا حَتّٰی یَاۡتِیَ اللّٰہُ بِاَمۡرِہٖ»\nTranslation: So pardon and graciously overlook until Allah brings His command."
    },
    {
      "id": 2717,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To forgive; to pardon; to show forbearance; to seek forgiveness",
      "hw": "معاف",
      "s": "« » means Allah's saving His servants from the punishment of their sins, i.e., forgiving them (124 verses: 2:58-2:175-2:199-2:221-2:263-2:268-2:284-2:285-2:286-3:16-3:17-3:31-3:129-3:133-3:135-3:136-3:147-3:157-3:159-3:193-4:48-4:64-4:96-4:106-4:110-4:116-4:137-4:168-5:9-5:18-5:40-5:74-5:118-7:23-7:149-7:151-7:155-7:161-7:169-8:4-8:29-8:33-8:38-8:70-8:74-9:80-9:113-11:3-11:11-11:47-11:52-11:61-11:90-12:29-12:92-12:97-12:98-13:6-14:10-14:41-18:55-19:47-20:73-22:50-23:109-23:118-24:22-24:26-24:62-26:51-26:82-26:86-27:46-28:16-33:35-33:71-34:4-35:7-36:11-36:27-38:24-38:25-38:35-39:53-40:7-40:55-41:6-41:43-42:5-42:37-42:43-45:14-46:31-47:15-47:19-47:34-48:2-48:11-48:14-48:29-49:3-51:18-53:32-57:20-57:21-57:28-59:10-60:4-60:5-60:12-61:12-63:5-63:6-64:14-64:17-66:8-67:12-71:4-71:7-71:10-71:28-73:20-74:56-110:3)",
      "d": "«غَفَرَ» «غَفَرَ الشَّبَاب بِالْخِضَاب» «مِغْفَر» «اَلْغَفَارَۃ» «اَلْغَفَارَۃ» «غُفْرَان» «غَفَرَ» «ل» «غُفْرَان»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ مَنۡ یَّغۡفِرُ الذُّنُوۡبَ اِلَّا اللّٰہُ»\nTranslation: And who can forgive sins except Allah?\nAnd to seek forgiveness from Allah for sins, « » is used, with the relation to Allah, whether His name is mentioned or not.\nFor example, Allah says:\n«سَوَاءٌ  عَلَیۡہِمۡ  اَسۡتَغۡفَرۡتَ لَہُمۡ  اَمۡ لَمۡ تَسۡتَغۡفِرۡ لَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: It is all the same for them whether you seek forgiveness for them or not; Allah will not forgive them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2718,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To forgive; to pardon; to show forbearance; to seek forgiveness",
      "hw": "معاف",
      "s": "« » is used to mean giving up one's right to forgive (3 verses: 2:280-4:92-5:45)",
      "d": "« » means to relinquish one's right and to forgive someone by giving up one's right to them (lexicon).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اِنۡ کَانَ ذُوۡ عُسۡرَۃٍ فَنَظِرَۃٌ اِلٰی مَیۡسَرَۃٍ ؕ وَ اَنۡ تَصَدَّقُوۡا خَیۡرٌ لَّکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And if the debtor is in difficulty, then grant him respite until it is easy for him. And to remit it as charity is better for you."
    },
    {
      "id": 2719,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To Forgive; To Pardon; To Overlook; To Seek Forgiveness",
      "hw": "معاف",
      "s": "« » means to overlook, to forgive, and to pardon. (1 verse: 46:16)",
      "d": "«جَازَ» «جَاوَزَ الْمَکَان» «تَجَاوَزَ عَنْہُ» «تَجَاوَزَ فِی الْاَمْرِ» «اُولٰٓئِکَ الَّذِیۡنَ نَتَقَبَّلُ عَنۡہُمۡ  اَحۡسَنَ مَا عَمِلُوۡا وَ نَتَجَاوُزُ عَنۡ سَیِّاٰتِہِمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2721,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To forgive, to pardon, to show forbearance, to seek forgiveness.",
      "hw": "معاف",
      "s": "« » is used to seek forgiveness for sins (2 verses: 2:58, 7:161).",
      "d": "«حَطَّ» «حَطَّ السَّعْر» «حَطُّ الْحَمْلَ» «اِنْحِطَاط» «حَطُّ» «حَطَطْتُ الرَّحَل» «حِطَّۃٌ» «وَّ قُوۡلُوۡا حِطَّۃٌ نَّغۡفِرۡ لَکُمۡ خَطٰیٰکُمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "592": [
    {
      "id": 2722,
      "a": "ح",
      "h": "capacity, status",
      "hw": "حیثیت",
      "s": "« » is commonly used for existing supplies (2 verses: 12:75, 65:6).",
      "d": "«وَجَدَ» «وُجْد» «اَسۡکِنُوۡہُنَّ مِنۡ حَیۡثُ سَکَنۡتُمۡ مِّنۡ وُّجۡدِکُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2723,
      "a": "ح",
      "h": "capacity, status",
      "hw": "حیثیت",
      "s": "« » is used for prosperity and determining its degree (4 verses: 2:247, 4:130, 24:22, 65:7).",
      "d": "«سَعَۃ» «لِیُنۡفِقۡ ذُوۡ سَعَۃٍ مِّنۡ سَعَتِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2724,
      "a": "ح",
      "h": "capacity, status",
      "hw": "حیثیت",
      "s": "« » generally comes for determining poverty and its degree (11 verses: 13:26, 17:30, 28:82, 29:62, 30:37, 34:36, 34:39, 39:52, 42:12, 65:7, 89:16).",
      "d": "«قَدَرَ» «اَللّٰہُ یَبۡسُطُ الرِّزۡقَ لِمَنۡ یَّشَآءُ وَ یَقۡدِرُ» «عَلَی الۡمُوۡسِعِ قَدَرُہٗ وَ عَلَی الۡمُقۡتِرِ قَدَرُہٗ مَتَاعًۢا بِالۡمَعۡرُوۡف»"
    }
  ],
  "593": [
    {
      "id": 2725,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To appoint, to decree",
      "hw": "مقرر",
      "s": "« » means to make something obligatory or to decree (11 verses: 2:197, 2:236, 2:237, 4:11, 4:24, 9:60, 24:1, 28:85, 33:38, 33:50, 66:2).",
      "d": "«فَرَضَ» «فَرَّضَ الْخَشْبَۃَ» «فَرَضَ الْاَمْر» «اَلْفَرْض» «فَرِیْضَۃً» «لَا جُنَاحَ عَلَیۡکُمۡ  اِنۡ طَلَّقۡتُمُ النِّسَآءَ مَا لَمۡ تَمَسُّوۡہُنَّ اَوۡ تَفۡرِضُوۡا لَہُنَّ فَرِیۡضَۃً»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2726,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To appoint, to decree",
      "hw": "مقرر",
      "s": "« » means to appoint someone as one's representative (2 verses: 6:89, 32:11).",
      "d": "«وَکَلَ» «وَکَّل» «فَاِنۡ یَّکۡفُرۡ بِہَا ہٰۤؤُلَآءِ  فَقَدۡ وَکَّلۡنَا بِہَا قَوْمًا لَّیۡسُوۡا بِہَا بِکٰفِرِیۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2727,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To appoint, to decree",
      "hw": "مقرر",
      "s": "« » means to set a term or period (45 verses: 2:231, 2:232, 2:234, 2:235, 2:282, 4:77, 6:2, 6:60, 6:128, 7:34, 7:135, 7:185, 10:11, 10:49, 11:3, 11:104, 13:2, 13:38, 14:10, 14:44, 15:5, 16:61, 17:99, 20:129, 22:5, 22:33, 23:43, 28:28, 28:29, 29:5, 29:53, 30:8, 31:29, 35:13, 35:45, 39:5, 39:42, 40:67, 42:14, 46:3, 63:10, 63:11, 65:2, 65:4, 71:4).",
      "d": "«اَجَل» «اَجَل» «دَنَا اَجَلُہٗ» «اَجَّلَ» «وَّ بَلَغۡنَاۤ  اَجَلَنَا الَّذِیۡۤ  اَجَّلۡتَ لَنَا»"
    }
  ],
  "594": [
    {
      "id": 2728,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "fly",
      "hw": "مکھی",
      "s": "« » means fly (1 verse: 22:73).",
      "d": "«ذُبَاب» «ذَبَّ عَنْہُ» «مَذِبَّۃ» «ذُبٌّ و اَذِبَّۃ» «وَ اِنۡ یَّسۡلُبۡہُمُ الذُّبَابُ شَیۡئًا لَّا یَسۡتَنۡقِذُوۡہُ مِنۡہُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2729,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "fly",
      "hw": "مکھی",
      "s": "« » is the generic term for the honey bee (1 verse: 16:68).",
      "d": "«نَحْل» «نَحْلَۃٌ» «وَ اَوۡحٰی رَبُّکَ اِلَی النَّحۡلِ اَنِ اتَّخِذِیۡ مِنَ الۡجِبَالِ بُیُوۡتًا وَّ مِنَ الشَّجَرِ وَ مِمَّا یَعۡرِشُوۡنَ»"
    }
  ],
  "595": [
    {
      "id": 2730,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to meet",
      "hw": "ملنا",
      "s": "« » means two things meeting face-to-face (2 verses: 2:14-2:76)",
      "d": "« » means to meet face-to-face, to encounter. To come and meet from the front. (m. l.)\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ اِذَا لَقُوا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا قَالُوۡۤا اٰمَنَّا»\nTranslation: And when these hypocrites meet the believers, they say, 'We have believed.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2731,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to meet",
      "hw": "ملنا",
      "s": "« » means to go and join something similar to the first thing (2 verses: 3:170-62:3)",
      "d": "« » means to go and join something similar to the first thing (m. l.). « » is the thing that joins with the first. The fruit of the second time after the first (source).\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ یَسۡتَبۡشِرُوۡنَ بِالَّذِیۡنَ لَمۡ یَلۡحَقُوۡا بِہِمۡ مِّنۡ خَلۡفِہِمۡ  ۙ اَلَّا خَوۡفٌ عَلَیۡہِمۡ وَ لَا ہُمۡ یَحۡزَنُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And they rejoice in those who have not yet joined them [in martyrdom] from behind them – there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve.\nAt another place, the Lord says:\n«وَّ اٰخَرِیۡنَ مِنۡہُمۡ  لَمَّا یَلۡحَقُوۡا بِہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And there are others among them who have not yet joined them. And He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
    },
    {
      "id": 2732,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to meet",
      "hw": "ملنا",
      "s": "« » means two living things being connected without temporal or spatial gap (1 verse: 9:123)",
      "d": "«وَلَی یَلیٰ وَلْیًا»\nExample in the spatial sense is:\nIn the Quran it is:\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا قَاتِلُوا الَّذِیۡنَ یَلُوۡنَکُمۡ مِّنَ الۡکُفَّارِ»\nTranslation: O you who have believed, fight those who are near you of the disbelievers.\nIts meaning is: fight the disbelievers who are adjacent to you first. Then if they become Muslim or accept obedience, then fight those adjacent to them, and then those living with them. And an example in the temporal sense is not found in the Quran. However, it is clear from the following saying of the Prophet ﷺ:\nProphetic Hadith states:\n«خَیْرُ الْقُرُوْنِ قَرْنِیْ ثُمَّ الَّذِیْنَ یَلُوْنَھُمْ ثُمَّ الَّذِیْنَ یَلُوْنَھُمْ»\nTranslation: The best generation is mine, then those who follow them, then those who follow them!\nAnd this refers to the time of the Prophet ﷺ, then the time of the Companions, then the time of the Successors."
    },
    {
      "id": 2735,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to meet",
      "hw": "ملنا",
      "s": "« » means one thing meeting another due to being in proximity (1 verse: 13:4)",
      "d": "« » means to share shade. Neighbor. And « » and « » mean to be contiguous due to proximity of distance. To be in proximity. To live as neighbors (source). To be side by side. To be in adjacency.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ قِطَعٌ مُّتَجٰوِرٰتٌ»\nTranslation: And on the earth are plots [of land] adjacent to one another."
    },
    {
      "id": 2736,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to meet",
      "hw": "ملنا",
      "s": "« » means to join and become sealed (1 verse: 21:30)",
      "d": "« » means two or several things to join together and become sealed, to stick together (m. source). And « » is the term for a woman whose labia majora are joined in such a way that intercourse is not possible (m.f.)\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«اَوَ لَمۡ  یَرَ الَّذِیۡنَ  کَفَرُوۡۤا  اَنَّ  السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضَ کَانَتَا رَتۡقًا فَفَتَقۡنٰہُمَا»\nTranslation: Have those who disbelieved not considered that the heavens and the earth were a joined entity, and We separated them?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2738,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to meet",
      "hw": "ملنا",
      "s": "« » means to gather scattered parts of something into the original thing, to include (2 verses: 6:143-6:144)",
      "d": "«اَلشَّمْل» «جَمَعَ اللہُ شَمْلَھُمْ» «فَرَّقَ اللہُ شَمْلَھُمْ» «شَمِلَ» «شَمَلَ» «شَمِلَ» «اِشْتَمَلَ»\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«قُلۡ ءٰٓالذَّکَرَیۡنِ حَرَّمَ اَمِ الۡاُنۡثَیَیۡنِ اَمَّا اشۡتَمَلَتۡ عَلَیۡہِ اَرۡحَامُ الۡاُنۡثَیَیۡنِ ؕ»\nTranslation: Say, 'Have you considered: if Allah should make the male [offspring] forbidden or the female, or what the wombs of the females contain?'\nNote: (Lexicon of antonyms refers to words that have two opposite meanings.)"
    }
  ],
  "596": [
    {
      "id": 2739,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to mix",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means to mix various things, to blend (2 verses: 9:102-38:24)",
      "d": "« » means to mix two or more different things together. To blend. To mix up. And its opposite is « ».\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ اٰخَرُوۡنَ اعۡتَرَفُوۡا بِذُنُوۡبِہِمۡ خَلَطُوۡا عَمَلًا صَالِحًا وَّ اٰخَرَ  سَیِّئًا»\nTranslation: And others have confessed their sins, mixing a righteous deed with another that is bad."
    },
    {
      "id": 2740,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to join",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means to join from behind (4 verses: 12:101-26:83-34:27-52:21)",
      "d": "« » means to go and join from behind.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«تَوَفَّنِیۡ مُسۡلِمًا وَّ اَلۡحِقۡنِیۡ  بِالصّٰلِحِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: [My Lord] cause me to die a Muslim and join me with the righteous."
    },
    {
      "id": 2741,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to connect",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means to mix and join (18 verses: 2:27-4:10-4:90-6:136-11:81-13:21-13:25-14:29-17:18-28:35-28:51-38:56-58:8-82:15-84:12-87:12-92:15-111:3)",
      "d": "« » means to join two things together so that they become connected (m. l.). « » is the opposite of « ». And (the opposite of connection is disconnection). To mix. To join. This word is used in both material and spiritual contexts. In material sense, it means to reach something. In spiritual sense, it means to join relationships and make them connected.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ یَقۡطَعُوۡنَ مَاۤ اَمَرَ اللّٰہُ بِہٖۤ  اَنۡ یُّوۡصَلَ»\nTranslation: And they sever what Allah has ordered to be joined."
    },
    {
      "id": 2742,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to unite",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means to gather scattered parts of the same thing (2 verses: 3:103-8:63)",
      "d": "« » means to gather scattered parts of the same thing. To fix and join the scattered thread. And its opposite is « ». Meaning to agree with each other's thoughts and to remove differences of hearts and create love. And « » means heartfelt love. And composition is such a phrase where various parts are collected in the correct places considering precedence and sequence. (m.f.)\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ اَلَّفَ بَیۡنَ قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ ؕ لَوۡ اَنۡفَقۡتَ مَا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ جَمِیۡعًا مَّاۤ  اَلَّفۡتَ بَیۡنَ قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And Allah united the hearts of the believers. If you had spent all that is in the earth, you could not have united their hearts."
    },
    {
      "id": 2746,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "mixing",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means two similar things mixing together to become one (1 verse: 76:2)",
      "d": "« » means mixing. Blending and mixing, and « » means mixed, blended. Its plural is « ». (Majid) i.e., two similar things mixing together to become one.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اِنَّا خَلَقۡنَا الۡاِنۡسَانَ مِنۡ نُّطۡفَۃٍ  اَمۡشَاجٍ ٭ۖ  نَّبۡتَلِیۡہِ»\nTranslation: And We have created man from a mixed drop (i.e., the sperm of both man and woman) which We then test."
    },
    {
      "id": 2747,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To mix",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means to mix something into a drink (3 verses: 76:5, 76:17, 83:27).",
      "d": "«مَزَجَ» «اَلشَّرَاب» «مِزْج» «مِزَاج» «اَطِبَّاء» «وَ یُسۡقَوۡنَ  فِیۡہَا کَاۡسًا کَانَ مِزَاجُہَا زَنۡجَبِیۡلًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2748,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "mixing",
      "hw": "ملانا",
      "s": "« » means to mix two similar things in such a way that their individual characteristics remain intact (2 verses: 25:53-55:19)",
      "d": "«مَرَجَ» «غُصْنٌ مَرِیْجٌ» «اَمْرٌ مَرَیْج»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«مَرَجَ  الۡبَحۡرَیۡنِ یَلۡتَقِیٰنِ»\nTranslation: He has released the two seas, meeting together. (Jalandhari) Two flowing seas that meet. (Osmani)"
    }
  ],
  "597": [
    {
      "id": 2752,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "turning away",
      "hw": "منہ",
      "s": "«تَوَلّٰی عَنْ»",
      "d": "«تَوَلّٰی» «تَوَلّٰی عَن»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ تَوَلَّ عَنۡہُمۡ حَتّٰی حِیۡنٍ»\nTranslation: So turn away from them for a time."
    },
    {
      "id": 2753,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "turning away",
      "hw": "منہ",
      "s": "« » is used for severe turning away (2 verses: 6:46-6:157)",
      "d": "«اَعْرَضَ عَنْہُ و صَدّ» «صَدَف» «عَنْ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«سَنَجۡزِی الَّذِیۡنَ یَصۡدِفُوۡنَ عَنۡ اٰیٰتِنَا سُوۡٓءَ الۡعَذَابِ  بِمَا  کَانُوۡا  یَصۡدِفُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: We will surely recompense those who turn away from Our signs with the worst of punishment for what they used to do.\nAt another place, the Lord says:\n«اُنۡظُرۡ  کَیۡہَ نُصَرِّفُ الۡاٰیٰتِ ثُمَّ ہُمۡ یَصۡدِفُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: See how We diversify the verses, yet they turn away."
    }
  ],
  "598": [
    {
      "id": 2754,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "making compatible",
      "hw": "موافقت",
      "s": "« » means Allah making circumstances favorable for someone (used in a good sense) (1 verse: 4:35)",
      "d": "«اَلْوَفْق» «وَفَّقَ تَوْفِیْقًا»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اِنۡ یُرِیۡدَاۤ  إِصۡلَاحًا یُّوَفِّقِ اللّٰہُ بَیۡنَہُمَا»\nTranslation: If both (the spouses) desire reconciliation, Allah will bring about harmony between them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2755,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "making compatible",
      "hw": "موافقت",
      "s": "«وَطَأ عَلَی الْاَمْر»",
      "d": "«وَطَأ» «وَطَأ عَلَی الْاَمْر»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اِنَّمَا النَّسِیۡٓءُ زِیَادَۃٌ فِی الۡکُفۡرِ  یُضَلُّ بِہِ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا یُحِلُّوۡنَہٗ عَامًا وَّ یُحَرِّمُوۡنَہٗ عَامًا لِّیُوَاطِئُوۡا عِدَّۃَ مَا حَرَّمَ اللّٰہُ فَیُحِلُّوۡا مَا حَرَّمَ اللّٰہُ»\nTranslation: Indeed, the postponing of restriction is an increase in disbelief by which those who have disbelieved are led astray. They make it lawful one year and unlawful another year to correspond with the number of months that Allah has made sacred, so they make lawful what Allah has made forbidden."
    }
  ],
  "599": [
    {
      "id": 2756,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "bending",
      "hw": "موڑنا",
      "s": "« » means to bend something in one direction, even if it becomes double (1 verse: 11:5)",
      "d": "« » means two, and « » means second, and «  ,  » means to double, bend, or fold (Mufradat, Majid).\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اَلَاۤ  اِنَّہُمۡ  یَثۡنُوۡنَ صُدُوۡرَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: Do they not see that they are turning their breasts (bending them)?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2757,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "bending",
      "hw": "موڑنا",
      "s": "« » means to bend or twist something, sometimes here and sometimes there (4 verses: 3:78-3:153-4:135-63:5)",
      "d": "«لَوَی الْحَبَل» «لَوٰی یَدَہٗ» «لِیًّا بِدَیْنِہٖ» «لِوَاء» «اَلْاَلْوَاءِ»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَ اِنَّ مِنۡہُمۡ لَفَرِیۡقًا یَّلۡوٗنَ اَلۡسِنَتَہُمۡ بِالۡکِتٰبِ»\nTranslation: And indeed, among them is a group who twist their tongues while reciting the Book."
    }
  ],
  "600": [
    {
      "id": 2759,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "compassionate",
      "hw": "مہربان",
      "s": "« » means the heart swelling with compassion upon seeing someone's hardship (11 verses: 2:143-2:207-3:30-9:117-9:128-16:7-16:47-22:65-24:20-57:9-59:10)",
      "d": "« » means tenderness to arise and compassion upon seeing someone's hardship. The heart swelling with compassion upon seeing someone's trouble.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اَلزَّانِیَۃُ وَ الزَّانِیۡ فَاجۡلِدُوۡا کُلَّ وَاحِدٍ مِّنۡہُمَا مِائَۃَ جَلۡدَۃٍ ۪ وَّ لَا  تَاۡخُذۡکُمۡ بِہِمَا رَاۡفَۃٌ  فِیۡ  دِیۡنِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: The [adulteress] and the [adulterer] - each of them give a hundred lashes, and let not pity for them take you away from the law of Allah.\nAnd « » means tender-hearted (i.e., compassionate, merciful) whose heart swells upon seeing someone's hardship and is concerned with its removal.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«لَقَدۡ جَآءَکُمۡ رَسُوۡلٌ مِّنۡ اَنۡفُسِکُمۡ عَزِیۡزٌ عَلَیۡہِ مَا عَنِتُّمۡ حَرِیۡصٌ عَلَیۡکُمۡ بِالۡمُؤۡمِنِیۡنَ رَءُوۡفٌ رَّحِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: O people, there has come to you a Messenger from among yourselves; severe upon him is what you suffer; [he is] concerned for you and for the believers [he is] kind and merciful."
    },
    {
      "id": 2761,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Merciful",
      "hw": "مہربان",
      "s": "« » means a mercy and compassion like that of a mother for her child (1 verse: 19:13).",
      "d": "«اَلْحَنِیْن» «حَنَتِ المَرْاَۃُ اَوِ النَّاقَۃُ لِوَلَدِھَا» «حَنَّ» «حَنَّان» «وَّ حَنَانًا مِّنۡ لَّدُنَّا وَ زَکٰوۃً ؕ وَ کَانَ تَقِیًّا»"
    }
  ],
  "601": [
    {
      "id": 2762,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To stamp, to seal",
      "hw": "مہر ",
      "s": "« » means to stamp or print (11 verses: 4:155, 7:100, 7:101, 9:87, 9:93, 10:74, 16:108, 30:59, 40:35, 47:16, 63:3).",
      "d": "«طَبَعَ» «تَطَبَّعَ النَّھْر» «طَبَعَ» «طَبَعَ الدَّرَاھِم» «مَطْبَع» «مَطْبُوْع» «طَوَابِع» «طَبَعَ» «بَلۡ طَبَعَ اللّٰہُ عَلَیۡہَا بِکُفۡرِہِمۡ فَلَا یُؤۡمِنُوۡنَ  اِلَّا قَلِیۡلًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2763,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To stamp, to seal",
      "hw": "مہر ",
      "s": "« » means to seal something upon its completion so that nothing can enter or exit it (6 verses: 2:7, 6:46, 33:40, 36:65, 42:24, 45:23).",
      "d": "«خَتَمَ» «خَتَمَ الْاَنَاء» «خَتَام» «خَتَمَ الْقُرآن» «خَتَمَ اللّٰہُ عَلٰی قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ وَ عَلٰی سَمۡعِہِمۡ»"
    }
  ],
  "602": [
    {
      "id": 2764,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To grant respite",
      "hw": "مہلت",
      "s": "« » and « » : to gradually and gently increase the respite (indefinite period) (2 verses: 73:11, 86:17).",
      "d": "«مَھَّلَ» «سَارَ عَلٰی مَھْلٍ» «مَھَّل» «فَمَہِّلِ الۡکٰفِرِیۡنَ  اَمۡہِلۡہُمۡ رُوَیۡدًا» «مَھَّل» «اَمْھَل»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2765,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "To grant respite",
      "hw": "مہلت",
      "s": "« » means to lengthen the rope (5 verses: 7:183, 13:32, 22:44, 22:48, 68:45).",
      "d": "«مَلَا» «مَلَاکَ اللہ» «مَلَا» «مَلِیٌّ مِنَ الدَّھْر» «مَلِیٌّ» «اَمْلٰی» «وَ  اُمۡلِیۡ   لَہُمۡ  اِنَّ  کَیۡدِیۡ مَتِیۡنٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2766,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "to grant respite",
      "hw": "مہلت",
      "s": "« » means waiting with leniency until a specified time (2 verses: 2:280-37:88)",
      "d": "«نَظَرَ» «نَظَرَ فُلَانَا الْمَدِیْن» «اَنْظَار» «وَ اِنۡ کَانَ ذُوۡ عُسۡرَۃٍ فَنَظِرَۃٌ اِلٰی مَیۡسَرَۃٍ»"
    }
  ],
  "603": [
    {
      "id": 2767,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Guest",
      "hw": "مہمان",
      "s": "« » means guest (6 verses: 11:78-15:51-15:68-18:77-51:24-54:37)",
      "d": "« » means guest. It is a well-known word. Its plurals are « » and « ». « » can be used as both singular and plural.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«فَاتَّقُوا اللّٰہَ وَ لَا تُخۡزُوۡنِ فِیۡ ضَیۡفِیۡ»\nTranslation: So fear Allah and do not disgrace me in my guests."
    },
    {
      "id": 2768,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "guest; delegation",
      "hw": "مہمان",
      "s": "« » means a delegation, i.e., a royal guest (1 verse: 19:85)",
      "d": "«وَفَدَ» «یَوۡمَ نَحۡشُرُ الۡمُتَّقِیۡنَ  اِلَی الرَّحۡمٰنِ وَفۡدًا»"
    }
  ],
  "604": [
    {
      "id": 2769,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Months",
      "hw": "مہینے",
      "s": "« » means the months of the year (1 verse: 9:36)",
      "d": "« » means all months. The maximum number of months.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«اِنَّ عِدَّۃَ الشُّہُوۡرِ عِنۡدَ اللّٰہِ اثۡنَا عَشَرَ شَہۡرًا فِیۡ  کِتٰبِ اللّٰہِ یَوۡمَ خَلَقَ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضَ»\nTranslation: Indeed, the number of months in the sight of Allah is twelve months, in the record of Allah, from the day He created the heavens and the earth."
    },
    {
      "id": 2770,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Months",
      "hw": "مہینے",
      "s": "« » means the specified months (17 verses: 2:185-2:194-2:197-2:217-2:226-2:234-4:92-5:2-5:97-9:2-9:5-9:36-34:12-46:15-58:4-65:4-97:3)",
      "d": "« » means the specified months. Their number is always less than or equal to twelve. When the number is mentioned and is singular, « » is used. « » is the plural of paucity, which applies to numbers from 3 to 10.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«لِلَّذِیۡنَ یُؤۡلُوۡنَ مِنۡ نِّسَآئِہِمۡ تَرَبُّصُ اَرۡبَعَۃِ اَشۡہُرٍ»\nTranslation: For those who take an oath not to have sexual relations with their wives is a waiting period of four months."
    }
  ],
  "605": [
    {
      "id": 2771,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Nail / Peg",
      "hw": "میخ",
      "s": "« » means nail, peg. (1 Verse: 54:13)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « », meaning nail, peg. « » means to spear or to drive in a peg. « » refers to the small peg driven to fasten, seal, or strengthen something. And « » also refers to a rope made from palm bark used to bind a ship. (Nail / Peg)\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ  حَمَلۡنٰہُ  عَلٰی ذَاتِ اَلۡوَاحٍ  وَّ دُسُرٍ»\nTranslation: And We carried him on a ship made of planks and pegs."
    },
    {
      "id": 2772,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Nail / Peg",
      "hw": "میخ",
      "s": "« » means stakes, pegs, wooden pins. (3 Verses: 38:12-78:7-89:10)",
      "d": "«اَوْتَاد» «وَتَد» «وَتَد» «وَتَدَان» «وَتَد» «وَتَدَ» «وَتْد» «اَوْتَادُ الْاَرْضِ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اَلَمۡ  نَجۡعَلِ الۡاَرۡضَ مِہٰدًا وَّ  الۡجِبَالَ  اَوۡتَادًا»\nTranslation: Have We not made the earth a resting place and the mountains as stakes?"
    }
  ],
  "606": [
    {
      "id": 2773,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Despair",
      "hw": "نا امید",
      "s": "« » means to despair. It is general in meanings of hopelessness. « » means to lose hope gradually. (4 Verses: 12:80-12:87-12:110-13:31)",
      "d": "« » means to cut off hope, i.e., to cease hoping for something or to become hopeless regarding it. This can happen before or during the time of desire. « » means to gradually end expectations regarding a matter. To finally become hopeless after experience.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنَّہٗ  لَا یَایۡئَسُ مِنۡ رَّوۡحِ اللّٰہِ  اِلَّا الۡقَوۡمُ  الۡکٰفِرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: None despair of the mercy of Allah except the disbelieving people.\nAnd « » means to gradually lose hope in a matter. To finally become hopeless after experience.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«حَتّٰۤی اِذَا اسۡتَیۡئَسَ الرُّسُلُ وَ ظَنُّوۡۤا اَنَّہُمۡ قَدۡ کُذِبُوۡا جَآءَہُمۡ نَصۡرُنَا»\nTranslation: Until when the messengers had lost hope and thought that they were denied, Our victory came to them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2774,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Despair",
      "hw": "نا امید",
      "s": "« » means to despair of good; it is a more severe degree of despair than « ». (5 Verses: 15:56-30:36-39:53-41:49-42:28)",
      "d": "« » means to despair of good. To break one's hope. And « » means the most intense form of despair. And « » as a descriptor refers to a person who is accustomed to considering only the dark aspects and faults of every matter and who rarely ponders the good aspects.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«لَا یَسۡئَمُ الۡاِنۡسَانُ مِنۡ دُعَآءِ  الۡخَیۡرِ ۫ وَ اِنۡ مَّسَّہُ  الشَّرُّ  فَیَئُوۡسٌ قَنُوۡطٌ»\nTranslation: Man does not tire of praying for good, but if evil touches him, he becomes despairing and hopeless."
    },
    {
      "id": 2775,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Despair",
      "hw": "نا امید",
      "s": "« » means a despair that causes one to be afflicted with grief. (5 Verses: 6:44-23:77-30:12-30:49-43:75)",
      "d": "« » means to become grief-stricken due to intense despair. And it also means to be unaware. To be grief-stricken and broken-hearted. When despair leads to grief, this word is used. Satan is also called Iblis because he became despairing and broken-hearted regarding Allah's mercy.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ اِنۡ کَانُوۡا مِنۡ قَبۡلِ اَنۡ یُّنَزَّلَ عَلَیۡہِمۡ مِّنۡ  قَبۡلِہٖ لَمُبۡلِسِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And they were despairing before it was sent down upon them, from before it came."
    }
  ],
  "607": [
    {
      "id": 2776,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Impure",
      "hw": "ناپاک",
      "s": "« » refers to things declared unlawful by Sharia. (9 Verses: 5:90-6:125-6:145-7:71-9:95-9:125-10:100-22:30-33:33)",
      "d": "« » can mean filth as well as impurity. (See details under 'Filth'). It refers to the impurity of things that Sharia has declared haram or impure, whether material or spiritual.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«فَاَعۡرِضُوۡا عَنۡہِمۡ ؕ اِنَّہُمۡ  رِجۡسٌ ۫ وَّ مَاۡوٰىہُمۡ  جَہَنَّمُ»\nTranslation: So turn away from them. Indeed, they are impure, and their abode is Hell."
    },
    {
      "id": 2777,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Impure / Evil",
      "hw": "ناپاک",
      "s": "« » means foul things and people whose nature inclines toward vulgarity. (8 Verses: 2:267-3:179-4:2-5:100-7:58-8:37-14:26-24:26)",
      "d": "«خَبِیْث» «طَیَّب» «خَبِیْث» «خَبِثُ الْحَدِیْء»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تَیَمَّمُوا الۡخَبِیۡثَ مِنۡہُ تُنۡفِقُوۡنَ وَ لَسۡتُمۡ بِاٰخِذِیۡہِ اِلَّاۤ اَنۡ تُغۡمِضُوۡا فِیۡہِ»\nTranslation: And do not aim toward the defective thereof from which you spend, and you would not take it except that you close your eyes to it.\nAnd in its spiritual usage, « » refers to a person whose nature is inclined to vulgarity or who is wicked.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«اَلۡخَبِیۡثٰتُ لِلۡخَبِیْثِیۡنَ وَ الۡخَبِیْثُوۡنَ لِلۡخَبِیْثٰتِ»\nTranslation: Evil women are for evil men, and evil men are for evil women."
    }
  ],
  "608": [
    {
      "id": 2779,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Detestable",
      "hw": "ناپسندیدہ",
      "s": "« » is that which a person of sound nature (i.e., one who is composed and of good nature) dislikes. (27 Verses: 2:216-3:83-4:19-8:8-9:32-9:33-9:46-9:53-9:81-10:82-10:99-13:15-16:62-16:106-17:38-20:73-24:33-40:14-41:11-46:15-47:9-47:26-47:28-49:7-49:12-61:8-61:9)",
      "d": "« » means to dislike something. And « » is everything that is offensive to a person of sound nature and that nature finds repulsive (unpalatable).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اَیُحِبُّ  اَحَدُکُمۡ  اَنۡ یَّاۡکُلَ  لَحۡمَ  اَخِیۡہِ  مَیۡتًا فَکَرِہۡتُمُوۡہُ»\nTranslation: Would any of you like to eat the flesh of his dead brother? You would surely detest it!\nThen there are matters that seem detestable on the surface but are actually based on benefit. Sharia has identified such matters.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«کُتِبَ عَلَیۡکُمُ الۡقِتَالُ وَ ہُوَ کُرۡہٌ لَّکُمۡ ۚ وَ عَسٰۤی اَنۡ تَکۡرَہُوۡا شَیۡئًا وَّ ہُوَ خَیۡرٌ لَّکُمۡ»\nTranslation: Fighting has been prescribed for you, though it is disliked by you. And perhaps you dislike a thing while it is good for you.\nThus, « » is that which is disliked by both reason and Sharia.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«کُلُّ ذٰلِکَ کَانَ سَیِّئُہٗ عِنۡدَ رَبِّکَ مَکۡرُوۡہًا»\nTranslation: All that - its evil is ever, in the sight of your Lord, detestable."
    },
    {
      "id": 2780,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Detestable",
      "hw": "ناپسندیدہ",
      "s": "« » means an extremely detestable matter that causes an uproar. (1 Verse: 19:89)",
      "d": "«اِدَّ» «اَرِیْد» «اَدَّ الْاَمْر» «اَدِیْد» «اِدّ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ قَالُوا  اتَّخَذَ  الرَّحۡمٰنُ  وَلَدًا لَقَدۡ  جِئۡتُمۡ  شَیۡئًا  اِدًّا»\nTranslation: And they say, \"The Most Merciful has taken a son.\" You have indeed brought forth a terrible thing."
    },
    {
      "id": 2781,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Detestable / Reprehensible",
      "hw": "ناپسندیدہ",
      "s": "« » is that which society considers ugly and bad. (17 Verses: 3:104-3:110-3:114-5:79-7:157-9:67-9:71-9:112-12:58-16:90-22:41-22:72-24:21-29:29-29:45-31:17-58:2)",
      "d": "« » means every strange and astonishing matter, every matter that is disliked or forbidden by Sharia, evil matters or evil deeds. And « » is every matter that society considers ugly and bad.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَلۡتَکُنۡ مِّنۡکُمۡ اُمَّۃٌ یَّدۡعُوۡنَ اِلَی الۡخَیۡرِ وَ یَاۡمُرُوۡنَ بِالۡمَعۡرُوۡفِ وَ یَنۡہَوۡنَ عَنِ الۡمُنۡکَرِ»\nTranslation: And let there be from among you a nation who invite to good, enjoin what is right, and forbid what is wrong.\nThen Sharia did not leave « » merely to the approval and disapproval of society; rather, wherever an incorrect or unlawful matter has become prevalent in society and society does not consider it ugly, Sharia has commanded its rectification.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«وَ تَاۡتُوۡنَ فِیۡ نَادِیۡکُمُ الۡمُنۡکَرَ»\nTranslation: And you commit the reprehensible in your meetings."
    },
    {
      "id": 2782,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Disapproved",
      "hw": "ناپسندیدہ",
      "s": "« » means an extremely unreasonable, irrational, and un-Islamic matter. (1 Verse: 18:71)",
      "d": "«اِمْر» «مُنْکَرًا عَظِیْمًا» «اَمِرَ الْاَمْر»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«قَالَ اَخَرَقۡتَہَا لِتُغۡرِقَ اَہۡلَہَا ۚ لَقَدۡ جِئۡتَ شَیۡئًا اِمۡرًا»\nTranslation: Moses said, 'Did you break it so that its occupants would drown? You have certainly done a most disapproved thing.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2784,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Disapproved",
      "hw": "ناپسندیدہ",
      "s": "« » is used idiomatically to express disgust at something bad. (3 Verses: 17:23-21:67-46:17)",
      "d": "« » originally refers to every dirty and detestable thing, such as filth, dirt, and nail clippings, etc. But idiomatically, this word is spoken to express disgust at something bad (muf).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اُفٍّ لَّکُمۡ وَ لِمَا تَعۡبُدُوۡنَ مِنۡ دُوۡنِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: 'Fie upon you and upon what you worship besides Allah!'"
    }
  ],
  "609": [
    {
      "id": 2785,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Ignorant",
      "hw": "نادان",
      "s": "« » means ignorant, unaware. (10 Verses: 2:67-2:273-6:35-7:199-11:46-12:33-12:89-25:63-28:55-39:64)",
      "d": "« » means ignorant, unaware. Its opposite is « ». Ignorant means a person's mind being empty of knowledge (muf). The reason can be anything (muf). This word is general. For example: The Quran states:\n«یَحۡسَبُہُمُ الۡجَاہِلُ اَغۡنِیَآءَ مِنَ التَّعَفُّفِ»\nTranslation: 'The ignorant think them rich because of their abstention.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2786,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Ignorant",
      "hw": "نادان",
      "s": "« » means a person of low intellect and poor morals. (6 Verses: 2:13-2:130-2:142-4:5-6:140-7:155)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of «  ,  » meaning a person of low intellect and poor morals. Its opposite is « » meaning forbearance, tolerance, and gentleness. In the meaning of « », two aspects are found: (1) low intellect and (2) having poor morals (m. l). And « » means such an ignorant person who, due to lack of intellect, remains incapable of learning or acquiring knowledge, and whose morals are also poor. That is, to object despite not knowing or understanding is his habit; a fool (m. q).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«سَیَقُوۡلُ السُّفَہَآءُ مِنَ النَّاسِ مَا وَلّٰىہُمۡ عَنۡ قِبۡلَتِہِمُ الَّتِیۡ کَانُوۡا عَلَیۡہَا»\nTranslation: 'The foolish among the people will say, 'What has turned them away from the direction they used to face?'"
    }
  ],
  "610": [
    {
      "id": 2787,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Displeasure",
      "hw": "ناراضگی",
      "s": "« » means anger, displeasure. (3 Verses: 3:162-5:80-9:58)",
      "d": "« » means anger, displeasure. Dislike. Its opposite is « » meaning contentment and pleasure. And « » means being unhappy with an action contrary to one's will. Being angry. For example: The Quran states:\n«فَاِنۡ اُعۡطُوۡا مِنۡہَا رَضُوۡا وَ اِنۡ لَّمۡ یُعۡطَوۡا مِنۡہَاۤ اِذَا ہُمۡ یَسۡخَطُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: 'If they are given some of it, they are pleased; but if they are not given any, they become angry.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2788,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Displeasure",
      "hw": "ناراضگی",
      "s": "« » means enmity, malice, hatred, hostility. (2 Verses: 47:29-47:37)",
      "d": "« » means intense, hidden enmity, strong hatred. Such displeasure that one keeps concealed in the heart. That is, such displeasure that a person does not remove from his heart.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اَمۡ حَسِبَ الَّذِیۡنَ فِیۡ  قُلُوۡبِہِمۡ مَّرَضٌ اَنۡ  لَّنۡ یُّخۡرِجَ اللّٰہُ  اَضۡغَانَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: 'Or do those in whose hearts is disease think that Allah would never bring forth their malice?'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2789,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Displeasure",
      "hw": "ناراضگی",
      "s": "« » means grudge, enmity; such displeasure that reaches the level of enmity and is concealed in the heart. (3 Verses: 7:43-15:47-59:10)",
      "d": "In the meaning of « », two aspects are found: (1) intensity of hatred, hidden enmity (muf), (2) theft and betrayal. Secretly taking something and keeping it in one's belongings (m. q). And « » means grudge, rancor (mansajd).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ نَزَعۡنَا مَا فِیۡ صُدُوۡرِہِمۡ مِّنۡ غِلٍّ»\nTranslation: 'And We removed from their breasts any grudge.'"
    }
  ],
  "611": [
    {
      "id": 2790,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Ungrateful",
      "hw": "ناشکرا",
      "s": "« » means ungrateful for favors. (15 Verses: 11:9-17:27-17:67-17:89-17:99-22:38-22:66-25:50-31:32-34:17-35:36-42:48-43:15-76:3-76:24)",
      "d": "In the meaning of « », two aspects are found: (1) denying Allah, (2) denying Allah's favors. Being ungrateful for blessings. For the one who denies Allah, the word « » is generally used, and for the one who denies His favors, the words « » or « » are generally used. Its opposite is « » and « ».\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنَّا ہَدَیۡنٰہُ  السَّبِیۡلَ  اِمَّا شَاکِرًا وَّ اِمَّا کَفُوۡرًا»\nTranslation: 'Indeed, We have shown him the way; so whether he is grateful or ungrateful.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2791,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Ungrateful",
      "hw": "ناشکرا",
      "s": "« » is such an ungrateful person who constantly mentions calamities and difficulties but never even mentions the name of Allah's bestowed favors. (1 Verse: 100:6)",
      "d": "« » means to be ungrateful, and « » is used for such an ungrateful person who constantly mentions calamities and difficulties but never even mentions the name of Allah's bestowed favors. Ungrateful. Miser. Ungrateful for favors (mansajd. m. q).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنَّ  الۡاِنۡسَانَ لِرَبِّہٖ  لَکَنُوۡدٌ»\nTranslation: 'Indeed, man is to his Lord ungrateful.'"
    }
  ],
  "612": [
    {
      "id": 2794,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Disobey",
      "hw": "نافرمانی",
      "s": "« » means to persist in sins recklessly, to sin, to commit evil. (6 Verses: 38:28-71:27-75:5-80:42-82:14-83:7-)",
      "d": "« » means to widely tear something, and « » is used for a person who is completely immersed in sins. And does not even consider sin as sin, nor inclines towards repentance (muf). Immoral. And « » means engrossed in sins. Fornicator (mansajd). And « » means to be audacious.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«اِنَّکَ اِنۡ تَذَرۡہُمۡ یُضِلُّوۡا عِبَادَکَ وَ لَا یَلِدُوۡۤا  اِلَّا  فَاجِرًا کَفَّارًا»\nTranslation: 'If you leave them, they will mislead Your servants and will not produce except a wicked, ungrateful offspring.'"
    }
  ],
  "613": [
    {
      "id": 2795,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Nose",
      "hw": "ناک",
      "s": "« » is used for the body part (nose) (1 verse: 5:45)",
      "d": "«اَنْف» «اَنْف» «اَنْفُ الْجَبْل»\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«وَ الۡعَیۡنَ بِالۡعَیۡنِ وَ الۡاَنۡفَ بِالۡاَنۡفِ»\nTranslation: An eye for an eye and a nose for a nose."
    },
    {
      "id": 2796,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Nose",
      "hw": "ناک",
      "s": "« » a long and downward-growing nose or the nose of a large and proud man (1 verse: 68:16)",
      "d": "«خُرْطُوْم» «اِنْخَرْطَمَ» «خَرَاطِیْم» «خَرَاطِیْمُ الْقَوْم»\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«اِذَا تُتۡلٰی عَلَیۡہِ اٰیٰتُنَا قَالَ اَسَاطِیۡرُالۡاَوَّلِیۡنَ . سَنَسِمُہٗ عَلَی الۡخُرۡطُوۡمِ»\nTranslation: When Our verses are recited to him, he says, 'These are the fables of the ancients.' We will surely mark him on the nose."
    }
  ],
  "614": [
    {
      "id": 2798,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "name; to name",
      "hw": "نام",
      "s": "« » means an attributive name, a name given due to a particular attribute, aside from the real name (1 verse: 49:11)",
      "d": "«لَقَب» «اِذۡ قَالَتِ الۡمَلٰٓئِکَۃُ یٰمَرۡیَمُ اِنَّ اللّٰہَ یُبَشِّرُکِ بِکَلِمَۃٍ مِّنۡہُ ٭ۖ اسۡمُہُ الۡمَسِیۡحُ عِیۡسَی ابۡنُ مَرۡیَمَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2799,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Name. Giving a name.",
      "hw": "نام",
      "s": "« » a bad nickname, a shameful name (1 verse: 49:11)",
      "d": "« » is also a type of nickname, but it presents a person's bad attributes, whether they exist in him or not, and whether it relates to lineage or character. And « » means to give someone a bad name or nickname (muf. m.).\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«وَ لَا تَنَابَزُوۡا بِالۡاَلۡقَابِ»\nTranslation: And do not call each other by [bad] nicknames."
    },
    {
      "id": 2800,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Name. Giving a name.",
      "hw": "نام",
      "s": "« » saying 'so-and-so' instead of mentioning a person's name (1 verse: 25:28)",
      "d": "«فُلَانٌ» «فُلَانَۃٌ» «ال» «رَکَیْتُ الْفُلَانَ» «جَلَبْتُ الْفُلَانَۃَ»\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«یٰوَیۡلَتٰی لَیۡتَنِیۡ لَمۡ اَتَّخِذۡ فُلَانًا خَلِیۡلًا»\nTranslation: 'Woe to me! I wish I had not taken so-and-so as a close friend.'"
    }
  ],
  "615": [
    {
      "id": 2801,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "ill-omened; cursed",
      "hw": "نامبارک",
      "s": "« » means ill-omened, ill-fated (2 verses: 56:9-90:19)",
      "d": "«شَئَم» «شَاءَمَ» «شَئَمَ» «یَمَنَ» «شَأمَ» «شَامَت» «مَشْئَمَۃ» «شَئَمَ» «وَ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا بِاٰیٰتِنَا ہُمۡ اَصۡحٰبُ الۡمَشۡئَمَۃِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2802,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Blessed Name",
      "hw": "نامبارک",
      "s": "« » meaning ill-fated or unfortunate (2 verses: 41:16-54:19)",
      "d": "« » its opposite is « ». And « » means good fortune and in acquiring good, the divine affairs assist and help a person (muf. m. l). And « » is that in which divine will has a greater role. In the terminology of astronomers, « » refers to Saturn and Mars, and « » to Jupiter and Venus (m.).\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«اِنَّاۤ اَرۡسَلۡنَا عَلَیۡہِمۡ رِیۡحًا صَرۡصَرًا فِیۡ یَوۡمِ  نَحۡسٍ  مُّسۡتَمِرٍّ»\nTranslation: And We sent upon them a screaming wind during a continuous ill-fated day."
    },
    {
      "id": 2803,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Blessed Name",
      "hw": "نامبارک",
      "s": "« » such a misfortune that is continuous and ongoing until it erases all traces (1 verse: 69:7)",
      "d": "« » is such a misfortune that is continuous and ongoing until it erases all traces of something. (For details, see continuous.)\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«سَخَّرَہَا عَلَیۡہِمۡ  سَبۡعَ  لَیَالٍ وَّ ثَمٰنِیَۃَ اَیَّامٍ ۙ حُسُوۡمًا ۙ فَتَرَی الۡقَوۡمَ فِیۡہَا صَرۡعٰی»\nTranslation: He [Allah] subjected it [the wind] to them for seven nights and eight days continuously; then you would see the people [of Thamud] lying dead therein."
    }
  ],
  "616": [
    {
      "id": 2804,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To be saved",
      "hw": "نجات",
      "s": "« » meaning to escape from a calamity (52 verses: 2:49-2:50-6:63-6:64-7:64-7:72-7:83-7:89-7:141-7:165-10:22-10:23-10:73-10:92-10:103-11:58-11:66-11:94-11:116-12:45-12:110-14:6-17:67-19:72-20:40-20:80-21:9-21:71-21:74-21:76-21:88-23:28-26:65-26:119-26:170-27:53-27:57-29:15-29:24-29:32-29:65-31:32-37:76-37:115-37:134-39:61-40:41-41:18-44:30-54:34-61:10-70:14)",
      "d": "The word « » is used only for escaping from a calamity. To attain release. In any manner. Its usage is general.\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«وَ قَالَ الَّذِیۡ نَجَا مِنۡہُمَا وَ ادَّکَرَ  بَعۡدَ اُمَّۃٍ»\nTranslation: And the one who escaped from among them [the two prisoners] said, after a long time, 'I will inform you of its interpretation.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2805,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To be saved",
      "hw": "نجات",
      "s": "« » meaning to be saved from a calamity and to reach the beloved thing (20 verses: 3:185-4:13-4:73-5:119-6:16-9:72-9:89-9:100-9:111-10:64-33:71-37:60-40:9-44:57-45:30-48:5-57:12-61:12-64:9-85:11)",
      "d": "The word « » is used for being saved from a calamity and reaching the beloved thing. (Faq l 273) To attain good with safety (muf).\nFor instance, in the Quran:\n«فَمَنۡ زُحۡزِحَ عَنِ النَّارِ وَ اُدۡخِلَ الۡجَنَّۃَ فَقَدۡ فَازَ»\nTranslation: So whoever is removed away from the Fire and admitted into Paradise, he has indeed attained success.\n«فَازَ» «فَوْز» «فَوَّزَ الرَّجُل» «مَفَازَۃ»\nFor instance, the divine declaration is:\n«فَلَا تَحۡسَبَنَّہُمۡ بِمَفَازَۃٍ مِّنَ الۡعَذَابِ ۚ وَ لَہُمۡ عَذَابٌ اَلِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: So do not think that they will escape from the punishment; and for them is a painful punishment.\nIn this verse, the word « » gives the meaning of the place of perdition and its cause."
    }
  ],
  "617": [
    {
      "id": 2807,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "vows and offerings; sacrifice",
      "hw": "نذر و نیاز",
      "s": "« » is everything a person gives purely to attain Allah's pleasure and proximity in His way (2 verses: 3:183-5:27)",
      "d": "«قُرْبَانَ الْمَلَک» «اِذۡ قَرَّبَا قُرۡبَانًا فَتُقُبِّلَ مِنۡ اَحَدِہِمَا وَ لَمۡ یُتَقَبَّلۡ مِنَ الۡاٰخَرِ»"
    }
  ],
  "618": [
    {
      "id": 2808,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Soft / To Soften",
      "hw": "نرم",
      "s": "« » means softness or flexibility (1 verse: 39:23)",
      "d": "«لَانَ، لِیْن» «قَوْلًا لَّیِّنًا» «خَشُونَت» «ثُمَّ  تَلِیۡنُ جُلُوۡدُہُمۡ وَ قُلُوۡبُہُمۡ  اِلٰی ذِکۡرِ اللّٰہِ» «اَلَان» «وَ اَلَنَّا لَہُ  الۡحَدِیۡدَ اَنِ اعۡمَلۡ سٰبِغٰتٍ وَّ قَدِّرۡ فِی السَّرۡدِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2809,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Soft / To Soften",
      "hw": "نرم",
      "s": "« » means to soften something with oil (2 verses: 23:20-68:9)",
      "d": "«دُھْن» «اَدْھَنَ» «وَدُّوۡا  لَوۡ  تُدۡہِنُ  فَیُدۡہِنُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2810,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Soft / To Soften",
      "hw": "نرم",
      "s": "« » means heart's softness, i.e., tender-heartedness (2 verses: 9:114-11:75)",
      "d": "«اٰہَ» «اَوَّاہٌ» «اِنَّ اِبۡرٰہِیۡمَ  لَاَوَّاہٌ  حَلِیۡمٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2811,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Soft / To Soften",
      "hw": "نرم",
      "s": "« » means to adopt caution and softness in performing an action (1 verse: 18:19)",
      "d": "«لَطْفَ» «تَلَطّف» «فَلۡیَاۡتِکُمۡ بِرِزۡقٍ مِّنۡہُ  وَ لۡـیَؔ‍‍‍تَلَطَّفۡ وَ لَا  یُشۡعِرَنَّ  بِکُمۡ  اَحَدًا»"
    }
  ],
  "619": [
    {
      "id": 2812,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Near / To Bring Near",
      "hw": "نزدیک",
      "s": "« » means to be near to doing something but not doing it (21 verses: 2:20-2:71-4:78-7:150-9:117-14:17-17:73-17:76-18:93-19:90-20:15-22:72-24:35-24:43-25:42-28:10-42:5-43:52-67:8-68:51-72:19)",
      "d": "«کَادَ» «یَکَادُ الۡبَرۡقُ یَخۡطَفُ اَبۡصَارَہُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2813,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Near / To Bring Near",
      "hw": "نزدیک",
      "s": "« » means to be near; this word is general, used for nearness in distance, time, relation, and status (36 verses: 2:35-2:187-2:222-2:237-3:167-4:11-4:43-4:172-5:8-5:82-6:151-6:152-7:19-7:114-9:28-9:99-12:60-16:77-17:32-17:34-17:57-18:24-18:81-19:52-22:13-26:42-34:37-39:3-46:28-50:16-51:27-56:11-56:85-56:88-83:21-83:28)",
      "d": "«قَرُبَ» «بَعُدَ» «قَرُبَ» «اَوۡ  تَحُلُّ قَرِیۡبًا مِّنۡ دَارِہِمۡ» «وَ لَا تَقۡرَبُوۡہُنَّ حَتّٰی یَطۡہُرۡنَ» «لَا نَشۡتَرِیۡ بِہٖ ثَمَنًا وَّ لَوۡ  کَانَ ذَا قُرۡبٰی» «وَ اَنۡ تَعۡفُوۡۤا اَقۡرَبُ لِلتَّقۡوٰی» «اِقْتَرَبَ» «وَ اسۡجُدۡ وَ اقۡتَرِبۡ» «اِقۡتَرَبَتِ السَّاعَۃُ  وَ انۡشَقَّ  الۡقَمَرُ» «قَرَّبَ» «اسۡمُہُ الۡمَسِیۡحُ عِیۡسَی ابۡنُ مَرۡیَمَ وَجِیۡہًا فِی الدُّنۡیَا وَ الۡاٰخِرَۃِ وَ مِنَ الۡمُقَرَّبِیۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2814,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Near / To Bring Near",
      "hw": "نزدیک",
      "s": "« » is used for nearness in distance and for degradation in status (13 verses: 2:61-2:282-4:3-5:108-7:169-30:3-32:21-33:51-33:59-53:8-53:9-58:7-73:20)",
      "d": "«دَنٰی» «آخرت» «ثُمَّ  دَنَا فَتَدَلّٰی» «اَدْنٰی» «اَعْلٰی» «اَتَسۡتَبۡدِلُوۡنَ الَّذِیۡ ہُوَ اَدۡنٰی بِالَّذِیۡ ہُوَ خَیۡرٌ» «اَدْنٰی» «اِنَّ  رَبَّکَ یَعۡلَمُ  اَنَّکَ  تَقُوۡمُ  اَدۡنٰی مِنۡ ثُلُثَیِ الَّیۡلِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2815,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Near / To Bring Near",
      "hw": "نزدیک",
      "s": "« » is used to express the tightness of time (2 verses: 40:18-53:57)",
      "d": "«اَزِفَ» «اَزِفَتِ الشُّخُوْصُ» «اٰزِفۃ» «وَ اَنۡذِرۡہُمۡ یَوۡمَ الۡاٰزِفَۃِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2816,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Be Near / To Bring Near",
      "hw": "نزدیک",
      "s": "« » is used for nearness in rank and status (9 verses: 26:64-26:90-34:37-38:25-38:40-39:3-50:31-67:27-81:13)",
      "d": "«زَلَفَ» «وَ اِنَّ لَہٗ عِنۡدَنَا لَزُلۡفٰی وَ حُسۡنَ مَاٰبٍ» «اَزْلَفَ» «وَ  اِذَا  الۡجَنَّۃُ   اُزۡلِفَتۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2818,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To draw near. To bring close.",
      "hw": "نزدیک",
      "s": "« » implies such nearness in time or distance that two things seem joined together (1 verse: 43:53).",
      "d": "«قَرَن» «قَرِیْن» «قَرَنَ» «قَرَنَ الثَّوْرَیْن» «اِقْتَرَنَ» «اِقْتَرَن»\n«اَوۡ جَآءَ مَعَہُ الۡمَلٰٓئِکَۃُ مُقۡتَرِنِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: Or (it happens) that the angels gather and come with him (Jalandhari).\nComing with him, the angels, tied in a bundle (Othmani)."
    }
  ],
  "620": [
    {
      "id": 2821,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Sign. Sign.",
      "hw": "نشانی",
      "s": "« » is a sign that, through contemplation, leads to the acquisition of knowledge (353 verses: 2:39-2:41-2:61-2:73-2:99-2:106-2:118-2:129-2:145-2:151-2:164-2:187-2:211-2:219-2:221-2:231-2:242-2:248-2:252-2:259-2:266-3:4-3:7-3:11-3:13-3:19-3:21-3:41-3:49-3:50-3:58-3:70-3:97-3:98-3:101-3:103-3:108-3:112-3:113-3:118-3:164-3:190-3:199-4:56-4:140-4:155-5:10-5:44-5:75-5:86-5:89-5:114-6:4-6:21-6:25-6:27-6:33-6:35-6:37-6:39-6:46-6:49-6:54-6:55-6:65-6:68-6:93-6:97-6:98-6:99-6:105-6:109-6:118-6:124-6:126-6:130-6:150-6:157-6:158-7:9-7:26-7:32-7:35-7:36-7:37-7:40-7:51-7:58-7:64-7:72-7:73-7:103-7:106-7:126-7:132-7:133-7:136-7:146-7:147-7:156-7:174-7:175-7:176-7:177-7:182-7:203-8:2-8:31-8:52-8:54-9:9-9:11-9:65-10:1-10:5-10:6-10:7-10:15-10:17-10:20-10:21-10:24-10:67-10:71-10:73-10:75-10:92-10:95-10:97-10:101-11:1-11:59-11:64-11:96-11:103-12:1-12:7-12:35-12:105-13:1-13:2-13:3-13:4-13:7-13:27-13:38-14:5-15:1-15:75-15:77-15:81-16:11-16:12-16:13-16:65-16:67-16:69-16:79-16:101-16:104-16:105-17:1-17:12-17:59-17:98-17:101-18:9-18:17-18:56-18:57-18:105-18:106-19:10-19:21-19:58-19:73-19:77-20:22-20:23-20:42-20:47-20:54-20:56-20:126-20:127-20:128-20:133-20:134-21:5-21:32-21:37-21:77-21:91-22:16-22:51-22:52-22:57-22:72-23:30-23:45-23:50-23:58-23:66-23:105-24:1-24:18-24:34-24:46-24:58-24:59-24:61-25:36-25:37-25:73-26:2-26:4-26:8-26:15-26:67-26:103-26:121-26:128-26:139-26:154-26:158-26:174-26:190-26:197-27:1-27:12-27:13-27:52-27:81-27:82-27:83-27:84-27:86-27:93-28:2-28:35-28:36-28:45-28:47-28:59-28:87-29:15-29:23-29:24-29:35-29:44-29:47-29:49-29:50-30:10-30:16-30:20-30:21-30:22-30:23-30:24-30:25-30:28-30:37-30:46-30:53-30:58-31:2-31:7-31:31-31:32-32:15-32:22-32:24-32:26-33:34-34:5-34:9-34:15-34:19-34:38-34:43-36:33-36:37-36:41-36:46-37:14-38:29-39:42-39:52-39:59-39:63-39:71-40:4-40:13-40:23-40:35-40:56-40:63-40:69-40:78-40:81-41:3-41:15-41:28-41:37-41:39-41:40-41:44-41:53-42:29-42:32-42:33-42:35-43:46-43:47-43:48-43:69-44:33-45:3-45:4-45:5-45:6-45:8-45:9-45:11-45:13-45:25-45:31-45:35-46:7-46:26-46:27-48:20-51:20-51:37-53:18-54:2-54:15-54:42-57:9-57:17-57:19-58:5-62:2-62:5-64:10-65:11-68:15-74:16-78:28-79:20-83:13-90:19)",
      "d": "« » is any sign that, upon reflection, yields knowledge of that thing and its attributes (Muf). For example, if one knows that certain types of signs exist on a particular path, and those signs are found, then one becomes certain that they have found the way and are proceeding correctly. In the Quran, the word 'āyah' is used in three meanings: (1) a sentence of the Quran, (2) a sign (as defined above), (3) a miracle given to prophets. A Quranic sentence also serves as a sign due to its eloquence and rhetoric, proving it is the speech of a being above humanity. Thus, every sentence is a sign, and in the other meanings, they naturally fall under the mentioned verses.\n«سَنُرِیۡہِمۡ اٰیٰتِنَا فِی الۡاٰفَاقِ وَ فِیۡۤ اَنۡفُسِہِمۡ حَتّٰی یَتَبَیَّنَ لَہُمۡ اَنَّہُ الۡحَقُّ»\nTranslation: We will show them Our signs in the horizons and within themselves until it becomes clear to them that it (the Quran) is the truth."
    },
    {
      "id": 2823,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Sign. Sign.",
      "hw": "نشانی",
      "s": "« » means the existence of a thing or the fulfillment of an act is contingent upon another act or thing: e.g., wudu is a condition for prayer; without it, prayer is not valid (1 verse: 47:18).",
      "d": "«اَشْرَطَ الْاِبِلَ» «شرط» «اشراط» «اَشْرَاطُ السَّاعَۃ»\n«فَہَلۡ یَنۡظُرُوۡنَ اِلَّا السَّاعَۃَ اَنۡ تَاۡتِیَہُمۡ بَغۡتَۃً ۚ فَقَدۡ جَآءَ اَشۡرَاطُہَا»\nTranslation: So do they await anything but the Hour that it should come upon them unexpectedly? But already its signs have come (into effect)."
    },
    {
      "id": 2824,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Sign. Sign.",
      "hw": "نشانی",
      "s": "« » means a sign erected on the road, such as a stone, etc. (3 verses: 5:3-70:43-88:19)",
      "d": "«نَصَبَ الشَّیْءِ» «اَلنَّصْب» «نُصُب» «نُصْب»\n«یَوۡمَ یَخۡرُجُوۡنَ مِنَ الۡاَجۡدَاثِ سِرَاعًا کَاَنَّہُمۡ اِلٰی نُصُبٍ یُّوۡفِضُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: On the Day they will emerge from the graves in haste, as if they are rushing toward a sign."
    },
    {
      "id": 2825,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Sign. Sign.",
      "hw": "نشانی",
      "s": "« » means a distinguishing sign (6 verses: 2:273-7:46-7:48-47:30-48:29-55:41)",
      "d": "« » means sign, mark. And « » means to mark so that one is distinguished from others (Muf). Thus, « » refers to an emblematic or distinguishing sign.\n«سِیۡمَاہُمۡ فِیۡ وُجُوۡہِہِمۡ مِّنۡ اَثَرِ السُّجُوۡدِ»\nTranslation: Their mark is on their faces from the trace of prostration."
    },
    {
      "id": 2826,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Sign. Sign.",
      "hw": "نشانی",
      "s": "« » means religious symbols: signs that have a connection to religion (4 verses: 2:158-5:2-22:32-22:36)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « », meaning religious symbols, i.e., signs given sanctity in a religious context. Things of reverence, places, and symbols. Sha'air of Hajj: the rites and places of Hajj. Sha'air of Allah: signs that Allah has deemed respectable. And Sha'air of Allah also refers to sacrificial animals sent toward the House of Allah.\n«اِنَّ الصَّفَا وَ الۡمَرۡوَۃَ مِنۡ شَعَآئِرِ اللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: Indeed, Safa and Marwah are among the symbols of Allah.\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا لَا تُحِلُّوۡا شَعَآئِرَ اللّٰہِ وَ لَا الشَّہۡرَ الۡحَرَامَ وَ لَا الۡہَدۡیَ وَ لَا الۡقَلَآئِدَ»\nTranslation: O you who believe! Do not violate the symbols of Allah, nor the sacred month, nor the sacrificial animals, nor the garlands."
    }
  ],
  "621": [
    {
      "id": 2828,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To mark. To brand.",
      "hw": "نشان",
      "s": "« » is used for making inscriptions or marks for beauty or branding (8 verses: 2:273-7:46-7:48-15:75-47:30-48:29-55:41-68:16)",
      "d": "« » means to mark, to brand (Muf). It also means to inscribe or carve on the body, to tattoo (M. L.). And « » means to dye. And « » and « » are the thing with which a mark is made or color applied. And « » means beautiful (M. Q.).\n«سَنَسِمُہٗ عَلَی الۡخُرۡطُوۡمِ»\nTranslation: We will surely mark him on the snout (the prominent part of the nose)."
    }
  ],
  "622": [
    {
      "id": 2829,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Advice. To advise. To obtain.",
      "hw": "نصیحت",
      "s": "« » means to speak or act with goodwill toward someone (5 verses: 7:62-7:79-7:93-9:91-11:34)",
      "d": "« » means to do good to someone. And « » is every word or action in which the goodwill of another is sought (Muf).\n«وَ لَا یَنۡفَعُکُمۡ نُصۡحِیۡۤ اِنۡ اَرَدۡتُّ اَنۡ اَنۡصَحَ لَکُمۡ اِنۡ کَانَ اللّٰہُ یُرِیۡدُ اَنۡ یُّغۡوِیَکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And my advice will not benefit you, if I intend to advise you, while Allah intends to misguide you."
    },
    {
      "id": 2830,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "advice; to advise; to receive advice",
      "hw": "نصیحت",
      "s": "« » is advice that refreshes the remembrance of Allah (181 verses: 2:114-2:221-2:269-2:282-3:7-3:58-5:13-5:14-5:91-6:44-6:68-6:69-6:70-6:80-6:90-6:118-6:119-6:121-6:126-6:138-6:152-7:2-7:3-7:26-7:57-7:63-7:69-7:130-7:165-7:201-8:2-8:57-9:126-10:3-11:24-11:30-11:114-11:120-12:42-12:104-13:19-13:28-14:5-14:25-14:52-15:6-15:9-16:13-16:17-16:43-16:44-16:90-17:41-17:46-18:28-18:57-18:70-18:83-18:101-19:2-20:3-20:14-20:34-20:42-20:44-20:99-20:113-20:124-21:2-21:7-21:10-21:24-21:42-21:48-21:50-21:84-21:105-22:35-23:71-23:85-23:110-24:1-24:27-24:37-25:18-25:29-25:50-25:62-25:73-26:5-26:209-26:227-27:62-28:43-28:46-28:51-29:45-29:51-32:4-32:15-32:22-33:34-33:41-35:37-36:11-36:19-36:69-37:3-37:13-37:155-37:168-38:1-38:8-38:29-38:32-38:43-38:46-38:49-38:87-39:9-39:21-39:22-39:23-39:27-39:45-40:13-40:54-40:58-41:41-43:5-43:36-43:44-44:13-44:58-45:23-47:18-47:20-50:8-50:37-50:45-51:49-51:55-52:29-53:29-54:17-54:22-54:25-54:32-54:40-56:62-56:73-57:16-58:19-62:9-63:9-65:10-68:51-68:52-69:12-69:42-69:48-72:17-73:19-74:31-74:49-74:54-74:55-74:56-76:29-77:5-79:43-80:4-80:11-81:27-87:9-87:10-88:21-89:23-94:4-79:35)",
      "d": "«ذَکَرَ» «نَسِیَ» «ذِکْر» «ذِکْر» «تَذْکِرَہ» «ذِکْر» «ذَکَّرَ» «ذَکَّرَ الْقَوْم» «وَّ  ذَکِّرۡ فَاِنَّ  الذِّکۡرٰی تَنۡفَعُ الۡمُؤۡمِنِیۡنَ» «تَذَکَّر» «وَ یُبَیِّنُ  اٰیٰتِہٖ لِلنَّاسِ لَعَلَّہُمۡ  یَتَذَکَّرُوۡنَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2831,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Advice. To advise. To obtain.",
      "hw": "نصیحت",
      "s": "« » means to advise through exhortation (arousing desire) and intimidation (instilling fear) (15 verses: 2:66-2:232-2:275-3:138-4:63-4:66-5:46-7:145-10:57-11:120-16:125-24:34-26:136-58:3-65:2)",
      "d": "« » means to speak of goodness that softens the heart (M. L.), to incline toward piety through threat and promise. Admonition mixed with fear, instilling fear of Allah's punishment and arousing desire for reward (Muf. Manjad).\n«یٰۤاَیُّہَا النَّاسُ قَدۡ جَآءَتۡکُمۡ مَّوۡعِظَۃٌ مِّنۡ رَّبِّکُمۡ وَ شِفَآءٌ لِّمَا فِی الصُّدُوۡرِ»\nTranslation: O mankind! There has come to you an admonition from your Lord and a healing for what is in the breasts."
    },
    {
      "id": 2832,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Advice. To advise. To obtain.",
      "hw": "نصیحت",
      "s": "« » to guide someone in an advisory manner before an event occurs (18 verses: 2:132-2:180-2:182-2:240-4:11-4:12-4:131-5:106-6:144-6:151-6:152-6:153-19:31-29:8-31:14-36:50-42:13-46:15)",
      "d": "« » meaning to guide in an advisory manner before an event occurs (muf)\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«مِنۡۢ بَعۡدِ وَصِیَّۃٍ یُّوۡصٰی بِہَاۤ اَوۡ دَیۡنٍ»\nTranslation: This division of inheritance will be after the execution of the will (of the deceased) that he made or after the repayment of the debt.\nAnd when it is attributed to Allah, its meaning will be to emphasize or command.\nFor example: The divine command is:\n«یُوۡصِیۡکُمُ اللّٰہُ فِیۡۤ  اَوۡلَادِکُمۡ»\nTranslation: Allah commands you regarding the division of inheritance among your children."
    }
  ],
  "623": [
    {
      "id": 2834,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » meaning kindness, mercy done to others (23 verses: 2:211-3:171-3:174-5:7-5:20-8:53-14:6-16:18-16:53-16:71-26:22-29:67-33:9-37:57-39:8-39:49-43:13-49:8-54:35-68:2-68:49-92:19-93:11)",
      "d": "«نِعْمَۃ» «نِعَمْ» «اَنْعُمْ نِعْمَۃٌ»\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«یَسۡتَبۡشِرُوۡنَ بِنِعۡمَۃٍ مِّنَ اللّٰہِ وَ فَضۡلٍ»\nTranslation: They rejoice in the bounties and grace of Allah."
    },
    {
      "id": 2835,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » the means and requisites of comfort and ease (2 verses: 44:27-73:11)",
      "d": "« » meaning every thing that causes improvement, abundance, and prosperity in livelihood (m. l). The means and requisites of comfort and ease.\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَّ  نَعۡمَۃٍ  کَانُوۡا فِیۡہَا  فٰکِہِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And the comforts in which they used to enjoy."
    },
    {
      "id": 2836,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » basic requisites of life's necessities (34 verses: 7:69-7:74-53:55-55:13-55:16-55:18-55:21-55:23-55:25-55:28-55:30-55:32-55:34-55:36-55:38-55:40-55:42-55:45-55:47-55:49-55:51-55:53-55:55-55:57-55:59-55:61-55:63-55:65-55:67-55:69-55:71-55:73-55:75-55:77)",
      "d": "«اٰلَاء» «اِلًی» «اَلیٰ ۔ یَا لُوْ»\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«لَا یَاۡلُوۡنَکُمۡ خَبَالًا»\nTranslation: They do not bear any deficiency in your corruption.\nAnd « » refers to those bounties that fulfill human necessities and come continuously, so one does not feel lack of anything in life (faqih 160). And generally it is used in plural because such a bounty is not singular. Therefore « » occurs.\nFor example: The divine command is:\n«ذُو الۡعَصۡفِ وَ الرَّیۡحَانُ فَبِاَیِّ  اٰلَآءِ  رَبِّکُمَا تُکَذِّبٰانِ»\nTranslation: The one with fruits and palm trees with sheaths, and grain with husk, and fragrant flowers. So which of the bounties of your Lord do you both deny?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2837,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To bestow bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » to do kindness and honor. It is general (only used for humans) (63 verses: 1:6-2:40-2:47-2:122-2:150-2:211-2:231-3:103-3:171-3:174-4:69-4:72-5:3-5:6-5:7-5:11-5:20-5:23-5:110-8:53-11:10-12:6-14:6-14:28-14:34-16:18-16:53-16:71-16:72-16:81-16:83-16:112-16:114-16:121-17:83-19:58-26:22-27:19-28:17-29:67-31:20-31:31-33:9-33:37-35:3-37:57-39:8-39:49-41:51-43:13-43:59-44:27-46:15-48:2-49:8-52:29-54:35-68:2-68:49-73:11-89:15-92:19-93:11)",
      "d": "«اَنْعَمَ» «اَنْعَمَ عَلٰی فَرْسِہٖ»\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«اِہۡدِ نَا الصِّرَاطَ الۡمُسۡتَقِیۡمَ صِرَاطَ الَّذِیۡنَ اَنۡعَمۡتَ عَلَیۡہِمۡ»\nTranslation: Guide us to the straight path, the path of those upon whom You have bestowed Your favors.\nAnd « » means to bestow bounty upon someone.\nFor example: The divine command is:\n«فَاَمَّا الۡاِنۡسَانُ  اِذَا مَا ابۡتَلٰىہُ  رَبُّہٗ فَاَکۡرَمَہٗ  وَ نَعَّمَہٗ»\nTranslation: But as for man, when his Lord tests him and honors him and bestows bounty upon him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2838,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To bestow bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » to grant. To bestow. To make owner (3 verses: 6:94-39:8-39:49)",
      "d": "« » meaning to grant. To bestow. To make owner (minj). And meaning to grant honor and service (muf).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَّ تَرَکۡتُمۡ مَّا خَوَّلۡنٰکُمۡ  وَرَآءَ  ظُہُوۡرِکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And you have left behind what We granted you behind your backs."
    },
    {
      "id": 2839,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To bestow bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » to be intoxicated due to abundance of comfort and ease (3 verses: 11:116-21:13-23:33)",
      "d": "« » meaning abundance of comfort and ease. Abundance of bounties that can lead man astray. And « » means the affluent who are intoxicated by abundance of wealth (muf).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ اتَّبَعَ  الَّذِیۡنَ  ظَلَمُوۡا مَاۤ اُتۡرِفُوۡا فِیۡہِ وَ کَانُوۡا مُجۡرِمِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: And those who did wrong followed what they were intoxicated with therein, and they were criminals."
    },
    {
      "id": 2841,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To bestow bounty",
      "hw": "نعمت",
      "s": "« » to make rich and satisfy, to give treasure, and according to some, to make poor (1 verse: 53:48)",
      "d": "« » meaning to make rich and satisfy (muf. minj). That is, to give so much wealth and property that besides fulfilling needs, one is also satisfied. And meaning to make rich then increase that wealth. To grant treasure (m. q). And according to some lexicographers, « » is opposite of « ». Meaning to make poor. And « » is from the category of opposite words (idhaad).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ اَنَّہٗ  ہُوَ  اَغۡنٰی وَ  اَقۡنٰی»\nTranslation: And that it is He who enriches and grants treasure (Thana'i). He makes rich and makes poor (Jalandhri).\nNote: (Opposite words are those that have two separate meanings that are opposite to each other.)"
    }
  ],
  "624": [
    {
      "id": 2843,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Loss. To incur loss.",
      "hw": "نقصان",
      "s": "« » to incur loss in trade. To have reduction in principal (3 verses: 17:82-35:39-71:21)",
      "d": "« » meaning to have reduction in principal (muf). In a transaction, to have loss instead of profit. To be broken. To be at loss. Its opposite is « ».\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ لَا یَزِیۡدُ الۡکٰفِرِیۡنَ  کُفۡرُہُمۡ اِلَّا خَسَارًا»\nTranslation: And it does not increase the disbelievers in their disbelief except loss."
    },
    {
      "id": 2844,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "loss; to incur loss",
      "hw": "نقصان",
      "s": "« » means goods not selling in trade; the market becoming sluggish (1 verse: 9:24)",
      "d": "«کَسَاد» «وَ تِجَارَۃٌ تَخۡشَوۡنَ  کَسَادَہَا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2845,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Loss. To incur loss.",
      "hw": "نقصان",
      "s": "« » means receiving inferior and worthless things in exchange for good ones. (7 verses: 2:282-7:85-11:15-11:85-12:20-26:183-72:13)",
      "d": "«بَخْس» «یَبْخَس» «فَمَنۡ یُّؤۡمِنۡۢ  بِرَبِّہٖ  فَلَا یَخَافُ بَخۡسًا وَّ لَا رَہَقًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2846,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Loss. To incur loss.",
      "hw": "نقصان",
      "s": "« » means to be destroyed while incurring loss. (9 verses: 14:28-17:102-25:13-25:14-25:18-35:10-35:29-48:12-84:11)",
      "d": "«بُوْر» «بَوَار» «وَ اَنۡفَقُوۡا مِمَّا رَزَقۡنٰہُمۡ سِرًّا وَّ عَلَانِیَۃً  یَّرۡجُوۡنَ  تِجَارَۃً  لَّنۡ تَبُوۡرَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2847,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Loss. To incur loss.",
      "hw": "نقصان",
      "s": "« » means to be liable for a debt or fine, to undertake the responsibility of payment from someone. (5 verses: 9:60-9:98-52:40-56:66-68:46)",
      "d": "«اَلْغُرْم» «غَرِم» «غَرِیْم» «اِنَّمَا الصَّدَقٰتُ لِلۡفُقَرَآءِ وَ الۡمَسٰکِیۡنِ وَ الۡعٰامِلِیۡنَ عَلَیۡہَا وَ الۡمُؤَلَّفَۃِ قُلُوۡبُہُمۡ وَ فِی الرِّقَابِ وَ الۡغٰرِمِیۡنَ وَ فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ وَ ابۡنِ السَّبِیۡلِ ؕ» «مَغْرَم» «غُرْم» «مُغْرَم» «لَوۡ نَشَآءُ  لَجَعَلۡنٰہُ  حُطَامًا فَظَلۡتُمۡ تَفَکَّہُوۡنَ اِنَّا  لَمُغۡرَمُوۡنَ»"
    }
  ],
  "625": [
    {
      "id": 2848,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To marry. To arrange marriage.",
      "hw": "نکاح",
      "s": "« » means the marriage contract, specifically for accountable beings, jinn and humans. (19 verses: 2:221-2:230-2:232-2:235-2:237-4:3-4:6-4:22-4:25-4:127-24:3-24:32-24:33-24:60-28:27-33:49-33:50-33:53-60:10)",
      "d": "«النِّکَاح» «نَکَحَ» «فَانۡکِحُوۡا مَا طَابَ لَکُمۡ مِّنَ النِّسَآءِ» «اَنْکَحَ» «وَ لَا تُنۡکِحُوا الۡمُشۡرِکِیۡنَ حَتّٰی یُؤۡمِنُوۡا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2849,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to marry; to arrange marriage",
      "hw": "نکاح",
      "s": "« » means to pair, to join. It is general. It also includes the concept of divorce after marriage (72 verses: 2:25-2:35-2:102-2:230-2:232-2:234-2:240-3:15-4:1-4:12-4:20-4:57-6:139-6:143-7:19-7:189-9:24-11:40-13:3-13:23-13:38-15:88-16:72-20:53-20:117-20:131-21:90-22:5-23:6-23:27-24:6-25:74-26:7-26:166-30:21-31:10-33:4-33:6-33:28-33:37-33:50-33:52-33:53-33:59-35:11-36:36-36:56-37:22-38:58-39:6-40:8-42:11-42:50-43:12-43:70-44:54-50:7-51:49-52:20-53:45-55:52-56:7-58:1-60:11-64:14-66:1-66:3-66:5-70:30-75:39-78:8-81:7)",
      "d": "«زَوْج» «زَوَّج» «زَوْج» «زَوَّج» «زَوَّج» «ب» «زَوَّجْنَا ھُمْ بِحُوْرٍ عِیْنٍ» «زَوَّجْنٰھُمْ حُوْرًا» «زَوَّجْنٰھُمْ بِحُوْرٍ» «زَوَّجْتُہٗ اِمْرَأَۃً»"
    }
  ],
  "626": [
    {
      "id": 2850,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To exit. To come out.",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to exit. It is commonly used. (51 verses: 2:74-2:149-2:150-2:240-2:243-4:66-4:100-5:22-5:37-5:61-7:13-7:18-7:58-8:47-9:42-9:47-9:83-12:31-15:34-16:69-18:5-19:11-20:22-22:22-23:20-24:43-24:53-27:12-28:20-28:21-28:32-28:79-30:25-30:48-32:20-34:2-37:64-38:77-41:47-47:16-49:5-54:7-55:22-57:4-59:2-59:11-59:12-60:1-65:1-70:43-86:7-)",
      "d": "«خَرَجَ» «دَخَلَ» «لَئِنۡ  اُخۡرِجۡتُمۡ  لَنَخۡرُجَنَّ مَعَکُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2851,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To exit. To come out.",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to exit into the field, to come forward. (7 verses: 2:250-3:154-4:81-14:21-14:48-26:91-79:36)",
      "d": "«بَرَزَ» «بَرْز» «دَعْوَتِ مُبَارِزَت» «وَ لَمَّا بَرَزُوۡا لِجَالُوۡتَ وَ جُنُوۡدِہٖ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2852,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To exit. To come out.",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to set out for battle or a campaign. (10 verses: 4:71-9:38-9:39-9:41-9:81-9:122-46:29-18:34-46:29-72:1)",
      "d": "«نَفَرَ» «اَلنَّفْر» «نَفِیْر» «نَفِیْرُ الْعَام» «فَانۡفِرُوۡا ثُبَاتٍ اَوِ انۡفِرُوۡا جَمِیۡعًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2854,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To exit. To come out.",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to flee after defeat or in distress. (1 verse: 17:81)",
      "d": "«زَھَقَ» «زَھَقَ النَّفْس» «زَھَقَ الْبَاطِل» «زَاھِقْ» «زَھَقَ» «زَاھِق» «زھق» «وَ قُلۡ جَآءَ الۡحَقُّ وَ زَہَقَ الۡبَاطِلُ ؕ اِنَّ الۡبَاطِلَ  کَانَ  زَہُوۡقًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2855,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To exit. To come out.",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to pass through, to exit from one side to the other. (1 verse: 55:33)",
      "d": "«نَفَذَ» «نَفَاذ» «یٰمَعۡشَرَ الۡجِنِّ وَ الۡاِنۡسِ  اِنِ اسۡتَطَعۡتُمۡ اَنۡ  تَنۡفُذُوۡا مِنۡ  اَقۡطَارِ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الۡاَرۡضِ فَانۡفُذُوۡا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2856,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to exit",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to slip away secretly (1 verse: 24:63)",
      "d": "« » means to exit quietly and stealthily (m. l) to slip away."
    },
    {
      "id": 2857,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to exit",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to exit while avoiding notice (1 verse: 24:63)",
      "d": "«لَاذَ» «لَاذَ بِالْجَبَل» «لَوْذ» «مَلَاذ» «لِوَاذًا»\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«قَدۡ یَعۡلَمُ  اللّٰہُ  الَّذِیۡنَ  یَتَسَلَّلُوۡنَ مِنۡکُمۡ  لِوَاذًا»\nTranslation: Indeed, Allah knows those among you who slip away covertly."
    },
    {
      "id": 2858,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to exit",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to surge forward with force and power. To leap out (1 verse: 86:6)",
      "d": "« » means for something to surge forward with force and power. To leap out (m. l).\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«فَلۡیَنۡظُرِ الۡاِنۡسَانُ مِمَّ خُلِقَ خُلِقَ مِنۡ مَّآءٍ  دَافِقٍ»\nTranslation: So let man consider from what he is created. He is created from a surging fluid."
    },
    {
      "id": 2859,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to exit",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means for the sun to rise (14 verses: 2:115-2:142-2:177-2:258-15:73-19:16-24:35-26:28-26:60-38:18-39:69-43:38-55:17-73:9)",
      "d": "«شَرْق» «شِرْق» «شَرَقَتِ الشَّمْس» «مَشْرِق» «شَرَقَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«وَ اَشۡرَقَتِ  الۡاَرۡضُ بِنُوۡرِ رَبِّہَا»\nTranslation: And the earth will shine with the light of its Lord.\nAnd « » also means to do something at the time of sunrise.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«فَاَتۡبَعُوۡہُمۡ مُّشۡرِقِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: So the Pharaoh's people pursued them at sunrise."
    },
    {
      "id": 2860,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to rise (of celestial bodies)",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means for stars and planets (including the sun) to rise. It is general (3 verses: 18:17-18:90-97:5)",
      "d": "«طَلَعَ» «طَلَعَ» «شَرَقَ» «طَلَعَ الْبَدْرُ عَلَیْنَا» «طَلَعَ»\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«سَلٰم ٌ ۟ ۛ ہِیَ حَتّٰی مَطۡلَعِ  الۡفَجۡرِ»\nTranslation: It (the night) is peace until the break of dawn."
    },
    {
      "id": 2861,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to take out",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » is general for 'to take out' (101 verses: 2:22-2:36-2:61-2:72-2:84-2:85-2:191-2:240-2:246-2:257-2:267-3:27-3:110-3:195-4:75-5:16-5:110-6:93-6:95-6:99-6:148-7:25-7:27-7:32-7:57-7:82-7:88-7:110-7:123-8:5-8:30-9:40-10:31-12:76-12:100-14:1-14:5-14:13-14:32-15:48-16:14-16:78-17:13-17:76-17:80-18:82-19:66-20:53-20:55-20:57-20:63-20:88-20:117-22:5-22:40-23:35-23:107-24:40-26:35-26:57-26:167-27:25-27:37-27:56-27:67-27:82-30:19-32:27-33:43-35:12-35:27-35:37-36:33-39:21-40:67-43:11-45:35-46:17-47:13-47:29-47:37-48:29-51:35-57:9-59:2-59:8-59:11-59:12-60:1-60:8-60:9-63:8-65:1-65:2-65:11-71:18-78:15-79:29-79:31-87:4-99:2)",
      "d": "« » means to take out. Its usage is general.\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«اِلَّا تَنۡصُرُوۡہُ فَقَدۡ  نَصَرَہُ  اللّٰہُ  اِذۡ اَخۡرَجَہُ الَّذِیۡنَ  کَفَرُوۡا»\nTranslation: If you do not aid him, Allah already aided him when those who disbelieved expelled him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2862,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to take out",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to bring forth into the open. (7 verses: 2:250-3:154-4:81-14:21-14:48-26:91-79:36)",
      "d": "« » means to take something out and bring it into an open, clear space.\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«وَ بُرِّزَتِ  الۡجَحِیۡمُ  لِمَنۡ یَّرٰی»\nTranslation: And Hell will be brought forth for whoever sees."
    },
    {
      "id": 2863,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "to take out",
      "hw": "نکلنا",
      "s": "« » means to expel someone while considering them contemptible and vile (2 verses: 6:52-11:30)",
      "d": "« » means to expel someone while considering them contemptible and vile. To drive away (muf) to repel forcefully (f l 188).\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«وَ لَا تَطۡرُدِ الَّذِیۡنَ یَدۡعُوۡنَ رَبَّہُمۡ بِالۡغَدٰوۃِ  وَ الۡعَشِیِّ  یُرِیۡدُوۡنَ وَجۡہَہٗ»\nTranslation: And do not drive away those who invoke their Lord morning and evening, seeking His countenance."
    }
  ],
  "627": [
    {
      "id": 2864,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "sight",
      "hw": "نگاہ",
      "s": "« » is a general word for sight or gaze (82 verses: 2:7-2:17-2:20-3:13-6:46-6:103-6:104-6:110-7:47-7:179-7:195-7:198-7:201-10:31-10:43-10:67-11:20-14:42-15:15-16:77-16:78-16:108-17:12-17:36-17:59-18:26-19:38-19:42-20:96-21:3-21:97-22:46-23:78-24:30-24:31-24:37-24:43-24:44-27:13-27:54-27:86-28:11-28:72-29:38-32:9-32:12-32:27-33:10-36:9-36:66-37:175-37:179-38:45-38:63-40:61-41:20-41:22-43:51-45:23-46:26-47:23-50:8-50:22-51:21-52:15-53:17-54:7-54:50-56:85-59:2-67:3-67:4-67:23-68:5-68:43-68:51-69:38-69:39-70:11-70:44-75:7-79:9)",
      "d": "« » means the eye as well, and the action of the eye, i.e., sight or gaze, and to see. And from this word, only the action of seeing is understood.\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«فَبَصَرُکَ الۡیَوۡمَ حَدِیۡدٌ»\nTranslation: So your sight today is sharp."
    },
    {
      "id": 2865,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "gaze",
      "hw": "نگاہ",
      "s": "« » means the edge or limit of something (6 verses: 14:43-27:40-37:48-38:52-42:45-55:56)",
      "d": "«طَرْف» «طَرْف» «طَرْفُ الْعَیْن» «طَرْفَۃُ عَیْنٍ» «طَرْف»\nFor example: The Noble Quran says:\n«اَنَا اٰتِیۡکَ بِہٖ قَبۡلَ  اَنۡ یَّرۡتَدَّ اِلَیۡکَ طَرۡفُکَ»\nTranslation: I can bring it to you before your glance returns to you (i.e., in the blink of an eye).\n«بَصَر» «طَرْفٌ خَفِیٌّ» «قٰصِرٰتُ الطَّرۡفِ»"
    }
  ],
  "628": [
    {
      "id": 2866,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Guardian",
      "hw": "نگہبان",
      "s": "« » one who protects, one who saves something from being lost or destroyed (29 verses: 2:238-4:34-4:80-6:92-6:104-6:107-9:112-11:57-11:86-12:12-12:55-12:63-12:64-12:81-15:9-21:82-23:5-23:9-33:35-34:21-42:6-42:48-50:4-50:32-70:29-70:34-82:10-83:33-86:4)",
      "d": "« » means to save something from being lost or destroyed (manjad). To guard. (m. r.) To try to save something from external dangers. Its opposite is « » meaning to waste. And « » is a active participle meaning one who protects, and « » contains an intensive form, meaning one who protects at all times.\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«فَاللّٰہُ خَیۡرٌ حٰفِظًا»\nTranslation: And Allah is the best Guardian.\nSimilarly, at another place, the divine command states:\n«وَ مَاۤ اَنَا عَلَیۡکُمۡ  بِحَفِیۡظٍ»\nTranslation: And I am not a guardian over you."
    },
    {
      "id": 2867,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Guardian",
      "hw": "نگہبان",
      "s": "« » a guardian who is himself vigilant and aware of every movement of the thing under his care (5 verses: 4:1-5:117-11:93-33:52-50:18)",
      "d": "« » means neck. And « » means to keep an eye on someone's neck or to supervise and guard them (muf). And « » means caution, guardianship, protection, and fear (manjad). Therefore, « » means a guardian who is himself always vigilant. And nothing that the one under his guardianship does remains hidden from him (faq la 170).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ کُنۡتُ عَلَیۡہِمۡ شَہِیۡدًا مَّا دُمۡتُ فِیۡہِمۡ ۚ فَلَمَّا تَوَفَّیۡتَنِیۡ کُنۡتَ اَنۡتَ الرَّقِیۡبَ عَلَیۡہِمۡ ؕ»\nTranslation: And I was a witness over them as long as I remained among them. But when You took me, You were the Watcher over them."
    },
    {
      "id": 2868,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Guardian",
      "hw": "نگہبان",
      "s": "« » a guardian who possesses full power to protect (1 verse: 4:85)",
      "d": "«قُوَّۃ ، قَاتَ» «اَقَاتَ» «مُقِیْت» «مُقِیْت» «مُقِیْت» «مُقِیْت»\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ کَانَ اللّٰہُ  عَلٰی کُلِّ  شَیۡءٍ  مُّقِیۡتًا»\nTranslation: And Allah is the Guardian over all things."
    },
    {
      "id": 2870,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Guardian",
      "hw": "نگہبان",
      "s": "« » one who takes under his protection and safeguards (2 verses: 5:48-59:23)",
      "d": "«مُھَیْمِن» «ھَیْمَنَ الطَّائِرُ عَلٰی فَرَاخِہٖ» «مُھَیْمِن»\nExample 1 - Meaning to take under protection: For example, in the Quran it is said:\n«اَلۡمَلِکُ الۡقُدُّوۡسُ السَّلٰمُ  الۡمُؤۡمِنُ الۡمُہَیۡمِنُ»\nTranslation: He is the King (the True and free from all defects), the Holy, the Source of Peace, the Giver of Security, and the Guardian.\nExample 2 - Not letting a right be wasted. For example, the divine command states:\n«وَ اَنۡزَلۡنَاۤ اِلَیۡکَ الۡکِتٰبَ بِالۡحَقِّ مُصَدِّقًا لِّمَا بَیۡنَ یَدَیۡہِ مِنَ الۡکِتٰبِ وَ مُہَیۡمِنًا عَلَیۡہِ»\nTranslation: And We have revealed to you, [O Muhammad], the Book in truth, confirming what preceded it of the Scripture and as a guardian over it."
    }
  ],
  "629": [
    {
      "id": 2871,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Swallow",
      "hw": "نگلنا",
      "s": "« » means to swallow. To take down through the throat. Common usage (1 verse: 11:44)",
      "d": "« » or « » means throat. The passage for eating food. And « » means to swallow. To take down through the throat. (muf)\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ قِیۡلَ یٰۤاَرۡضُ ابۡلَعِیۡ مَآءَکِ»\nTranslation: And it was said, 'O earth, swallow your water.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2872,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Swallow",
      "hw": "نگلنا",
      "s": "« » means for something to easily reach the stomach (1 verse: 4:4)",
      "d": "« » is the name of that passage which goes from the throat to the stomach, through which food reaches the stomach. And « » means the food easily reached the stomach through that passage (muf). And « » means food that easily reaches the stomach. (faq la 245)\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«فَاِنۡ طِبۡنَ لَکُمۡ عَنۡ شَیۡءٍ مِّنۡہُ نَفۡسًا فَکُلُوۡہُ ہَنِیۡٓئًا مَّرِیۡٓئًا»\nTranslation: But if they, of their own accord, give you a portion thereof, then consume it with pleasure and enjoyment."
    },
    {
      "id": 2873,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Swallow",
      "hw": "نگلنا",
      "s": "« » means for something (food or drink) to go down the throat easily and pleasantly due to its good taste (3 verses: 14:17-16:66-35:12)",
      "d": "« » means for food or drink to go down the throat easily and pleasantly (manjad).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«لَّبَنًا خَالِصًا سَآئِغًا لِّلشّٰرِبِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: [And] pure milk, palatable to the drinkers.\nAnd « » means to take food or drink down through the throat.\nFor example: The divine command states:\n«وَ یُسۡقٰی مِنۡ مَّآءٍ صَدِیۡدٍ یَّتَجَرَّعُہٗ  وَ لَا یَکَادُ یُسِیۡغُہٗ»\nTranslation: He will be given to drink scalding water which will sever his intestines."
    },
    {
      "id": 2874,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Swallow",
      "hw": "نگلنا",
      "s": "« » means for food to get stuck in the throat, i.e., to be unable to swallow (1 verse: 73:13)",
      "d": "« » means for food or water to get stuck in the throat (manjad). For food to get stuck in the throat and be unable to swallow.\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«اِنَّ  لَدَیۡنَاۤ  اَنۡکَالًا وَّ  جَحِیۡمًا وَّ طَعَامًا ذَا غُصَّۃٍ»\nTranslation: Indeed, with Us are shackles and burning fire and food that chokes."
    },
    {
      "id": 2875,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Swallow",
      "hw": "نگلنا",
      "s": "« » means to eat hastily, to swallow without chewing (3 verses: 7:117-20:69-26:45)",
      "d": "«لَقِفَ» «لَقِفَ الطَّعَام»\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«وَ اَلۡقِ مَا فِیۡ یَمِیۡنِکَ تَلۡقَفۡ مَا صَنَعُوۡا»\nTranslation: And throw what is in your right hand; it will swallow what they have crafted."
    },
    {
      "id": 2876,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To Swallow",
      "hw": "نگلنا",
      "s": "« » means to gulp down, to make large mouthfuls or to swallow at once (1 verse: 37:142)",
      "d": "« » means to make a mouthful. As much food as can fit in the mouth at once. To put from hand into mouth. (m. l.) And « » means to gulp down hastily (manjad). And means to gulp down by making large mouthfuls (muf).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said:\n«فَالۡتَقَمَہُ  الۡحُوۡتُ وَ ہُوَ  مُلِیۡمٌ»\nTranslation: Then the fish swallowed him, while he was blameworthy."
    }
  ],
  "630": [
    {
      "id": 2877,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Bathing. Washing.",
      "hw": "نہانا",
      "s": "« » and « » mean to wash away dirt and filth (3 verses: 5:6-4:43-38:42).",
      "d": "« » means to wash something and remove dirt and filth.\n«اِذَا قُمۡتُمۡ اِلَی الصَّلٰوۃِ فَاغۡسِلُوۡا وُجُوۡہَکُمۡ وَ اَیۡدِیَکُمۡ»\nTranslation: When you stand for prayer, wash your faces and your hands.\nAnd « » means to cleanse the entire body from dirt and filth or to bathe.\n«وَ لَا جُنُبًا اِلَّا عَابِرِیۡ سَبِیۡلٍ حَتّٰی تَغۡتَسِلُوۡا»\nTranslation: And [if] one of you is in a state of major impurity, he may not approach [the prayer] until he has bathed, except for a traveler on a journey [who may perform tayammum]."
    },
    {
      "id": 2878,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Bathing. Washing.",
      "hw": "نہانا",
      "s": "« » and « » mean to remove impurity as well as dirt (26 verses: 2:25-2:125-2:222-2:232-3:15-3:42-3:55-4:57-5:6-5:41-7:82-8:11-9:103-9:108-11:78-22:26-25:48-27:56-33:33-33:53-56:79-58:12-74:4-76:21-80:14-98:2).",
      "d": "« » is the opposite of « », meaning a woman's state of menstruation. And « » means being free from menstruation and becoming pure after bathing. The word « » is used in a much broader sense than « ». Purity is of three types: apparent, legal, and spiritual. For example, if urine splashes on clothing, the garment does not become dirty but it becomes impure.\n«وَ ثِیَابَکَ فَطَہِّرۡ»\nTranslation: And keep your garments pure.\nThus, « » means both to clean garments from dirt and to purify them from impurity. And this is the difference between « » (to bathe and become pure) and « » (to bathe)."
    }
  ],
  "631": [
    {
      "id": 2879,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "No. Not.",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » is an incomplete verb in Arabic grammar meaning 'is not' or 'was not' (75 verses: 2:113-2:177-2:189-2:198-2:249-2:272-2:282-3:28-3:36-3:66-3:75-3:113-3:128-3:167-3:182-4:18-4:101-4:123-4:176-5:93-5:116-6:30-6:51-6:53-6:70-6:89-6:122-7:61-7:67-8:51-9:91-11:8-11:16-11:46-11:47-11:78-11:81-15:42-16:99-17:36-17:65-22:10-22:71-24:15-24:29-24:58-24:60-24:61-29:8-29:10-29:68-31:15-33:5-36:81-39:32-39:36-39:37-39:60-40:42-40:43-42:11-43:51-46:32-46:34-48:11-48:17-53:39-53:58-56:2-58:10-69:35-70:2-75:40-88:6-95:8).",
      "d": "« » is an incomplete verb. It only appears in the past tense and is used with full conjugations, conveying both past and present meanings. For example, « » means 'you are not' or 'you were not', and « » means 'we are not' or 'we were not'.\n«ب» «لَا» «لَمْ» «لَنْ» «لَا» «لَا یَضْرِبُ» «لَمْ» «لَمْ یَضْرِبْ» «لَنْ» «لَنْ یَّضْرِبَ»\n« »  « », and « » : These three have their own meanings, but when followed by « », their meanings change to 'not' or 'no'.\n«اِنۡ اَنۡتُمۡ اِلَّا تَکۡذِبُوۡنَ»\nMeaning: 'You are not but liars', i.e., your only work is to lie.\n«مَا مِنْ اِلٰہٍ اِلَّا اللہ»\n«ہَلۡ کُنۡتُمۡ اِلَّا بَشَرًا رَّسُوۡلًا»\nMeaning: 'Am I not but a human messenger?'\nAnd for 'no' or 'not', the following independent particles are used: « »  « »  « »  « »  « »  «  ( )», and « »."
    },
    {
      "id": 2880,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "No. Not.",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » means 'no', used in negative responses to positive statements (1204 verses: 1:7-2:2-2:6-2:11-2:12-2:13-2:17-2:18-2:22-2:26-2:30-2:32-2:35-2:38-2:41-2:42-2:48-2:60-2:62-2:68-2:71-2:78-2:80-2:83-2:84-2:86-2:87-2:100-2:101-2:102-2:104-2:105-2:107-2:112-2:113-2:118-2:119-2:120-2:123-2:124-2:132-2:134-2:136-2:141-2:147-2:150-2:152-2:154-2:158-2:162-2:163-2:168-2:169-2:170-2:171-2:173-2:174-2:182-2:185-2:187-2:188-2:190-2:191-2:193-2:195-2:196-2:197-2:203-2:205-2:208-2:216-2:217-2:221-2:222-2:224-2:225-2:228-2:229-2:230-2:231-2:232-2:233-2:234-2:235-2:236-2:237-2:240-2:243-2:249-2:254-2:255-2:256-2:258-2:262-2:264-2:267-2:272-2:273-2:274-2:275-2:276-2:277-2:279-2:281-2:282-2:283-2:285-2:286-3:2-3:5-3:6-3:8-3:9-3:10-3:18-3:25-3:28-3:32-3:57-3:60-3:64-3:66-3:67-3:73-3:75-3:77-3:80-3:84-3:86-3:88-3:102-3:103-3:105-3:111-3:116-3:118-3:119-3:120-3:130-3:139-3:140-3:153-3:154-3:156-3:160-3:161-3:169-3:170-3:171-3:175-3:176-3:178-3:180-3:187-3:188-3:194-3:195-3:196-3:199-4:2-4:5-4:6-4:11-4:18-4:19-4:20-4:22-4:23-4:24-4:25-4:29-4:32-4:34-4:36-4:38-4:40-4:42-4:43-4:46-4:48-4:49-4:53-4:65-4:75-4:77-4:78-4:84-4:87-4:89-4:94-4:95-4:98-4:102-4:104-4:105-4:107-4:108-4:114-4:116-4:121-4:123-4:124-4:127-4:128-4:129-4:135-4:137-4:140-4:142-4:143-4:144-4:148-4:154-4:155-4:168-4:171-4:172-4:173-5:2-5:3-5:5-5:8-5:13-5:19-5:21-5:25-5:26-5:41-5:44-5:48-5:49-5:51-5:54-5:57-5:58-5:64-5:67-5:68-5:69-5:70-5:76-5:77-5:79-5:82-5:84-5:87-5:89-5:95-5:100-5:101-5:103-5:104-5:105-5:106-5:108-5:109-5:115-5:116-6:8-6:12-6:14-6:17-6:19-6:20-6:21-6:25-6:27-6:33-6:34-6:35-6:37-6:38-6:48-6:50-6:51-6:52-6:56-6:59-6:61-6:68-6:70-6:71-6:76-6:80-6:81-6:90-6:91-6:102-6:103-6:106-6:108-6:109-6:113-6:114-6:115-6:121-6:125-6:135-6:136-6:138-6:141-6:142-6:144-6:145-6:147-6:148-6:150-6:151-6:152-6:153-6:158-6:160-6:163-6:164-7:2-7:3-7:17-7:19-7:27-7:28-7:31-7:33-7:34-7:35-7:38-7:40-7:42-7:47-7:49-7:55-7:56-7:58-7:62-7:73-7:74-7:79-7:85-7:86-7:95-7:99-7:100-7:105-7:131-7:142-7:146-7:148-7:150-7:158-7:163-7:169-7:170-7:179-7:182-7:186-7:187-7:188-7:191-7:192-7:193-7:195-7:197-7:198-7:202-7:205-7:206-8:15-8:20-8:21-8:22-8:25-8:27-8:34-8:39-8:46-8:47-8:48-8:55-8:56-8:58-8:59-8:60-8:65-9:6-9:8-9:10-9:12-9:16-9:19-9:23-9:24-9:28-9:29-9:31-9:34-9:36-9:37-9:39-9:40-9:44-9:45-9:49-9:54-9:55-9:66-9:74-9:79-9:80-9:81-9:84-9:85-9:87-9:91-9:92-9:93-9:94-9:96-9:101-9:108-9:109-9:110-9:116-9:118-9:120-9:121-9:126-9:127-9:129-10:7-10:11-10:15-10:16-10:17-10:18-10:26-10:33-10:35-10:36-10:37-10:40-10:42-10:43-10:44-10:47-10:49-10:54-10:55-10:60-10:61-10:62-10:64-10:65-10:68-10:69-10:71-10:77-10:81-10:85-10:88-10:89-10:90-10:94-10:95-10:96-10:100-10:101-10:104-10:105-10:106-10:107-11:14-11:15-11:17-11:22-11:26-11:29-11:31-11:34-11:36-11:37-11:42-11:43-11:46-11:49-11:51-11:52-11:55-11:57-11:64-11:70-11:78-11:81-11:84-11:85-11:89-11:105-11:109-11:112-11:113-11:115-11:118-11:121-12:5-12:10-12:11-12:15-12:21-12:23-12:37-12:38-12:40-12:52-12:56-12:60-12:67-12:68-12:69-12:86-12:87-12:90-12:92-12:96-12:107-12:110-13:1-13:11-13:14-13:16-13:20-13:30-13:31-13:33-13:36-13:37-13:41-14:9-14:17-14:18-14:22-14:31-14:34-14:38-14:42-14:43-14:47-15:13-15:48-15:53-15:55-15:65-15:68-15:69-15:88-16:1-16:2-16:8-16:17-16:18-16:20-16:22-16:23-16:26-16:35-16:37-16:38-16:43-16:45-16:49-16:51-16:56-16:60-16:61-16:62-16:70-16:73-16:74-16:75-16:76-16:78-16:84-16:85-16:91-16:92-16:94-16:95-16:101-16:104-16:105-16:107-16:109-16:111-16:115-16:116-16:127-17:10-17:15-17:22-17:23-17:26-17:29-17:31-17:32-17:33-17:34-17:36-17:37-17:39-17:44-17:45-17:48-17:56-17:68-17:69-17:71-17:75-17:76-17:77-17:82-17:86-17:88-17:99-17:107-17:110-18:5-18:19-18:21-18:22-18:23-18:26-18:27-18:28-18:30-18:38-18:39-18:49-18:51-18:60-18:69-18:70-18:73-18:76-18:93-18:101-18:105-18:108-18:110-19:39-19:42-19:44-19:60-19:62-19:84-19:87-20:8-20:14-20:16-20:21-20:40-20:42-20:46-20:47-20:52-20:58-20:61-20:68-20:69-20:74-20:77-20:81-20:89-20:94-20:97-20:98-20:107-20:108-20:109-20:110-20:112-20:114-20:117-20:118-20:119-20:120-20:123-20:131-20:132-21:7-21:8-21:13-21:19-21:20-21:23-21:24-21:25-21:27-21:28-21:37-21:39-21:40-21:43-21:45-21:47-21:66-21:87-21:89-21:94-21:95-21:100-21:102-21:103-22:7-22:8-22:12-22:26-22:37-22:38-22:46-22:52-22:55-22:67-22:73-23:27-23:44-23:56-23:59-23:62-23:65-23:74-23:88-23:94-23:101-23:108-23:115-23:116-23:117-24:2-24:3-24:4-24:11-24:19-24:21-24:22-24:27-24:28-24:31-24:33-24:35-24:37-24:53-24:55-24:57-24:58-24:60-24:61-24:63-25:3-25:9-25:14-25:19-25:21-25:22-25:33-25:40-25:52-25:55-25:58-25:68-25:72-26:13-26:50-26:87-26:88-26:101-26:151-26:152-26:156-26:181-26:183-26:201-26:202-26:213-26:226-27:4-27:10-27:18-27:20-27:24-27:26-27:37-27:41-27:48-27:50-27:61-27:65-27:70-27:73-27:80-27:82-27:85-28:7-28:9-28:11-28:13-28:23-28:25-28:28-28:31-28:35-28:37-28:39-28:41-28:50-28:55-28:56-28:57-28:66-28:70-28:76-28:77-28:78-28:80-28:82-28:83-28:84-28:86-28:87-28:88-29:2-29:8-29:17-29:22-29:33-29:36-29:46-29:48-29:53-29:60-29:63-30:6-30:30-30:31-30:39-30:43-30:45-30:52-30:56-30:57-30:59-30:60-31:13-31:15-31:18-31:20-31:23-31:25-31:28-31:33-32:2-32:4-32:15-32:17-32:18-32:23-32:29-33:1-33:13-33:15-33:16-33:17-33:18-33:32-33:33-33:36-33:37-33:39-33:48-33:51-33:52-33:53-33:55-33:59-33:60-33:65-33:69-34:3-34:8-34:22-34:23-34:25-34:28-34:30-34:31-34:36-34:37-34:42-34:51-35:2-35:3-35:5-35:8-35:11-35:14-35:18-35:20-35:21-35:22-35:35-35:36-35:39-35:43-35:44-36:7-36:9-36:10-36:21-36:22-36:23-36:31-36:36-36:40-36:43-36:50-36:54-36:60-36:67-36:75-36:76-37:8-37:13-37:25-37:35-37:47-37:92-38:22-38:26-38:35-38:44-38:59-38:60-38:62-39:3-39:6-39:7-39:9-39:20-39:25-39:29-39:43-39:45-39:49-39:53-39:54-39:55-39:61-39:69-40:3-40:4-40:16-40:17-40:18-40:20-40:27-40:28-40:40-40:43-40:52-40:57-40:58-40:59-40:61-40:62-40:65-41:4-41:7-41:16-41:22-41:26-41:30-41:34-41:37-41:38-41:40-41:42-41:44-41:47-41:49-42:7-42:8-42:13-42:15-42:18-42:23-42:31-42:40-42:47-42:52-43:52-43:61-43:62-43:66-43:68-43:75-43:80-43:86-43:88-44:8-44:19-44:39-44:41-44:56-45:10-45:14-45:18-45:22-45:26-45:32-45:35-46:5-46:8-46:9-46:10-46:13-46:19-46:25-46:26-46:32-46:35-47:11-47:13-47:19-47:33-47:35-47:36-47:38-48:15-48:17-48:22-48:27-49:1-49:2-49:4-49:11-49:12-49:14-49:17-50:28-51:28-51:51-51:59-52:15-52:16-52:23-52:29-52:33-52:36-52:46-52:47-53:26-53:27-53:28-53:32-53:60-55:9-55:20-55:33-55:35-55:39-55:56-55:74-56:19-56:25-56:33-56:44-56:61-56:75-56:79-56:85-57:8-57:10-57:15-57:16-57:22-57:23-58:7-58:9-58:14-58:17-58:22-59:6-59:7-59:9-59:10-59:11-59:12-59:13-59:14-59:19-59:20-59:22-59:23-60:1-60:3-60:5-60:8-60:10-60:12-60:13-61:2-61:3-61:5-61:7-62:5-62:7-63:3-63:6-63:7-63:8-63:9-64:13-65:1-65:3-65:6-65:7-65:6-66:6-66:7-66:8-68:8-68:10-68:18-68:24-68:42-68:44-68:48-69:18-69:33-69:34-69:36-69:37-69:38-69:39-69:42-70:10-70:40-71:4-71:13-71:23-71:24-71:26-71:27-71:28-72:3-72:10-72:13-72:18-72:20-72:21-72:26-73:9-74:6-74:28-74:31-74:53-75:1-75:2-75:11-75:16-75:31-76:9-76:13-76:24-77:31-77:35-77:36-77:48-78:24-78:27-78:35-78:37-78:38-81:15-82:19-84:16-84:20-84:21-86:10-87:6-87:13-88:7-88:11-89:17-89:18-89:25-89:26-90:1-90:11-91:15-92:15-93:9-93:10-96:19-107:3-109-2-109:3-109:4-109:5).",
      "d": "« » is extensively used. It is employed in negating positive statements, for responses, for conjunctions, and for repetition.\n«فَلَا صَدَّقَ وَ لَا صَلّٰی»\nTranslation: He neither believed nor prayed.\n(For detailed explanation, refer to any book on Arabic grammar.)"
    },
    {
      "id": 2881,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "No. Not.",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » is used for negating a past event (152 verses: 2:17-2:33-2:89-2:101-2:214-2:246-2:249-2:250-2:259-3:36-3:52-3:142-4:77-5:117-6:5-6:44-6:76-6:77-6:78-7:22-7:116-7:126-7:134-7:135-7:143-7:149-7:150-7:154-7:155-7:165-7:166-7:189-7:190-8:48-9:16-9:76-9:114-10:12-10:13-10:23-10:39-10:54-10:76-10:77-10:80-10:81-10:98-11:58-11:66-11:70-11:74-11:77-11:82-11:94-11:101-11:111-12:15-12:22-12:28-12:31-12:50-12:54-12:59-12:63-12:65-12:66-12:68-12:69-12:70-12:80-12:88-12:94-12:96-12:99-14:22-15:61-17:67-18:59-18:61-18:62-19:49-20:11-21:12-25:37-26:21-26:41-26:61-27:8-27:10-27:13-27:36-27:40-27:42-27:44-28:14-28:19-28:22-28:23-28:25-28:29-28:30-28:31-28:36-28:48-29:31-29:33-29:65-29:68-31:32-32:24-33:22-33:37-34:14-34:33-34:43-35:42-36:32-37:102-37:103-38:8-40:25-40:66-40:83-40:84-40:85-41:41-42:44-43:30-43:35-43:47-43:50-43:55-43:57-43:63-46:7-46:24-46:29-49:14-50:5-59:16-61:5-61:6-62:3-66:3-67:27-68:26-68:51-69:11-72:13-72:19-80:23-86:4).",
      "d": "« » generally means 'not yet' or 'had not' in the past tense, used for negating a past event.\n«وَ لَمَّا یَعۡلَمِ اللّٰہُ الَّذِیۡنَ جٰہَدُوۡنَ مِنۡکُمۡ»\nTranslation: And Allah has not yet known those who have strived among you.\n(For further details, consult a book on Arabic grammar!)"
    },
    {
      "id": 2882,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "No. Not.",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » means 'why not?' (33 verses: 2:49-2:124-2:155-2:249-3:152-3:154-3:186-4:6-5:48-5:94-6:165-7:141-7:163-7:168-8:17-10:30-11:7-14:6-16:92-18:7-21:35-23:30-27:40-33:11-37:106-44:33-47:4-47:31-67:2-68:17-76:2-89:15-89:16).",
      "d": "« » is used when a question is negative and the answer intends to negate that negation, i.e., to affirm positively. It means 'why not?'.\n«اَلَسۡتُ بِرَبِّکُمۡ ؕ قَالُوۡا بَلٰی»\nTranslation: [Allah asked] 'Am I not your Lord?' They said, 'Yes indeed!' (i.e., why not?)"
    },
    {
      "id": 2883,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "No. Not.",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » means 'never' (33 verses: 19:79-19:82-23:100-26:15-26:62-34:27-70:15-70:39-74:16-74:32-74:53-74:54-75:11-75:20-75:26-78:4-78:5-80:11-80:23-82:9-83:7-83:14-83:15-83:18-89:17-78:21-96:6-96:15-96:19-102:3-102:4-102:5-104:4).",
      "d": "« » means 'never'. It is used to emphatically reject a preceding statement. It serves to nullify the previous discourse.\n«عَمَّ یَتَسَآءَلُوۡنَ عَنِ النَّبَاِ الۡعَظِیۡمِ الَّذِیۡ ہُمۡ فِیۡہِ مُخۡتَلِفُوۡنَ کَلَّا سَیَعۡلَمُوۡنَ ثُمَّ کَلَّا سَیَعۡلَمُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: What is [the matter with] them that they are in such confusion about the great news? No! They will come to know. Then no! They will come to know."
    },
    {
      "id": 2884,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "No. Not.",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » is a restrictive particle in Arabic grammar meaning 'nothing but' or 'only' (137 verses: 2:11-2:14-2:102-2:117-2:137-2:169-2:173-2:181-2:275-3:20-3:47-3:155-3:175-3:178-3:185-4:10-4:17-4:111-4:171-5:27-5:33-5:55-5:90-5:91-6:19-6:36-6:109-6:156-6:159-7:33-7:131-7:173-7:187-7:203-8:2-9:18-9:28-9:37-9:45-9:55-9:60-9:65-9:85-9:93-10:20-10:23-10:24-10:108-11:12-11:33-12:86-13:7-13:19-13:36-13:40-14:42-15:15-16:40-16:51-16:82-16:92-16:95-16:100-16:101-16:103-16:105-16:115-16:124-17:15-18:110-19:19-19:35-19:84-19:97-20:69-20:72-20:90-20:98-21:45-21:108-22:49-23:117-24:51-24:54-24:62-26:153-26:185-27:40-27:91-27:92-28:78-29:6-29:17-29:25-29:50-31:12-32:15-33:33-33:63-34:46-34:50-35:6-35:18-35:28-36:11-36:82-37:19-38:65-39:9-39:10-39:41-39:49-40:39-40:68-41:6-42:42-44:58-46:23-47:36-47:38-48:10-49:10-49:15-51:5-52:16-58:10-60:9-64:12-64:15-66:7-67:26-72:20-76:9-77:7-79:13-79:45-88:21).",
      "d": "« » is called a 'word of restriction' in Arabic grammar. It means 'nothing but' or 'only'. It restricts the meaning to a specific thing.\n«قُلۡ اِنَّمَاۤ اَنَا بَشَرٌ مِّثۡلُکُمۡ یُوۡحٰۤی اِلَیَّ»\nTranslation: Say, 'I am only a human being like you, to whom has been revealed [the message].'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2886,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "no; not",
      "hw": "نہیں",
      "s": "« » means 'no' or 'was not' (1 verse: 38:3)",
      "d": "«لَات» «لَیْسَ» «فَنَادَوۡا  وَّ  لَاتَ حِیۡنَ مَنَاصٍ» «لَاتَ الْحِیْنَ حِینَ مَنَاص» «لَاتَ حِیۡنَ مَنَاص»"
    }
  ],
  "632": [
    {
      "id": 2887,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "New. To become new.",
      "hw": "نیا",
      "s": "« » means the emergence of something new (8 verses: 2:76-18:70-20:113-21:2-26:5-65:1-93:11-99:4).",
      "d": "« » is the opposite of « » (non-existence). It means something new coming into existence, or something that was not new but people forgot it and it reappears as if new.\n«لَا تَدۡرِیۡ لَعَلَّ اللّٰہَ یُحۡدِثُ بَعۡدَ ذٰلِکَ اَمۡرًا»\nTranslation: You do not know; perhaps Allah will bring about after that a new matter."
    },
    {
      "id": 2889,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "New. To be new.",
      "hw": "نیا",
      "s": "« » To create something new without a precedent, to innovate. (3 verses: 2:117-6:101-46:9)",
      "d": "« » has two meanings: (1) to initiate something, and (2) to create something for which there is no prior example or model (M. L.). In this sense, Allah's name is « », meaning The Originator (who brings something into existence for the first time). And « » means one who initiates something or a beginning.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«قُلۡ مَا کُنۡتُ بِدۡعًا مِّنَ الرُّسُلِ»\nTranslation: Say, [O Muhammad], 'I am not a new [or unprecedented] messenger.'"
    }
  ],
  "633": [
    {
      "id": 2890,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Below",
      "hw": "نیچے",
      "s": "« » is an adverbial noun. Meaning: below. (50 verses: 2:25-2:266-3:15-3:136-3:195-3:198-4:13-4:57-4:122-5:12-5:66-5:85-5:119-6:6-6:65-7:43-9:72-9:89-9:100-10:9-13:35-14:23-16:31-18:31-18:82-19:24-20:6-20:76-22:14-22:23-25:10-29:55-29:58-39:16-39:20-41:29-43:51-47:12-48:5-48:17-48:18-57:12-58:22-61:12-64:9-65:11-66:8-66:10-85:11-98:8)",
      "d": "« » is an adverbial noun meaning below. Its opposite is « », meaning above. It is used in both physical and spiritual senses.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَوۡ اَنَّہُمۡ اَقَامُوا التَّوۡرٰىۃَ وَ الۡاِنۡجِیۡلَ وَ مَاۤ اُنۡزِلَ اِلَیۡہِمۡ مِّنۡ رَّبِّہِمۡ لَاَکَلُوۡا مِنۡ فَوۡقِہِمۡ وَ مِنۡ تَحۡتِ اَرۡجُلِہِمۡ»\nTranslation: And if they had upheld the Torah and the Gospel and what was revealed to them from their Lord, they would have eaten [provision] from above them and from beneath their feet."
    },
    {
      "id": 2891,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Below",
      "hw": "نیچے",
      "s": "«اَسْفَلَ سَافِل»",
      "d": "«اَسْفَلَ» «اعلٰی» «اَسْفَل» «اَعْلٰی» «اَسْفَلَہٗ اَغْلَظُ مِنْ اَعْلَاہُ»\nFor rank and status, « » denotes highness, and « » denotes lowness and inferiority. Its feminine form is « ».\nFor example, the saying of the Holy Prophet ﷺ is:\n«اَلْیَدُ الْعُلْیَا خَیْرٌ مِّنْ یَدِ السُّفْلٰی»\nMeaning: The upper hand (the giving hand) is better than the lower hand (the receiving hand).\nIn this hadith, « » and « » are used in a spiritual sense, meaning the hand that gives charity is better than the hand that takes.\nAnd the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ جَعَلَ کَلِمَۃَ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوا السُّفۡلٰی ؕ وَ کَلِمَتُ اللّٰہِ ہِیَ الۡعُلۡیَا»\nTranslation: And Allah has debased the word of those who disbelieved [i.e., their false claims], and the word of Allah is the highest [i.e., supreme].\nAnd « » means low in rank and status, contemptible. And « » means the lowly people (pl.).\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«لَقَدۡ خَلَقۡنَا الۡاِنۡسَانَ فِیۡۤ اَحۡسَنِ تَقۡوِیۡمٍ ۫ثُمَّ رَدَدۡنٰہُ اَسۡفَلَ سٰفِلِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: We have certainly created man in the best of stature; Then We return him to the lowest of the low."
    },
    {
      "id": 2892,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To lower. To keep. To abase.",
      "hw": "نیچے",
      "s": "« » For something to be pressed down or to press down. To lower the gaze, arm, or side. (4 verses: 15:88-17:24-26:215-56:3)",
      "d": "«خَفَضَ» «رَفَعَ» «خافِض» «رافِع» «خَفَضَ الصَّوْت» «خَفَضَ الْجَنَاحَ»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اخۡفِضۡ لَہُمَا جَنَاحَ الذُّلِّ مِنَ الرَّحۡمَۃِ»\nTranslation: And lower to them the wing of humility and mercy."
    },
    {
      "id": 2893,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To lower. To keep. To abase.",
      "hw": "نیچے",
      "s": "« » Used for lowering the gaze or voice. (In general circumstances). (4 verses: 24:30-24:31-31:19-49:3)",
      "d": "«غَضَّ» «غَضَّ صَوْتُہٗ» «غَضَّ بَصَرُہٗ»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«قُلۡ لِّلۡمُؤۡمِنٰتِ یَغۡضُضۡنَ مِنۡ اَبۡصَارِہِنَّ»\nTranslation: And tell the believing women to lower [i.e., guard] their gaze.\nAt another place, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ اقۡصِدۡ فِیۡ مَشۡیِکَ وَ اغۡضُضۡ مِنۡ صَوۡتِکَ»\nTranslation: And be moderate in your pace and lower your voice."
    },
    {
      "id": 2894,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To lower. To keep. To abase.",
      "hw": "نیچے",
      "s": "« » To restrict the gaze. Not to use the full gaze. (3 verses: 37:48-38:52-55:56)",
      "d": "«قَصَرَ» «صَلٰوۃُ الْقَصْر» «قَصَرُ الطَّرْف»\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ عِنۡدَہُمۡ قٰصِرٰتُ الطَّرۡفِ عِیۡنٌ»\nTranslation: And with them will be women with modest, restrained glances."
    },
    {
      "id": 2895,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "To lower. To keep. To abase.",
      "hw": "نیچے",
      "s": "« » Such a fear whose effects begin to manifest on the limbs and organs. (15 verses: 2:45-3:199-20:108-21:90-23:2-33:35-41:39-42:45-54:7-57:16-59:21-68:43-70:44-79:9-88:2)",
      "d": "« » originally refers to a fear whose effects begin to manifest on the limbs and organs (M.). These effects can be manifest through the face, voice, or eyes. Therefore, this word is used for lowering them. And for gaze and voice, the word « » is also used. The difference is that if it is in a general state, « » is used, and if it is due to fear, « » is used.\nFor example, for the gaze, the Noble Quran states:\n«خَاشِعَۃً اَبۡصَارُہُمۡ تَرۡہَقُہُمۡ ذِلَّۃٌ»\nTranslation: Their eyes will be humbled, and they will be covered with humility.\nAnd for the voice, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ خَشَعَتِ الۡاَصۡوَاتُ لِلرَّحۡمٰنِ»\nTranslation: And the voices will be humbled before the Most Merciful [i.e., they will be low due to fear].\nAnd for the face, the Noble Quran states:\n«وُجُوۡہٌ یَّوۡمَئِذٍ خَاشِعَۃٌ»\nTranslation: [Some] faces, that Day, will be humbled."
    }
  ],
  "634": [
    {
      "id": 2896,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Righteous. Virtuous.",
      "hw": "نیک",
      "s": "« » One who reforms himself and rectifies all kinds of corruption. (123 verses: 2:25-2:62-2:82-2:130-2:277-3:39-3:46-3:57-3:114-4:34-4:57-4:69-4:122-4:124-4:173-5:9-5:69-5:84-5:93-6:85-7:42-7:168-7:189-7:190-7:196-9:75-9:102-9:120-10:4-10:9-11:11-11:23-11:46-12:9-12:101-13:29-14:23-16:97-16:122-17:9-17:25-18:2-18:30-18:46-18:82-18:88-18:107-18:110-19:60-19:76-19:96-20:75-20:82-20:112-21:72-21:75-21:86-21:94-21:105-22:14-22:23-22:50-22:56-23:51-23:100-24:32-24:55-25:70-25:71-26:83-26:227-27:19-28:27-28:67-28:80-29:7-29:9-29:27-29:58-30:15-30:44-30:45-31:8-32:12-32:19-33:31-34:4-34:11-34:37-35:7-35:10-35:37-37:100-37:112-38:24-38:28-40:40-40:58-41:8-41:33-41:46-42:22-42:23-42:26-45:15-45:21-45:30-46:15-47:2-47:12-48:29-63:10-64:9-65:11-66:4-66:10-68:50-72:11-84:25-85:11-95:6-98:7-103:3)",
      "d": "« » means to rectify corruption, and its opposite is « » (to corrupt) (M. L.). And « » means one who purifies himself, one who reforms his soul (M.), one who adopts good deeds and abandons bad ones, and one who remains engaged in striving for his own reformation.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ کَانَ اَبُوۡہُمَا صَالِحًا»\nTranslation: And their father was a righteous man.\nAt another place, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَ لَا تُفۡسِدُوۡا فِی الۡاَرۡضِ بَعۡدَ اِصۡلَاحِہَا»\nTranslation: And do not cause corruption on the earth after its reformation."
    },
    {
      "id": 2897,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Righteous. Virtuous.",
      "hw": "نیک",
      "s": "« » This (plural of « ») is a person who is always prepared to do good, one who does abundant good deeds. (9 verses: 3:193-3:198-19:14-19:32-76:5-80:16-82:13-83:18-83:22)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « ». « » means to do good on a wide scale (M.). « » essentially does not mean goodness itself, but rather the characteristic and innate disposition of being constantly inclined towards goodness. Its opposite is « », meaning sin and disobedience.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«لَنۡ تَنَالُوا الۡبِرَّ حَتّٰی تُنۡفِقُوۡا مِمَّا تُحِبُّوۡنَ»\nTranslation: You will never attain righteousness until you spend [in the way of Allah] from what you love.\nAnd « » and « » is a person whose nature is always prepared to do good, and when an opportunity arises, he does such a good deed. And an accepted Hajj (Hajj-e-Mabrur) is that Hajj which is performed exactly according to the Sunnah of the Prophet ﷺ, without any deficiency.\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«وَّ بَرًّۢا بِوَالِدَیۡہِ وَ لَمۡ یَکُنۡ جَبَّارًا عَصِیًّا»\nTranslation: And [he was] dutiful to his parents, and he was not a rebellious disobedient [person]."
    },
    {
      "id": 2898,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Righteous. Virtuous.",
      "hw": "نیک",
      "s": "« » This is an intensive form from « », meaning a person who is always prepared to do exceedingly abundant good. (1 verse: 80:16)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « ». It is stronger than « » and carries more emphasis (intensiveness).\nFor example, the Noble Quran states:\n«بِاَیۡدِیۡ سَفَرَۃٍ کِرَامٍۭ بَرَرَۃٍ»\nTranslation: [Written] by the hands of noble, righteous scribes."
    },
    {
      "id": 2899,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Righteous / Fortunate",
      "hw": "نیک",
      "s": "« » one with good habits and conduct. Righteous. (3 verses: 11:78-11:87-11:97)",
      "d": "« » means 'steadfastness on the right path' (M. L.), i.e., walking correctly on the path or remaining on the straight path. Its opposite is « », meaning to deviate onto a wrong path.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«قَدۡ تَّبَیَّنَ الرُّشۡدُ مِنَ الۡغَیِّ»\nTranslation: Guidance has become clearly distinct from misguidance.\nAnd « » means guided, one with good habits and conduct, righteous.\nFor example, the divine command is:\n«فَاتَّقُوا اللّٰہَ وَ لَا تُخۡزُوۡنِ فِیۡ ضَیۡفِیۡ ؕ اَلَـیۡسَ مِنۡکُمۡ رَجُلٌ رَّشِیْدٌ»\nTranslation: Fear Allah and do not disgrace me in front of my guests. Is there not among you a man of good conduct?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2900,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Righteous / Fortunate",
      "hw": "نیک",
      "s": "« » a person who is naturally good. Fortunate. (1 verse: 11:105)",
      "d": "« » is a person who is naturally good. That is, fortunate and blessed. Its opposite is « », meaning wretched. And « » means good fortune. And the attainment of good with divine assistance in matters of faith (Muf. M. L.).\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«یَوۡمَ یَاۡتِ لَا تَکَلَّمُ نَفۡسٌ اِلَّا بِاِذۡنِہٖ ۚ فَمِنۡہُمۡ شَقِیٌّ وَّ سَعِیْدٌ»\nTranslation: On the Day when no soul will speak except by His permission, then among them will be the wretched and the fortunate."
    },
    {
      "id": 2902,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Righteous / Fortunate",
      "hw": "نیک",
      "s": "« » ascetic. Godly people. Sheikhs of the type of worshippers and ascetics. (3 verses: 3:79-5:44-5:63)",
      "d": "Imam Raghub has discussed this word extensively. Some scholars write its meaning as 'one who nurtures knowledge'. Others relate it to « » as « » to « ». Similarly, « » to « ». And its meaning is 'belonging to Allah' or 'pious'. Both meanings are written by Sahib al-Munjid. A great scholar as well as a person of Allah. An 'arif billah' (one who knows Allah) as well. However, the second opinion seems more prevalent. Because in the Quran, « » is followed by « » (scholars) separately (5/44). Similarly, in the Quran, the word « » appears (3/146) with the same meaning.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«لَوۡ لَا یَنۡہٰہُمُ الرَّبّٰنِیُّوۡنَ وَ الۡاَحۡبَارُ عَنۡ قَوۡلِہِمُ الۡاِثۡمَ وَ اَکۡلِہِمُ السُّحۡتَ»\nTranslation: Why do their rabbis and scholars not forbid them from sinful speech and consuming unlawful earnings?"
    }
  ],
  "635": [
    {
      "id": 2903,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Goodness / Good Deeds",
      "hw": "نیکی",
      "s": "«عُرف ، مَعْرُوْف»",
      "d": "« » means to recognize something, and its opposite is « », meaning to be surprised or astonished. And « » and « » is every matter that good people of society consider good. The good customs of society. The ways of good people. The national customs that are considered praiseworthy. Such as sitting respectfully before elders and calling them with respect, etc.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«خُذِ الۡعَفۡوَ وَ اۡمُرۡ بِالۡعُرۡفِ وَ اَعۡرِضۡ عَنِ الۡجٰہِلِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: (O Muhammad ﷺ!) Choose forgiveness and enjoin what is good, and turn away from the ignorant.\nAt another place, the divine command is:\n«وَلۡتَکُنۡ مِّنۡکُمۡ اُمَّۃٌ یَّدۡعُوۡنَ اِلَی الۡخَیۡرِ وَ یَاۡمُرُوۡنَ بِالۡمَعۡرُوۡفِ وَ یَنۡہَوۡنَ عَنِ الۡمُنۡکَرِ»\nTranslation: And let there be among you a group who invite to good, enjoin what is right, and forbid what is wrong."
    },
    {
      "id": 2904,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Goodness / Good Deeds",
      "hw": "نیکی",
      "s": "« » every action that is in accordance with reason and Shariah. (31 verses: 2:201-3:120-4:40-4:78-4:79-4:85-6:160-7:95-7:131-7:156-7:168-9:50-9:52-11:114-13:6-13:22-16:30-16:41-16:122-16:125-25:70-27:46-27:89-28:54-28:84-33:21-39:10-41:34-42:23-60:4-60:6)",
      "d": "« » its plural is « ». Every pleasing and praiseworthy action that is in accordance with reason and Shariah. Its opposite is « », and its plural is « ».\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«اِنَّ الۡحَسَنٰتِ یُذۡہِبۡنَ السَّیِّاٰتِ»\nTranslation: Indeed, good deeds erase bad deeds."
    },
    {
      "id": 2905,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Goodness / Good Deeds",
      "hw": "نیکی",
      "s": "« » every action that is desirable to all or whose benefit reaches the people. (170 verses: 2:54-2:61-2:103-2:105-2:106-2:110-2:148-2:158-2:180-2:184-2:197-2:215-2:216-2:220-2:221-2:263-2:269-2:271-2:272-2:273-2:280-3:15-3:26-3:30-3:54-3:104-3:110-3:114-3:115-3:150-3:157-3:178-3:180-3:198-4:19-4:25-4:46-4:59-4:66-4:77-4:114-4:127-4:128-4:149-4:170-4:171-5:48-5:114-6:17-6:32-6:57-6:158-7:12-7:26-7:85-7:87-7:89-7:155-7:169-7:188-8:19-8:23-8:30-8:70-9:3-9:41-9:61-9:74-9:88-9:109-10:11-10:58-10:107-10:109-11:31-11:84-11:86-12:39-12:57-12:59-12:64-12:80-12:109-16:30-16:76-16:95-16:126-17:11-17:35-18:36-18:40-18:44-18:46-18:81-18:95-19:73-19:76-20:73-20:131-21:35-21:73-21:89-21:90-22:11-22:30-22:36-22:58-22:77-23:29-23:56-23:61-23:72-23:109-23:118-24:11-24:12-24:27-24:33-24:60-25:10-25:15-25:24-27:36-27:59-27:89-28:24-28:26-28:60-28:80-28:84-29:16-30:38-33:19-33:25-34:39-35:32-37:62-38:32-38:76-41:40-41:49-42:36-43:32-43:52-43:58-44:37-46:11-47:21-49:5-49:11-50:25-54:43-55:70-58:12-61:11-62:9-62:11-64:16-66:5-68:12-68:32-70:21-70:41-73:20-87:17-93:4-97:3-98:7-99:7-100:8)",
      "d": "« » its plural is « ». And its opposite is « ». « » means the perfection of goodness. Actions whose benefit reaches the people (Muf.). Great good deeds. Great actions of goodness. Also, « » means an action that is desirable to all (Muf.), such as arranging water for travelers on the road, etc.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«یَاۡمُرُوۡنَ بِالۡمَعۡرُوۡفِ وَ یَنۡہَوۡنَ عَنِ الۡمُنۡکَرِ وَ یُسَارِعُوۡنَ فِی الۡخَیۡرٰتِ»\nTranslation: They enjoin what is right, forbid what is wrong, and hasten towards good deeds."
    },
    {
      "id": 2906,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Goodness / Good Deeds",
      "hw": "نیکی",
      "s": "« » the constant inclination of the nature towards goodness at all times. (9 verses: 2:44-2:177-2:189-2:224-3:92-5:2-52:28-58:9-60:8)",
      "d": "« » means the constant inclination of the nature towards every good deed and performing it when the opportunity arises. Its opposite is « », meaning sin, transgression, moral or religious crime. (For details, see above under 'Righteous').\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«تَعَاوَنُوۡا عَلَی الۡبِرِّ وَ التَّقۡوٰی ۪ وَ لَا تَعَاوَنُوۡا عَلَی الۡاِثۡمِ وَ الۡعُدۡوَانِ»\nTranslation: Cooperate in righteousness and piety, but do not cooperate in sin and aggression."
    }
  ],
  "636": [
    {
      "id": 2907,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant / More / Much",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » its usage is general. Increase in number or quantity of anything. (71 verses: 2:26-2:109-2:245-2:249-2:269-3:41-3:146-3:186-4:1-4:19-4:82-4:94-4:100-4:114-4:160-5:15-5:32-5:49-5:62-5:64-5:66-5:68-5:71-5:77-5:80-5:81-5:91-6:119-6:137-7:179-8:43-8:45-9:25-9:34-9:82-10:92-11:91-14:36-17:70-20:33-20:34-22:18-22:40-23:19-23:21-25:14-25:38-25:49-26:227-27:15-30:8-33:21-33:35-33:41-36:62-38:24-38:51-41:22-42:30-42:34-43:73-48:19-48:20-49:7-49:12-56:32-57:16-57:26-57:27-62:10-71:24)",
      "d": "« » means 'more'. It comes in both contexts of quantity and number. And it is used in both material and spiritual senses. Its usage is general. And its opposite is « », meaning few and little.\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ مَنۡ یُّؤۡتَ الۡحِکۡمَۃَ فَقَدۡ اُوۡتِیَ خَیۡرًا کَثِیۡرًا»\nTranslation: And whoever is given wisdom has indeed been given much good.\nIn the mentioned verse, « » is used in a spiritual sense for quantity, and in the following verse fragment, it is used in a tangible sense for number.\nFor example, the divine command is:\n«فَاٰتَیۡنَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡا مِنۡہُمۡ اَجۡرَہُمۡ ۚ وَ کَثِیۡرٌ مِّنۡہُمۡ فٰسِقُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: So We gave those who believed among them their reward, and many of them were defiantly disobedient.\n«کَوْثَر» «تَکَاثُرَ الشَّیْء» «رَجُلٌ کَاثِرٌ» «کَوْثَر» «کَوْثَر»\nFor example, the divine command is:\n«اِنَّاۤ اَعۡطَیۡنٰکَ الۡکَوۡثَرَ»\nTranslation: Indeed, We have granted you, [O Muhammad], al-Kawthar."
    },
    {
      "id": 2908,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant / More / Much",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » the gathering of something in large quantity at one place. (1 verse: 89:20)",
      "d": "«جَمّ» «جَمَّ الْبِئْر» «جَمَّ الْمِکْیَال»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَّ تُحِبُّوۡنَ الۡمَالَ حُبًّا جَمًّا»\nTranslation: And you love wealth with [great] love."
    },
    {
      "id": 2909,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant / More / Much",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » to be piled up layer upon layer. (2 verses: 8:37-52:44)",
      "d": "«رَکَمَ» «رُکَام» «مَرْکُوْم» «رَکَمَ السَّحَاب» «سَحَابٌ مَرْکُوم»\nFor example, the Quran says:\n«وَ یَجۡعَلَ الۡخَبِیۡثَ بَعۡضَہٗ عَلَی بَعۡضٍ فَیَرۡکُمَہٗ جَمِیۡعًا»\nTranslation: And He will place the wickedness of some upon others and make them into a heap."
    },
    {
      "id": 2910,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant. More. Much.",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » refers to the gathering of scattered parts of something into a heap at one place. (2 verses: 72:19-90:6)",
      "d": "«لِبْد» «لِبْدَةُ» «مَالٌ لُبْدٌ» «لَبَّدَ شَعْرُہٗ» «لُبَدَ الشَّیء»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«یَقُوۡلُ اَہۡلَکۡتُ مَالًا لُّبَدًا»\nTranslation: Man says, \"I have destroyed a heap of wealth.\"\nAnd when attributed to people of intellect, it means crowding so much that there's no space to sit.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«وَّ اَنَّہٗ لَمَّا قَامَ عَبۡدُ اللّٰہِ یَدۡعُوۡہُ کَادُوۡا یَکُوۡنُوۡنَ عَلَیۡہِ لِبَدًا»\nTranslation: And when the servant of Allah (Muhammad ﷺ) stood up in worship, the disbelievers crowded around him.\nNote: Namda is the name of that thick cloth made by compressing sheep's hair, wool, or felt with soap etc.; a thick woolen cloth and also a cap."
    },
    {
      "id": 2911,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant. More. Much.",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » is used exclusively for the abundance of food and sustenance. (3 verses: 2:35-2:58-16:112)",
      "d": "« » comes only for sustenance or food. To eat to one's fill or to be provided with abundant sustenance.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ کُلَا مِنۡہَا رَغَدًا حَیۡثُ شِئۡتُمَا»\nTranslation: (O Adam and Hawwa) Eat from it (the fruits of Paradise) to your fill, wherever you wish."
    },
    {
      "id": 2912,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant. More. Much.",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » is used for the abundance of water when it is also beneficial. (1 verse: 72:16)",
      "d": "« » means to rain in large quantities and as a blessing.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَّ اَنۡ لَّوِ اسۡتَقَامُوۡا عَلَی الطَّرِیۡقَۃِ لَاَسۡقَیۡنٰہُمۡ مَّآءً غَدَقًا»\nTranslation: If they had remained steadfast on the path, We would have given them abundant water to drink."
    },
    {
      "id": 2913,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant. More. Much.",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » is used for the pouring and flowing of water in large quantities. (1 verse: 78:14)",
      "d": "« » means to pour and flow water forcefully. And « » means a torrent of water.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَّ اَنۡزَلۡنَا مِنَ الۡمُعۡصِرٰتِ مَآءً ثَجَّاجًا»\nTranslation: And We sent down from the rain-bearing clouds water in torrents."
    },
    {
      "id": 2914,
      "a": "ز",
      "h": "Abundant. More. Much.",
      "hw": "زیادہ",
      "s": "« » comes for the completeness and abundance of something. (1 verse: 17:63)",
      "d": "«وَفَر» «وَفَّرَ» «وَفَرَ جَزَاءُہٗ»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«قَالَ اذۡہَبۡ فَمَنۡ تَبِعَکَ مِنۡہُمۡ فَاِنَّ جَہَنَّمَ جَزَآؤُکُمۡ جَزَآءً مَّوۡفُوۡرًا»\nTranslation: Allah said: \"Go! Whoever follows you among them, then Hell is your recompense, a recompense in full.\""
    }
  ],
  "637": [
    {
      "id": 2915,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Companions. Those with.",
      "hw": "والا",
      "s": "« » means those who have accompanied for a long time or those who give companionship. (70 verses: 2:39-2:81-2:82-2:119-2:217-2:257-2:275-3:116-4:47-5:10-5:29-5:86-6:71-7:36-7:42-7:44-7:46-7:47-7:48-7:50-9:70-9:113-10:26-10:27-11:23-13:5-15:78-15:80-18:9-20:135-22:44-22:51-25:24-25:38-26:61-26:176-29:15-35:6-36:13-36:55-38:13-39:8-40:6-40:43-46:14-46:16-50:12-50:14-51:59-56:8-56:9-56:27-56:38-56:41-56:90-56:91-57:19-58:17-59:20-60:13-64:10-67:10-67:11-68:17-74:31-74:39-85:4-90:18-90:19-105:1)",
      "d": "« » is the plural of « », meaning one who has accompanied for a long time or gives companionship. Whether this companionship is with a human, an animal, a place, or a time. Although this word can be used metaphorically in a spiritual sense, generally its use is related to physical companionship. Such as Ashab al-Kahf, Ashab al-Rass, Ashab al-Sabt, Ashab al-Fil, Ashab al-Qubur, Ashab al-Safinah, etc."
    },
    {
      "id": 2916,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Companions. Those with.",
      "hw": "والا",
      "s": "« » is attributed only to a renowned personality and nobles. Such as Aal Muhammad ﷺ, Aal Ibrahim, Aal Imran. (23 verses: 2:49-2:50-2:248-3:11-3:33-4:54-7:130-7:141-8:52-8:54-12:6-14:6-15:59-15:61-19:6-27:56-28:8-34:13-40:28-40:45-40:46-54:34-54:41)",
      "d": "The word « » is used only as an attribute for a renowned personality and nobles. Such as Aal Muhammad, Aal Ibrahim, Aal Imran. One can say Aal Fir'aun but cannot say Aal al-Khayyat. And in Aal, all those people are included who consider that noble person as honorable and have mental agreement and unity with him. Thus, Aal Muhammad does not only mean the family of the Prophet ﷺ, but also includes those who have a special connection with him in terms of knowledge and insight. Similarly, Aal Fir'aun means all his officials and those who are mentally aligned with him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2917,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Companions. Those with.",
      "hw": "والا",
      "s": "« » means family, household members. Its attribution can be to anything. (51 verses: 2:105-2:109-3:64-3:65-3:69-3:70-3:71-3:72-3:75-3:98-3:99-3:110-3:113-3:199-4:123-4:153-4:159-4:171-5:15-5:19-5:47-5:59-5:65-5:68-5:77-7:96-7:97-7:98-9:101-9:120-11:73-12:109-15:67-16:43-18:77-20:40-21:7-28:12-28:45-29:46-33:13-33:26-33:33-38:64-57:29-59:2-59:7-59:11-74:56-98:1-98:6)",
      "d": "« » can also be attributed to non-rational entities, such as Ahl al-Balad (people of the city), Ahl al-Ard (people of the land), Ahl al-Qarya (people of the villages), Ahl al-Bayt, Ahl al-Kitab, Ahl al-Dhikr, and Ahl al-Nar, etc. And when it is attributed to rational beings, it means the people of the house, wife, children, clan, or family. For example, Ahl al-Khayyat means the people of the tailor's house, his family and clan members, which includes his wife as well. (For further distinction between « » and « », see \"Offspring\")"
    }
  ],
  "639": [
    {
      "id": 2921,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Time",
      "hw": "وقت",
      "s": "«وَقْت، مِیْقَات»",
      "d": "«وَقْت» «اَلْوَقْت» «زَمَانٌ مَّعْلُوْمٌ» «اَوْقَات»\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«قُلۡ اِنَّمَا عِلۡمُہَا عِنۡدَ رَبِّیۡ ۚ لَا یُجَلِّیۡہَا لِوَقۡتِہَاۤ اِلَّا ہُوَ»\nTranslation: Say, \"Its knowledge is only with my Lord. He will manifest it at its appointed time; none but He can reveal it.\"\nAnd « » is a noun of time from « ». It is used in both temporal and spatial senses. Its plural is « ». In the following verse, Miqat is used in the temporal sense.\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«وَ وٰعَدۡنَا مُوۡسٰی ثَلٰثِیۡنَ لَیۡلَۃً وَّ اَتۡمَمۡنٰہَا بِعَشۡرٍ فَتَمَّ مِیۡقَاتُ رَبِّہٖۤ اَرۡبَعِیۡنَ لَیۡلَۃً»\nTranslation: And We appointed for Moses thirty nights, and completed them with ten, so the appointed time of his Lord was fulfilled as forty nights.\nAnd in the following verse, the word Miqat is used in both temporal and spatial senses, meaning both an appointed time and place.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَمَّا جَآءَ مُوۡسٰی لِمِیۡقَاتِنَا وَ کَلَّمَہٗ رَبُّہٗ»\nTranslation: And when Moses came at Our appointed time (on Mount Tur) and his Lord spoke to him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2922,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Time",
      "hw": "وقت",
      "s": "« » means an unspecified time. (33 verses: 2:36-2:177-5:101-5:106-7:24-10:98-11:5-12:35-14:25-16:6-16:80-21:39-21:111-23:25-23:54-24:58-25:42-26:218-28:15-30:17-30:18-36:44-37:148-37:174-37:178-38:3-38:88-39:42-39:58-51:43-52:48-56:84-76:1)",
      "d": "« » refers to the time when a news arrives or something is obtained. It is an indefinite noun. Its plural is « » and « », meaning sometimes, occasionally.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ لَکُمۡ فِی الۡاَرۡضِ مُسۡتَقَرٌّ وَّ مَتَاعٌ اِلٰی حِیۡنٍ»\nTranslation: And for you on the earth is a place of settlement and provision for a time.\nAnd after « », adding « » makes « », which points to a specific time, meaning \"at that time\".\nFor example: The Divine declaration is:\n«وَ اَنۡتُمۡ حِیۡنَئِذٍ تَنۡظُرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: And you, at that time, are looking on."
    },
    {
      "id": 2923,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Time",
      "hw": "وقت",
      "s": "« » and « » mean the present time (12 verses: 2:71, 2:187, 3:113, 4:18, 8:66, 10:51, 10:91, 12:51, 20:130, 39:9, 57:16, 72:9)",
      "d": "« » or « » means the time has arrived; something reaching its utmost limit and maturity.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«أَلَمْ يَأْنِ لِلَّذِينَ آمَنُوا أَنْ تَخْشَعَ قُلُوبُهُمْ لِذِكْرِ اللَّهِ»\nTranslation: Has the time not yet come for the believers that their hearts should become humble at the remembrance of Allah?\nAnd « » in the plural is « », meaning hours. The definite article « » is always prefixed to this word, i.e., « » means the present time, now, at this time.\nFor example, the Divine declaration states:\n«الْآنَ خَفَّفَ اللَّهُ عَنْكُمْ وَ عَلِمَ أَنَّ فِيكُمْ ضَعْفًا»\nTranslation: Now Allah has lightened your burden and knows that there is weakness among you."
    },
    {
      "id": 2924,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Time",
      "hw": "وقت",
      "s": "« » means just now, at the very beginning of something, a little while ago (1 verse: 47:16)",
      "d": "«أنف» «أنف الجبل» «أنف اللحية» «استأنف الشيء» «استأنف الأمر» «آنِفا»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«قَالُوا لِلَّذِينَ أُوتُوا الْعِلْمَ مَاذَا قَالَ آنِفًا»\nTranslation: They say to those who have been given knowledge, 'What did he say just now (at the start)?'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2925,
      "a": "و",
      "h": "Time",
      "hw": "وقت",
      "s": "« » means an appointed time and the intervening period until the present time (45 verses: 2:231, 2:232, 2:234, 2:235, 2:282, 4:77, 6:2, 6:60, 6:128, 7:34, 7:135, 7:185, 10:11, 10:49, 11:3, 11:104, 13:2, 13:38, 14:10, 14:44, 15:5, 16:61, 17:99, 20:129, 22:5, 22:33, 23:43, 28:28, 28:29, 29:5, 29:53, 30:8, 31:29, 35:13, 35:45, 39:5, 39:42, 40:67, 42:14, 46:3, 63:10, 63:11, 65:2, 65:4, 71:4)",
      "d": "« » means to delay. « » and « » mean that which happens after a delay. The Hereafter. « » is the opposite of « », meaning one who hastens, quick. Both words are common. They are generally used in the context of the payment of the dower (mahr) at the time of marriage. « » means that which is paid immediately in cash, and « » means on credit. « » means period, time, death. Thus, the word « » comes to mean the time from the present until a promised or appointed period, and sometimes until death. Its usage is very extensive.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَجَعَلَ لَهُمْ أَجَلًا لَا رَيْبَ فِيهِ»\nTranslation: And He has appointed for them a time about which there is no doubt.\nIn this verse, the translation of « » can be as 'time', 'period', 'appointed term', or 'time of death' – all are appropriate here."
    }
  ],
  "640": [
    {
      "id": 2926,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "hand",
      "hw": "ہاتھ",
      "s": "« » means hand, power, and grasp (72 verses: 2:79-2:95-2:195-2:237-2:249-3:26-3:73-3:182-4:43-4:62-4:77-4:91-5:6-5:11-5:28-5:33-5:38-5:64-5:94-6:7-6:93-7:108-7:124-7:149-7:195-8:51-8:70-9:14-9:29-9:52-9:67-11:70-12:31-12:50-14:9-17:29-18:57-20:22-20:71-22:10-23:88-24:24-24:40-25:27-26:33-26:49-27:12-28:32-28:47-30:36-30:41-36:35-36:65-36:71-36:83-38:44-38:45-38:75-42:30-42:48-48:10-48:20-48:24-51:47-57:29-59:2-60:2-62:7-67:1-78:40-80:15-111:1)",
      "d": "«یَد» «یَدَی» «یَدَان» «یَدَیْن» «اَیْدِی» «فَوَیۡلٌ لَّہُمۡ  مِّمَّا کَتَبَتۡ اَیۡدِیۡہِمۡ وَ وَیۡلٌ لَّہُمۡ مِّمَّا یَکۡسِبُوۡنَ» «یَد» «اِلَّاۤ  اَنۡ یَّعۡفُوۡنَ اَوۡ یَعۡفُوَا الَّذِیۡ بِیَدِہٖ عُقۡدَۃُ النِّکَاحِ» «بَیْنَ یَدَی» «بَیْنَ اَیْدِی» «یٰۤاَیُّہَا الَّذِیۡنَ اٰمَنُوۡۤا اِذَا نَاجَیۡتُمُ الرَّسُوۡلَ  فَقَدِّمُوۡا بَیۡنَ یَدَیۡ نَجۡوٰىکُمۡ صَدَقَۃً» «وَ جَعَلۡنَا مِنۡۢ بَیۡنِ اَیۡدِیۡہِمۡ سَدًّا وَّ مِنۡ خَلۡفِہِمۡ سَدًّا» «فَقُلۡنَا لَہُمۡ کُوۡنُوۡا قِرَدَۃً خٰسِئِیۡنَ . فَجَعَلۡنٰہَا نَکَالًا لِّمَا بَیۡنَ یَدَیۡہَا وَ مَا خَلۡفَہَا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2927,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Hand",
      "hw": "ہاتھ",
      "s": "« » means the right hand; it is also used for complete grasp, authority, and oath (23 verses: 16:48, 17:71, 18:17, 18:18, 20:17, 20:69, 29:48, 33:50, 33:52, 34:15, 37:28, 37:93, 39:67, 50:17, 56:27, 56:38, 56:90, 56:91, 69:19, 69:45, 70:37, 74:39, 84:7)",
      "d": "The plural of « » is « ». « » is used in three meanings: (1) « » means the right hand. (2) « » means the right side; its opposite is left. (3) « » means an oath.\nNow, let us see examples:\nFor the right hand, for example, the Quran states:\n«وَمَا تِلْكَ بِيَمِينِكَ يَا مُوسَى»\nTranslation: And what is that in your right hand, O Moses?\nAnd for the right side, for example, the Quran states:\n«لَقَدْ كَانَ لِسَبَإٍ فِي مَسْكَنِهِمْ آيَةٌ جَنَّتَانِ عَنْ يَمِينٍ وَ شِمَالٍ»\nTranslation: There was for Saba a sign in their dwelling place: two gardens on the right and left.\nThen, just as the word « » comes to mean power and grasp, « » comes to mean in a wider sense because the right hand is superior and better than the left in terms of power and function. And 'milk yamin' refers to that over which one has complete grasp and authority. And idiomatically, this word is also used to mean a female slave or a male slave.\nFor example, the Divine declaration states:\n«وَالْمُحْصَنَاتُ مِنَ النِّسَاءِ إِلَّا مَا مَلَكَتْ أَيْمَانُكُمْ»\nTranslation: And [also prohibited are] married women, except those whom your right hands possess (i.e., female slaves taken as captives).\nBesides this, it was the custom of the Arabs to strengthen their covenants and oaths by placing their right hand in the right hand of the person they were addressing or striking it. Hence, this word began to be used in the meaning of an oath. And « » is the name of an oath that is taken to strengthen a covenant.\nFor example, the Divine declaration states:\n«أَلَا تُقَاتِلُونَ قَوْمًا نَكَثُوا أَيْمَانَهُمْ»\nTranslation: Will you not fight a people who broke their oaths?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2929,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Hand",
      "hw": "ہاتھ",
      "s": "« » means the part from the elbow to the tip of the middle finger (2 verses: 18:51, 28:35)",
      "d": "«ذراع» «ذرع الثوب» «ذراع» «ذَرْعُهُ كَذَا» «ذراع» «ذراع»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«ثُمَّ فِي سِلْسِلَةٍ ذَرْعُهَا سَبْعُونَ ذِرَاعًا فَاسْلُكُوهُ»\nTranslation: Then in a chain whose length is seventy cubits, drag him."
    }
  ],
  "641": [
    {
      "id": 2930,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Yes",
      "hw": "ہاں",
      "s": "« » means yes; an affirmative answer to a positive question (4 verses: 7:44, 7:114, 26:42, 37:18)",
      "d": "« » means yes. It is a word of affirmation. The answer to a question when both the question and the answer are in a positive sense.\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَجَاءَ السَّحَرَةُ فِرْعَوْنَ قَالُوا إِنَّ لَنَا لَأَجْرًا إِنْ كُنَّا نَحْنُ الْغَالِبِينَ . قَالَ نَعَمْ وَ إِنَّكُمْ لَمِنَ الْمُقَرَّبِينَ»\nTranslation: The magicians came to Pharaoh and said, 'Indeed, for us is a reward if we are the victorious.' He said, 'Yes, and indeed, you will be of those near [to me].'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2931,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Yes",
      "hw": "ہاں",
      "s": "« » is used when giving a positive and emphatic response to a positive question. For example: Yes, indeed, certainly (1 verse: 10:53)",
      "d": "« » meaning yes, indeed. Certainly. It is an affirmative word. Used when answering a question positively and emphatically, leaving no room for doubt. And an oath is necessary after it ( ).\nFor example: In the Quran:\n«یَسۡتَنۡۢبِئُوۡنَکَ اَحَقٌّ ہُوَ  ؕ ؔ قُلۡ اِیۡ  وَ رَبِّیۡۤ  اِنَّہٗ  لَحَقٌّ»\nTranslation: They ask you whether it (the Hereafter) is true. Say: Yes, indeed! By my Lord, it is certainly true.\nNote: (An affirmative word is one used to affirm something or to respond to a call or question.)"
    }
  ],
  "642": [
    {
      "id": 2933,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "To pant",
      "hw": "ہانپنا",
      "s": "« » means to pant due to running fast (1 verse: 100:1)",
      "d": "«ضبح الفرس»\nFor example, the Quran states:\n«وَالْعَادِيَاتِ ضَبْحًا»\nTranslation: By the chargers at dawn, panting (as they run)."
    },
    {
      "id": 2934,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to pant",
      "hw": "ہانپنا",
      "s": "« » refers to panting due to thirst or fatigue (1 verse: 7:176)",
      "d": "« » means to protrude the tongue out of the mouth and emit a sound from the chest due to severe thirst ( ). To pant and let the tongue hang out due to thirst or fatigue ( ).\nFor example: In the Quran:\n«فَمَثَلُہٗ  کَمَثَلِ الۡکَلۡبِ ۚ اِنۡ  تَحۡمِلۡ عَلَیۡہِ یَلۡہَثۡ اَوۡ تَتۡرُکۡہُ یَلۡہَثۡ»\nTranslation: Its example is like that of a dog: if you chase it away, it pants, or if you leave it, it pants.\nNote: (  means: internal cavity, the space inside something, the inner part of anything that is hollow, a hole.)"
    }
  ],
  "643": [
    {
      "id": 2935,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to ward off external dangers or attacks in the protection and support of something, and to push away. (4 verses: 2:251-22:40-23:96-41:34)",
      "d": "« » means to ward off external dangers or attacks in the protection and support of something, and to push away. (Muf, Manjad) « » means protection and support. And « » means to retaliate.\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَ لَوۡ لَا دَفۡعُ اللّٰہِ النَّاسَ بَعۡضَہُمۡ بِبَعۡضٍ»\nTranslation: And were it not that Allah repels people, some by means of others...\nAnd when this word is followed by « », it means to hand over something to someone, to entrust, or to give.\nFor example: The command of Allah is:\n«فَادۡفَعُوۡۤا اِلَیۡہِمۡ اَمۡوَالَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: Then hand over to them their wealth."
    },
    {
      "id": 2936,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to turn someone aside, to remove. It is a general term. (2 verses: 87:11-92:17)",
      "d": "« » means side or direction. And « » and « » mean to repel, to remove, to turn aside and save, or to strike on the side. (Manjad)\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَ سَیُجَنَّبُہَا  الۡاَتۡقَی الَّذِیۡ یُؤۡتِیۡ مَالَہٗ یَتَزَکّٰی»\nTranslation: And the most righteous will be kept away from it (Hell), he who gives his wealth to purify himself."
    },
    {
      "id": 2937,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to save someone from harm by removing them from a place. (2 verses: 2:96-3:185)",
      "d": "«اَلْزَحْزَح» «زَحْزَحَ» «زَحْزَحَ عَنْ»\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«فَمَنۡ زُحۡزِحَ عَنِ النَّارِ وَ اُدۡخِلَ الۡجَنَّۃَ فَقَدۡ فَازَ»\nTranslation: And whoever is removed from the Fire and admitted to Paradise has indeed succeeded."
    },
    {
      "id": 2938,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to keep harm away with full force and effort. (4 verses: 3:168-13:22-24:8-28:54)",
      "d": "« » means to save someone from harm by pushing them away with full force. (Muf) And it means to push forcefully, to remove. (Manjad)\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«وَ یَدۡرَؤُا  عَنۡہَا الۡعَذَابَ اَنۡ تَشۡہَدَ اَرۡبَعَ شَہٰدٰتٍۭ بِاللّٰہِ»\nTranslation: And if the woman testifies four times by Allah that he (the accuser) is lying, this will ward off the punishment from her.\nAnd « » means to shift the blame onto another so that one may be saved from punishment.\nFor example: The command of Allah is:\n«وَ اِذۡ قَتَلۡتُمۡ نَفۡسًا فَادّٰارَءۡتُمۡ فِیۡہَا»\nTranslation: And when you killed a soul, then you disputed concerning it..."
    },
    {
      "id": 2939,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to push out with shoves, to remove. (2 verses: 52:13-107:2)",
      "d": "« » means to push out with shoves, to repel harshly. (F L 188)\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«فَذٰلِکَ الَّذِیۡ یَدُعُّ  الۡیَتِیۡمَ»\nTranslation: That is the one who repels the orphan."
    },
    {
      "id": 2940,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to drive out with a push, to expel, regardless of reason. (4 verses: 7:18-17:18-17:39-37:9)",
      "d": "In « », two basic meanings are found: (1) to drive away, (2) to remove. (M, L) Meaning to drive someone out with a push.\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«قَالَ اخۡرُجۡ مِنۡہَا مَذۡءُوۡمًا مَّدۡحُوۡرًا»\nTranslation: Allah said: 'Get out of it (Paradise), accursed and expelled!'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2941,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to remove",
      "hw": "ہٹانا",
      "s": "« » means to drive away with disdain and humiliation. (4 verses: 2:65-7:166-23:108-67:4)",
      "d": "«خَسَّاَ النَّظَر» «خسَأَ الْکَلْب» «خَاسِیءُ مِنَ الْکِلاَبِ وَ الْخَنَازِیْر»\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«فَقُلۡنَا لَہُمۡ کُوۡنُوۡا قِرَدَۃً خٰسِئِیۡنَ»\nTranslation: So we said to them: 'Be apes, despised and humiliated.'"
    }
  ],
  "644": [
    {
      "id": 2942,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to guide; to find",
      "hw": "ہدایت",
      "s": "« » means to walk on the straight path. (56 verses: 2:16-2:53-2:70-2:135-2:137-2:150-2:157-2:170-3:20-3:103-4:98-5:104-5:105-6:56-6:82-6:97-6:117-6:140-7:30-7:43-7:158-7:178-9:18-10:45-10:108-16:15-16:16-16:125-17:15-17:97-18:17-18:57-19:76-20:82-20:135-21:31-23:49-24:54-27:24-27:41-27:92-28:56-28:64-32:3-34:50-36:21-39:41-43:10-43:22-43:37-43:49-46:11-47:17-53:30-57:26-68:7)",
      "d": "« » means to guide someone with grace and favor, to show the path of goodness. (Muf) Its opposite is « » and « », meaning to misguide, to lead astray, to make one lose the good path or obscure it. « » has three meanings:\n(1) Innate guidance that Allah has placed in every thing by creation, like a newborn baby's instinct to seek its mother's breast.\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«رَبُّنَا الَّذِیۡۤ اَعۡطٰی کُلَّ شَیۡءٍ خَلۡقَہٗ  ثُمَّ  ہَدٰی»\nTranslation: Our Lord is He who gave everything its creation and then guided it.\n(2) Turning a person's mind from error to guidance, from disbelief to Islam, from disobedience to obedience to Allah. This occurs through prophets and messengers, but the turning is solely by Allah's will.\nFor example: The command of Allah is:\n«اِنَّکَ لَا تَہۡدِیۡ مَنۡ  اَحۡبَبۡتَ وَ لٰکِنَّ اللّٰہَ یَہۡدِیۡ مَنۡ یَّشَآءُ»\nTranslation: (O Muhammad) you cannot guide whom you love, but Allah guides whom He wills.\n(3) Showing the straight path to those who come to Allah's obedience or Islam, and continuing to guide them. This is the primary responsibility of prophets and messengers, and other Muslims participate in it (though it occurs by Allah's decree).\nFor example: The command of Allah is:\n«اَفَاَنۡتَ تَہۡدِی الۡعُمۡیَ وَ لَوۡ کَانُوۡا لَا یُبۡصِرُوۡنَ»\nTranslation: Can you guide the blind even though they will not see?\nAnother verse says:\n«وَ اِنَّکَ لَتَہۡدِیۡۤ  اِلٰی صِرَاطٍ مُّسۡتَقِیۡمٍ»\nTranslation: And indeed, you (Muhammad) guide to a straight path.\nAnd « » means to find guidance, to walk on the straight path.\nFor example: The command of Allah is:\n«فَمَنِ اہۡتَدٰی فَاِنَّمَا یَہۡتَدِیۡ لِنَفۡسِہٖ»\nTranslation: So whoever is guided is only guided for himself."
    },
    {
      "id": 2943,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "to guide; to find",
      "hw": "ہدایت",
      "s": "« » means to adopt good habits and persist on them after choosing the straight path. (13 verses: 2:186-2:256-4:6-7:146-18:10-18:17-18:24-18:66-21:51-72:2-72:10-72:14-72:21)",
      "d": "« » means a person who comes to the right path and also adopts good conduct. Its opposite is « » meaning misguided, one who follows the wrong path. (Q, M) And « » means steadfastness on the path of truth, adherence. Its opposite is « ». (Manjad)\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«اَلَـیۡسَ مِنۡکُمۡ  رَجُلٌ  رَّشِیۡدٌ»\nTranslation: Is there not among you a man of good conduct? (Imam translation)"
    }
  ],
