      "s": "« » means to perish. (8 verses: 7:139-11:101-17:7-18:35-25:39-35:29-40:37-111:1)",
      "d": "« » means to perish, to break, to cut, to sever; all these meanings are applicable. (Manjad)\nFor example: The Quran says:\n«تَبَّتۡ یَدَاۤ  اَبِیۡ  لَہَبٍ وَّ  تَبَّ»\nTranslation: May the hands of Abu Lahab be ruined, and ruined is he."
