      "hw": "ہلاک",
      "s": "« » means a garden becoming completely desolate, utterly destroyed and ruined (1 verse: 18:35)",
      "d": "« » means desert, and its plural is « ». And « » means a garden becoming completely desolate, utterly destroyed and ruined ( ).\nFor example: In the Quran:\n«قَالَ مَاۤ اَظُنُّ اَنۡ تَبِیۡدَ ہٰذِہٖۤ  اَبَدًا»\nTranslation: He said: I do not think that this garden will ever be utterly destroyed."
