      "s": "« » means to shake a large or heavy thing with a jerk (3 verses: 19:25, 27:10, 28:31)",
      "d": "«ھَزَّ» «وَ ہُزِّیۡۤ  اِلَیۡکِ بِجِذۡعِ النَّخۡلَۃِ» «اِھْتَزَّ» «فَلَمَّا رَاٰہَا تَہۡتَزُّ کَاَنَّہَا جَآنٌّ  وَّلّٰی مُدۡبِرًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 2968,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Shaking / Moving",
      "hw": "ہلانا",
      "s": "« » means to shake something light or soft with a jerk. (1 verse: 20:18)",
      "d": "«ھَشَّ» «ھَزَّ» «ھَشَّ» «ھَشَّ الْوَرَق» «ھَشِیْش» «ھَشَّ» «ھَشَّاش» «ہشاش بشاش»\n«قَالَ ہِیَ عَصَایَ ۚ اَتَوَکَّؤُا عَلَیۡہَا وَ اَہُشُّ بِہَا عَلٰی غَنَمِیۡ»\nTranslation: Moses (peace be upon him) said, 'This is my staff. I lean on it and I also shake leaves from trees for my sheep with it.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 2969,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Shaking / Moving",
      "hw": "ہلانا",
      "s": "« » means to twist or jerk something. (4 verses: 3:78-3:153-4:135-63:5)",
      "d": "«لَوَی الْحَبْل» «لَوَیْتُ الْحَیَّۃُ» «لَوٰی لِسَانَہٗ» «لَوّٰی» «لَوّٰی رَأسَہٗ»\n«وَ اِذَا قِیۡلَ لَہُمۡ تَعَالَوۡا یَسۡتَغۡفِرۡ لَکُمۡ رَسُوۡلُ اللّٰہِ لَوَّوۡا رُءُوۡسَہُمۡ»\nTranslation: And when it is said to them, 'Come, the Messenger of Allah will seek forgiveness for you,' they shake their heads."
    },
    {
      "id": 2970,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Shaking / Moving",
      "hw": "ہلانا",
      "s": "« » means to shake the head due to surprise, mockery, or trembling. This word is specific for shaking the head. (1 verse: 17:51)",
      "d": "«نَغَضَ» «نَغَضَ رَأسَہٗ» «نَغْض» «اَلْاَنْغَاض»\n«فَسَیُنۡغِضُوۡنَ اِلَیۡکَ رُءُوۡسَہُمۡ وَ یَقُوۡلُوۡنَ مَتٰی ہُوَ ؕ قُلۡ عَسٰۤی اَنۡ یَّکُوۡنَ قَرِیۡبًا»\nTranslation: So they will shake their heads at you and say, 'When will it be?' Say, 'Perhaps it will be soon.'"
    }
  ],
  "649": [
    {
      "id": 2971,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "harmony / to be in harmony",
      "hw": "ہم آہنگی",
      "s": "« » means a companion of the same age or close associate (6 verses: 4:38-37:51-43:36-43:38-50:23-50:27)",
      "d": "«قُرُوْن» «قَرَن» «قُرُوْن» «قَرِیْن» «قَرَن» «قَرَنَ الثَّوْرَیْن» «قَرِیْن» «قُرَنَاء»\nFor example: In the Quran:\n«وَ مَنۡ  یَّکُنِ  الشَّیۡطٰنُ  لَہٗ  قَرِیۡنًا فَسَآءَ  قَرِیۡنًا»\nTranslation: And whoever has Satan as a companion—what an evil companion he is!"
    },
    {
      "id": 2972,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Harmony / Being together",
      "hw": "ہم آہنگی",
      "s": "« » means friends or companions of the same age and temperament. (3 verses: 38:52-56:37-78:33)",
      "d": "« » means dust, soil. And « » means to become dusty, also to be poor and needy. And « » means to be wealthy, also to be healthy, and this is from the antonyms (terminology). And « » means to play together in the dust, to be of the same age, to be friends. And the feminine of « » is « ». Its plural is « ». And it means a female friend, of the same age, of the same lineage, of the same group (terminology). « » is often used for women (terminology). So atrab refers to such friends and women of the same age among whom there is complete harmony in temperament.\n«فَجَعَلۡنٰہُنَّ اَبۡکَارًا عُرُبًا اَتۡرَابًا»\nTranslation: We have made them virgins, loving and of the same age."
    },
    {
      "id": 2973,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Harmony / Being together",
      "hw": "ہم آہنگی",
      "s": "« » means having the same name. (2 verses: 19:7-19:65)",
      "d": "« » means name, and « » means having the same name. Such two or more people who have the same name.\n«اسۡمُہٗ یَحۡیٰی ۙ لَمۡ نَجۡعَلۡ لَّہٗ مِنۡ قَبۡلُ سَمِیًّا»\nTranslation: His name is Yahya. We have not given this name to anyone before him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2974,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Harmony / Being together",
      "hw": "ہم آہنگی",
      "s": "« » means equal in rank and status, peer. (1 verse: 112:4)",
      "d": "«کَفَأ، کُفْو» «کُفٰی» «کِفَاءٌ» «کُفْو» «فُلَانٌ کُفْوٌ لِفَلَانٍ»\n«وَ لَمۡ یَکُنۡ لَّہٗ کُفُوًا اَحَدٌ»\nTranslation: And there is none equal to Him."
    },
    {
      "id": 2976,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Harmony / Being together",
      "hw": "ہم آہنگی",
      "s": "« » means similarity in shape, appearance, or habits. (1 verse: 9:30)",
      "d": "«ضَاھَی الرَّجُل» «ضَھِیٌّ»\n«یُضَاہِئُوۡنَ قَوۡلَ الَّذِیۡنَ کَفَرُوۡا»\nTranslation: They imitate the sayings of those who disbelieved."
    }
  ],
  "650": [
    {
      "id": 2977,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Losing Courage",
      "hw": "ہمت",
      "s": "« » is used for losing heart and courage right from the beginning. (4 verses: 3:122-3:152-8:43-8:46)",
      "d": "« » means to show cowardice during battle or hardship (terminology). To lose courage. To despair. To show weakness and cowardice.\n«حَتّٰۤی اِذَا فَشِلۡتُمۡ وَ تَنَازَعۡتُمۡ فِی الۡاَمۡرِ»\nTranslation: Until when you became weak and disputed about the matter."
    },
    {
      "id": 2978,
      "a": "ہ",
      "h": "Losing Courage",
      "hw": "ہمت",
      "s": "« » is used after expending all effort and then losing courage. (2 verses: 3:146-23:76)",
      "d": "« » means to become tired and weak after all effort, finally losing courage. To become helpless. To surrender. To be subdued.\n«فَمَا وَہَنُوۡا لِمَاۤ اَصَابَہُمۡ فِیۡ سَبِیۡلِ اللّٰہِ وَ مَا ضَعُفُوۡا وَ مَا اسۡتَکَانُوۡا»\nTranslation: So they did not weaken because of what afflicted them in the cause of Allah, nor did they become weak, nor did they surrender."
    }
  ],
