  "669": [
    {
      "id": 3067,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Bay'ah - Bay'ah",
      "hw": "بیعت",
      "s": "In the context of Bay'ah, this word 'bay'' symbolizes a covenant or symbolic transaction of loyalty, where a contract of obedience and support is made.",
      "d": "«إِنَّ اللَّهَ اشْتَرَىٰ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ أَنفُسَهُمْ وَأَمْوَالَهُم بِأَنَّ لَهُمُ الْجَنَّةَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3068,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Bay'ah - Bay'ah",
      "hw": "بیعت",
      "s": "In the context of Bay'ah, 'ati' signifies the specific act of stepping forward or presenting oneself to accept a covenant or commitment.",
      "d": "«إِنَّ الَّذِينَ يُبَايِعُونَكَ إِنَّمَا يُبَايِعُونَ اللَّهَ يَدُ اللَّهِ فَوْقَ أَيْدِيهِمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3069,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Bay'ah - Bay'ah",
      "hw": "بیعت",
      "s": "« » in the context of Bay'ah signifies the symbolic movement of the hand, which is evidence of the strength of the covenant and practical commitment.",
      "d": "«يدي» «یَد» «قَسَم» «عَهْد» «إِنَّ الَّذِينَ يُبَايِعُونَكَ إِنَّمَا يُبَايِعُونَ اللَّهَ يَدُ اللَّهِ فَوْقَ أَيْدِيهِمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3070,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Bay'ah - Bay'ah",
      "hw": "بیعت",
      "s": "« » in the context of bay'ah signifies a firm covenant and pledge based on mutual consent and responsibility.",
      "d": "« » means to bind something firmly, to establish a promise or obligation. This word is distinguished from other words like ' ' (promise) or ' ' (oath) in that it emphasizes a two-way agreement, legal or moral responsibility, and continuity. For example: The Quran states:\n«الَّذِينَ يَنقُضُونَ عَهْدَ اللَّهِ مِن بَعْدِ مِيثَاقِهِ»\nTranslation: \"Those who break the covenant of Allah after having firmly bound it.\""
    }
  ],
  "670": [
    {
      "id": 3072,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Unity - Unity",
      "hw": "اتحاد",
      "s": "The distinctive feature of « » is that in unity, it describes not only closeness and friendship but also a strong bond of guardianship and support.",
      "d": "« » means to be near, to become a friend, to guard or supervise. This word differs from others like ' ' (friend) or ' ' (helper) in that it involves a deep connection of brotherhood, responsibility, and mutual cooperation. In the context of unity, it is not merely superficial association but indicates a connection from the depths of the heart. For example: The Quran states:\n«يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا لَا تَتَّخِذُوا الْيَهُودَ وَالنَّصَارَىٰ أَوْلِيَاءَ»\nTranslation: \"O you who have believed, do not take the Jews and the Christians as allies (or guardians).\""
    },
    {
      "id": 3074,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Unity - Unity",
      "hw": "اتحاد",
      "s": "« » in the context of unity signifies different paths or methods that lead towards a common objective.",
      "d": "« » is linguistically derived from the root  - -  which conveys the meaning of 'path' or 'method'. This word is different from other synonyms like ' ' (way) or ' ' (method) in that it emphasizes multiple and diverse paths that guide towards mutual harmony and unity. For example: The Quran states:\n«وَأَنَّ هَـٰذَا صِرَاطِي مُسْتَقِيمًا فَاتَّبِعُوهُ ۖ وَلَا تَتَّبِعُوا السُّبُلَ فَتَفَرَّقَ بِكُمْ عَن سَبِيلِهِ»\nTranslation: \"And that this is My straight path, so follow it; and do not follow the other paths, lest they separate you from His way.\""
    }
  ],
  "671": [
    {
      "id": 3079,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Mihrab - Mihrab",
      "hw": "محراب",
      "s": "The specific meaning of « » in the context of mihrab is to describe the state of worship with God-consciousness and humility.",
      "d": "« » means a respectful fear that arises in the heart due to someone's greatness and awe, expressing deep humility during worship. This word is different from general fear (e.g.,  ,  ) because the element of reverence and love predominates in it. For example: The Quran states:\n«إِذْ نَادَىٰ رَبَّهُ نِدَاءً خَفِيًّا»\nTranslation: \"When he called his Lord with a quiet invocation.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 3080,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Mihrab - Mihrab",
      "hw": "محراب",
      "s": "The specific nuance of « » in the context of 'mihrab' expresses the concept of causing harm or injury, which includes any kind of physical or spiritual damage.",
      "d": "« » means to cause harm to someone, to inflict injury, or to worsen their condition. This word is different from other words like ' ' (harm) in that ' ' more clearly and severely implies loss, whereas ' ' can also denote temporary harm. For example: The Quran states:\n«وَلَا تُضَارُّوهُنَّ لِتُضَيِّقُوا عَلَيْهِنَّ»\nTranslation: \"And do not harm them to make things difficult for them.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 3081,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Mihrab - Mihrab",
      "hw": "محراب",
      "s": "« » refers to the protrusion or curvature in the structure of the mihrab.",
      "d": "« » means for something to protrude or to assume a curved shape. This word is different from other words like ' ' (arch) or ' ' (bending) in that it specifically describes the roundedness and prominent structure of the mihrab. For example: The Quran states:\n«فَهَنِيئًا لَّكَ وَأَتْبَاعَكَ»"
    }
  ],
  "672": [
    {
      "id": 3084,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Animals - Animals",
      "hw": "جانور",
      "s": "« » describes the property of being halal in relation to animals, i.e., those animals that are permissible to eat according to Islamic Shariah.",
      "d": "« » means to declare something halal or permissible. This word is derived from the trilateral root  - -  which encompasses meanings such as analysis (to open), dissolution (to enter), and permissibility (to be lawful). In the context of animals, it is distinguished from other words like ' ' (good) or ' ' (permitted) in that it is specifically used in contrast to prohibited/haram under the injunctions of Shariah.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«أُحِلَّتْ لَكُم بَهِيمَةُ الْأَنْعَامِ»\nTranslation: \"The beasts of cattle have been made halal for you (except those that will be recited to you).\""
    },
    {
      "id": 3085,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Animal - Animal",
      "hw": "جانور",
      "s": "« » denotes the characteristic of animals eating, which includes chewing, swallowing, and digesting.",
      "d": "«اكل» «طعام» «شرب» «وَآخَرُ يَعْلُوهُ مِنَ الطَّعَامِ تَأْكُلُهُ الطَّيْرُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3086,
      "a": "ج",
      "h": "Animal - Animal",
      "hw": "جانور",
      "s": "« » denotes animals being surrounded or their collective gathering.",
      "d": "«كلل» «وَالطَّيْرَ صَافَّاتٍ كُلٌّ قَدْ عَلِمَ صَلَاتَهُ وَتَسْبِيحَهُ»"
    }
  ],
  "673": [
    {
      "id": 3087,
      "a": "چ",
      "h": "Ants - Ants",
      "hw": "چیونٹیاں",
      "s": "The specific meaning of « » pertains to the movement and social life of ants, reflecting their natural harmony and subtle coordination.",
      "d": "« » means to move something with softness and flexibility or to work in harmony for one's purpose. This word differs from other words like « » or « » in that it does not merely mean physical movement but also includes purposefulness and social balance.\n«وَحُشِرَ لِسُلَيْمَانَ جُنُودُهُ مِنَ الْجِنِّ وَالْإِنسِ وَالطَّيْرِ فَهُمْ يُوزَعُونَ حَتَّىٰ إِذَا أَتَوْا عَلَىٰ وَادِ النَّمْلِ قَالَتْ نَمْلَةٌ يَا أَيُّهَا النَّمْلُ ادْخُلُوا مَسَاكِنَكُمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3089,
      "a": "چ",
      "h": "Ants - Ants",
      "hw": "چیونٹیاں",
      "s": "« » carries a specific meaning referring to the unique collective behavior, precautionary measures, and movement of ants, as described in Surah An-Naml.",
      "d": "« » means to move toward something, to come, or to bring, but this word does not signify mere general movement; rather, it conveys movement that is purposeful, strategic, or part of a collective action. In the context of ants, it highlights their organized method of work, their natural wisdom in avoiding danger, and their ability to warn one another. Other terms (e.g.,  ,  ) lack this nuance.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«حَتَّىٰ إِذَا أَتَوْا عَلَىٰ وَادِ النَّمْلِ قَالَتْ نَمْلَةٌ يَا أَيُّهَا النَّمْلُ ادْخُلُوا مَسَاكِنَكُمْ»\nTranslation: Until when they came upon the valley of the ants, an ant said, 'O ants, enter your dwellings.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 3090,
      "a": "چ",
      "h": "Ants - Ants",
      "hw": "چیونٹیاں",
      "s": "« » denotes a specific type of ant that is small and organized, as mentioned in the Quran in the story of Prophet Sulaiman (peace be upon him).",
      "d": "«نمل» «حَتَّىٰ إِذَا أَتَوْا عَلَىٰ وَادِ النَّمْلِ قَالَتْ نَمْلَةٌ يَا أَيُّهَا النَّمْلُ ادْخُلُوا مَسَاكِنَكُمْ»"
    }
  ],
  "674": [
    {
