      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Monkey - Monkey",
      "hw": "بندر",
      "s": "« » specifically denotes a type of monkey that is generally associated with a degraded and transformed form.",
      "d": "«قرد» «وَلَقَدْ عَلِمْتُمُ الَّذِينَ اعْتَدَوْا مِنكُمْ فِي السَّبْتِ فَقُلْنَا لَهُمْ كُونُوا قِرَدَةً خَاسِئِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3093,
      "a": "ب",
      "h": "Monkey - Monkey",
      "hw": "بندر",
      "s": "« » has a specific usage in the Quran in the context of an immediate and divine command for transformation, such as the command to become monkeys.",
      "d": "«كون» «وَلَقَدْ عَلِمْتُمُ الَّذِينَ اعْتَدَوْا مِنكُمْ فِي السَّبْتِ فَقُلْنَا لَهُمْ كُونُوا قِرَدَةً خَاسِئِينَ»"
    }
  ],
  "675": [
    {
      "id": 3097,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Apostasy - Apostasy",
      "hw": "ارتداد",
      "s": "In the context of apostasy, the meaning of « » refers to returning from sin to Allah and indicates the acceptance of repentance.",
      "d": "« » means to return to Allah with deep remorse and sincerity. This word is distinct from other terms like « » or « » in that it specifically emphasizes abandoning sin and complete return to the Lord's mercy, whereas in contrast to apostasy (turning from religion), this act of repentance also includes the aspect of renewing faith.\n«يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا تُوبُوا إِلَى اللَّهِ تَوْبَةً نَّصُوحًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3098,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Apostasy - Apostasy",
      "hw": "ارتداد",
      "s": "« » in the context of apostasy denotes the paths or ways that lead one to misguidance or deviation.",
      "d": "« » means various paths or ways, often indicating negative and scattered directions. This word differs from other synonyms like « » (clear, straight path) or « » (common path) in that « » implies multiplicity and dispersion, especially used for misleading paths.\n«وَلَا تَتَّبِعُوا السُّبُلَ فَتَفَرَّقَ بِكُمْ عَن سَبِيلِهِ»"
    }
  ],
  "676": [
