  "682": [
    {
      "id": 3132,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Ayyub - Ayyub",
      "hw": "ایوب",
      "s": "«Raḥmah» in the story of Ayyub (peace be upon him) refers to Allah's special mercy and granting relief after affliction.",
      "d": "«Raḥmah» «فَاسْتَجَبْنَا لَهُ فَكَشَفْنَا مَا بِهِ مِن ضُرٍّ وَآتَيْنَاهُ أَهْلَهُ وَمِثْلَهُم مَّعَهُمْ رَحْمَةً مِّنْ عِندِنَا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3133,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Ayyub - Ayyub",
      "hw": "ایوب",
      "s": "«Dhikr» in the story of Ayyub (peace be upon him) particularly emphasizes the remembrance of patience and trial, and deriving lessons from them.",
      "d": "«Dhikr» means to refresh something verbally or spiritually, especially remembering Allah's blessings or the events of the prophets. This word goes beyond mere 'remembering' and clarifies the aspect of practical lessons and admonition. Unlike other words such as 'fikr' (contemplation) or 'tadhkirah' (reminder), 'dhikr' includes an active and purposeful remembrance.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَاذْكُرْ عَبْدَنَا أَيُّوبَ إِذْ نَادَىٰ رَبَّهُ أَنِّي مَسَّنِيَ الشَّيْطَانُ بِنُصْبٍ وَعَذَابٍ»\nTranslation: And remember Our servant Ayyub, when he called to his Lord, 'Indeed, the devil has afflicted me with hardship and torment.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 3134,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Job - Job",
      "hw": "ایوب",
      "s": "« » (Ati) in the name of Job refers to the meaning of repentance and turning to Allah.",
      "d": "«اتي» «جاء» «وَاذْكُرْ عَبْدَنَا أَيُّوبَ إِذْ نَادَىٰ رَبَّهُ أَنِّي مَسَّنِيَ الشَّيْطَانُ بِنُصْبٍ وَعَذَابٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3135,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Job - Job",
      "hw": "ایوب",
      "s": "« » (Wahb) signifies the special concept of gifts from Allah to Job (Ayyub, peace be upon him), such as patience and offspring.",
      "d": "«وهب» «أعطى» «منح» «وَآتَيْنَاهُ أَهْلَهُ وَمِثْلَهُم مَّعَهُمْ رَحْمَةً مِّنْ عِندِنَا وَذِكْرَىٰ لِلْعَابِدِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3136,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Job - Job",
      "hw": "ایوب",
      "s": "« » (Nadi) from Job (Ayyub, peace be upon him) expresses the specific meaning of crying out and supplication in the Divine court.",
      "d": "«ندي» «دعا» «صلا» «وَأَيُّوبَ إِذْ نَادَىٰ رَبَّهُ أَنِّي مَسَّنِيَ الضُّرُّ وَأَنتَ أَرْحَمُ الرَّاحِمِينَ»"
    }
  ],
  "683": [
    {
      "id": 3138,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Azar - Azar",
      "hw": "آزر",
      "s": "« » (Abu) in the context of Azar signifies the meaning of a guardian or mentor, rather than a biological father.",
      "d": "«ابو» «والد» «ابو» «وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ لِأَبِيهِ آزَرَ أَتَتَّخِذُ أَصْنَامًا آلِهَةً»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3139,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Azar - Azar",
      "hw": "آزر",
      "s": "«Ḍalal» in the context of Azar describes the severe form of misguidance and deviation from the path of truth, particularly the misguidance that inclines towards polytheism.",
      "d": "«Ḍalal» means to lead someone astray from the path of truth and push them into the depths of misguidance. This word is distinguished from other words like 'ghayy' or 'zallal' in that it indicates systematic and persistent misguidance, while 'zallal' denotes a temporary slip. For example, Azar (the father of Prophet Ibrahim, peace be upon him) is described in the Quran with this attribute when he persists in idolatry.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ لِأَبِيهِ آزَرَ أَتَتَّخِذُ أَصْنَامًا آلِهَةً ۖ إِنِّي أَرَاكَ وَقَوْمَكَ فِي ضَلَالٍ مُّبِينٍ»\nTranslation: And [mention] when Ibrahim said to his father Azar, 'Do you take idols as deities? Indeed, I see you and your people in clear misguidance.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 3140,
      "a": "آ",
      "h": "Azar - Azar",
      "hw": "آزر",
      "s": "«Rāy» means to hold a false belief or misguided opinion, particularly in the case of Azar, who was the father of Prophet Ibrahim (peace be upon him) and practiced idolatry.",
      "d": "«Rāy» «وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ لِأَبِيهِ آزَرَ أَتَتَّخِذُ أَصْنَامًا آلِهَةً ۖ إِنِّي أَرَاكَ وَقَوْمَكَ فِي ضَلَالٍ مُّبِينٍ»"
    }
  ],
