  "685": [
    {
      "id": 3147,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Back - Back",
      "hw": "پیٹھ",
      "s": "«Ẓahr» is used in the meaning of back, which also signifies support, strength, or being behind something, in addition to the physical back.",
      "d": "«Ẓahr» «وَإِذْ أَخَذَ رَبُّكَ مِن بَنِي آدَمَ مِن ظُهُورِهِمْ ذُرِّيَّتَهُمْ...»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3149,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Back - Back",
      "hw": "پیٹھ",
      "s": "«Kūn» means to clarify the structure of the back and its creative status in the context of existence or creation.",
      "d": "«Kūn» means existence, state of being, or the fundamental creative quality of something. This word differs from other synonyms like «khalq» (to create) or «ṣanʿ» (to make) in that it not only refers to the general aspect of existence but also expresses the permanent and natural state of something. For example, the back (the structure of humans) is described through «kūn» as its natural and complete existence.\nFor example, in the Quran:\n«وَإِذْ أَخَذَ رَبُّكَ مِن بَنِي آدَمَ مِن ظُهُورِهِمْ ذُرِّيَّتَهُمْ»\nTranslation: And [mention] when your Lord took from the children of Adam, from their backs, their descendants.\n(This verse connects «ẓuhūr» (backs) with the fundamental quality of «kūn» in the context of human creation, where the origin of the human lineage is expressed through the structure of the back.)"
    },
    {
      "id": 3151,
      "a": "پ",
      "h": "Back - Back",
      "hw": "پیٹھ",
      "s": "The term « » in relation to 'back' conveys the specific sense of giving recompense or reward, implying that the result or wage of an action is placed upon the back.",
      "d": "«جزي» «وَمَا تُجْزَوْنَ إِلَّا مَا كُنتُمْ تَعْمَلُونَ»"
    }
  ],
