      "hw": "خوش",
      "s": "'Khurram' is the state of happiness characterized by deep freshness and vitality.",
      "d": "«مَّثَلُ ٱلَّذِينَ يُنفِقُونَ أَمْوَٰلَهُمُ ٱبْتِغَآءَ مَرْضَاتِ ٱللَّهِ وَتَثْبِيتًۭا مِّنْ أَنفُسِهِمْ كَمَثَلِ جَنَّةٍۭ بِرَبْوَةٍ أَصَابَهَا وَابِلٌۭ فَـَٔاتَتْ أُكُلَهَا ضِعْفَيْنِ»"
    }
  ],
  "711": [
    {
      "id": 3277,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Grief - Gham",
      "hw": "غم",
      "s": "'Gham' is used in all meanings of sorrow, anguish, restlessness, pain, and regret.",
      "d": "«ثُمَّ اَنۡزَلَ عَلَیۡکُمۡ مِّنۡۢ بَعۡدِ الۡغَمِّ اَمَنَۃً نُّعَاسًا یَّغۡشٰی طَآئِفَۃً مِّنۡکُمۡ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3278,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Grief - Anguish",
      "hw": "غم",
      "s": "« » describes a deep and permanent form of grief that envelops the heart.",
      "d": "«اندوہ» «حُزن» «كرب» «اندوہ» «فَأَثَابَكُمْ غُمًّا بِغَمٍّ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3279,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Grief - Miall",
      "hw": "غم",
      "s": "'Miall' expresses the deep feeling of regret and sorrow over the absence or loss of something.",
      "d": "«رُبَمَا يَوَدُّ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا لَوْ كَانُوا مُسْلِمِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3280,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Grief - Ranj",
      "hw": "غم",
      "s": "'Ranj' is linked to feelings of weakness, complexity, and hopelessness that oppress the heart.",
      "d": "«وَاللَّذِينَ جَاءُوا مِن بَعْدِهِمْ لَيَكُونَنَّ فِي تَرَدُّدٍ مِنْهُمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3281,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Grief - Regret",
      "hw": "غم",
      "s": "« » particularly expresses failure, loss, and a painful state of the heart in the expression of grief.",
      "d": "«افسوس» «غم» «افسوس» «أَفْسُوسَ عَلَى الْقَوْمِ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ إِذَا مَرُّوا بِهِمْ وَلَمْ يَجِدُوا فِيهِمْ مِنْ أَهْلِهِمْ أَحَدًا»"
    }
  ],
  "712": [
    {
      "id": 3282,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Anger - Anger",
      "hw": "غصہ",
      "s": "« » means when a person considers themselves great and ignores others, and also ignores their own reality.",
      "d": "«غصہ» «تعصب» «غرور» «غصہ» «وَلَقَدْ أَرْسَلْنَا مُوسَىٰ بِآيَاتِنَا وَسُلْطَانٍ مُّبِينٍ إِلَىٰ فِرْعَوْنَ وَمَلَأِهِۦ فَقَالُوآ إِنَّا نَحْنُ كَانَ الْمُؤْتَمِرُونَ قَالَ يَا فِرْعَوْنُ إِنِّي لَكَ الْمُنْذِرُ الْمُبِينُ لَقَدْ جَاءَكَ الْحَقُّ مِنْ رَّبِّكَ فَأَمَّا يَكُونَ لَكَ أَنْ تَكُونَ فِي الْمُحْتَشِمِينَ فَإِنَّهُ لَمَّا يَغْصُو فِي الْمُحْتَشِمِينَ وَإِنَّهُ لَمَّا يَغْصُو فِي الْمُحْتَشِمِينَ فَلَوْلَا أَنْ يَكُونَ فِي الْمُحْتَشِمِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3283,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Anger - Wrath",
      "hw": "غصہ",
      "s": "« » when a person becomes furious with anger and seeks revenge, whether small or big, it is related to the other person's essence, not one's own.",
      "d": "«غَضَبٌ» «اِتَّقُوْا مِنْ الْغَضَبِ فَاِنَّہٗ جُمْرَۃٌ تُوْقَدُ فِیْ قَلْبِ ابْنِ اٰدَمَ اَلَمْ تَرَوْا اِلَی انْتِفَاخِ اَوْدَاجِہٖ وَجُمْرَۃِ عَیْنَیْہِ» «غَضِبَ» «غَضْب» «وَ مَنۡ یَّحْلِلۡ عَلَیۡہِ غَضَبِیۡ فَقَدۡ ہَوٰی»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3284,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Anger - Fury",
      "hw": "غصہ",
      "s": "« » means a specific, ruthless emotion of anger that leads to the heart splitting.",
      "d": "« » means a specific, ruthless emotion of anger that leads to the heart splitting. It occurs with a sigh, which causes the heart to split and others to be exposed. There is a difference between qahr and anger; anger generally occurs with feeling, while qahr is an expression of additional pressure and a kind of ruthlessness. Example: In the Quran:\n«وَإِذْ أَخَذَ اللَّهُ مِيثَاقَ الَّذِينَ أَتَوْا مِن قَبْلِكَ لِيَقُولَنَّ الَّذِينَ أَحْسَنُوا وَالَّذِينَ قَدْ أَخْلَفُوا مِنْهُمْ أَنَّ اللَّهَ لَمْ يَكُنْ بِهِمْ عَلِيمًا»\nTranslation: 'And when Allah took the covenant from those who were before you that they would support their people with strength and aid, then later they said, \"Allah has no knowledge of us.\"'"
    },
    {
      "id": 3285,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Anger - Rage",
      "hw": "غصہ",
      "s": "« » means a specific point of anger that shows disorder, restlessness, and corruption of the heart.",
      "d": "«طیش» «غضب» «طیش» «طیش» «وَإِذَا مَسَّكَ اللَّهُ الْقَلْبَ فَلَا مُفَرِّضٍ لَّهُ وَإِذَا مَسَّكَ الْغَضَبَ فَلَا مُعَلِّقٍ لَّهُ»"
    }
  ],
  "713": [
    {
      "id": 3286,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love - Love",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "« » means a feeling of attachment created by God and filling the heart, which draws a person towards their Master.",
      "d": "«محبت» «عشق» «حب» «محبت» «وَلَمْ يَكُن لَّهُ كَنِيْٓءٌ وَّلَا وَلَدٌ وَّلَمْ يَكُن مَّعَهُ شَرِيكٌ فَلِيَّهُ الْحُبُّ وَلَهُ الْمَلَكُ وَهُوَ عَلَىٰ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ قَدِيرٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3287,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love - Ardent Love",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "'Ishq' is a special manifestation of love that expresses human and divine relationships.",
      "d": "«وَاللَّذِينَ جَاهَدُوا فِيْنَا لَنَحْنُهُمْ وَلَنَحْنُهُمْ وَإِلَيْهِ يَرْجِعُ الْأُمُورُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3288,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love - Inclination",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "'Al-Fat' signifies a special feeling and relationship that arises in a person's heart.",
      "d": "«وَاللَّذِينَ جَاءُوا مِن بَعْدِهِمْ يَقُولُونَ رَبَّنَا اغْفِرْ لَنَا وَلِإِخْوَانِنَا الَّذِينَ سَبَقُوا بِالْإِيمَانِ وَلَا نَجْعَلْ فِي قُلُوبِنَا غِلَّ الْقُوَّةِ إِلَىٰ أَهْلِهِ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ رَبَّنَا وَلَكَ الْحَمْدُ أَنْتَ وَلِيُّنَا فِي الدُّنْيَا وَالْآخِرَةِ وَلَكَ الْحَمْدُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3289,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love - Devotion",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "« » means the intense love and feeling that arises specifically in a person's heart, which is the most valued and does not ignore the filled soul of the heart.",
      "d": "« » in Urdu derives from the Arabic word 'piyaar' which originally means 'burning of hearts' or 'connection of hearts'. It means to love someone deeply, to burn one's heart for them, and to understand their state. In contrast, « » is the most general term, while « » specifically denotes heart-burning, intense love, and the belovedness of the heart. « » is a word that does not ignore the state of the heart but expresses it in the best way. Example: In the Quran:\n«وَالَّذِينَ جَاهَدُوا فِيْنَا لَنَحْنُ لَهُمْ مُّلْكُ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالأَرْضِ فَإِنَّمَا يَجْزَوْنَ مَا كَانُوا يَعْمَلُونَ»\nTranslation: 'And those who strive for Us - We will surely grant them the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And they will be recompensed only for what they used to do.'"
    },
    {
      "id": 3290,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Love - Desire",
      "hw": "محبت",
      "s": "'Chahat' means the feeling of love and the desire to see one's companion that arises from a person's heart.",
      "d": "«وَاللَّذِي جَاءَ بِالْحُكْمِ مِنَ اللَّهِ فَلَمْ يَجِدْ مِنْهُمْ أَحَدًا لَمْ يَكُن مُتَّبِعًا لِلْمَنْ هُوَ أَعْلَمُ بِالْمُعْتَقِدِينَ»"
    }
  ],
  "714": [
    {
      "id": 3291,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Hatred - Hatred",
      "hw": "نفرت",
      "s": "'Nafrat' means to feel intense disgust or revulsion towards something, which creates deep aversion in the heart and mind.",
      "d": "«كَأَنَّهُمْ حُمُرٌ مُّسْتَنفِرَةٌ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3292,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Hatred - Enmity",
      "hw": "نفرت",
      "s": "'Adawat' is that deep form of enmity and opposition that breeds hatred in hearts.",
      "d": "«يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا لَا تَتَّخِذُوا عَدُوَّي وَعَدُوَّكُمْ أَوْلِيَاءَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3293,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Hatred - Aversion",
      "hw": "نفرت",
      "s": "'Karahat' signifies the state of dislike or accepting something reluctantly, which is somewhat different from deep-seated hatred arising from the heart.",
      "d": "«كُتِبَ عَلَيْكُمُ الْقِتَالُ وَهُوَ كُرْهٌ لَّكُمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3294,
      "a": "ن",
      "h": "Hatred - Malice",
      "hw": "نفرت",
      "s": "'Bughd' means the feeling of deep hatred and enmity in the heart, often based on enmity or injustice.",
      "d": "«وَدُّوا لَوْ تَكْفُرُونَ كَمَا كَفَرُوا فَتَكُونُونَ سَوَاءً فَلَا تَتَّخِذُوا مِنْهُمْ أَوْلِيَاءَ حَتَّىٰ يُهَاجِرُوا فِي سَبِيلِ اللَّهِ فَإِن تَوَلَّوْا فَخُذُوهُمْ وَاقْتُلُوهُمْ حَيْثُ وَجَدتُّمُوهُمْ وَلَا تَتَّخِذُوا مِنْهُمْ وَلِيًّا وَلَا نَصِيرًا إِلَّا الَّذِينَ يَصِلُونَ إِلَى قَوْمٍ بَيْنَكُمْ وَبَيْنَهُم مِيثَاقٌ أَوْ جَاءُوكُمْ حَصِرَتْ صُدُورُهُمْ أَن يُقَاتِلُوكُمْ أَوْ يُقَاتِلُوا قَوْمَهُمْ وَلَوْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ لَسَلَّطَهُمْ عَلَيْكُمْ فَلَقَاتَلُوكُمْ فَإِنِ اعْتَزَلُوكُمْ فَلَمْ يُقَاتِلُوكُمْ وَأَلْقَوْا إِلَيْكُمُ السَّلَمَ فَمَا جَعَلَ اللَّهُ لَكُمْ عَلَيْهِمْ سَبِيلًا سَوْفَ تَجِدُونَ آخَرِينَ يُرِيدُونَ أَن يَأْمَنُوكُمْ وَيَأْمَنُوا قَوْمَهُمْ كُلَّ مَا رُدُّوا إِلَى الْفِتْنَةِ أُرْكِسُوا فِيهَا فَإِن لَّمْ يَعْتَزِلُوكُمْ وَيُلْقُوا إِلَيْكُمُ السَّلَمَ وَيَكُفُّوا أَيْدِيَهُمْ فَخُذُوهُمْ وَاقْتُلُوهُمْ حَيْثُ ثَقِفْتُمُوهُمْ وَأُولَٰئِكَ جَعَلْنَا لَكُمْ عَلَيْهِمْ سُلْطَانًا مُبِينًا»"
    }
  ],
  "715": [
    {
      "id": 3295,
      "a": "خ",
      "h": "Fear - Fear",
      "hw": "خوف",
      "s": "'Khawf' in the Quranic context denotes anxiety, dread, or apprehension, generally concerning Allah's displeasure or punishment, which includes the aspect of caution and piety.",
      "d": "«إِنَّمَا ذَٰلِكُمُ الشَّيْطَانُ يُخَوِّفُ أَوْلِيَاءَهُ فَلَا تَخَافُوهُمْ وَخَافُونِ إِن كُنتُم مُّؤْمِنِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3296,
      "a": "خ",
      "h": "Fear - Dread",
      "hw": "خوف",
      "s": "'Dar' in the context of fear expresses a cautious attitude concerning Allah's displeasure and punishment, aiming to avoid it.",
      "d": "«إِنَّمَا ذَٰلِكُمُ الشَّيْطَانُ يُخَوِّفُ أَوْلِيَاءَهُ فَلَا تَخَافُوهُمْ وَخَافُونِ إِن كُنتُم مُّؤْمِنِينَ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3297,
      "a": "خ",
      "h": "Fear - Terror",
      "hw": "خوف",
      "s": "'Dahshat' describes an intense and sudden state of fear that arises in the heart due to a danger or terrifying sight.",
      "d": "«أُولَـٰئِكَ الَّذِينَ لَعَنَهُمُ اللَّـهُ فَأَصَمَّهُمْ وَأَعْمَىٰ أَبْصَارَهُمْ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3298,
      "a": "خ",
      "h": "Fear - Dread",
      "hw": "خوف",
      "s": "«Dread» [a specific meaning of fear that also includes religious events, which protects a person's faith and religion]",
      "d": "«Dread» «خائف» «ڈر» «الَّذِينَ يُؤْمِنُونَ بِاللَّهِ وَالْيَوْمِ الْآخِرِ وَيَعْمَلُونَ صَالِحًا فَأُولَٰئِكَ يُحَبُّونَ اللَّهَ وَيُحَبُّونَهُ مُحَبَّةً كَثِيرَةً»"
    }
  ],
  "716": [
    {
      "id": 3299,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Hope - Hope",
      "hw": "امید",
      "s": "«Hope» means a peaceful desire for positive future outcomes with complete trust in Allah and expectation of His mercy.",
      "d": "«Hope» «وَمَن يَقْنَتَ مِنكُنَّ لِلَّهِ وَرَسُولِهِ وَتَعْمَلْ صَالِحًا نُؤْتِهَا أَجْرَهَا مَرَّتَيْنِ وَأَعْتَدْنَا لَهَا رِزْقًا كَرِيمًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3301,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Hope - Expectation",
      "hw": "امید",
      "s": "«Expectation» is the original meaning of hope which also includes the thought of the heart.",
      "d": "«Expectation» «hope» «expectation» «وَاللَّذِينَ جَاهَدُوا فِينَا لَنَحْنُ هُمُ الْمُهْتَدُونَ» «And those who strive for Us, it is they who are the guided.»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3302,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Hope - Supplication",
      "hw": "امید",
      "s": "«Supplication» is the original meaning of hope which plans human desire and the help of others.",
      "d": "«Supplication» «وَلَا تَأْخِرْنِي فِي الْمُحْتَجَّاتِ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ»"
    }
  ],
  "717": [
    {
      "id": 3303,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Despair - Despair",
      "hw": "مایوسی",
      "s": "«Despair» means a state where one does not obtain from Allah, and does not understand oneself; when one does not receive the mercy or blessings obtained from Allah, then the feeling of despair arises.",
      "d": "«Despair» «مایوس» «وَإِذْ قَالَ مُوسَىٰ لِقَوْمِهِ يَا قَوْمِ إِنَّكُمْ ظَلَمْتُمْ أَنْفُسَكُمْ بِاتِّخَاذِكُمُ الْعِجْلَ فَتُوبُوا إِلَىٰ بَارِئِكُمْ فَاقْتُلُوا أَنفُسَكُمْ فَأَسْلَمُوا وَهُوَ أَحْسَنُ لَكُمْ» «You have wronged yourselves by taking the calf, so repent to your Creator and kill yourselves; then you will be guided, and that is best for you.»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3304,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Despair - Disappointment",
      "hw": "مایوسی",
      "s": "«Disappointment» means the feeling of losing courage from Allah when a person sees the results of their actions with despair.",
      "d": "«Disappointment» «ہیں» «خیال» «Disappointment» «وَلَمْ يَكُن لَّهُمْ مِّنْ أَعْدَاءِ اللَّهِ مِنْ وَاقِعٍ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3305,
      "a": "م",
      "h": "Despair - Despondency",
      "hw": "مایوسی",
      "s": "«Despondency» is the original meaning of despair which disturbs a person's heart with hopelessness and failure.",
      "d": "«Despondency» «قنوط» «کُسْف» «خَسَرَانِی» «قنوطیت» «وَلَقَدْ أَرْسَلْنَا مُوسَىٰ بِآيَاتِنَا وَسُلْطَانٍ مُّبِینٍ» «And We certainly sent Moses with Our signs and a clear authority.»"
    }
  ],
  "718": [
    {
      "id": 3306,
      "a": "ح",
      "h": "Amazement - Amazement",
      "hw": "حیرت",
      "s": "«Amazement» means when something makes us feel unexpected and helpless, it explains it.",
      "d": "«Amazement» «تعجب» «حیرت» «أَلَمْ تَرَ إِلَى الَّذِي أَخَذَ قَوْلَكُمْ وَجَعَلَ مِنْهُمْ أَزْوَاجًا وَلَمْ يَكُنْ لَهُمْ مِنْ أَزْوَاجِهِمْ مِنْ بَعْدِ ذَلِكَ أَبَوَانِ مَنْ كَانَ لَهُمْ فِي الْقَوْلِ مِنْ حِلْمٍ وَإِنَّهُ لَمَّا تَصَدَّقَ الْمَوْعِظَةَ مِنْهُمْ وَمَنْ قَالَ لَهُمْ أَنْ لَيْسَ لَكُمْ مِنْ أَبَوَيْكُمْ مِنْ بَعْدِ ذَلِكَ أَبَوَانِ مِنْ حِلْمٍ وَإِنَّهُ لَمَّا تَصَدَّقَ الْمَوْعِظَةَ مِنْهُمْ» «Have you not seen those who took your words and made some of them into spouses, and there were no parents for them from their spouses after that? And when they were admonished, the death of their words was felt, and when they were admonished, there was no matter from their parents after that from modesty, and when they were admonished, the death of their words was felt.»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3307,
      "a": "ح",
      "h": "Amazement - Wonder",
      "hw": "حیرت",
      "s": "«Wonder» means to express the heart greatly towards something that is strange and extraordinary.",
      "d": "«Wonder» «تعجب» «حیرت» «Wonder» «وَإِذْ قَالَ مُوسَىٰ لِقَوْمِهِ ادْعُوا رَبَّكُمْ وَلْيَمْسَطْ لَكُمْ رِزْقَهُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3308,
      "a": "ح",
      "h": "Amazement - Astonishment",
      "hw": "حیرت",
      "s": "«Astonishment» means the feeling of wonder and amazement with the increasing appearance of Allah's great power and creation's reward when facing something that is extraordinary.",
      "d": "«Astonishment» «استعجاب» «وَالَّذِينَ جَاهَدُوا فِينَا لَنَحْنُ هُمُ الْمُهْتَدُونَ» «We felt that we have to face it for ourselves.»"
    }
  ],
  "719": [
    {
      "id": 3309,
      "a": "ش",
      "h": "Shame - Shame",
      "hw": "شرم",
      "s": "‘Sharm’ means to distress oneself over one's disobedience and sins, and to feel the heart beating because of it.",
      "d": "‘Sharm’ is an Arabic root (sh-r-m) which essentially manifests as a feeling in a person’s heart when they realize that their disobedience or sin might cause regret to others. This word represents a specific feeling of human moral connection, a sense of having crossed a boundary. It means a type of feeling that prevents a person from sinning, and it is different from words like ‘khajli’ (embarrassment) or ‘diwanagi’ (madness). For example: The Quran states:\n«وَالَّذِينَ إِذَا مَآ أَنْفَقُوا لَمْ يُسْرِفُوا وَلَمْ يَقْتُرُوا وَكَانُوا بَيْنَ ذَٰلِكَ رَاسِخِينَ»\nTranslation: ‘And those who, when they spend, are neither extravagant nor stingy, but hold a moderate course between them.’"
    },
    {
      "id": 3310,
      "a": "ش",
      "h": "Shame - Modesty",
      "hw": "شرم",
      "s": "‘Haya’ is a human and religious feeling given by God that prevents a person from indecent and inappropriate acts.",
      "d": "‘Haya’ originates from the Arabic root ‘haya’ ( - - ) which expresses a human and religious feeling. This word essentially is a feeling born in a person’s heart that prevents them from indecent and inappropriate acts. In contrast, ‘khajal’ (embarrassment) is a feeling that occurs in one’s personal life that prevents them from acts that seem wrong in their own eyes. ‘Haya’ represents a person’s religious and human feeling that helps them fulfill the laws given by God. For example: The Quran states:\n«الَّذِينَ يُؤْمِنُونَ بِاللَّهِ وَالْيَوْمِ الْآخِرِ وَيَأْمُرُونَ بِالْمَعْرُوفِ وَيَنْهَوْنَ عَنِ الْمُنكَرِ وَيُقِيمُونَ الصَّلَاةَ وَيُؤْتُونَ الزَّكَاةَ وَهُمْ يَخْشَوْنَ رَبَّهُمْ مِّنْ غَيْرِ مَا يَرَوْنَهُ وَهُمْ يُقِيمُونَ الْحَدِيثَ»\nTranslation: Those who have believed in Allah and the Last Day, they have enhanced society, prevented inappropriate acts, established prayer, given zakah, and they assist their Lord in fulfilling the laws given by God at that time."
    },
    {
      "id": 3311,
      "a": "ش",
      "h": "Shame - Regret",
      "hw": "شرم",
      "s": "‘Nadamat’ is the true meaning of shame that reflects a person’s goodness and beauty, when they keep themselves protected from exposure and wrong deeds.",
      "d": "‘Nadamat’ means the feeling of human goodness and beauty that prevents a person from their sins and wrong deeds. This feeling is such that a person realizes that their human goodness and moral virtues exist, and they want to keep their beauty and humanity protected from themselves. It means that we preserve our goodness, and we also reflect our beauty through our actions. It is contrasted with other words like ‘khajal’ or ‘be khajli’ which are not merely human feelings but specifically involve a sense of human goodness. For example: The Quran states:\n«وَلَا تَكُونُوا الَّذِينَ يُؤْلِينَ أَنْفُسَهُمْ وَيَحْسَدُونَ النَّاسَ عَلَىٰ مَا آتَاهُمُ اللَّهُ مِنْ فَضْلِهِ»\nTranslation: \"And do not be those who expose themselves and envy people for what Allah has given them of His bounty.\""
    }
  ],
  "720": [
    {
      "id": 3313,
      "a": "ف",
      "h": "Pride - Arrogance",
      "hw": "فخر",
      "s": "‘Ghurur’ means considering oneself more important and belittling others, which brings harm to a person.",
      "d": "‘Ghurur’ means considering oneself more important and belittling others, which brings harm to a person. Its Arabic root is ‘gh-r-r’ which in Urdu is synonymous with ‘fakhar’ (pride). Its lexical origins in Urdu also include ‘fakhar’, ‘bara’ (great), ‘khudpasandi’ (self-centeredness), and ‘eitmad’ (confidence), but ‘ghurur’ specifically means considering oneself more important, which results in belittling others. For example: The Quran states:\n«وَلَا تَفْرَحْ وَلَا تَغْرُورْ بِاللَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا»\nTranslation: ‘And do not rejoice or be arrogant because of those who disbelieved.’"
    },
    {
      "id": 3314,
      "a": "ف",
      "h": "Pride - Boasting",
      "hw": "فخر",
      "s": "‘Tafakhar’ means considering oneself superior to others and attempting to show one’s blessings and strength to others.",
      "d": "«وَلَمْ يَكُن لَّهُمْ فِي ذَٰلِكَ إِلَّا فَخْرٌ وَلَمْ يَكُن لَّهُمْ فِي ذَٰلِكَ إِلَّا فَخْرٌ»"
    }
  ],
  "721": [
    {
      "id": 3315,
      "a": "ص",
      "h": "Patience - Patience",
      "hw": "صبر",
      "s": "‘Sabr’ means to endure when calamities and difficulties befall.",
      "d": "‘Sabr’ means to endure a calamity or hardship when it befalls and not express restlessness, impatience, or lamentation. For example: The Quran states:\n«فَصَبَرُوۡا عَلٰی مَا کُذِّبُوۡا وَ اُوۡذُوۡا حَتّٰۤی اَتٰہُمۡ  نَصۡرُنَا»\nTranslation: So the prophets endured the denial and harm until Our help came to them."
    },
    {
      "id": 3316,
      "a": "ص",
      "h": "Patience - Endurance",
      "hw": "صبر",
      "s": "‘Tahammul’ emphasizes the readiness to bear burdens and the specific quality of enduring hardship in the sense of patience.",
      "d": "«رَبَّنَا وَلَا تُحَمِّلْنَا مَا لَا طَاقَةَ لَنَا بِهِ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3317,
      "a": "ص",
      "h": "Patience - Tolerance",
      "hw": "صبر",
      "s": "‘Bardashat’ expresses the quality of facing difficulties with calmness and steadfastness in the context of patience.",
      "d": "«وَاسْتَعِينُوا بِالصَّبْرِ وَالصَّلَاةِ»"
    }
  ],
  "722": [
    {
      "id": 3318,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Error - Error",
      "hw": "غلطی",
      "s": "‘Ghalti’ refers to an error that occurs in an action due to mistake, fault, or deviation from the path, usually caused unintentionally or due to negligence.",
      "d": "«وَمَا مَنَعَ النَّاسَ أَن يُؤْمِنُوا إِذْ جَاءَهُمُ الْهُدَىٰ إِلَّا أَنْ قَالُوا أَبَعَثَ اللَّهُ بَشَرًا رَّسُولًا»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3320,
      "a": "غ",
      "h": "Error - Slip",
      "hw": "غلطی",
      "s": "‘Laghsh’ means an expression of error that happens unintentionally or due to ignorance.",
      "d": "‘Laghsh’ means an expression of error that happens unintentionally or due to ignorance. Its Arabic root is ‘w-h-d’ which means ‘to guide’, and ‘laghsh’ means ‘against guidance’. It is also synonymous with ‘ghalti’, ‘afsos’ (regret), ‘khatta’ (error). The literal meaning of ‘laghsh’ is to be against guidance, while ‘ghalti’ means to deviate from the correct path. For example: The Quran states:\n«وَلَا تَقُولُوا لِمَنْ يَمُوتُ فِي مَلْكِهِ أَنَّهُ مَوْتٌ إِلَّا أَنْ تَقُولُوا لَهُ لَعَلَّ اللَّهَ لِيَجْعَلَ لَكُمْ خَيْرًا فِي مَلَكِهِ وَلَعَلَّهُ يَمُوتُ فِي مَلَكِهِ وَأَنْتُمْ تَعْمَلُونَ»\nTranslation: Do not say about one who dies in his land, ‘He is dead,’ but say, ‘Perhaps Allah will grant you better in his place, and perhaps he will die in his land while you are unaware.’"
    }
  ],
  "723": [
    {
