      "hw": "لینا",
      "s": "'To obtain' means to bring something to oneself by acquiring it, whereas 'to take' merely means to present or bring something to oneself.",
      "d": "«وَإِذَا مَسَّكُمُ الْقَلَبُ مِنَ الْحَزْنِ فَأَخَذَتْكُمُ الْمَوْتُ»"
    },
    {
      "id": 3421,
      "a": "ل",
      "h": "To Take - To Take",
      "hw": "لینا",
      "s": "« » means to take something, to encompass it, to grasp.",
      "d": "« » means to take something, to encompass it, to grasp (transitive). Its usage is both tangible (i.e., something perceived through one of the five senses) and intangible.\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ اِذۡ اَخَذَ اللّٰہُ مِیۡثَاقَ النَّبِیّٖنَ»\nTranslation: And when Allah took the covenant of the prophets.\nAt another place, the divine command states:\n«وَ لَمَّا سَکَتَ عَنۡ  مُّوۡسَی الۡغَضَبُ  اَخَذَ الۡاَلۡوَاحَ»\nTranslation: And when the anger of Moses subsided, he took up the tablets."
    }
  ],
  "757": [
    {
